query.107:
WITH fetch_reads AS (
  SELECT
    rds.*
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.non_comms_constraints_base_data_latest_reads` AS rds
  INNER JOIN
    --`data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.non_comms_billing_base_data_earliest_reads` earliest_read
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.non_comms_constraints_base_data_earliest_read_since_gt_bill` earliest_read
      ON  rds.msn = earliest_read.msn
      AND rds.readDateTime = earliest_read.readDateTime
), mapped_elec AS (
  SELECT
     elec.msn
    ,elec.fuel
    ,elec.readDateTime
    ,elec.tier
    --,map.clockingTimeId
    ,map.meterRegisterId
    ,FLOOR(elec.reading) AS reading
  FROM
    fetch_reads AS elec
  INNER JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.2019_10_28_meter_mappings` AS map
      ON  elec.msn = map.msn
      AND elec.tier = map.tier
  WHERE
    elec.fuel = 'electricity'
    AND clockingTimeId = 1 -- single rate, to be sure
), adj_elec AS (
  SELECT
       gt.msn
      ,gt.accountNumber
      ,gt.consumerNumber
      ,invoiceId
      ,statementId
      ,fuel
      ,gt.migrationRead
      ,gt.migrationReadDate
      ,gt.migrationReadType
      --,gt.meterRegisterId
      ,chg.readDateTime
      ,chg.reading
      ,CASE
        WHEN gt.migrationRead < chg.reading - 30 THEN 'charge greater than £5'
        WHEN gt.migrationRead >= chg.reading - 30 AND gt.migrationRead < chg.reading THEN 'charge less than £5'       
        WHEN gt.migrationRead > chg.reading + 30 THEN 'credit greater than £5' 
        WHEN gt.migrationRead <= chg.reading + 30 AND gt.migrationRead > chg.reading + 1 THEN 'credit less than £5'       
        ELSE 'equal' END AS adjustmentType
      ,ROUND(gt.migrationRead - chg.reading, 1) AS consumptionAdjustment
      ,DATE_DIFF(DATE(chg.readDateTime), gt.migrationReadDate, DAY) AS adjustmentDays
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.non_comms_billing_base_data_gt_single_rate_only` AS gt
  INNER JOIN
    mapped_elec AS chg
      ON  gt.msn = chg.msn
      AND gt.meterRegisterId = chg.meterRegisterId
      AND gt.migrationReadDate <= DATE(chg.readDateTime)
), adj_gas AS (
  SELECT
       gt.msn
      ,gt.accountNumber
      ,gt.consumerNumber
      ,invoiceId
      ,statementId
      ,fuel
      ,gt.migrationRead
      ,gt.migrationReadDate
      ,gt.migrationReadType
      ,chg.readDateTime
      ,FLOOR(chg.reading) AS reading
      ,CASE
        WHEN gt.migrationRead < FLOOR(chg.reading) - 30 THEN 'charge greater than £5'
        WHEN gt.migrationRead >= FLOOR(chg.reading) - 30 AND gt.migrationRead < FLOOR(chg.reading) THEN 'charge less than £5'       
        WHEN gt.migrationRead > FLOOR(chg.reading) + 30 THEN 'credit greater than £5' 
        WHEN gt.migrationRead <= FLOOR(chg.reading) + 30 AND gt.migrationRead > FLOOR(chg.reading) + 1 THEN 'credit less than £5'       
        ELSE 'equal' END AS adjustmentType
      ,ROUND(gt.migrationRead - FLOOR(chg.reading), 1) AS consumptionAdjustment
      ,DATE_DIFF(DATE(chg.readDateTime), gt.migrationReadDate, DAY) AS adjustmentDays
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.non_comms_billing_base_data_gt_single_rate_only` AS gt
  INNER JOIN
    fetch_reads AS chg
      ON  gt.msn = chg.msn
      AND gt.migrationReadDate <= DATE(chg.readDateTime)
  WHERE chg.fuel = 'gas'
), main AS (
    SELECT ae.* FROM adj_elec ae
    INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.non_comms_billing_base_data_eligible` e ON e.accountNumber = ae.accountNumber
    LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.2019_11_late_stage_collections` c ON c.account_No = CAST(ae.accountNumber AS INT64)
    WHERE adjustmentDays = 0 AND adjustmentType <> 'equal'
    AND c.account_No IS NULL
    UNION DISTINCT
    SELECT ag.* FROM adj_gas ag
    INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.non_comms_billing_base_data_eligible` e ON e.accountNumber = ag.accountNumber
    LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.2019_11_late_stage_collections` c ON c.account_No = CAST(ag.accountNumber AS INT64)
    WHERE adjustmentDays = 0 AND adjustmentType <> 'equal'
    AND c.account_No IS NULL
)
SELECT 
  accountNumber
  ,msn
  ,fuel
  ,consumerNumber
  ,invoiceId
  ,statementId
  ,migrationRead AS gentrackBilledRead
  ,migrationReadDate AS gentrackBilledDate
  ,migrationReadType AS gentrackBilledReadType
  ,reading AS smartReading
  ,readDateTime AS smartReadDateTime
  ,consumptionAdjustment AS readDifference
  ,COUNT(msn) OVER(PARTITION BY accountNumber) AS totalMetersOnThisAccount
FROM 
  main 
WHERE
  migrationReadDate >= DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL -2 MONTH)
ORDER By 
  accountNumber
query.556:
WITH electricity_consumption AS (
  SELECT STRUCT(metadata.traceToken AS traceToken,
                metadata.createdAt AS createdAt) AS metadata,
         mpan,
         msn,
         fromReading.readingDateTime AS fromDateTime,
         toReading.readingDateTime AS toDateTime,
         ARRAY(SELECT STRUCT(cons_reg.tier,
                             cons_reg.clockingTimeId,
                             from_reg.reading AS fromMeterReading,
                             to_reg.reading AS toMeterReading,
                             cons_reg.energy AS consumption,
                             fromReading.readingType AS fromReadingType,
                             toReading.readingType AS toReadingType)) tiers,
         kafkaData.insertTime AS insertTime
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v5` r
  INNER JOIN UNNEST (consumption.registers) AS cons_reg
  INNER JOIN UNNEST (fromReading.registers) AS from_reg ON from_reg.tier=cons_reg.tier
  INNER JOIN UNNEST (toReading.registers) AS to_reg ON to_reg.tier=cons_reg.tier

  UNION ALL

  SELECT STRUCT(metadata.traceToken AS traceToken,
         metadata.createdAt AS createdAt) AS metadata, 
         mpan,
         msn, 
         fromDateTime, 
         toDateTime, 
         tiers,
         kafkaData.insertTime AS insertTime
		FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v4` r
   
	  UNION ALL

		SELECT metadata,
           mpan,
           msn,
           fromDateTime,
           toDateTime,
           ARRAY(SELECT STRUCT(t.tier,
                               t.clockingTimeId,
                               t.fromMeterReading,
                               t.toMeterReading,
                               t.consumption,
                               'SmartReading' as fromReadingType,
                               'SmartReading' as toReadingType)) tiers,
           metadata.createdAt AS insertTime
		FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_historic_electricity_consumption` r
    INNER JOIN UNNEST(r.tiers) t
	
)

SELECT ec.*
FROM electricity_consumption AS ec
LEFT JOIN electricity_consumption AS overlapping 
ON overlapping.mpan = ec.mpan 
AND overlapping.fromDateTime < ec.toDateTime 
AND overlapping.toDateTime > ec.fromDateTime 
AND overlapping.insertTime > ec.insertTime
WHERE overlapping.mpan IS NULL
query.564:
WITH gas_energy_consumption AS (
    SELECT STRUCT(metadata.traceToken AS traceToken,
                  metadata.createdAt AS createdAt) AS metadata,
           mprn,
           msn,
           consumption.chargingZone,
           fromReading.readingDateTime AS fromDateTime,
           fromReading.reading AS fromMeterReading,
           fromReading.readingType AS fromReadingType,
           toReading.readingDateTime AS toDateTime,
           toReading.reading AS toMeterReading,
           toReading.readingType AS toReadingType,
           consumption.volume AS volume,
           consumption.calorificValues,
           consumption.effectiveCalorificValue,
           consumption.energy AS consumption,
           kafkaData.insertTime AS insertTime
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_gas_energy_consumption_generated_v5` r

  UNION ALL
	
		SELECT STRUCT(metadata.traceToken AS traceToken
                  , metadata.createdAt AS createdAt) AS metadata
                  , mprn
                  , msn
                  , chargingZone
                  , fromDateTime
                  , fromMeterReading
                  , fromReadingType	
                  , toDateTime
                  , toMeterReading
                  , toReadingType
                  , volume
                  , calorificValues
                  , effectiveCalorificValue
                  , consumption
                  , kafkaData.insertTime AS insertTime
		FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_gas_energy_consumption_generated_v2`
	
	UNION ALL
	
		SELECT metadata
          , mprn
          , msn
          , chargingZone
          , fromDateTime
          , fromMeterReading
          , 'SmartReading' AS fromReadingType
          , toDateTime
          , toMeterReading
          , 'SmartReading' AS toReadingType
          , volume
          , calorificValues
          , effectiveCalorificValue
          , consumption
          , metadata.createdAt AS insertTime
		FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_historic_gas_energy_consumption`
	
)

SELECT gec.*
FROM gas_energy_consumption AS gec
LEFT JOIN gas_energy_consumption AS overlapping
       ON overlapping.mprn = gec.mprn
       AND overlapping.fromDateTime < gec.toDateTime AND overlapping.toDateTime > gec.fromDateTime
       AND overlapping.insertTime > gec.insertTime
WHERE overlapping.mprn IS NULL
query.609:
with sfe as (
select  if (MSN is null, 'null', MSN) as MSN, 
        if (MPXN is null, 0, CAST(MPXN AS INT64)) as MPXN,
        timestamp,
        lower(fuel) fuel
        from (
         select snapshotData.device.serialNumber MSN,
                SAFE_CAST(snapshotData.device.servicePointNumber AS INT64) MPXN,
                snapshotData.device.supplyType fuel,                
                snapshotData.device.snapshotTime as timestamp,
                row_number() over (partition by snapshotData.device.servicePointNumber order by snapshotData.device.snapshotTime desc) rank
         from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_msd_received`
         where snapshotData.device.snapshotTime < current_timestamp()
        )
       where rank = 1
),

smets2_e as (
    select if (MSN is null, 'null', MSN) as MSN, 
           if (MPXN is null, 0, CAST(MPXN AS INT64)) as MPXN,
           timestamp,
           'electricity' fuel
    from (select body.xreadOut01.meter.msn MSN,
                 SAFE_CAST(body.xreadOut01.meter.importMpan AS INT64) MPXN,
                 header.timestamp as timestamp,
                 row_number() over (partition by body.xreadOut01.meter.importMpan order by header.timestamp desc) rank
           from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_BOL_XREADOUT01_validated` 
           where header.timestamp < current_timestamp()
     )
     where rank = 1
     and MPXN != 0
),

smets2_g as (
    select if (MSN is null, 'null', MSN) as MSN, 
           if (MPXN is null, 0, CAST(MPXN AS INT64)) as MPXN,
           timestamp,
           'gas' fuel
    from (select body.xreadOut01.meter.msn MSN,
                 SAFE_CAST(body.xreadOut01.meter.importMprn AS INT64) MPXN,
                 header.timestamp as timestamp,
                 row_number() over (partition by body.xreadOut01.meter.importMprn order by header.timestamp desc) rank
           from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_BOL_XREADOUT01_validated` 
           where header.timestamp < current_timestamp()
     )
     where rank = 1
     and MPXN != 0
),
           
smets2 as (
  select * from smets2_g 
  
  union all 
  
  select * from smets2_e
),           

latest_read_union as (
  select * from sfe
  
  union all
  
  select * from smets2
),

latest_read_mapping as (
  select *
  from (
      select MSN,
             MPXN,
             timestamp,
             fuel,
             row_number() over (partition by MPXN order by timestamp desc) rank
       from latest_read_union
   )
   where rank = 1
   AND CAST(timestamp AS DATE) >= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE,INTERVAL 2 MONTH)
),

spam_e AS (
    SELECT CAST(t.MPXN AS INT64) spam_MPXN, 
           if (MSN is null, 'null', MSN) spam_MSN, 
           insert_time,
           'electricity' fuel
    FROM (
        SELECT MPXN, 
               MSN, 
               kafkaData.insertTime as insert_time, 
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime DESC, kafkaData.offset DESC, sp.supplyStartDate DESC, ih.startDate DESC) AS rank
        FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
        INNER JOIN UNNEST(supplyPeriods) sp
        INNER JOIN UNNEST(installationHistory) ih
     ) t
     WHERE t.rank = 1
),
            
spam_g AS (
    SELECT CAST(t.MPXN AS INT64) spam_MPXN, 
           if (MSN is null, 'null', MSN) spam_MSN, 
           insert_time,
           'gas' fuel
    FROM (
        SELECT MPXN, 
               MSN, 
               kafkaData.insertTime as insert_time, 
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime DESC, kafkaData.offset DESC, sp.supplyStartDate DESC, ih.startDate DESC) AS rank
        FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_gasSupplyPointHistory_v2`
        INNER JOIN UNNEST(supplyPeriods) sp
        INNER JOIN UNNEST(installationHistory) ih
     ) t
     WHERE t.rank = 1
),

spam as (
    select * from spam_e
    where CAST(insert_time AS DATE) >= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE,INTERVAL 2 MONTH)
    
    union all 
    
    select * from spam_g
    where CAST(insert_time AS DATE) >= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE,INTERVAL 2 MONTH)
),

orion AS (
    SELECT cast(mpxn as int64) mpxn,
           true on_orion
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points`
    WHERE chargeMandateStatus = 'Has Current Charge Mandate'
),

sp_details as (
select spam_MPXN MPXN,
       spam_MSN msn, 
       s.fuel
from spam s
JOIN latest_read_mapping m on s.spam_MPXN = m.MPXN and s.fuel = m.fuel and s.spam_MSN != m.MSN
)

select sp_details.*,
       if(orion.on_orion is true, true, false) on_orion
from sp_details
left join orion on sp_details.mpxn = orion.mpxn
query.611:
with
latest_data_per_sp as (
  select * except(n) from (SELECT *, row_number() over(partition by MPXN order by kafkadata.inserttime desc, kafkadata.offset desc) n 
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
--   ignore BigQuery messages inserted more than 90 days ago
  where kafkaData.insertTime > TIMESTAMP_ADD(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), INTERVAL -90 DAY)) where n = 1),

with_latest_meter_and_supply as (
  select *, 
         (select as struct * from unnest(installationHistory) ih order by ih.startDate desc limit 1) latestInstallation,
         (select as struct * from unnest(supplyPeriods) sps order by sps.supplyStartDate desc limit 1) latestSupplyPeriod
  from latest_data_per_sp
),

with_convenience_fields as (
  select *,
          case
           when latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is true and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate < current_date()
             -- is loss confirmed and has an end date set and end date is before today
           then "offSupply"
           when (latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is null and (latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is false or latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is null))
             or (latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate >= current_date())
             -- isn't missing supply period data, and either doesn't have a loss journey (is not loss confirmed and has no end date set)
             -- or is in the loss journey but hasn't reached loss yet (has end date set and end date is before or equal to today)
           then "onSupply"
           when latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate < current_date() and (latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is false or latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is null)
           -- when it looks like it should have been lost, but we haven't received lossConfirmed, it's likely in dispute and so still on supply
           then "unconfirmedLoss"
           else "NULL" end supplyOnOff,
         latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and current_date() <= date_add(latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate, interval 20 day) inLoss,
         latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and current_date() < latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate ingain
  from with_latest_meter_and_supply),
  
ambiguous_meters as (select MSN, if(total > 1, true, false) ambiguous_meter from
           (select latestInstallation.MSN, count(1) total
            from with_convenience_fields
            where latestInstallation.MSN != "NULL"
            and supplyPointType != "export"
            and supplyOnOff != "offSupply"
            group by MSN))

select MPXN,
       (case when latestInstallation.MSN is null then "NULL" else latestInstallation.MSN end) MSN,
       kafkaData.insertTime insertTime,
       (case when latestInstallation.MSN is null then false else true end) mappingFound,
       (case when inloss = true then "in loss"
             when ingain = true then "in gain"
             else supplyOnOff end) supplyStatus,
       ambiguous_meter
from with_convenience_fields
LEFT JOIN ambiguous_meters on latestInstallation.MSN = ambiguous_meters.MSN

           when latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate < current_date() and (latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is false or latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is null)
           -- when it looks like it should have been lost, but we haven't received lossConfirmed, it's likely in dispute and so still on supply
           then "unconfirmedLoss"
           else "NULL" end supplyOnOff,
         latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and current_date() <= date_add(latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate, interval 20 day) inLoss,
         latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and current_date() < latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate ingain
  from with_latest_meter_and_supply),

ambiguous_meters as (select MSN, if(total > 1, true, false) ambiguous_meter from
           (select latestInstallation.MSN, count(1) total
            from with_convenience_fields
            where latestInstallation.MSN != "NULL"
            and supplyOnOff != "offSupply"
            group by MSN))

select MPXN,
       (case when latestInstallation.MSN is null then "NULL" else latestInstallation.MSN end) MSN,
       kafkaData.insertTime insertTime,
       (case when latestInstallation.MSN is null then false else true end) mappingFound,
       (case when inloss = true then "in loss"
             when ingain = true then "in gain"
             else supplyOnOff end) supplyStatus,
       ambiguous_meter
from with_convenience_fields
LEFT JOIN ambiguous_meters on latestInstallation.MSN = ambiguous_meters.MSN

WITH valid_ssc_tpr_combos as (
  select ssc valid_ssc,
         (SELECT STRING_AGG(tprs)
          FROM UNNEST(ARRAY(SELECT CAST(tpr as string)
                            FROM UNNEST(tprs) AS tpr
                            ORDER BY tpr)
                            ) AS tprs) valid_tprs
  FROM (
    SELECT Standard_Settlement_Configuration_ID ssc,
           ARRAY_AGG(DISTINCT Time_Pattern_Regime_ID) tprs
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_eligibility__valid_measurement_requirement_profile_class_view` 
    GROUP BY Standard_Settlement_Configuration_ID)
    ),

 spam_supply_points AS (
  SELECT MPXN,
         IF (meterRegisterHistory[ordinal(1)].ssc is null, 0, CAST(meterRegisterHistory[ordinal(1)].ssc AS INT64)) ssc,
         IF (meterRegisterHistory[ordinal(1)].meterRegisters is null or array_length(meterRegisterHistory[ordinal(1)].meterRegisters) = 0,
              "NULL",
              (SELECT STRING_AGG(CAST(tpr AS STRING))
                FROM (SELECT IF (registers.timePatternRegime IS NULL, 0, registers.timePatternRegime) AS tpr 
                      FROM unnest(meterRegisterHistory[ordinal(1)].meterRegisters) AS registers
                      ORDER BY tpr))) spam_tprs
  FROM (SELECT 
          MPXN, 
          MSN,
          kafkaData.insertTime,
          ARRAY(SELECT x
                FROM UNNEST(meterRegisterHistory) AS x 
                ORDER BY startDate DESC) AS meterRegisterHistory,
          ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime DESC, kafkaData.offset DESC, sp.supplyStartDate DESC, ih.startDate DESC) AS rank
        FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
        LEFT JOIN UNNEST(supplyPeriods) sp
        LEFT JOIN UNNEST(installationHistory) ih)
  WHERE rank = 1
    AND (meterRegisterHistory IS NOT NULL AND array_length(meterRegisterHistory) > 0)
    )
 
SELECT MPXN
  FROM spam_supply_points, valid_ssc_tpr_combos
  WHERE (spam_supply_points.ssc = valid_ssc_tpr_combos.valid_ssc
         and spam_supply_points.spam_tprs != valid_ssc_tpr_combos.valid_tprs)
     OR spam_supply_points.ssc NOT IN (SELECT valid_ssc FROM valid_ssc_tpr_combos)
  ORDER BY MPXN

query.639:
# Obtain latest RAC reads data by MPAN, counting the number of readings to identify number of registers
with latest_read_per_mpxn as (
  select value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.mpan as mpxn,
         array_agg(struct(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.msn as msn,
                          value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime as read_timestamp,
                          (select count(reading) from unnest(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.registers)) as n_readings,
                          (select string_agg(cast(tier as string)) from unnest(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.registers)) as registers,
                          (select string_agg(cast(reading as string)) from unnest(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.registers)) as readings
                          )
                    order by value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime desc
                    limit 1
                    ) as deets
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_msd_simplified_v2`
  where value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.msn is not null
  group by value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.mpan
),
# Obtain smart MSNs, identifying latest data
smart_MSNs as (
  select distinct ih.MSN,
         row_number() over (partition by mpxn order by kafkadata.insertTime desc, kafkadata.offset desc, sp.supplyStartDate desc, ih.startDate desc) as rn
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
  inner join unnest(supplyPeriods) sp
  inner join unnest(installationHistory) ih
  where ih.meterType = 'S1' or ih.meterType like 'S2%'
),
# Obtain latest MSN and register history for MPAN based on SPAM
latest_meter_register_history as (
  select MPXN,
         MSN,
         startdate,
         mrh
  from (
        select MPXN, 
               (select MSN from unnest(installationHistory) order by startdate desc limit 1) as MSN,
               (select startDate from unnest(installationHistory) order by startdate desc limit 1) as startdate,
               (select meterRegisterHistory from unnest(installationHistory) order by startdate desc limit 1) as mrh,
               (select endDate from unnest(installationHistory) order by startdate desc limit 1) as endDate
        from (
              select *,
                     row_number() over (partition by mpxn order by kafkadata.inserttime desc, kafkadata.offset desc, sp.supplyStartDate desc) n
              from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
              inner join unnest (supplyPeriods) sp
              ) x
        where n = 1)
  order by MPXN, MSN
),
# Count number of registers from SPAM MSN data where MSN is a smart meter
latest_tprs_smart_only as (
   select MPXN,
          MSN,
          string_agg(cast(lr.timePatternRegime as string) order by lr.timepatternregime) as tprs,
          count(distinct lr.meterregisterid) as n_registers,
          max(startdate) as startdate
  from (
        select MPXN,
               MSN,
               startdate,
               (select meterRegisters from unnest(mrh) order by startdate desc limit 1) as latest_registers
        from latest_meter_register_history
        ),
  unnest(latest_registers) lr
  where MSN in (select MSN from smart_MSNs where rn=1)
  group by MPXN, MSN
),
# Find if mpxn is on Orion
orion as (
  select MPXN,
         true as on_orion
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points`
  where chargeMandateStatus = 'Has Current Charge Mandate'
  and fuel = 'electricity'
)
# Select non-Orion MPXNs where the number of registers on SPAM and RAC don't match
select cast(MPXN as string) as MPXN 
from (
      select c.*,
             if(orion.on_orion, true, false) as on_orion,
             'electricity' as fuel
      from (
            select a.*,
                   b.*
            from latest_tprs_smart_only a
            left join (select mpxn as r_mpxn,
                              msn as r_msn,
                              registers,
                              read_timestamp,
                              n_readings as r_n_readings,
                              readings
                       from latest_read_per_mpxn,
                       unnest(deets)
                       ) b
            on a.MPXN = b.r_mpxn
            where r_msn is not null
              and r_msn = msn
              and date(read_timestamp) > startdate
              and n_registers <> r_n_readings
            order by read_timestamp desc, a.mpxn
            ) c
      left join orion on c.mpxn = orion.mpxn
      )
where on_orion is false
query.640:
# SPAM data, identifying latest data for elec MPAN
WITH cte_meter_dedupe as (
	SELECT sp.mpxn,
         ih.meterRegisterHistory,
	       ROW_NUMBER() over(partition by MPXN order by kafkaData.insertTime desc, ih.startDate desc) rank 
	FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2` sp
  INNER JOIN UNNEST(installationHistory) ih
),
# Obtain latest MPAN data, identify latest meter register data
cte_meter as (
	SELECT sp.mpxn,
	       mh.meterRegisters,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY sp.mpxn ORDER BY mh.startDate DESC) rank
	FROM cte_meter_dedupe sp
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(sp.meterRegisterHistory) mh
  WHERE sp.rank = 1
),
# Obtain latest meter register data, count the number of registers on the MPAN
cte_registers as (
    SELECT m.mpxn
          ,COUNT(DISTINCT mr.meterRegisterId) Num_Registers
    FROM cte_meter m
    LEFT JOIN UNNEST(m.meterRegisters) mr
    WHERE rank = 1
    GROUP BY m.mpxn
),
# Identify latest reads data
cte_Raw_Reads as (
    SELECT DISTINCT CAST(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime AS DATE) AS Read_Date,
                    value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.mpan as MPXN,
                    r.tier as Tier,
                    RANK() OVER(PARTITION BY value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.mpan ORDER BY CAST(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime AS DATE) DESC) RN
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_msd_simplified`,
    UNNEST(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.registers) r     
),
# Count number of tiers on the latest reads data
cte_tiers as (
    select reads.MPXN,
           Count(DISTINCT reads.Tier) as Num_Tiers
    from cte_raw_reads reads
    WHERE RN = 1
    group by reads.MPXN
),
# Count number of registers on the meter point in GT
GT_registers as (
SELECT I.meter_point_no,
       count(distinct register_id) as num_Registers
FROM `data-engineering-prod.reporting_meters.v_Register` R
INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reporting_meters.v_Installation` I
  ON R.installation_no=I.installation_no
INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Consumer` con
  ON con.meter_point_no = I.meter_point_no
  AND con.installation_no = I.installation_no
  AND con.Lifecycle_Category = 'Live (Excluding Loss)'
WHERE Is_Latest_Register = 1
  AND I.Utility_Type_Code = 'E'
GROUP BY meter_point_no
)
# Find profile class for contract and compare to the number of SPAM registers and number of GT registers for the MPAN FOR TRAD ACCOUNTS
SELECT DISTINCT core.Account_No,
       core.Meter_Type_Category,
       spam.Num_Registers as spam_registers,
       CASE WHEN cp.Profile_Class_Code = 'N/A' THEN NULL
            WHEN cp.Profile_Class_Code = '03' THEN 1
            WHEN cp.Profile_Class_Code = '04' THEN 2
            ELSE CAST(cp.Profile_Class_Code AS INT64)
       END as contract_registers,
       gt.Num_Registers as gt_registers,
       null as reads_registers
FROM `andromeda-data-nonprod.eligibility.core_accounts` core
INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Consumer` con on con.Account_No = core.Account_No and con.Lifecycle_Category = 'Live (Excluding Loss)'
INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reporting_contracts.v_Contract_Period` cp on cp.Consumer_No = con.Consumer_No AND cp.Is_Current_Contract_Period  = True
INNER JOIN cte_registers spam on CAST(spam.MPXN AS INT64) = CAST(con.Meter_Point_No AS INT64)
INNER JOIN gt_registers gt on con.Meter_Point_No = gt.Meter_Point_No
WHERE core.Meter_Type_Category like '%Dumb%'

UNION DISTINCT
# Find profile class for contract and compare profile class, number of SPAM registers, number of GT registers, and number of RAC tiers FOR SMART ACCOUNTS
SELECT DISTINCT core.Account_No,
       core.Meter_Type_Category,
       spam.Num_Registers as spam_registers,
       CASE WHEN cp.Profile_Class_Code = 'N/A' THEN NULL
            WHEN cp.Profile_Class_Code = '03' THEN 1
            WHEN cp.Profile_Class_Code = '04' THEN 2
            ELSE CAST(cp.Profile_Class_Code AS INT64)
       END as contract_registers,
       gt.Num_Registers as gt_registers,
       t.Num_Tiers as reads_registers
FROM `andromeda-data-nonprod.eligibility.core_accounts` core
INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Consumer` con on con.Account_No = core.Account_No and con.Lifecycle_Category = 'Live (Excluding Loss)'
INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reporting_contracts.v_Contract_Period` cp on cp.Consumer_No = con.Consumer_No AND cp.Is_Current_Contract_Period  = True
INNER JOIN cte_registers spam on CAST(spam.MPXN AS INT64) = CAST(con.Meter_Point_No AS INT64)
INNER JOIN gt_registers gt on con.Meter_Point_No = gt.Meter_Point_No
INNER JOIN cte_tiers t on CAST(t.mpxn AS INT64) = CAST(con.Meter_Point_No AS INT64)
WHERE core.Meter_Type_Category  like '%Smart%'

query.647:
with elec as (
  with
  real_multi as (
    with 
    multi_with_loss_info as (
      with
      multi_msn_same_150 as (
        select * from (
          select *, 
                 count(distinct msn) over (partition by file_id, mpxn) n
          from (
            select * from (
              select record.MpanCores.mpanCore mpxn,
                     header.fileIdentifier file_id,
                     mi.meterIdSerialNumber msn,
                     mi.dateOfMeterInstallation install_date
              from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_D0150001_split_v4`, unnest(record.MpanCores.meterRetrievalMethodDetails) mi)
            group by file_id, mpxn, msn, install_date))
        where n > 1),
      --multi_msn_same_150
      
      cos_loss as (
      select * from (
        select if(MPXN is null, 'null', MPXN) MPXN,
               if(MSN is null, 'null', MSN) MSN,
               status, fuel, ih
        from (
          select MPXN,
                 MSN,
                 'electricity' fuel,
                 CASE WHEN supplyStartDate <= CURRENT_DATE() AND supplyEndDate >= CURRENT_DATE() AND lossConfirmed = true THEN 'Loss confirmed'
                      WHEN supplyStartDate <= CURRENT_DATE() AND supplyEndDate >= CURRENT_DATE() THEN 'Loss notified'
                      WHEN supplyStartDate > CURRENT_DATE() THEN 'Onboarding'
                      WHEN supplyStartDate < CURRENT_DATE() AND supplyEndDate < CURRENT_DATE() THEN 'Off supply'
                      WHEN supplyStartDate <= CURRENT_DATE() AND supplyEndDate IS NULL THEN 'On supply'
                      ELSE NULL
                 END as status,
                 ih,
                 ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by MPXN, MSN order by kafkaData.insertTime desc, kafkaData.offset desc, sp.supplyStartDate desc, ih.startDate desc) as rank
          from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
          inner join unnest(supplyPeriods) sp
          inner join unnest(installationHistory) ih
          order by kafkaData.insertTime desc)
        where rank = 1)
      where MPXN <> 'null'
        and status in ('Loss confirmed','Off supply')),
      --cos_loss
  
      removals as (
        select * from (
          select record.MpanCores.mpanCore mpxn,
                 mr.meterIdSerialNumber msn,
                 mr.dateOfMeterRemoval remove_date
          from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_D0150001_split_v4`, unnest(record.MpanCores.metersRemoved) mr)
        group by mpxn, msn, remove_date)
      --removals
      
      select mm.*, 
             cos_loss.status, 
             removals.remove_date
      from multi_msn_same_150 mm 
      left join cos_loss
        on mm.mpxn = cos_loss.mpxn
      left join removals
        on mm.mpxn = removals.mpxn and
           mm.msn = removals.msn
      )
    --multi_with_loss_info
    
      select mpxn, msn from (
      select *, coalesce(remove_date, if(max(install_date) over (partition by mpxn) = install_date, null, max(install_date) over (partition by mpxn))) remove_date_inferred
      from multi_with_loss_info)
      where status is null and remove_date_inferred is null
    )
  --real_multi
  
    select mpxn,
           'electricity' fuel,
           count(distinct msn) number_of_meters,
           array_agg(distinct msn) msn
    from (
      select * from (
        select *, 
               count(distinct msn) over (partition by mpxn) n
        from real_multi)
      where n <> 1)
    group by mpxn, n
),
--elec
orion as (
  select mpxn,
         fuel,
         true on_orion
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points`
  where chargeMandateStatus = 'Has Current Charge Mandate' and
        mpxn is not null
)
--orion

select ms.*, if(orion.on_orion, true, false) on_orion from (
  select * from elec
  --union all
  --select * from gas
  ) ms
left join orion on
ms.mpxn = orion.mpxn and
ms.fuel = orion.fuel

ch.consumption,
c.charge_from_date,
c.charge_to_date,
is_consumption_adjustment,
row_number() over (partition by c.supply_Point, ch.clockingTimeID order by ch.clockingTimeID desc, charge_to_date desc, charge_from_date desc) as charge_order
FROM
`data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_charges_extract` c
INNER JOIN unnest (c.charges) ch
where is_cancelled = 0
)
,
cte_adjustment_reads as
(
Select
mpxn,
datetime(lastSmartReadDatetime) as fromDateTime,
datetime(finalReadDatetime) as toDateTime,
r.clockingTimeId,
r.meterRead as fromRead,
r.lossRead as toRead
From  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_loss_adjustments` la
inner Join unnest (la.meterRegisters) r
)
SELECT
Distinct
ach.*,
la.fromRead,
ach.charge_order as AdjustmentChargeOrder,
pch.charge_order as previousChargeOrder,
FROM

Inner join cte_adjustment_reads la on ach.supply_point = la.mpxn and ach.clockingTimeId = la.clockingTimeID and ach.toMeterReading = la.toRead and ach.charge_to_date = la.toDateTime and ach.charge_from_date = la.fromDateTime

query.865:
/*** HISTORICAL ESTIMATION FOR CONTRACT CHANGE DATES  ***/

-- piggybacking on Victor's code for contracts to start with
WITH cte_contracts_raw AS(  
  SELECT
    a.unionRecord.Contract.mpxn,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.serviceAccountId,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.fuel,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.contractId,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.metadata.createdAt,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.startDate,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.endDate,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.lossConfirmed,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY a.unionRecord.Contract.serviceAccountId, a.unionRecord.Contract.mpxn, a.unionRecord.Contract.contractId, a.unionRecord.Contract.startDate ORDER BY a.unionRecord.Contract.metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rn
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract_v3` a
  LEFT JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT unionRecord.Cancelled.contractId FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract_v3`) b --Remove cancelled contracts
  ON a.unionRecord.Contract.contractId = b.contractId
  WHERE a.unionRecord.Contract IS NOT NULL 
  AND b.contractId IS NULL
  ),
cte_contracts AS(    
  SELECT serviceAccountId
        , fuel
        , mpxn
        , contractId
        , createdAt
        , startDate
        , endDate  
        , ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY serviceAccountId, mpxn ORDER BY startDate DESC) contractOrderDesc
        , ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY serviceAccountId, mpxn ORDER BY startDate ASC) contractOrderAsc
        , lossConfirmed
  FROM cte_contracts_raw
  WHERE rn=1
  AND lossConfirmed IS NULL --J ust live supplies?
  AND startDate BETWEEN '2019-04-12' AND '2019-09-01' -- up to september last year
 ),
 --remove those accounts-mpxn where its last contract is loss confirmed
 cte_contracts_clean AS(
   SELECT a.serviceAccountId
          , a.fuel
          , a.mpxn
          , a.contractId
          , a.createdAt
          , a.startDate
          , a.endDate  
          , a.contractOrderDesc
          , a.contractOrderAsc
   FROM cte_contracts a
   LEFT JOIN
             (SELECT DISTINCT serviceAccountId, mpxn
             FROM cte_contracts 
             WHERE lossConfirmed IS true 
             AND contractOrderDesc = 1) b
   USING (serviceAccountId, mpxn)
   WHERE b.serviceAccountId IS NULL
),
 -- get consumption data
cte_consumption AS(
  SELECT DISTINCT
     mpan AS mpxn
    ,msn
    ,fromDateTime
    ,toDateTime
    ,consumption
    ,fromMeterReading
    ,toMeterReading
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v2` -- consumption v2 runs from April 2019 to September 2019, which covers the whole period required
  UNION ALL 
  SELECT DISTINCT 
     mprn AS mpxn
    ,msn
    ,fromDateTime
    ,toDateTime
    ,volume AS consumption
    ,fromMeterReading
    ,toMeterReading
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_gas_volume_consumption_generated_v2`-- consumption v2 runs from April 2019 to now, which covers the whole period required
),
-- removes cases where there is a consumption block terminating on contract start date (Victor's code)
cte_contracts_filtered AS(
  SELECT 
    a.*
  FROM cte_contracts_clean a
  LEFT JOIN cte_consumption b
  ON a.mpxn = b.MPXN
  AND a.startDate = DATE(b.toDateTime)
  WHERE b.MPXN IS NULL
  
  
  -- ****** BULK OF THE NEW CODE IS BELOW *******
  -- main addition: find consumption blocks bridging the contract start date, and work out the period between 
  -- the fromDate to the contract startDate as a proportion of the whole block. Rather than using days, the
  -- clever bit is to use the change in the cumulatiev demand coefficient. To do this, we first capture the
  -- demand coefficients and then express them in cumulative form:
),
  -- get coefficients
coefficients AS (
  SELECT
     settlement_date AS applicableDate
    ,AVG(ALP) AS usageCoefficient
    ,'gas' AS fuel
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.rac_gas_loadProfiles` 
  WHERE
    band = 1
    AND settlement_Date >= DATE_ADD('2019-04-12', INTERVAL -1 YEAR) -- go from one year before to one year after the constract start date
    AND settlement_Date <= DATE_ADD('2019-09-01', INTERVAL 1 YEAR)
  GROUP BY
    settlement_date
  UNION ALL
  SELECT
    settlementDate AS applicableDate
    ,SUM(customerDemand) AS usageCoefficient
    ,'electricity' AS fuel
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.rac_electricity_loadProfiles`
  WHERE
    profileClassId = 1
    AND settlementDate >= DATE_ADD('2019-04-12', INTERVAL -1 YEAR) -- go from one year before to one year after the constract start date
    AND settlementDate <= DATE_ADD('2019-09-01', INTERVAL 1 YEAR)
  GROUP BY 
    settlementDate
),
-- take the cumulative coefficient using the running sum (sum window) function
cumulative AS (
  SELECT
     applicableDate
    ,fuel
    ,SUM(usageCoefficient) OVER(PARTITION BY fuel ORDER BY applicableDate) AS cumulativeCoefficient
  FROM
    coefficients
-- gather all of the data on the consumption block that straddles the  contract change date. This involves triple-joining on the 
-- new cumulative coefficients table for each of the three main dates (block start, block end, contract start). Then, take the 
-- difference between the cumulative coefficient values for the contract start and block start, and contract end and block start
), straddling_block AS (
  SELECT
     ct.*
    ,cons.msn
    ,cons.fromDateTime
    ,cons.toDateTime
    ,cons.consumption
    ,cons.fromMeterReading
    ,cons.toMeterReading
    ,cu1.cumulativeCoefficient AS fromDateCoefficient
    ,cu2.cumulativeCoefficient AS toDateCoefficient
    ,cu.cumulativeCoefficient AS contractStartDateCoefficient
    ,cu2.cumulativeCoefficient - cu1.cumulativeCoefficient AS sumOfCoefficientsWholeBlock
    ,cu.cumulativeCoefficient - cu1.cumulativeCoefficient AS sumOfCoefficientsBefore
  FROM
    cte_contracts_filtered ct
  INNER JOIN
    cte_consumption cons
      ON  cons.mpxn = ct.mpxn
      AND DATE(cons.fromDateTime) < ct.startDate 
      AND DATE(cons.toDateTime) > ct.startDate
   INNER JOIN
      cumulative cu
        ON cu.fuel = ct.fuel
        AND cu.applicableDate = ct.startDate
   INNER JOIN
      cumulative cu1
        ON cu1.fuel = ct.fuel
        AND cu1.applicableDate = DATE(cons.fromDateTime)
   INNER JOIN
      cumulative cu2
        ON cu2.fuel = ct.fuel
        AND cu2.applicableDate = DATE(cons.toDateTime)
  ORDER BY
    serviceAccountId, ct.mpxn, ct.startDate
) 
  -- This then means we can simply work out the ratio between these two differences (giving the proportion of the block to 
  -- attribute to before the contract change. Adding this to the fromMeterReading gives us our estimate.
SELECT 
   * 
   ,sumOfCoefficientsBefore/sumOfCoefficientsWholeBlock AS proportionOfBlock
   ,ROUND(fromMeterReading + ((sumOfCoefficientsBefore / sumOfCoefficientsWholeBlock) * consumption),0) AS estimatedReading
FROM straddling_block
query.866:
-- ALL NOSIs per MPRN --
WITH NOSI AS(
  select MPXN, NOSI_MSN, NOSI_date from (
    select record.NosiGroup.meterPointReference MPXN, record.NosiGroup.meterSerialNumber NOSI_MSN, PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", header.createdDate) NOSI_date
    from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_NOSI_split_v1`)
  where MPXN is not null and NOSI_MSN is not null and NOSI_date is not null
  group by MPXN, NOSI_MSN, NOSI_date),

-- ALL MRIs per MPRN --
MRI AS
(select MPXN, MRI_MSN, MRI_date
 from (
 select record.MeterReadInstructions.meterPointReference MPXN, record.MeterReadInstructions.meterSerialNumber MRI_MSN, PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", header.creationDate) MRI_date
 from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_MRI_POST_NEXUS_split_v4`)
 where MRI_date is not null and MPXN is not null and MRI_MSN is not null
 group by MPXN, MRI_MSN, MRI_date),
 
-- ALL ONUPDs per MPRN --
ONUPD AS
(select MPXN, ONUPD_MSN, ONUPD_date from (
  select MP.meterPointReference MPXN, ASSET.serialNumber ONUPD_MSN, PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", header.createdDate) ONUPD_date
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_ONUPD_split_v4`,
  unnest(record.Transaction.meterPoint) AS MP,
  unnest(MP.asset) AS ASSET)),

-- LATEST SSD per MPRN --
SPAMSSD as
(select MPXN, MSN, SSD from
  (select MPXN, MSN, supplyStatusDate SSD, supplystatus SS
   from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_current_gas_mapping`
   where supplystatus = 'Gain completed')
 group by MPXN, MSN, SSD),

-- NEAREST MRI to SSD --
NMRI as (
  select MPXN, MRI_MSN, SSD, MRI_date, spam_mri_diff from (
    select *,
           row_number() over (partition by MPXN order by spam_mri_diff) n
    from (
      select SPAMSSD.*, MRI.MRI_date, MRI_MSN,
             abs(date_diff(MRI_date, SSD, Day)) spam_mri_diff
      from SPAMSSD
      left join MRI
      on SPAMSSD.MPXN = MRI.MPXN
      where MRI_date is not null
      order by SPAMSSD.MPXN, MRI_date desc)
    where spam_mri_diff <= 5)
  where n = 1),

-- NEAREST NOSI TO SSD --
NNOSI as (
  select MPXN, NOSI_MSN, SSD, NOSI_date, spam_nosi_diff from (
    select *,
           row_number() over (partition by MPXN order by spam_nosi_diff) n
    from (
      select SPAMSSD.*, NOSI.NOSI_date, NOSI_MSN,
             abs(date_diff(NOSI_date, SSD, Day)) spam_nosi_diff
      from SPAMSSD
      left join NOSI
      on SPAMSSD.MPXN = NOSI.MPXN
      where NOSI_date is not null
      order by SPAMSSD.MPXN, NOSI_date desc)
    where spam_nosi_diff <= 5)
  where n = 1),
  
-- NEAREST ONUPD TO SSD --
NONUPD as (
  select MPXN, ONUPD_MSN, SSD, ONUPD_date, spam_onupd_diff from (
    select *,
           row_number() over (partition by MPXN order by spam_onupd_diff) n
    from (
      select SPAMSSD.*, ONUPD.ONUPD_date, ONUPD_MSN,
             abs(date_diff(ONUPD_date, SSD, Day)) spam_onupd_diff
      from SPAMSSD
      left join ONUPD
      on SPAMSSD.MPXN = ONUPD.MPXN
      where ONUPD_date is not null
      order by SPAMSSD.MPXN, ONUPD_date desc)
    where spam_onupd_diff <= 5)
  where n = 1)

select * from (
select SPAMSSD.*,
ONUPD_MSN=MSN matching_ONUPD_MSN,
NOSI_MSN=MSN matching_NOSI_MSN,
MRI_MSN=MSN matching_MRI_MSN,
ONUPD_date, ONUPD_MSN, spam_onupd_diff, NOSI_date, NOSI_MSN, spam_nosi_diff, MRI_date, MRI_MSN, spam_mri_diff from SPAMSSD
left join NONUPD
on SPAMSSD.MPXN = NONUPD.MPXN
and SPAMSSD.SSD = NONUPD.SSD
left join NNOSI
on SPAMSSD.MPXN = NNOSI.MPXN
and SPAMSSD.SSD = NNOSI.SSD
left join NMRI
on SPAMSSD.MPXN = NMRI.MPXN
and SPAMSSD.SSD = NMRI.SSD)
where (NOSI_date is not null or MRI_date is not null or ONUPD_date is not null) and (matching_MRI_MSN = true and (matching_NOSI_MSN != true or matching_ONUPD_MSN != true))
order by SSD desc, MPXN
query.868:
/*  ======================================  */
/*  CONSUMPTION FROM ACTUAL METER READINGS  */
/*  ======================================  */


-- PURPOSE:
-- This view creates artifical consumption blocks excluding estimatedReadings, as is required for use in estimation. In 
-- order to ensure that only valid consumption blocks are created, SPAM latest mappings are checked against, and only 
-- consumption for the current meter is allowed.
-- Created: 2020-05-05
-- Last updated: 2020-05-05

WITH

/* CONSUMPTION FROM NON-ESTIMATES  */
-- from the full set of meter readings taken from mpxn consumption, create the latest available consumption blocks.
-- joining on SPAM data here ensures that no blocks are produces accross 
 actual_consumption AS (
   SELECT
     rd.mpxn
    ,rd.msn
    ,orionMeterType
    ,rd.tier
    ,rd.timeOfUseLabel
    ,rd.clockingTimeId
    ,readingDate AS toReadingDate
    ,meterReading AS toReading
    ,readingType AS toReadingType
    ,LAG(readingDate) OVER(PARTITION BY rd.mpxn, rd.msn, rd.tier, rd.timeOfUseLabel ORDER BY readingDate) AS fromReadingDate -- include tou label to ensure that no blocks are built across configs
    ,LAG(meterReading) OVER(PARTITION BY rd.mpxn, rd.msn, rd.tier, rd.timeOfUseLabel ORDER BY readingDate) AS fromReading
    ,LAG(readingType) OVER(PARTITION BY rd.mpxn, rd.msn, rd.tier, rd.timeOfUseLabel ORDER BY readingDate) AS fromReadingType
  FROM (
    SELECT
       rd.mpxn
      ,rd.msn
      ,CASE      -- this logic is safe, as SMETS2 is the only type with different register mappings and these types are robust in SPAM
        WHEN mp.meterType LIKE '%S2%' THEN 'SMETS2'
        WHEN mp.meterType LIKE 'S1%' THEN 'SMETS1'
        ELSE 'TRAD' END AS orionMeterType
      ,mp.tier
      ,mp.timeOfUseLabel
      ,mp.clockingTimeId
      ,readingDate
      ,meterReading
      ,readingType
      ,COUNT(DISTINCT rd.tier) OVER(PARTITION BY rd.mpxn,rd.msn,rd.readingDate) AS activeRegisterCount
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_unique_meter_readings` rd
    INNER JOIN
      `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_supply_meter_register_mappings` mp
        ON  rd.mpxn = mp.mpxn
        AND rd.msn = mp.msn
        AND COALESCE(rd.tier, 99) = mp.tier                               -- mapping data in mp guarantees tier. Default 99 for gas applied to the read data
        AND rd.readingDate >= mp.meterStartDate
        AND rd.readingDate < COALESCE(mp.meterEndDate, '2099-12-31')
        AND rd.readingDate >= mp.configStartDate
        AND rd.readingDate < COALESCE(mp.configEndDate, '2099-12-31') 
    WHERE
      readingType <> 'EstimatedReading'    -- only exclude estimated readings. This means we keep locked in estimates, like migration date reads. TODO review any new estimated type
  ) rd
),
cleaned_actual AS (
  SELECT
     mpxn
    ,msn
    ,orionMeterType
    ,tier
    ,timeOfUseLabel
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,fuel
    ,toReadingDate
    ,toReading
    ,ToReadingType
    ,fromReadingDate
    ,fromReading
    ,fromReadingType 
    ,usagePerDay
    ,blockLength
    ,CASE 
      WHEN usage < 0 THEN NULL                                      -- non-negative usage
      WHEN fuel = 'gas' AND usagePerDay >= 500 THEN NULL
      WHEN fuel = 'electricity' AND usagePerDay >= 200 THEN NULL    -- very high usage thresholds
      WHEN blockLength > 365 THEN NULL                               -- don't estimate very long blocks; ops want to avoid this
      ELSE usage END AS usage
    ,CASE
      WHEN usage < 0 THEN 'negative consumption'                    
      WHEN fuel = 'gas' AND usagePerDay >= 500 THEN 'upper tolerance breach'
      WHEN fuel = 'electricity' AND usagePerDay >= 200 THEN 'upper tolerance breach'
      WHEN blockLength > 365 THEN 'one year block'
      ELSE NULL END AS noConsumptionReason
  FROM (
    SELECT
       *
      ,CASE WHEN tier = 99 THEN 'gas' ELSE 'electricity' END AS fuel                              -- deriving fuel from tier (a little ugly but it's safe)
      ,SAFE_DIVIDE((toReading - fromReading) , DATE_DIFF(toReadingDate, fromReadingDate, DAY)) AS usagePerDay  -- these are used to set thresholds
      ,toReading - fromReading AS usage
      ,DATE_DIFF(toReadingDate, fromReadingDate, DAY) AS blockLength
    FROM
      actual_consumption
    WHERE
      fromReadingDate IS NOT NULL -- must be a complete block
  )
)
--TESTS:

--PRODUCTION:
SELECT * FROM cleaned_actual WHERE usage IS NULL
query.869:
WITH
all_D10 AS (
  SELECT 
     record.MpanCores.mpanCore AS mpan
    ,record.MpanCores.bscValidationStatus
    ,meterReadingTypes.meterIdSerialNumber AS msn
    ,meterReadingTypes.readingType
    ,registerReadings.meterRegisterId AS registerId
    ,PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", SUBSTR(registerReadings.readingDateTime,0,8)) AS readingDate
    ,registerReadings.registerReading AS reading
    ,registerReadings.meterReadingFlag
    ,meterReadingValidationResult.meterReadingReasonCode
    ,meterReadingValidationResult.meterReadingStatus
    ,header.fromMarketParticipantRoleCode
    ,header.fromMarketParticipantId
    ,header.toMarketParticipantRoleCode
    ,header.toMarketParticipantId
    ,header.fileIdentifier
    ,PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", SUBSTR(header.fileCreationTimestamp,0,8)) AS fileCreationTimestamp
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_D0010002_split_v1` 
  INNER JOIN UNNEST( record.MpanCores.meterReadingTypes )  AS meterReadingTypes
  INNER JOIN UNNEST( meterReadingTypes.registerReadings )  AS registerReadings
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST( registerReadings.meterReadingValidationResult )  AS meterReadingValidationResult
  WHERE
    PARTITIONTIME >= '2020-04-01'
), i_and_f AS (
  SELECT
    *
  FROM (
    SELECT 
      *
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpan, msn, readingDate, registerId ORDER BY fileCreationTimestamp DESC) AS orderReceived
    FROM 
      all_d10 
    WHERE 
      readingType IN ('F', 'I') 
  ) AS d10
  -- check that supplies are on Orion now
  INNER JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT
       sp.mpxn
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_migration.orion_migration_success_v2`
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(supplyPointList) AS sp
  ) AS orion
    ON orion.mpxn = d10.mpan
  WHERE 
    orderReceived = 1
    AND readingDate >= '2020-04-01'
  ORDER BY 
    mpan
), true_mex AS (  -- this removes cases where old msn = new msn (dummy mex)
SELECT i.* FROM (
  SELECT DISTINCT mpan, msn, readingDate FROM i_and_f WHERE readingType = 'I') AS i
INNER JOIN (
  SELECT DISTINCT mpan, msn, readingDate FROM i_and_f WHERE readingType = 'F') AS f
    ON  i.mpan = f.mpan
    AND i.readingDate = f.readingDate
    AND i.msn <> f.msn
), existing_reads AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
     event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.msn 
    ,DATE(event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime) AS readingDate
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_manual_read_submitted_v2`
  WHERE
    DATE(event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime) >= '2020-04-01'    -- TODO change to rolling 3 months
), reads_to_submit AS (
  SELECT 
    fi.*
  FROM 
    i_and_f AS fi
  INNER JOIN 
    true_mex  AS tm
      ON  fi.mpan = tm.mpan
      AND fi.readingDate = tm.readingDate
  LEFT JOIN
    existing_reads AS er
      ON  er.msn = fi.msn
      AND er.readingDate = fi.readingDate
  WHERE
    er.msn IS NULL -- checks that there is no reading for this msn and date already in R&C
)
SELECT
   rs.msn
  ,rs.mpan AS mpxn
  ,spam.fuel AS fuel
  ,CASE 
    WHEN meterType LIKE '%S2%' THEN 'SMETS2'
    WHEN meterType LIKE '%S1%' THEN 'SMETS1'
    ELSE 'TRAD' END AS orionMeterType
  ,'electricity MEX' AS readRequestedReason
  ,rs.readingDate AS readRequestedDate
  ,CASE
    WHEN rs.readingType = 'F' THEN 'MexReadingFinal'
    WHEN rs.readingType = 'I' THEN 'MexReadingInitial'
    END AS orionReadingType
  ,CAST(rs.reading AS FLOAT64) AS registerReading
  ,spam.timeOfUseLabel
FROM
  reads_to_submit rs
INNER JOIN
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_supply_meter_register_mappings` spam
    ON  spam.mpxn = rs.mpan
    AND spam.msn = rs.msn
    AND spam.meterRegisterId = rs.registerId
    AND spam.meterStartDate <= rs.readingDate
    AND COALESCE(spam.meterEndDate, '2999-12-31') >= rs.readingDate
    AND spam.configStartDate <= rs.readingDate
    AND COALESCE(spam.configEndDate, '2999-12-31') >= rs.readingDate
ORDER BY rs.mpan, readingType
query.870:
WITH

last_read AS (
  SELECT
     rd.mpxn
    ,rd.msn
    ,rd.tier
    ,rd.meterReading
    ,rd.readingType
    ,rd.readingDate
    ,COUNT(DISTINCT rd.tier) OVER(PARTITION BY rd.mpxn, rd.msn) AS activeRegisterCount    
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_unique_meter_readings` rd
  INNER JOIN (
    SELECT
       mpxn     --AMBIGUOUS FIX
      ,msn
      ,MAX(readingDate) AS lastReadDate
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_unique_meter_readings` 
    WHERE
      readingType <> 'EstimatedReading'
    GROUP BY
      mpxn --AMBIGUOUS FIX
       , msn
    ) lst
      ON lst.mpxn=rd.mpxn --AMBIGUOUS FIX
      AND  lst.msn = rd.msn
      AND lst.lastReadDate = rd.readingDate
),

last_read_mapped AS (
/* JOIN SPAM DATA */
-- join on register count to ensure that only correct registers are estimated
  SELECT 
     rd.mpxn
    ,mp.region
    ,rd.msn
    ,mp.fuel
    ,CASE      -- this logic is safe, as SMETS2 is the only type with different register mappings and these types are robust in SPAM
      WHEN mp.meterType LIKE '%S2%' THEN 'SMETS2'
      WHEN mp.meterType LIKE 'S1%' THEN 'SMETS1'
      ELSE 'TRAD' END AS orionMeterType
    ,rd.tier
    ,mp.timeOfUseLabel
    ,mp.clockingTimeId      -- still temporarily needed for personal projections
    ,rd.meterReading
    ,rd.readingType
    ,rd.readingDate
    ,rd.activeRegisterCount
    ,mp.imperialMeterIndicator --Imperial update
  FROM
    last_read rd
  INNER JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_supply_meter_register_mappings` mp -- join on SPAM for tou label and to confirm that the mapping is correct
      ON  rd.mpxn = mp.mpxn
      AND rd.msn = mp.msn
      AND COALESCE(rd.tier, 99) = mp.tier                               -- mapping data in mp guarantees tier. Default 99 for gas applied to the read data
      AND rd.readingDate >= mp.meterStartDate
      AND rd.readingDate < COALESCE(mp.meterEndDate, '2099-12-31')
      AND rd.readingDate >= mp.configStartDate
      AND rd.readingDate < COALESCE(mp.configEndDate, '2099-12-31')   
      AND rd.activeRegisterCount = mp.activeRegisterCount               -- of counts differ, don't estimate
  ),


/* TARGET DATES */
new_block AS (
  SELECT
     r.mpxn
    ,r.region
    ,r.msn
    ,r.fuel
    ,r.orionMeterType
    ,r.tier
    ,r.timeOfUseLabel
    ,r.clockingTimeId
    ,r.meterReading AS lastReading
    ,r.readingType AS lastReadingType
    ,r.readingDate AS lastReadingDate
    ,r.activeRegisterCount
    ,d.readRequestedDate
    ,d.readRequestedReason
    ,r.imperialMeterIndicator --Imperial update
  FROM
    last_read_mapped r
  INNER JOIN (
    -- join the target dates on SPAM data as well, so that we can check register count and timeOfUseLabel
    SELECT d.mpxn, d.readRequestedDate, d.readRequestedReason, mp.timeOfUseLabel, mp.activeRegisterCount, mp.imperialMeterIndicator
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_read_dates_required_v2` d
    INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_supply_meter_register_mappings` mp
       ON d.mpxn = mp.mpxn
      AND d.readRequestedDate >= mp.meterStartDate
      AND d.readRequestedDate < COALESCE(mp.meterEndDate, '2099-12-31')
      AND d.readRequestedDate >= mp.configStartDate
      AND d.readRequestedDate < COALESCE(mp.configEndDate, '2099-12-31')  
    WHERE readRequestedReason IN ('missing contract change read', 'missing billing read', 'missing loss confirmation read')   -- exclude migration dates
    ) d
      ON  r.mpxn = d.mpxn
      AND r.readingDate < d.readRequestedDate -- extrapolation only applies to dates forward of last reading
      AND r.timeOfUseLabel = d.timeOfUseLabel
      AND r.activeRegisterCount = d.activeRegisterCount
      AND COALESCE(r.imperialMeterIndicator, "NA") = COALESCE(d.imperialMeterIndicator, "NA") --Imperial update: in case of null imperialMeterIndicator, those won't be mapped as NULL=NULL is not True. Hence the coalesce
),

/* GET CVS */
cv AS(
  SELECT
    chargingZone,
    applicableGasDay,
    value
  FROM (
    SELECT
      metadata.createdAt,
      chargingZone,
      applicableGasDay,
      value,
      status,
      ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
        PARTITION BY chargingZone,
        applicableGasDay
        ORDER BY
          metadata.createdAt DESC
      ) as rn
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_calorific_value_received_v1`
    WHERE
      value IS NOT NULL
  )
  WHERE
    rn = 1
),

  /*  GET COEFFICIENTS   */
coefficients AS (
  SELECT
     settlement_date AS applicableDate
    ,AVG(ALP) AS usageCoefficient
    ,'gas' AS fuel
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.rac_gas_loadProfiles` 
  WHERE
    band = 1
    AND settlement_date >= DATE_ADD('2020-01-01', INTERVAL -1 YEAR)
    AND settlement_date <= DATE_ADD('2020-12-31', INTERVAL 1 YEAR)
  GROUP BY
    settlement_date
  UNION ALL
  SELECT
    settlementDate AS applicableDate
    ,SUM(customerDemand) AS usageCoefficient
    ,'electricity' AS fuel
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.rac_electricity_loadProfiles`
  WHERE
    profileClassId = 1
    AND settlementDate >= DATE_ADD('2020-01-01', INTERVAL -1 YEAR)
    AND settlementDate <= DATE_ADD('2020-12-31', INTERVAL 1 YEAR)
  GROUP BY 
    settlementDate
),
-- take the cumulative coefficient using the running sum (sum window) function
cumulative AS (
  SELECT
     applicableDate
    ,fuel
    ,SUM(usageCoefficient) OVER(PARTITION BY fuel ORDER BY applicableDate) AS cumulativeCoefficient
  FROM
    coefficients
),

/* GET USAGE PROJECTION */
--latest projection by mpxn and register
usage_projections AS(
SELECT
   mpxn
  ,clockingTimeId
  ,projectedConsumption
FROM (
  SELECT 
     event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.metadata.createdAt
    ,event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.mprn AS mpxn
    ,event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom
    ,9999 AS clockingTimeId
    ,event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.projectedConsumption --kWh
    ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
      PARTITION BY event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.mprn 
      ORDER BY event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rn -- assume latest projection is the best one. Projection logic should make this safe
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_personal_projections_calculated_v5`
  WHERE
    PARTITIONTIME >= '2020-01-01'
    AND event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.projectedConsumption < 150000
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 
     event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.metadata.createdAt
    ,event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan AS mpxn
    ,event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom
    ,prc.clockingTimeId                                                                           -- @TODO this will be replaced by timeOfUseLabel soon
    ,prc.projectedConsumption
    ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
      PARTITION BY event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan, prc.clockingTimeId 
      ORDER BY event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rn -- assume latest projection is the best one. Projection logic should make this safe
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_personal_projections_calculated_v5` 
  INNER JOIN 
    UNNEST (event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.projectedRegisterConsumption) AS prc
  WHERE
    PARTITIONTIME >= '2020-01-01'
    AND prc.projectedConsumption < 30000 -- TODO review these
  )
WHERE
  rn = 1
),
-- TEST:  (confirm zero results)


/* CALCULATE ESTIMATE */
extrapolation AS (

SELECT 
   nb.*
  ,effectiveCalorificValue
  ,up.projectedConsumption
  ,cu1.cumulativeCoefficient AS fromDateCoefficient
  ,cu2.cumulativeCoefficient AS toDateCoefficient
  ,cu2.cumulativeCoefficient - cu1.cumulativeCoefficient AS sumOfCoefficientsBlock
FROM
  new_block nb
INNER JOIN        -- from reading
  cumulative cu1
    ON  cu1.fuel = nb.fuel
    AND cu1.applicableDate = nb.lastReadingDate
INNER JOIN        -- to reading
  cumulative cu2
    ON  cu2.fuel = nb.fuel
    AND cu2.applicableDate = nb.readRequestedDate
LEFT JOIN
  usage_projections up
    ON  up.mpxn = nb.mpxn
    AND up.clockingTimeId = nb.clockingTimeId -- both are defaulted to 9999 for gas
LEFT JOIN ( -- get effective calorific value (gas only)
  SELECT
     nb.mpxn
    ,nb.msn
    ,nb.readRequestedDate
    ,AVG(value) AS effectiveCalorificValue
  FROM (
    SELECT mpxn, msn, region, lastReadingDate, readRequestedDate FROM new_block)
    nb
  INNER JOIN
    cv
      ON  nb.region = cv.chargingZone
      AND nb.lastReadingDate <= cv.applicableGasDay
      AND nb.readRequestedDate > cv.applicableGasDay
  GROUP BY
     nb.mpxn
    ,nb.msn
    ,nb.region
    ,nb.lastReadingDate
    ,nb.readRequestedDate 
  ) cv
    ON  cv.mpxn = nb.mpxn
    AND cv.msn = nb.msn
    AND cv.readRequestedDate = nb.readRequestedDate
)
--,

/* CREATE ESTIMATED READING */
--estimate AS (
  SELECT 
     mpxn
    ,msn
    ,orionMeterType
    ,imperialMeterIndicator --Imperial update
    ,region
    ,fuel
    ,tier
    ,timeOfUseLabel
    ,clockingTimeId    
    ,readRequestedReason
    ,readRequestedDate    
    ,lastReadingDate
    ,lastReadingType
    ,ROUND(lastReading, 1) AS lastReading
    ,ROUND(projectedConsumption,1) AS projectedConsumption
    ,ROUND(effectiveCalorificValue,1) AS effectiveCalorificValue
    -- estimate calculation. For electricity, we multiply projection by sum of coefficients
    -- for gas, we need to back volume out from energy (multiply by 3.6, divide by CV and volume correction factor 1.02264
    -- for gas an imperial, 100 cubic feet = 2.83168 cubic m
    ,CASE
      WHEN fuel = 'electricity' THEN ROUND( (sumOfCoefficientsBlock * projectedConsumption) + lastReading, 0)
      WHEN fuel = 'gas' AND imperialMeterIndicator = 'Y' THEN ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(                            --Imperial update
                                       (sumOfCoefficientsBlock * projectedConsumption * 3.6)                --Imperial update
                                      ,effectiveCalorificValue * 1.02264 * 2.83168) + lastReading, 0        --Imperial update
                                      )
      WHEN fuel = 'gas' AND COALESCE(imperialMeterIndicator, "NA") <> 'Y' THEN ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE( --COALESCE added since there are some nulll cases that would not be picked otherwise
                              (sumOfCoefficientsBlock * projectedConsumption * 3.6)
                              ,effectiveCalorificValue * 1.02264) + lastReading, 0
                                      )
      END AS estimatedReading
    ,'EstimatedReading' AS orionReadingType
  FROM 
    extrapolation
    
    --WHERE DATE_DIFF(readRequestedDate, lastReadingDate, DAY) > 5 --Added here to improve performance
    WHERE NOT (readRequestedReason = 'missing billing read' AND DATE_DIFF(readRequestedDate, lastReadingDate, DAY) <= 5)
--)

-- SELECT 'multiple anytime registers' AS test, mpxn, msn, '' AS timeOfUseLabel, COUNT(*) FROM last_read_mapped WHERE timeOfUseLabel = 'anytime' GROUP BY mpxn, msn  HAVING COUNT(*) > 1

WITH
all_onjob AS (
 SELECT
    meterPoint.meterPointReference AS mprn
   ,transactionTypeCode
   ,record.Transaction.transactionTypeCode AS transactionTypeCode_b
   ,asset.serialNumber AS msn
   ,meter.meterTypeCode
   ,PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", reading.readingDate) AS readingDate 
   ,reading.readingIndex AS reading
   ,header.originatorId 
   ,header.originatorRole
   ,header.recipientId
   ,header.recipientRole
   ,PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", header.createdDate) AS fileCreationTimeStamp
   ,header.fileIdentifier
   ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY meterPoint.meterPointReference, asset.serialNumber, PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", reading.readingDate) ORDER BY PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", header.createdDate) DESC) AS orderReceived
 FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_ONJOB_split_v4` onj
 INNER JOIN UNNEST( record.Transaction.meterPoint ) AS meterPoint
 INNER JOIN UNNEST( meterPoint.asset ) AS asset
 INNER JOIN UNNEST( asset.meter ) AS meter
 INNER JOIN UNNEST( asset.registerDetails ) AS registerDetails
 INNER JOIN UNNEST( registerDetails.reading ) AS reading
  WHERE
    PARTITIONTIME >= '2020-04-01' 
    AND record.Transaction.transactionTypeCode = 'EXCHG'
), i_and_f AS (
  SELECT
    *
  FROM
    all_onjob  onj
  -- check that supplies are on Orion now
  INNER JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT
       sp.mpxn
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_migration.orion_migration_success_v2`
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(supplyPointList) AS sp
  ) AS orion
    ON orion.mpxn = onj.mprn
  WHERE
    orderReceived = 1
    AND readingDate >= '2020-04-01'
  ORDER BY 
     mprn
    ,transactionTypeCode
), existing_reads AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
     event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.msn 
    ,DATE(event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime) AS readingDate
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_manual_read_submitted_v2`
  WHERE
    DATE(event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime) >= '2020-04-01'    
), reads_to_submit AS (
  SELECT 
    fi.*
  FROM 
    i_and_f AS fi
  LEFT JOIN
    existing_reads AS er
      ON  er.msn = fi.msn
      AND er.readingDate = fi.readingDate
  WHERE
    er.msn IS NULL -- checks that there is no reading for this msn and date already in R&C
)
SELECT
   rs.msn
  ,rs.mprn AS mpxn
  ,spam.fuel AS fuel
  ,CASE 
    WHEN meterType LIKE '%S2%' THEN 'SMETS2'
    WHEN meterType LIKE '%S1%' THEN 'SMETS1'
    ELSE 'TRAD' END AS orionMeterType
  ,'gas MEX' AS readRequestedReason
  ,rs.readingDate AS readRequestedDate
  ,CASE
    WHEN rs.transactionTypeCode = 'REMVE' THEN 'MexReadingFinal'
    WHEN rs.transactionTypeCode = 'INSTL' THEN 'MexReadingInitial'
    END AS orionReadingType
  ,CAST(rs.reading AS FLOAT64) AS registerReading
  ,spam.timeOfUseLabel
FROM
  reads_to_submit rs
INNER JOIN
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_supply_meter_register_mappings` spam
    ON  spam.mpxn = rs.mprn
    AND spam.msn = rs.msn
    AND spam.meterStartDate <= rs.readingDate
    AND COALESCE(spam.meterEndDate, '2999-12-31') >= rs.readingDate
    AND spam.configStartDate <= rs.readingDate
    AND COALESCE(spam.configEndDate, '2999-12-31') >= rs.readingDate
WHERE NOT (
  rs.transactionTypeCode = 'REMVE' AND rs.reading IN ('0000', '00000')) -- avoid cases where final and initial are swapped
ORDER BY rs.mprn, transactionTypeCode

WITH
--Select migrated accounts

targets AS (
  SELECT
     mpxn
    ,fuel
    ,readRequestedDate
    ,readRequestedReason
  FROM
   `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_read_dates_required_v2`
  WHERE
    readRequestedReason = 'missing migration read'  -- migration date read missing
),

--Get gentrack reads
invoice_reads AS(
SELECT 
   msn
  ,mpxn
  ,clockingTimeId
  ,gentrackReadDate
  ,gentrackReading
  ,gentrackReadCategory
  ,gentrackReadCategoryGroup
FROM(
  SELECT 
     reg.Meter_Serial_No AS msn 
    ,inst.Meter_Point_No AS mpxn
    ,CASE 
      WHEN reg.Register_Type LIKE 'G%' THEN 9999 
      ELSE CAST(reg.Time_Pattern AS NUMERIC)
      END AS clockingTimeId                                -- clockingTimeId and TPR are synonymous
    ,invr.Current_Read_Date AS gentrackReadDate    
    ,invr.Current_Read AS gentrackReading
    ,rc.Read_Category  AS gentrackReadCategory
    ,rc.Read_Category_Group AS gentrackReadCategoryGroup   --actual/estimated
    ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
      PARTITION BY reg.Meter_Serial_No, CASE WHEN reg.Register_Type LIKE 'G%' THEN '9999' ELSE reg.Time_Pattern END, Current_Read_Date 
      ORDER BY ETL_Datetime DESC) AS rowNumber
  FROM (
    SELECT
       Invoice_ID
      ,Meter_Serial_No
      ,Register_ID
      ,Current_Read_Date
      ,Current_Read_Type_Code
      ,Current_Read
      ,Installation_No
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY Meter_Serial_No, Register_ID, Current_Read_Date ORDER BY ETL_Datetime DESC) AS rowNumber
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.reporting_billing.v_Invoice_Register`
      ) invr
   --join to "reporting billing.v_Invoice" using Invoice_ID and exclude the ones that are reverse
  LEFT JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT Invoice_ID FROM  `data-engineering-prod.reporting_billing.v_Invoice` WHERE Reversed_Datetime IS NOT NULL) invoice 
      ON invr.Invoice_ID = invoice.Invoice_ID
  INNER JOIN 
    `data-engineering-prod.reporting_meters.v_Read_Type` rt
      ON invr.Current_Read_Type_Code = rt.Read_Type_Code
  INNER JOIN (
    SELECT * FROM `data-engineering-prod.reporting_meters.v_Read_Category` WHERE Read_Category_Group IS NOT NULL
    ) rc
      ON rt.Read_Category_Code = rc.Read_Category_Code
  INNER JOIN (
    SELECT
       Register_ID
      ,Meter_Serial_No
      ,Register_Type
      ,Time_Pattern
      ,ETL_Datetime
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY Register_ID,Meter_Serial_No ORDER BY ETL_Datetime DESC) AS regRowNum
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.reporting_meters.v_Register` WHERE Register_ID != 'JUN-6505' AND Register_Type IS NOT NULL
    ) reg
      ON invr.Register_ID = reg.Register_ID
      AND invr.Meter_Serial_No = reg.Meter_Serial_No
-- The following snippet was added to include mpxn on the analysis. This ensure uniqueness in case of Ambiguos meters. This inner join resulted on the query returning slighltly less results (e.g. 316 vs 295)    
  INNER JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT Installation_No
                  , Meter_Point_No 
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.reporting_meters.v_Installation` 
    WHERE  Billing_System= 'GENTRACK'
    ) inst
  ON invr.Installation_No = inst.Installation_No
--  
  WHERE
    rowNumber = 1 -- latest invoice version
    AND regRowNum = 1
    AND invoice.Invoice_ID IS NULL
  )
  WHERE 
    rowNumber = 1
),

/* READS TO SUBMIT */
missing_migration_reads AS (
  SELECT
     tgt.mpxn
    ,map.msn
    ,CASE      -- this logic is safe, as SMETS2 is the only type with different register mappings and these types are robust in SPAM
      WHEN map.meterType LIKE '%S2%' THEN 'SMETS2'
      WHEN map.meterType LIKE 'S1%' THEN 'SMETS1'
      ELSE 'TRAD' END AS orionMeterType
    ,tgt.fuel  
    ,map.tier
    ,map.clockingTimeId
    ,map.timeOfUseLabel
    ,tgt.readRequestedDate
    ,tgt.readRequestedReason
    ,inv.gentrackReadDate
    ,inv.gentrackReading
    ,inv.gentrackReadCategoryGroup
    ,CASE 
      WHEN inv.gentrackReadCategoryGroup = 'Estimated Read' THEN 'MigrationReadingEstimated'
      WHEN inv.gentrackReadCategoryGroup = 'Actual Read' THEN 'MigrationReadingActual'
      END AS orionReadingType
  FROM
    invoice_reads inv
  INNER JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_supply_meter_register_mappings` map
      ON  inv.msn = map.msn
      AND inv.mpxn = map.mpxn
      AND inv.clockingTimeId = map.clockingTimeId
      AND inv.gentrackReadDate >= configStartDate
      AND inv.gentrackReadDate >= meterStartDate
      AND inv.gentrackReadDate < COALESCE(configEndDate, '2999-12-31')
      AND inv.gentrackReadDate < COALESCE(meterEndDate, '2999-12-31')
  INNER JOIN
    targets AS tgt
      ON  tgt.mpxn = map.mpxn
      AND tgt.readRequestedDate = inv.gentrackReadDate
)

WITH

  /*  GET COEFFICIENTS   */
coefficients AS (
  SELECT
     settlement_date AS applicableDate
    ,AVG(ALP) AS usageCoefficient
    ,'gas' AS fuel
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.rac_gas_loadProfiles` 
  WHERE
    band = 1
    AND settlement_date >= DATE_ADD('2020-01-01', INTERVAL -1 YEAR)
    AND settlement_date <= DATE_ADD('2020-12-31', INTERVAL 1 YEAR)
  GROUP BY
    settlement_date
  UNION ALL
  SELECT
    settlementDate AS applicableDate
    ,SUM(customerDemand) AS usageCoefficient
    ,'electricity' AS fuel
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.rac_electricity_loadProfiles`
  WHERE
    profileClassId = 1
    AND settlementDate >= DATE_ADD('2020-01-01', INTERVAL -1 YEAR)
    AND settlementDate <= DATE_ADD('2020-12-31', INTERVAL 1 YEAR)
  GROUP BY 
    settlementDate
),
-- take the cumulative coefficient using the running sum (sum window) function
cumulative AS (
  SELECT
     applicableDate
    ,fuel
    ,SUM(usageCoefficient) OVER(PARTITION BY fuel ORDER BY applicableDate) AS cumulativeCoefficient
  FROM
    coefficients
),

/* JOIN ON TARGET DATES */
straddling_block AS (
  SELECT
     cons.mpxn
    ,cons.msn
    ,cons.orionMeterType
    ,cons.tier
    ,cons.timeOfUseLabel
    ,cons.clockingTimeId
    ,cons.fuel
    ,ct.readRequestedDate
    ,ct.readRequestedReason
    ,cons.fromReadingDate
    ,cons.toReadingDate
    ,cons.usage
    ,cons.fromReading
    ,cons.toReading
    ,cons.fromReadingType
    ,cons.toReadingType
    ,cu1.cumulativeCoefficient AS fromDateCoefficient
    ,cu2.cumulativeCoefficient AS toDateCoefficient
    ,cu.cumulativeCoefficient AS billingDateCoefficient
    ,cu2.cumulativeCoefficient - cu1.cumulativeCoefficient AS sumOfCoefficientsWholeBlock
    ,cu.cumulativeCoefficient - cu1.cumulativeCoefficient AS sumOfCoefficientsBefore   
  FROM (
    SELECT * 
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_read_dates_required_v2` 
    WHERE readRequestedReason IN ('missing contract change read', 'missing billing read', 'missing loss confirmation read')
    ) ct
  INNER JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_consumption_history_from_actual_readings` cons
      ON  cons.mpxn = ct.mpxn
      AND cons.fromReadingDate < ct.readRequestedDate 
      AND cons.toReadingDate > ct.readRequestedDate
   INNER JOIN
      cumulative cu
        ON  cu.fuel = cons.fuel
        AND cu.applicableDate = ct.readRequestedDate
   INNER JOIN
      cumulative cu1
        ON  cu1.fuel = cons.fuel
        AND cu1.applicableDate = cons.fromReadingDate
   INNER JOIN
      cumulative cu2
        ON  cu2.fuel = cons.fuel
        AND cu2.applicableDate = cons.toReadingDate
), 
/* calculate the estimate */
estimate AS (
  SELECT 
     mpxn
    ,msn
    ,fuel
    ,orionMeterType
    ,tier
    ,timeOfUseLabel
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,readRequestedDate
    ,readRequestedReason
    ,fromReadingDate
    ,toReadingDate
    ,fromReading
    ,toReading
    ,fromReadingType
    ,toReadingType
    ,usage
    --      ,fromDateCoefficient
    --      ,toDateCoefficient
    --      ,billingDateCoefficient
    --      ,sumOfCoefficientsWholeBlock
    --      ,sumOfCoefficientsBefore
    --      ,sumOfCoefficientsBefore / sumOfCoefficientsWholeBlock AS proportionOfBlock
    ,ROUND(fromReading + ((sumOfCoefficientsBefore / sumOfCoefficientsWholeBlock) * usage),0) AS estimatedReading
    ,'EstimatedReading' AS orionReadingType
  FROM 
    straddling_block
)
