query.874:
WITH 

/* CREATE DATE RANGE */
-- we only want to create reads up to three months in the past. This creates the range dates of interest
target_dates AS (
  SELECT 
    targetDate
  FROM 
    UNNEST(
      GENERATE_DATE_ARRAY(
        DATE_ADD(
          CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL -3 MONTH
        ), CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL 1 DAY
      )
    ) AS targetDate
),

/* MIGRATION DATES  */
-- never create estimates before migration dates
migrations AS (
  SELECT
     accountId
    ,globalAccountId
    ,fuel
    ,mpxn
    ,DATE(createdAt)  AS migrationRunDate
    ,migrationDate 
  FROM (
    SELECT
       accountId
      ,globalAccountId
      ,migrationDate
      ,sp.mpxn
      ,fuel
      ,metadata.createdAt
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY sp.mpxn ORDER BY migrationDate DESC, metadata.createdAt DESC) AS ordering
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_migration.orion_migration_success_v2`
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(supplyPointList) AS sp
  )
  WHERE
    ordering = 1
),

/* CONTRACTS */
-- fetch customer contract data, needed to get billing dates and contract change dates
contracts AS(  
  SELECT
     serviceAccountId
    ,fuel
    ,mpxn
    ,contractId
    ,startDate
    ,endDate  
    ,createdAt
  FROM (
    SELECT
      ct.unionRecord.Contract.mpxn,
      ct.unionRecord.Contract.serviceAccountId,
      ct.unionRecord.Contract.fuel,
      ct.unionRecord.Contract.contractId,
      ct.unionRecord.Contract.metadata.createdAt,
      ct.unionRecord.Contract.startDate,
      ct.unionRecord.Contract.endDate,
      ct.unionRecord.Contract.lossConfirmed,
      ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
          PARTITION BY ct.unionRecord.Contract.serviceAccountId, ct.unionRecord.Contract.mpxn, ct.unionRecord.Contract.contractId, ct.unionRecord.Contract.startDate 
          ORDER BY ct.unionRecord.Contract.metadata.createdAt DESC
          ) AS rn
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract_v3` ct
    LEFT JOIN (
      SELECT DISTINCT 
        unionRecord.Cancelled.contractId 
      FROM 
        `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract_v3`
    ) rm                --Remove cancelled contracts
        ON ct.unionRecord.Contract.contractId = rm.contractId
    WHERE 
      ct.unionRecord.Contract IS NOT NULL 
      AND rm.contractId IS NULL
  )
  WHERE
    rn = 1                      -- de-duplicate
    AND lossConfirmed IS NULL   -- Just live supplies
),     


/* BILLING DATES */
-- use BAST billing info to find the correct billing date. If none is available, default to 1st
bast_billing AS(
  SELECT 
     accountId
    ,billingDayOfTheMonth
  FROM (
    SELECT 
       accountId
      ,status.Active.billingFrequency
      ,status.Active.billingDayOfTheMonth
      ,row_number() OVER (PARTITION BY accountId ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rn 
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_bast_secure.bast_account_billing_information_v1`
    )
  WHERE 
    rn = 1 
    AND billingFrequency IS NOT NULL
),
billing_dates AS( 
  SELECT
     fuel
    ,serviceAccountId
    ,mpxn
    ,CASE 
      WHEN billingDayOfTheMonth IS NOT NULL THEN billingDayOfTheMonth
      ELSE 1 END AS billingDayOfTheMonth
  FROM (
    SELECT 
       ct.fuel
      ,ct.serviceAccountId
      ,ct.mpxn
      ,bs.billingDayOfTheMonth
    FROM ( -- for billing dates we just need the mpxn-account mappign
      SELECT DISTINCT serviceAccountId, mpxn, fuel
      FROM contracts 
    ) ct
    LEFT JOIN 
      bast_billing bs
        ON ct.serviceAccountId = bs.accountId 
  )
),

/*  BILLING DATE TARGETS  */
-- create a target list of dates by taking all billing dates since migration and in the last 3 months
target_billing_dates AS (
  SELECT
     b.fuel
    ,b.serviceAccountId
    ,b.mpxn
    ,td.targetDate AS readRequestedDate
    ,'missing billing read' AS readRequestedReason
  FROM 
    billing_dates b
  INNER JOIN
    target_dates td
      ON EXTRACT(DAY FROM td.targetDate) = b.billingDayOfTheMonth
  INNER JOIN 
    migrations m 
      ON  m.mpxn = b.mpxn 
      AND b.serviceAccountId = m.accountId
      AND DATE_ADD(m.migrationDate, INTERVAL +1 DAY) < td.targetDate  -- first billing date is the day after migration. Exclude this.
  WHERE
    td.targetDate >= '2020-04-01'  -- hard backstop, as we've already re-issued reads up to April
   
),

/*  CONTRACT CHANGE DATE TARGETS  */
-- create a target list of dates by taking all contract change dates since migration and in the period targetted 
target_contract_dates AS (
  SELECT
     ct.fuel
    ,ct.serviceAccountId
    ,ct.mpxn
    ,td.targetDate AS readRequestedDate
    ,'missing contract change read' AS readRequestedReason
  FROM 
    contracts ct
  INNER JOIN                              -- check within 3 month range
    target_dates td
      ON td.targetDate = ct.startDate
  INNER JOIN 
    migrations m 
      ON  m.mpxn = ct.mpxn 
      AND m.migrationDate < ct.startDate  -- must be later than migration date
),

/*  MIGRATION DATE TARGETS  */
-- create a target list of dates by taking all billing dates since migration and in the last 3 months
target_migration_dates AS (
  SELECT
     m.fuel
    ,m.accountId AS serviceAccountId
    ,m.mpxn
    ,td.targetDate AS readRequestedDate
    ,'missing migration read' AS readRequestedReason
  FROM 
    migrations m
  INNER JOIN
    target_dates td
      ON td.targetDate = m.migrationDate

),

/* ALL DATES TOGETHER */
all_dates AS(
  SELECT * FROM target_billing_dates
  UNION ALL 
  SELECT * FROM target_contract_dates
  UNION ALL 
  SELECT * FROM target_migration_dates
),

  /* EXCLUDE ALL CASES WHERE WE HOLD A READING  */
missing_reads AS (
  SELECT
     ad.mpxn
    ,ad.readRequestedDate
    ,ad.readRequestedReason
    ,ad.fuel
  FROM
    all_dates ad
  LEFT JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT mpxn, readingDate FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.READ_SUBMISSION_unique_meter_readings`) r
      ON  r.mpxn = ad.mpxn
      AND r.readingDate = ad.readRequestedDate
  WHERE
    r.readingDate IS NULL             -- no read on target date
)

query.876:
/*  ======================================  */
/*  DEFINITIVE METER AND REGISTER MAPPINGS  */
/*  ======================================  */


-- PURPOSE:
-- This view provides a clean view of SPAM data for both fuels, giving the latest version of all known supply
-- histories. 
-- Created: 2020-05-05
-- Last updated: 2020-05-28: add imperial meter indicator column

WITH

-- derive the configuration end date. To do this, we need to order the config start dates without including registers
electricity_config_dates AS (
  SELECT
     mpxn
    ,msn
    ,meterStartDate
    ,meterEndDate
    ,configStartDate
    ,configEndDate
  FROM (
    SELECT DISTINCT
       MPXN                           AS mpxn
      ,gspGroupId                     AS region
      ,installationHistory.MSN        AS msn
      ,installationHistory.startDate  AS meterStartDate
      ,installationHistory.endDate    AS meterEndDate 
      ,installationHistory.meterType
      ,meterRegisterHistory.startDate AS configStartDate
      -- now derive the configuration 'end date' by looking up the next valid start date for the supply-meter-register combination
      ,LEAD(meterRegisterHistory.startDate) OVER(
                PARTITION BY mpxn, installationHistory.MSN
                ORDER BY meterRegisterHistory.startDate)
                AS configEndDate
    FROM (
      -- take the latest history for each MPXN
      SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rowNumber 
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
      ) 
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(installationHistory) AS installationHistory
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(installationHistory.meterRegisterHistory) AS meterRegisterHistory
    WHERE
          rowNumber = 1
  )
),

/* SPAM ELECTRICITY */
-- fetch the current view of supply to meter to register mapping from SPAM. We look for the latest view only, and then 
-- derive dates that configuration end for register configurations
electricity_supply_history AS (
  SELECT
     hist.mpxn
    ,region
    ,hist.msn
    ,CAST(NULL AS string) AS imperialMeterIndicator
    ,'electricity' AS fuel
    ,hist.meterStartDate
    ,hist.meterEndDate
    ,meterType
    ,hist.configStartDate
    ,dt.configEndDate
    ,tier
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,meterRegisterId
    ,timeOfUseLabel
    ,COUNT(DISTINCT tier) OVER(PARTITION BY hist.mpxn, hist.msn, hist.meterStartDate, hist.meterEndDate, hist.configStartDate) AS activeRegisterCount
    ,COUNT(clockingTimeId) OVER(PARTITION BY hist.mpxn, hist.msn, hist.meterStartDate, hist.meterEndDate, hist.configStartDate) AS clockingTimeIdCount --Victor Update
  FROM (
    SELECT 
       MPXN                           AS mpxn
      ,gspGroupId                     AS region
      ,installationHistory.MSN        AS msn
      ,installationHistory.startDate  AS meterStartDate
      ,installationHistory.endDate    AS meterEndDate 
      ,installationHistory.meterType
      ,meterRegisterHistory.startDate AS configStartDate
      -- we can apply defaults to tiers, because of the following:
      -- 1) all known smart meters already have tiers asigned
      -- 2) trad meters default to SMETS1 behaviour (0 is night, 1 is day)
      -- 3) any unknown smart meter is smets1, which behaves as trad
      ,CASE 
        WHEN meterRegisters.tier IS NOT NULL THEN meterRegisters.tier
        WHEN meterRegisters.tier IS NULL AND timeOfUseLabel = 'anytime' THEN 0
        WHEN meterRegisters.tier IS NULL AND timeOfUseLabel = 'offpeak' THEN 0
        WHEN meterRegisters.tier IS NULL AND timeOfUseLabel = 'peak' THEN 1
        END AS tier
      ,clockingTimeId
      ,meterRegisters.meterRegisterId
      ,meterRegisters.timeOfUseLabel
    FROM (
      -- take the latest history for each MPXN
      SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rowNumber 
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
      ) 
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(installationHistory) AS installationHistory
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(installationHistory.meterRegisterHistory) AS meterRegisterHistory
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(meterRegisterHistory.meterRegisters) AS meterRegisters
    WHERE
          rowNumber = 1
      AND meterRegisters.timeOfUseLabel IS NOT NULL  -- this would render the meter un-mappable
  ) hist
  -- this join gives us the config end date
  INNER JOIN
    electricity_config_dates dt
      ON  hist.mpxn = dt.mpxn
      AND hist.msn = dt.msn
      AND hist.meterStartDate = dt.meterStartDate
      AND hist.meterStartDate = dt.meterStartDate
      AND hist.configStartDate = dt.configStartDate
  
),

/* REMOVE INVALID MAPPINGS */
-- any case where the time of use label doesn't match the register count, exclude
electricity_supply_history_cleaned AS (
  SELECT
    *
  FROM
    electricity_supply_history
  WHERE
    NOT (activeRegisterCount > 1 AND timeOfUseLabel = 'anytime')
    AND NOT (activeRegisterCount = 1 AND timeOfUseLabel <> 'anytime') 
    AND NOT (activeRegisterCount<>clockingTimeIdCount) --Victor's update: Some elec supplypoints happen to have more than 1 registers mapped for single rate or more than 2 for multirate. This scenario sometimes happens after a MEX. In the case of a multi-rate, this could result with the same clockingTimeId duplicated or 4 different clockingTimeId if the regime has changed. For now all those cases are filtered out using this condition. For the single rate cases this should have been filtered in the previous 2 conditions
),

/* SPAM GAS */
-- fetch the current view of supply to meter mapping from SPAM. In gas configuration and registers are not included 
-- so no derivation of dates is required. Fields are defaulted which are not applicable so that schemas match.
gas_supply_history AS (
  SELECT
     mpxn
    ,region
    ,msn
    ,imperialMeterIndicator
    ,'gas' AS fuel
    ,meterStartDate
    ,meterEndDate
    ,meterType
    ,configStartDate
    ,configEndDate
    ,tier
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,meterRegisterId
    ,timeOfUseLabel
    ,COUNT(DISTINCT tier) OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn,msn,meterStartDate,meterEndDate,configStartDate,configEndDate) AS activeRegisterCount
  FROM (
    SELECT 
       MPXN                           AS mpxn
      ,LDZ                            AS region
      ,installationHistory.MSN        AS msn
      ,installationHistory.imperialMeterIndicator AS imperialMeterIndicator
      ,installationHistory.startDate  AS meterStartDate
      ,installationHistory.endDate    AS meterEndDate 
      ,installationHistory.meterType
      ,installationHistory.startDate  AS configStartDate  -- default to meter start date
      ,installationHistory.endDate    AS configEndDate    -- default to meter end date
      ,99                             AS tier
      ,9999                           AS clockingTimeId   -- create defaults for tier and cti
      ,CAST(NULL AS STRING)           AS meterRegisterId  -- no default needed for registerID at present
      ,'anytime'                      AS timeOfUseLabel   -- gas is always anytime
    FROM (
      -- take the latest history for each MPXN
      SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rowNumber 
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_gasSupplyPointHistory_v2` 
      ) 
    INNER JOIN

/*  ====================================  */
/*  METER READINGS FROM MPXN CONSUMPTION  */
/*  ====================================  */


-- PURPOSE:
-- This view extracts all unique meter readings from the latest version of both gas volume and electriicty consumption generated tables.
-- Created: 2020-05-05
-- Last updated: 2020-05-05
-- Source Versions: 'rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v5', 'rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v4'
--                  'rac_mpxn_gas_volume_consumption_generated_v3', 'rac_mpxn_gas_volume_consumption_generated_v2'

WITH

/* RAW CONSUMPTION DATA */
-- fetch gas and electricity consumption data from latest two versions
-- of each of the mpxn consumption tables
consumption AS(
  SELECT DISTINCT
     mpan AS mpxn
    ,msn
    ,f.tier
    ,fromDate
    ,toDate
    ,f.reading AS fromMeterReading
    ,fromReading.readingType AS fromReadingType
    ,t.reading AS toMeterReading
    ,toReading.readingType AS toReadingType
    ,metadata.createdAt
    ,5 AS version                                 -- topic version
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v5` 
  INNER JOIN  UNNEST(fromReading.registers) AS f
  INNER JOIN  UNNEST(toReading.registers) AS t ON t.tier = f.tier
  --INNER JOIN  UNNEST(consumption.registers) AS c ON c.tier = f.tier
  UNION ALL 
  SELECT DISTINCT 
     mprn AS mpxn
    ,msn
    ,99 AS tiers                                  -- int identifer for gas tier (not used)       
    ,fromDate                                     -- no timezone conversion required as these are in local date form
    ,toDate
    ,fromReading.reading AS fromMeterReading
    ,fromReading.readingType AS fromReadingType
    ,toReading.reading AS toMeterReading
    ,toReading.readingType AS toReadingType
    ,metadata.createdAt
    ,3 AS version
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_gas_volume_consumption_generated_v3`
  UNION ALL                                       -- now take old topic versions of topics
  SELECT DISTINCT
     mpan AS mpxn
    ,msn
    ,tiers.tier
    ,DATE(fromDateTime, 'Europe/London') AS fromDate
    ,DATE(toDateTime, 'Europe/London') AS toDate
    ,tiers.fromMeterReading
    ,tiers.fromReadingType AS fromReadingType
    ,tiers.toMeterReading
    ,tiers.toReadingType AS toReadingType
    ,metadata.createdAt
    ,4 AS version
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v4`
  INNER JOIN UNNEST(tiers) AS tiers
  WHERE PARTITIONTIME >= '2020-01-01'           -- limit to 2020. Earlier estimation is performed on demand
  UNION ALL 
  SELECT DISTINCT 
     mprn AS mpxn
    ,msn
    ,99 AS tier
    ,DATE(fromDateTime, 'Europe/London') AS fromDate  --timezone conversion requrired as these are stored as UTC datetime
    ,DATE(toDateTime, 'Europe/London') AS toDate
    ,fromMeterReading
    ,fromReadingType
    ,toMeterReading
    ,toReadingType
    ,metadata.createdAt
    ,2 AS version
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_gas_volume_consumption_generated_v2`
  WHERE PARTITIONTIME >= '2020-01-01'
),

/* CLEAN CONSUMPTION DATA */
-- de-duplicating on mpxn, msn, tier, fromDate, toDate. Note that this doesn't prevent 
-- overlapping consumption (not problematic as we will extract the reads only)
clean_consumption AS (
  SELECT
     mpxn
    ,msn
    ,tier
    ,fromDate
    ,toDate
    ,fromMeterReading
    ,fromReadingType
    ,toMeterReading 
    ,toReadingType
    ,createdAt
  FROM (
    SELECT
       mpxn
      ,msn
      ,tier
      ,fromDate
      ,toDate
      ,fromMeterReading
      ,fromReadingType
      ,toMeterReading
      ,toReadingType
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn, msn, tier, fromDate, toDate ORDER BY version DESC, createdAt DESC) AS latestVersion
      ,createdAt
    FROM
      consumption
--     WHERE
--       fromDate >= '2020-01-01'
  )
  WHERE latestVersion = 1
),

/* READS FROM CONSUMPTION */
-- extract all meter readings (from and to) from consumption, allowing only one instance
-- by mpxn, msn, tier, readingDate
reads AS (
  SELECT 
     mpxn
    ,msn
    ,tier
    ,readingDate
    ,meterReading
    ,readingType
  FROM (
    SELECT 
       *
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
          PARTITION BY mpxn, msn, tier, readingDate 
          ORDER BY createdAt DESC
        ) AS rn
    FROM (
      SELECT
         mpxn
        ,msn
        ,tier
        ,fromDate AS readingDate
        ,fromMeterReading AS meterReading
        ,fromReadingType AS readingType
        ,createdAt
      FROM
        clean_consumption
      UNION ALL
      SELECT
         mpxn
        ,msn
        ,tier
        ,toDate AS readingDate
        ,toMeterReading AS meterReading
        ,toReadingType AS readingType
        ,createdAt
      FROM
        clean_consumption
     )
  )
  WHERE
    rn = 1
)
--  TEST: this should return no results
--SELECT mpxn, msn, tier, readingDate, COUNT(meterReading) AS readCount FROM reads GROUP BY mpxn, msn, tier, readingDate HAVING COUNT(meterReading) > 1
-- PRODUCTION:
SELECT * FROM reads

-- ALL NOSIs per MPRN --
WITH NOSI AS(
  select MPXN, NOSI_MSN, NOSI_date from (
    select record.NosiGroup.meterPointReference MPXN, record.NosiGroup.meterSerialNumber NOSI_MSN, PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", header.createdDate) NOSI_date
    from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_NOSI_split_v1`)
  where MPXN is not null and NOSI_MSN is not null and NOSI_date is not null
  group by MPXN, NOSI_MSN, NOSI_date),

-- ALL MRIs per MPRN --
MRI AS
(select MPXN, MRI_MSN, MRI_date
 from (
 select record.MeterReadInstructions.meterPointReference MPXN, record.MeterReadInstructions.meterSerialNumber MRI_MSN, PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", header.creationDate) MRI_date
 from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_MRI_POST_NEXUS_split_v4`)
 where MRI_date is not null and MPXN is not null and MRI_MSN is not null
 group by MPXN, MRI_MSN, MRI_date),

-- LATEST SSD per MPRN --
SPAMSSD as
(select MPXN, MSN, SSD from
  (select MPXN, MSN, supplyStatusDate SSD, supplystatus SS
   from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_current_gas_mapping`
   where supplystatus = 'Gain completed')
 group by MPXN, MSN, SSD),

-- NEAREST MRI to SSD --
NMRI as (
  select MPXN, MRI_MSN, SSD, MRI_date, spam_mri_diff from (
    select *,
           row_number() over (partition by MPXN order by spam_mri_diff) n
    from (
      select SPAMSSD.*, MRI.MRI_date, MRI_MSN,
             abs(date_diff(MRI_date, SSD, Day)) spam_mri_diff
      from SPAMSSD
      left join MRI
      on SPAMSSD.MPXN = MRI.MPXN
      where MRI_date is not null
      order by SPAMSSD.MPXN, MRI_date desc)
    where spam_mri_diff <= 5)
  where n = 1),

-- NEAREST NOSI TO SSD --
NNOSI as (
  select MPXN, NOSI_MSN, SSD, NOSI_date, spam_nosi_diff from (
    select *,
           row_number() over (partition by MPXN order by spam_nosi_diff) n
    from (
      select SPAMSSD.*, NOSI.NOSI_date, NOSI_MSN,
             abs(date_diff(NOSI_date, SSD, Day)) spam_nosi_diff
      from SPAMSSD
      left join NOSI
      on SPAMSSD.MPXN = NOSI.MPXN
      where NOSI_date is not null
      order by SPAMSSD.MPXN, NOSI_date desc)
    where spam_nosi_diff <= 5)
  where n = 1)

select * from (
select SPAMSSD.*,
NOSI_MSN=MSN matching_NOSI_MSN,
MRI_MSN=MSN matching_MRI_MSN,
NOSI_date, NOSI_MSN, spam_nosi_diff, MRI_date, MRI_MSN, spam_mri_diff from SPAMSSD
left join NNOSI 
on SPAMSSD.MPXN = NNOSI.MPXN
and SPAMSSD.SSD = NNOSI.SSD
left join NMRI
on SPAMSSD.MPXN = NMRI.MPXN
and SPAMSSD.SSD = NMRI.SSD)
where NOSI_date is not null or MRI_date is not null
order by SSD desc, MPXN

/*
This view aims to identify Smart Meters both based on the code used by Utiliserve and the MSN itself. 
A regex based on a list of MSN patterns provided by SPAM has been used to identify meter type on msn.
NOTE: The results shows a clear bias towards false positives. This means that probably the list of MSN provided by SPAM was not full comprehensive. This basically means that some Smart Meters are likely to be labelled as Traditional (false under Smart_Meter_Type_by_MSN column).

#Author: Victor Irles
#Date: 14-01-2020

#Amended: Pete Diwell
#Date: 02-06-2020
#Reason: use new SPAM topic
*/

--ELECTRICITY
--take the latest view
WITH cte_latest_mappings AS(
SELECT MPXN
      , MSN
      , profileClassId
      , meterRegisterHistory
      , meterType
FROM (SELECT *
            ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime DESC, kafkaData.offset DESC, ih.startDate DESC, sp.supplyStartDate DESC) AS rn 
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
      INNER JOIN UNNEST(installationHistory) ih
      INNER JOIN UNNEST(supplyPeriods) sp)
WHERE rn=1
),
--latest register mapping
cte_latest_mappings_reg AS(
    SELECT MPXN
          , MSN
          , profileClassId
          , ssc
          , startDate AS registerConfigEffectiveFrom
          , meterType
          , meterRegisters
    FROM (
          SELECT MPXN, MSN, profileClassId, meterType, regHist.startDate, regHist.ssc, regHist.meterRegisters
                , ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY regHist.startDate DESC) AS rn2 
          FROM cte_latest_mappings
          INNER JOIN UNNEST (meterRegisterHistory) AS regHist)
    WHERE rn2=1
),
--latest supply points in utility group
cte_ug AS(
SELECT * 
FROM `data-engineering-prod.reporting_utiliserve.tbl_electricity_tracker` 
WHERE Utiliserve_Not_Live_Reason != "Failed Gain" 
AND Is_Latest_Utiliserve_Transfer_Attempt	= 1
),
--union both
cte_union AS(
  SELECT a.Meter_Point_No
        , a.Utiliserve_Supply_Start_Date
        , a.Utiliserve_Reported_Status
        , a.Utiliserve_Meter_Serial_No
        , a.Utiliserve_Meter_Install_Date
        , a.Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code
        , a.Utiliserve_Smart_Meter_Smets_Version_Code
        , b.meterType AS SPAM_Meter_Type_Code
        , b.msn
        --, b.MPXN
  FROM cte_ug a 
  LEFT JOIN cte_latest_mappings_reg b
  ON a.Meter_Point_No    = CAST(CAST(b.MPXN AS INT64) AS STRING)
)

--Create new columns to identify smart meters by using the msn and the code
SELECT *
      , REGEXP_CONTAINS(Utiliserve_Meter_Serial_No, r"^([0-9][0-9][A-Z]\d+|Z[0-9][0-9](N|Q)\d+)") AS Smart_Meter_Type_by_MSN
      , CASE WHEN Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code IN ('S1', 'S2A', 'S2B', 'S2C', 'S2AD', 'S2BD', 'S2CD', 'S2ADE', 'S2BDE', 'S2CDE') THEN True 
             WHEN Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code IN ('CHECK', 'H', 'K' , 'LAG', 'LEAD', 'MAIN', 'N', 'NCAMR', 'NSS', 'RCAMR', 'RCAMY', 'S', 'SPECL', 'T') THEN False 
             ELSE null END AS Smart_Meter_Type_by_Code_UG
      , CASE WHEN SPAM_Meter_Type_Code IN ('S1', 'S2A', 'S2B', 'S2C', 'S2AD', 'S2BD', 'S2CD', 'S2ADE', 'S2BDE', 'S2CDE') THEN True 
             WHEN SPAM_Meter_Type_Code IN ('CHECK', 'H', 'K' , 'LAG', 'LEAD', 'MAIN', 'N', 'NCAMR', 'NSS', 'RCAMR', 'RCAMY', 'S', 'SPECL', 'T') THEN False 
             ELSE null END AS Smart_Meter_Type_by_Code_SPAM
FROM cte_union a

/*
This view aims to identify Smart Meters both based on the code used by Utiliserve and the MSN itself. 
A regex based on a list of MSN patterns provided by SPAM has been used to identify meter type on msn.
NOTE: The results shows a clear bias towards false positives. This means that probably the list of MSN provided by SPAM was not full comprehensive. This basically means that some Smart Meters are likely to be labelled as Traditional (false under Smart_Meter_Type_by_MSN column).

#Author: Victor Irles 
#Date: 14-01-2020

#Amended: Pete Diwell
#Date: 02-06-2020
#Reason: use new SPAM topic
*/


--GAS
--take the latest view
WITH cte_latest_mappings AS(
SELECT MPXN
      , MSN
      , meterType
FROM (SELECT *
            ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime DESC, kafkaData.offset DESC, ih.startDate DESC, sp.supplyStartDate DESC) AS rn 
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_gasSupplyPointHistory_v2`
      INNER JOIN UNNEST(installationHistory) ih
      INNER JOIN UNNEST(supplyPeriods) sp)
WHERE rn=1
),
--latest supply points in utility group
cte_ug AS(
SELECT * 
FROM `data-engineering-prod.reporting_utiliserve.tbl_gas_tracker` 
WHERE Utiliserve_Not_Live_Reason != "Failed Gain" AND Is_Latest_Utiliserve_Transfer_Attempt	= 1
),

--union both
cte_union AS(
  SELECT a.Meter_Point_No
        , a.Utiliserve_Supply_Start_Date
        , a.Utiliserve_Reported_Status
        , a.Utiliserve_Meter_Serial_No
        , a.Utiliserve_Meter_Install_Date
        , a.Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code
        , b.meterType AS SPAM_Meter_Type_Code
        , b.MSN
  FROM cte_ug a 
  LEFT JOIN cte_latest_mappings b
  ON a.Meter_Point_No   = CAST(CAST(b.MPXN AS INT64) AS STRING)
  --ON a.Meter_Point_No    = b.MPXN
)
--SELECT * FROM cte_union LIMIT 10

--Create new columns to identify smart meters by using the msn and the code
SELECT *
      , NOT REGEXP_CONTAINS(Utiliserve_Meter_Serial_No, r"^((L|M)[0-9][0-9][0-9][^6]\d{6}(M|S)|[A-Z][0-9][A-Z]\d{7}(([6-9][0-9])|(0[0-9])|(1[0-2]))0[1-2]|\d{7}S?|\d{6}S?|\d{8})$") AS Smart_Meter_Type_by_MSN
      , CASE WHEN Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code IN ('S1', 'S2') THEN True 
             WHEN Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code IN ('NS','CR', 'MT', 'ET', 'CM', 'PP', 'TH') THEN False 
             ELSE null END AS Smart_Meter_Type_by_Code_UG
      , CASE WHEN Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code IN ('S1', 'S2') THEN True 
             WHEN Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code IN ('NS','CR', 'MT', 'ET', 'CM', 'PP', 'TH') THEN False 
             ELSE null END AS Smart_Meter_Type_by_Code_SPAM
FROM cte_union
--WHERE Meter_Point_No != MPXN
--WHERE Utiliserve_Meter_Type_Code != SPAM_Meter_Type_Code

with cte_contract_dedupe as
(
  SELECT contract_contractId as contractId,
         contract_mpxn as mpxn,
         contract_serviceAccountId as serviceAccountId,
         contract_fuel as fuel,
         contract_startDate as startDate,
         contract_endDate as endDate,
         contract_unitRate as unitRate,
         contract_standingRate as standingRate,
         contract_tariffId as tariffId,
         insertTime as latestCreatedEventTime,
         kafkaOffset as latestCreatedKafkaOffset,
         row_number() over (partition by contract_contractId order by topic desc, insertTime desc, kafkaOffset desc, contract_createdAt desc) as dedupe_rownum
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract__no_dedupe`
  where contract_eventId is not null
),
cte_first_contract as
(
  with cte_union as
  (
    select contract_contractId as contractId,
           contract_createdAt as createdAt
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract`
    where contract_eventId is not null
    union all
    select contractId,
           createdAt
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract_created__no_dedupe`
  )
  select contractId,
         min(createdAt) as createdDate
  from cte_union
  group by contractId
),
cte_cancelled as
(
  select cancelled_contractId as contractId,
         max(insertTime) as latestCancellationEventTime,
         max(kafkaOffset) as latestCancellationKafkaOffset
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract__no_dedupe`
  where cancelled_eventId is not null
  group by cancelled_contractId
)
select ctr.*,
      'Fixed Rate' as contractType,
       c1.createdDate
from cte_contract_dedupe ctr
LEFT JOIN cte_first_contract c1 on ctr.contractId = c1.contractId
left join cte_cancelled can on ctr.contractId = can.contractId
                           and (can.latestCancellationEventTime > ctr.latestCreatedEventTime
                            or (can.latestCancellationEventTime = ctr.latestCreatedEventTime
                            and can.latestCancellationKafkaOffset > ctr.latestCreatedKafkaOffset)) -- Need the offset tiebreaker to deal with data we backfilled
where ctr.dedupe_rownum = 1
  and can.contractId is NULL -- Filter cancelled from the view so we only show current state

# Cheapest Tariff Messaging
# Written By: Alex Ashford
# Edited By: Pete Diwell 2020-08-25
# Reviewed By: Alex Ashford 2020-08-25
# Latest Edit Info: Use latest SPTC version

WITH latest_tariff_costs AS ( # Get latest SPTC data
  SELECT *,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY currentContract.mpxn ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime DESC) AS rn
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_supply_point_tariff_costs_v7`
),

staging AS ( # Unnest fields and retrieve tariff information for current plan and cheapest plans
  SELECT sptc.currentContract.serviceAccountId as Account_No
        ,sptc.currentContract.mpxn as Meter_Point_No
        ,sptc.currentContract.contractId as Contract_ID
        ,sptc.currentContract.fuel as Fuel
        ,sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.tariff.planDisplayName as Current_Plan
        ,tc.tariff.type as tariff_type
        ,sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.vatRate as VAT_Rate
        ,ROUND(tc.tariff.standingRate * (1.00 + sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.vatRate),4) as Current_Standing_Rate # Add on VAT
        ,tc.tariff.unitRates as Current_Unit_Rate # Array
        ,tc.annualCostVatIncl as Current_Tariff_Estimated_Cost
        ,tc.tariff.exitFee as Current_Tariff_Exit_Fee
        ,tc.tariff.versionId as Current_Tariff_Version
        ,sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.contract.startDate as Current_Contract_Start_Date
        ,sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.contract.endDate as Current_Contract_End_Date
        ,tc.tariff.activeFrom as Tariff_Active_From
        ,tc.tariff.length as Tariff_Length
        ,sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.tariff.paymentMethod as Payment_Method
        ,sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.usage as Usage # Array
        ,sptc.personalProjection.effectiveFrom as Personal_Projection_Effective_From
        ,IFNULL(LEAD(sptc.personalProjection.effectiveFrom) OVER(PARTITION BY sptc.currentContract.mpxn, sptc.metadata.eventId ORDER BY sptc.personalProjection.effectiveFrom) ,CAST('2999-12-31' AS DATE)) as Personal_Projection_Effective_To # If not latest personal projection, get next projection start date, else put default future date
        ,sptc.personalProjection.projectedRegisterConsumption as Personal_Projection # Array
        ,stc.tariff.planName as Cheapest_Similar_Plan
        ,ROUND(stc.tariff.standingRate * (1.00 + sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.vatRate),4) as Cheapest_Similar_Standing_Rate # Add on VAT
        ,stc.tariff.unitRates as Cheapest_Similar_Unit_Rate # Array
        ,stc.annualCostVatIncl as Cheapest_Similar_Cost
        ,stc.savingAmountVatIncl as Cheapest_Similar_Saving
        ,stc.tariff.exitFee as Cheapest_Similar_Exit_Fee
        ,stc.tariff.versionId as Cheapest_Similar_Version
        ,sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.contract.endDate as Cheapest_Similar_Price_Guarantee --Advised by Alex V
        ,ctc.tariff.planName as Cheapest_Overall_Plan
        ,ROUND(ctc.tariff.standingRate * (1.00 + sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.vatRate),4) as Cheapest_Overall_Standing_Rate # Add on VAT
        ,ctc.tariff.unitRates as Cheapest_Overall_Unit_Rate # Array
        ,ctc.annualCostVatIncl as Cheapest_Overall_Cost
        ,ctc.savingAmountVatIncl as Cheapest_Overall_Saving
        ,ctc.tariff.exitFee as Cheapest_Overall_Exit_Fee
        ,ctc.tariff.versionId as Cheapest_Overall_Version
        ,sptc.aboutYourTariffLabel.contract.endDate as Cheapest_Overall_Price_Guarantee --Advised by Alex V
  FROM latest_tariff_costs sptc
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(sptc.annualTariffCosts) ctc ON ctc.tariff.tariffId = cheapestOverallTariff.tariffId AND ctc.tariff.versionId = cheapestOverallTariff.versionId
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(sptc.annualTariffCosts) stc ON stc.tariff.tariffId = cheapestSimilarTariff.tariffId AND stc.tariff.versionId = cheapestSimilarTariff.versionId
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(sptc.annualTariffCosts) tc ON tc.tariff.tariffId = currentTariff.tariffId AND tc.tariff.versionId = currentTariff.versionId
  WHERE sptc.rn=1
),

contract_dates AS ( # Get dates on contract, customerContractStartDate is important as startDate is not accurate for true contract start date
  SELECT contract_serviceAccountId,
         contract_contractId as contractId,
         contract_customerContractStartDate as customerContractStartDate,
         contract_customerContractExpiryDate as customerContractExpiryDate,
         contract_startDate as startDate,
         contract_endDate as endDate,
         t.value as contract_tag,
         cancelled,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY contract_contractId ORDER BY kafkaOffset DESC) as RN
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract` c
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(tags) t ON t.key = 'source'
  ORDER BY c.contract_serviceAccountId
)

# Bring through all fields from the dedupe, but unnest arrays and remove array references and replace with single line fields
SELECT DISTINCT s.*  EXCEPT(Current_Contract_Start_Date,Current_Contract_End_Date,Current_Unit_Rate,Personal_Projection,Cheapest_Similar_Unit_Rate,Cheapest_Overall_Unit_Rate,Usage)
      ,c.contract_tag
      # Obtain current contract start date via these rules:
      #  - If tariff type is fixed and tag = 'migrated', use customerContractStartDate and customerContractExpiryDate
      #  - If tariff type is fixed and tag <> 'migrated', take the contract end date and subtract tariff length (in months, make sure it is calculating correct day)
      #  - If tariff type is variable and tag = 'migrated', take customerContractStartDate - if null, tariff active from
      #  - If tariff type is variable and tag <> 'migrated', take customerContractStartDate - if null, startDate - if null, tariff active from
      ,CASE WHEN s.tariff_type = 'fixed' AND c.contract_tag = 'migrated' THEN c.customerContractStartDate
            WHEN s.tariff_type = 'fixed' THEN DATE_ADD(DATE_SUB(coalesce(s.Current_Contract_End_Date,c.customerContractExpiryDate,c.endDate), INTERVAL s.tariff_length MONTH), INTERVAL 1 DAY)
            WHEN s.tariff_type = 'variable' AND c.contract_tag = 'migrated' THEN COALESCE(c.customerContractStartDate,s.Tariff_Active_From)
            WHEN s.tariff_type = 'variable' THEN COALESCE(c.customerContractStartDate,c.startDate,s.Tariff_Active_From)
       END as Contract_Start_Date
      ,COALESCE(s.Current_Contract_End_Date,c.customerContractExpiryDate) as Contract_End_Date
      ,cur.timeOfUseLabel as Current_Clocking_Time
      ,ROUND(cur.unitRate * (1.00 + VAT_Rate),4) as Current_Unit_Rate # Add on VAT
      ,u.value as Usage
      ,pp.projectedRegisterConsumption.projectedConsumption as projectedConsumption
      ,csr.timeOfUseLabel as Cheapest_Similar_Clocking_Time
      ,ROUND(csr.unitRate * (1.00 + VAT_Rate),4) as Cheapest_Similar_Unit_Rate # Add on VAT
      ,cor.timeOfUseLabel as Cheapest_Overall_Clocking_Time
      ,ROUND(cor.unitRate * (1.00 + VAT_Rate),4) as Cheapest_Overall_Unit_Rate # Add on VAT
FROM staging s
INNER JOIN contract_dates c ON s.Contract_ID = c.contractId AND c.rn = 1 AND NOT c.cancelled # Remove cancelled contracts
LEFT JOIN UNNEST(Current_Unit_Rate) cur
LEFT JOIN UNNEST(Usage) u ON u.label = cur.timeOfUseLabel
LEFT JOIN UNNEST(Cheapest_Similar_Unit_Rate) csr ON csr.timeOfUseLabel = cur.timeOfUseLabel
LEFT JOIN UNNEST(Cheapest_Overall_Unit_Rate) cor ON cor.timeOfUseLabel = cur.timeOfUseLabel
LEFT JOIN UNNEST(Personal_Projection) pp ON pp.projectedRegisterConsumption.timeOfUseLabel = cur.timeOfUseLabel
ORDER BY Account_No

/**************************************************************************/
/***                                                                    ***/
/*** Determine whether a meter is SMETS1 or SMETS2 from received reads  ***/
/***                                                                    ***/
/**************************************************************************/


WITH
-- check gas msd reads. If we have at least one, it's smets1
gas_msd AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT 
    value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.msn
    ,'Gas' AS fuel
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_msd_stripped_v1` 
  WHERE
    PARTITIONTIME >= '2020-04-17'
    AND value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.metadata.traceToken	LIKE 'MSD%'
),
-- check elec msd reads. If we have at least one, it's smets1
elec_msd AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT 
    value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.msn	
    ,'Electricity' AS fuel
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_msd_stripped_v1` 
  WHERE
    PARTITIONTIME >= '2020-04-17'
    AND value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.metadata.traceToken	LIKE 'MSD%'
),
both AS (
  SELECT * FROM gas_msd
  UNION ALL 
  SELECT * FROM elec_msd

), 
-- check secure schedules. If we have one, it's smets1. This should account for missing comms meters
schedules AS (
  SELECT
     supplyType AS fuel
    ,deviceNo AS msn
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_SFE_DAILYREADSCHEDULE_validated`
), 
-- join both. If either condition is met, mark as SMETS1
smets1 AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
      COALESCE(s.msn, b.msn) AS msn
     ,COALESCE(s.fuel, b.fuel) AS fuel
     ,'Secure SMETS1' AS meterType
  FROM
    both b
  FULL OUTER JOIN
    schedules s
      ON b.msn = s.msn
), 
-- use the XREADs to determine if a meter is SMETS2. If we have one, consider it to be SMETS2
smets2 AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
    body.xreadOut01.meter.msn
    ,CASE WHEN body.xreadOut01.meter.importMpan IS NOT NULL THEN 'Electricity'
          WHEN body.xreadOut01.meter.importMprn IS NOT NULL THEN 'Gas'
          END AS fuel
    ,'SMETS2' AS meterType
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_BOL_XREADOUT01_validated`
)
-- bring it together. we outer join and union because if a meter appears to be both S1 and S2, it's S1 (S2 MSN enterred wrong)
-- there can of course be traditional meters given SMETS2 MSNs, but the numbers will be few. Broadly, we can consider this to be safe
SELECT DISTINCT
   COALESCE(s1.msn, s2.msn) AS msn    -- there were 6 overlaps. Coelesce with S1 first as these overlaps are 'stolen' MSNs from S1
  ,COALESCE(s1.fuel, s2.fuel) AS fuel
  ,COALESCE(s1.meterType, s2.meterType) AS meterType
FROM
  smets1 s1
FULL OUTER JOIN
  smets2 s2
    ON s1.msn = s2.msn

-- Elec Consumption
with cte_elec_consumption as
(
  with cte_elec_consumption_union as
  (
    SELECT consumptionId,
           createdAt,
           mpan as mpxn,
           fromDateTime,
           fromMeterReading,
           toDateTime, 
           toMeterReading, 
           consumption
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_consumption_generated__no_dedupe`
    where consumptionId is not null
    union all
    SELECT firstRefined_consumptionId     as consumptionId,
           createdAt,
           firstRefined_mpan              as mpxn,
           firstRefined_fromDateTime      as fromDateTime,
           firstRefined_fromMeterReading  as fromMeterReading,
           firstRefined_toDateTime        as toDateTime, 
           firstRefined_toMeterReading    as toMeterReading, 
           firstRefined_consumption       as consumption     
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_consumption_generated__no_dedupe`
    where firstRefined_consumptionId is not null
    union all
    SELECT secondRefined_consumptionId    as consumptionId,
           createdAt,
           secondRefined_mpan             as mpxn,
           secondRefined_fromDateTime     as fromDateTime,
           secondRefined_fromMeterReading as fromMeterReading,
           secondRefined_toDateTime       as toDateTime, 
           secondRefined_toMeterReading   as toMeterReading, 
           secondRefined_consumption      as consumption
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_consumption_generated__no_dedupe`
    where secondRefined_consumptionId is not null
  ),  
  cte_elec_consumption_dedupe as
  (
    SELECT *,
           row_number() over (partition by consumptionId order by createdAt desc) as dedupe_rownum
    FROM cte_elec_consumption_union
  ),
  cte_elec_deleted as
  (
    -- If a previous consumptionId has been refined then we need to delete what we had before
    select previousConsumptionId as consumptionId,
           max(createdAt) as latestDeletedTime
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_consumption_generated__no_dedupe`
    where previousConsumptionId is not null
    group by previousConsumptionId
  )
  select c.*
  from cte_elec_consumption_dedupe c
  left join cte_elec_deleted del on c.consumptionId = del.consumptionId
                                and del.latestDeletedTime > c.createdAt
  where c.dedupe_rownum = 1
    and del.consumptionId is null
),
-- Gas Consumption
cte_gas_consumption as
(
  with cte_gas_consumption_generated as
  (
    with cte_gas_consumption_generated_union as
    (
      SELECT gen.generated_consumptionId as consumptionId,
             gen.generated_mprn          as mprn, 
             gen.generated_fromDateTime  as fromDateTime,
             gen.generated_fromMeterReading  as fromMeterReading,
             gen.generated_toDateTime    as toDateTime,
             gen.generated_toMeterReading  as toMeterReading,
             gen.generated_volume        as volume,
             gen.generated_consumption   as consumption,
             gen.createdAt               as createdAt,
             'generated'                 as operation
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_gas_consumption_generated__no_dedupe` gen
      where gen.generated_consumptionId IS NOT NULL
      union all
      SELECT gen.firstRefined_consumptionId as consumptionId,
             gen.firstRefined_mprn          as mprn, 
             gen.firstRefined_fromDateTime  as fromDateTime,
             gen.firstRefined_fromMeterReading  as fromMeterReading,
             gen.firstRefined_toDateTime    as toDateTime,
             gen.firstRefined_toMeterReading  as toMeterReading,
             gen.firstRefined_volume        as volume,
             gen.firstRefined_consumption   as consumption,
             gen.createdAt               as createdAt,
             'generated'                 as operation
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_gas_consumption_generated__no_dedupe` gen
      where gen.firstRefined_consumptionId IS NOT NULL
      union all
      SELECT gen.secondRefined_consumptionId as consumptionId,
             gen.secondRefined_mprn          as mprn, 
             gen.secondRefined_fromDateTime  as fromDateTime,
             gen.secondRefined_fromMeterReading  as fromMeterReading,
             gen.secondRefined_toDateTime    as toDateTime,
             gen.secondRefined_toMeterReading  as toMeterReading,
             gen.secondRefined_volume        as volume,
             gen.secondRefined_consumption   as consumption,
             gen.createdAt               as createdAt,
             'generated'                 as operation
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_gas_consumption_generated__no_dedupe` gen
      where gen.secondRefined_consumptionId IS NOT NULL
    ),    
    cte_gas_consumption_generated_dedupe as
    (
      SELECT gen.consumptionId,
             gen.mprn, 
             gen.fromDateTime,
             gen.fromMeterReading,
             gen.toDateTime,
             gen.toMeterReading,
             gen.volume,
             gen.consumption,
             gen.createdAt,
             gen.operation,
             row_number() over (partition by gen.consumptionId order by gen.createdAt desc) as dedupe_rownum
      FROM cte_gas_consumption_generated_union gen
      where gen.consumptionId IS NOT NULL
    )
    select *
    from cte_gas_consumption_generated_dedupe
    where dedupe_rownum = 1
  ),
  cte_gas_consumption_updated as
  (
    with cte_gas_consumption_updated_dedupe as
    (
      SELECT upd.updated_consumptionId  as consumptionId,
             upd.updated_consumption    as consumption,
             upd.createdAt              as createdAt,
             'updated'                  as operation,
             row_number() over (partition by upd.updated_consumptionId order by upd.createdAt desc) as dedupe_rownum
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_gas_consumption_generated__no_dedupe` upd
      where upd.updated_consumptionId IS NOT NULL
    )
    select *
    from cte_gas_consumption_updated_dedupe
    where dedupe_rownum = 1
  ),
  cte_gas_deleted as
  (
    -- If a previous consumptionId has been refined then we need to delete what we had before
    select previousConsumptionId as consumptionId,
           max(createdAt) as latestDeletedTime
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_gas_consumption_generated__no_dedupe`
    where previousConsumptionId is not null
    group by previousConsumptionId
  )
  select c.consumptionId,
         c.mprn as mpxn,
         c.fromDateTime,
         c.fromMeterReading,
         c.toDateTime,
         c.toMeterReading,
         c.volume,
         coalesce(upd.consumption, c.consumption) as consumption
  from cte_gas_consumption_generated c
  left join cte_gas_consumption_updated upd on c.consumptionId = upd.consumptionId
                                          and upd.createdAt > c.createdAt
  left join cte_gas_deleted del on c.consumptionId = del.consumptionId
                               and del.latestDeletedTime > c.createdAt
  where c.dedupe_rownum = 1
    and del.consumptionId is null
),
cte_combined_consumption as
(
  select mpxn,
         fromDateTime,
         cast(fromDateTime as date) as fromDate,
         fromMeterReading,
         toDateTime,
         toMeterReading,
         cast(toDateTime as date) as toDate,
         consumptionId,
         null as volume,
         consumption
  from cte_elec_consumption
  union all
  select mpxn,
         fromDateTime,
         cast(fromDateTime as date) as fromDate,
         fromMeterReading,
         toDateTime,
         toMeterReading,
         cast(toDateTime as date) as toDate,
         consumptionId,
         volume,
         consumption
  from cte_gas_consumption
)
select *
from cte_combined_consumption

with cte_consumption_charge_generated as (
  with cte_consumption_charge_created as (
    with cte_charge_dedupe as (
      select created_eventId            as event_id,
             created_createdAt          as created_at,
             created_chargeId           as charge_id,
             created_from               as charge_from,
             created_to                 as charge_to,
             created_contractId         as contract_id,
             created_supplyPoint        as supply_point,
             created_charges            as charges,
             created_amount             as charge_amount,
             created_unitRate           as unit_rate,
             created_consumption        as consumption,
             created_consumptionId      as consumption_id,
             insertTime                 as latestCreateInsertTime,
             kafkaOffset                as latestCreateKafkaOffset,
             0                          as is_consumption_adjustment,
             row_number() Over (partition by created_chargeId order by topic desc, insertTime desc, created_createdAt desc) as charge_dedupe_rownum
      from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_consumption_charge_generated__no_dedupe`
      WHERE created_eventId is not null
      
      union all
      
      select final_eventId            as event_id,
             final_createdAt          as created_at,
             final_chargeId           as charge_id,
             final_from               as charge_from,
             final_to                 as charge_to,
             final_contractId         as contract_id,
             final_supplyPoint        as supply_point,
             ARRAY(SELECT STRUCT(clockingTimeId,
                                 clockingTimeLabel,
                                 consumptionAdjustment as consumption,
                                 unitRate,
                                 amount,
                                 cast(null as float64) as fromMeterReading,
                                 cast(null as string) as fromReadingType,
                                 cast(null as float64) as toMeterReading,
                                 cast(null as string) as toReadingType)  
                   FROM c.final_charges)           as charges,            
             final_amount             as charge_amount,
             final_unitRate           as unit_rate,
             final_consumptionAdjustment as consumption,
             cast(null as string)       as consumption_id,
             insertTime                 as latestCreateInsertTime,
             kafkaOffset                as latestCreateKafkaOffset,
             1                          as is_consumption_adjustment,
             row_number() Over (partition by final_chargeId order by topic desc, insertTime desc, final_createdAt desc) as charge_dedupe_rownum
      from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_consumption_charge_generated__no_dedupe` c
      WHERE final_eventId is not null
    ),
    
    cte_created_times as (
      select created_chargeId       as charge_id,
             min(created_createdAt) as charge_first_created_time
      from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_consumption_charge_generated__no_dedupe`
      group by created_chargeId
      
      union all
      
      select final_chargeId       as charge_id,
             min(final_createdAt) as charge_first_created_time
      from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_consumption_charge_generated__no_dedupe`
      group by final_chargeId
    )
    
    select d.*,
           ct.charge_first_created_time
    from cte_charge_dedupe d
    left join cte_created_times ct on d.charge_id = ct.charge_id
    where charge_dedupe_rownum = 1
  ),
  
  cte_consumption_charge_updated as (
    with cte_charge_dedupe as (
      select updated_eventId   as event_id,
             updated_chargeId           as charge_id,
             updated_consumptionId      as consumption_id,
             updated_charges            as charges,
             updated_amount             as charge_amount,
             updated_unitRate           as unit_rate,
             updated_consumption        as consumption,
             updated_createdAt          as created_at,
             insertTime                 as latestUpdateInsertTime,
             kafkaOffset                as latestUpdateKafkaOffset,
             row_number() Over (partition by updated_chargeId order by insertTime desc, updated_createdAt desc) as charge_dedupe_rownum
      from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_consumption_charge_generated`
      WHERE updated_eventId is not null
    )
    
    select *
    from cte_charge_dedupe
    where charge_dedupe_rownum = 1
  )
  
  select 
        COALESCE(cc_updated.event_id, cc_created.event_id) event_id,
        cc_created.charge_id,
        cc_created.charge_first_created_time,
        cc_created.charge_from,
        cc_created.charge_to,
        cc_created.contract_id,
        cc_created.supply_point,
        coalesce(cc_updated.consumption_id, cc_created.consumption_id) as consumption_id,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.charges, cc_created.charges) as charges,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.charge_amount, cc_created.charge_amount) charge_amount, -- Favour an update over a created to pick up new CV values
        COALESCE(cc_updated.consumption, cc_created.consumption) consumption,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.unit_rate, cc_created.unit_rate) unit_rate,
        cc_created.is_consumption_adjustment,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.created_at, cc_created.created_at) as charge_last_updated_time,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.latestUpdateInsertTime, cc_created.latestCreateInsertTime) as latestGeneratedInsertTime,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.latestUpdateKafkaOffset, cc_created.latestCreateKafkaOffset) as latestGeneratedKafkaOffset
  from cte_consumption_charge_created cc_created
  left join cte_consumption_charge_updated cc_updated  on cc_created.charge_id = cc_updated.charge_id
                                                      and (cc_updated.latestUpdateInsertTime > cc_created.latestCreateInsertTime
                                                       OR (cc_updated.latestUpdateInsertTime = cc_created.latestCreateInsertTime
                                                       AND cc_updated.latestUpdateKafkaOffset > cc_created.latestCreateKafkaOffset)) -- Need the offset tiebreaker to deal with data we backfilled
),

cte_consumption_charge_cancelled as (
  select cancelled_chargeId        as charge_id,
         max(cancelled_createdAt)  as latestCancelledCreatedAt, # updated from insertTime PJD 2020-01-31
         MAX(kafkaOffset)          as latestCancelledKafkaOffset
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_consumption_charge_generated`
  where cancelled_eventId is NOT null
  group by cancelled_chargeId
),

cte_consumption_charge as (
  select 
      cc_generated.supply_point,
      cc_generated.contract_id,
      cc_generated.charge_id,
      cc_generated.consumption_id,
      cc_generated.charges,
      cc_generated.charge_first_created_time,
      cc_generated.charge_last_updated_time,
      CAST(cc_generated.charge_from AS datetime) AS Charge_From_Date,
      CAST(cc_generated.charge_to AS datetime)   AS Charge_To_Date,
      TIMESTAMP_DIFF(cc_generated.charge_to, cc_generated.charge_from, HOUR) charge_span_hours, -- a sensible person would use SECONDS and divide by 60, but I'm lazy sue me... - Pete Grace 23-10-19
      cc_generated.charge_amount,
      cc_generated.unit_rate,
      cc_generated.consumption,
      case when cc_cancelled.charge_id is null then 0 else 1 end is_cancelled,
      'consumption_charge' as charge_type,
      cc_generated.is_consumption_adjustment
  from cte_consumption_charge_generated cc_generated
  left join cte_consumption_charge_cancelled cc_cancelled on cc_cancelled.charge_id = cc_generated.charge_id
                                                            and (cc_cancelled.latestCancelledCreatedAt > cc_generated.charge_last_updated_time
                                                             OR (cc_cancelled.latestCancelledCreatedAt = cc_generated.charge_last_updated_time
                                                             AND cc_cancelled.latestCancelledKafkaOffset > cc_generated.latestGeneratedKafkaOffset))
)

select cc.*,
       cc.supply_point as mpxn
from cte_consumption_charge cc
where is_cancelled = 0

    from cte_charge_dedupe d
    left join cte_created_times ct on d.charge_id = ct.charge_id
    where charge_dedupe_rownum = 1
  ),
  
  cte_consumption_charge_updated as (
    with cte_charge_dedupe as (
      select updated_eventId   as event_id,
             updated_chargeId           as charge_id,
             updated_consumptionId      as consumption_id,
             updated_charges            as charges,
             updated_amount             as charge_amount,
             updated_unitRate           as unit_rate,
             updated_consumption        as consumption,
             updated_createdAt          as created_at,
             insertTime                 as latestUpdateInsertTime,
             kafkaOffset                as latestUpdateKafkaOffset,
             row_number() Over (partition by updated_chargeId order by insertTime desc, updated_createdAt desc) as charge_dedupe_rownum
      from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_consumption_charge_generated`
      WHERE updated_eventId is not null
    )
    
    select *
    from cte_charge_dedupe
    where charge_dedupe_rownum = 1
  )
  
  select 
        COALESCE(cc_updated.event_id, cc_created.event_id) event_id,
        cc_created.charge_id,
        cc_created.charge_first_created_time,
        cc_created.charge_from,
        cc_created.charge_to,
        cc_created.contract_id,
        cc_created.supply_point,
        coalesce(cc_updated.consumption_id, cc_created.consumption_id) as consumption_id,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.charges, cc_created.charges) as charges,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.charge_amount, cc_created.charge_amount) charge_amount, -- Favour an update over a created to pick up new CV values
        COALESCE(cc_updated.consumption, cc_created.consumption) consumption,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.unit_rate, cc_created.unit_rate) unit_rate,
        cc_created.is_consumption_adjustment,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.created_at, cc_created.created_at) as charge_last_updated_time,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.latestUpdateInsertTime, cc_created.latestCreateInsertTime) as latestGeneratedInsertTime,
        COALESCE(cc_updated.latestUpdateKafkaOffset, cc_created.latestCreateKafkaOffset) as latestGeneratedKafkaOffset
  from cte_consumption_charge_created cc_created
  left join cte_consumption_charge_updated cc_updated  on cc_created.charge_id = cc_updated.charge_id
                                                      and (cc_updated.latestUpdateInsertTime > cc_created.latestCreateInsertTime
                                                       OR (cc_updated.latestUpdateInsertTime = cc_created.latestCreateInsertTime
                                                       AND cc_updated.latestUpdateKafkaOffset > cc_created.latestCreateKafkaOffset)) -- Need the offset tiebreaker to deal with data we backfilled
),

cte_consumption_charge_cancelled as (
  select cancelled_chargeId        as charge_id,
         max(cancelled_createdAt)  as latestCancelledCreatedAt, # updated from insertTime PJD 2020-01-31
         MAX(kafkaOffset)          as latestCancelledKafkaOffset
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_consumption_charge_generated`
  where cancelled_eventId is NOT null
  group by cancelled_chargeId
),

cte_consumption_charge as (
  select 
      cc_generated.supply_point,
      cc_generated.contract_id,
      cc_generated.charge_id,
      cc_generated.consumption_id,
      cc_generated.charges,
      cc_generated.charge_first_created_time,
      coalesce(latestCancelledCreatedAt, cc_generated.charge_last_updated_time) as charge_last_updated_time,
      CAST(cc_generated.charge_from AS datetime) AS Charge_From_Date,
      CAST(cc_generated.charge_to AS datetime)   AS Charge_To_Date,
      TIMESTAMP_DIFF(cc_generated.charge_to, cc_generated.charge_from, HOUR) charge_span_hours, -- a sensible person would use SECONDS and divide by 60, but I'm lazy sue me... - Pete Grace 23-10-19
      cc_generated.charge_amount,
      cc_generated.unit_rate,
      cc_generated.consumption,
      case when cc_cancelled.charge_id is null then 0 else 1 end is_cancelled,
      'consumption_charge' as charge_type,
      cc_generated.is_consumption_adjustment
  from cte_consumption_charge_generated cc_generated
  left join cte_consumption_charge_cancelled cc_cancelled on cc_cancelled.charge_id = cc_generated.charge_id
                                                            and (cc_cancelled.latestCancelledCreatedAt > cc_generated.charge_last_updated_time
                                                             OR (cc_cancelled.latestCancelledCreatedAt = cc_generated.charge_last_updated_time
                                                             AND cc_cancelled.latestCancelledKafkaOffset > cc_generated.latestGeneratedKafkaOffset))
)

select cc.*,
       cc.supply_point as mpxn
from cte_consumption_charge cc

with cte_losses as
(
  with cte_loss_dedupe as
  (
    select mpxn,
           lossDate,
           lossNotificationReceivedDate,
           row_number() over (partition by mpxn order by lossNotificationReceivedDate desc) as loss_dedupe_rownum
    from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys`
    where lossJourneyStatus in ('Loss notification received', 'Loss confirmed', 'Loss completed')
  )
  select *
  from cte_loss_dedupe
  where loss_dedupe_rownum = 1
),
cte_tariffs as (
  select distinct tariffId,
         region,
         profileClass
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tariffs`
),
cte_contracts as (
  select DISTINCT c.serviceAccountId,
         c.mpxn,
         c.fuel,
         t.region,
         t.profileClass,
         c.PlanName,
         c.tariffType,
         c.startDate,
         c.endDate,
         c.customerContractStartDate,
         c.customerContractExpiryDate
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` c
  inner join cte_tariffs t using (tariffId)
  order by mpxn
)
select cm.mpxn,
       cm.fuel,
       coalesce(sp.regionCode, cm.region) as regionCode,
       coalesce(sp.profileClassId, cm.profileClass) as profileClassId,
       cm.planName,
         cm.tariffType,
       coalesce(cm.customerContractStartDate, cm.startDate) as contractStartDate,    
       coalesce(cm.customerContractExpiryDate, cm.endDate) as contractExpiryDate, 
       next_ctr.planName as futureContractPlanName,
         next_ctr.tariffType as futureContractTariffType,
       next_ctr.customerContractStartDate as futureContractStartDate, 
       next_ctr.customerContractExpiryDate as futureContractExpiryDate,
       l.lossDate,
       coalesce(eac.estimatedAnnualConsumption, sp.forecastedAnnualConsumption) as forecastedAnnualConsumption,
       sp.ssc,
       r.timePatternRegime as tpr,
       sp.meterTimeswitchCode,
       sp.lineLossFactorClassId,
       sp.distributorId,
       cm.contractOrder
from (select *, 
             row_number() over (partition by serviceAccountId, mpxn order by startDate asc) as contractOrder
      from cte_contracts) cm
left join cte_contracts next_ctr on next_ctr.mpxn = cm.mpxn
                                and next_ctr.startDate = date_add(cm.endDate, interval 1 day)
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp on cm.mpxn = sp.mpxn
left join unnest(sp.currentMeterRegisters.meterRegisters) r
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.multi_rate_projections_4_eacs` eac on sp.mpxn = eac.mpan
                                                                      and r.timePatternRegime = eac.timePatternRegime
left join cte_losses l on cm.mpxn = l.mpxn
                      and l.lossDate >= cm.startDate
where CURRENT_DATE() between cm.startDate and coalesce(cm.endDate, '2999-01-01') # Current contracts
   or (cm.contractOrder=1 and cm.startDate > current_date())                     # Onboarded contracts

query.895:
with cte_contract_dedupe as (
  SELECT contract_contractId as contractId,
         contract_mpxn as mpxn,
         contract_serviceAccountId as serviceAccountId,
         contract_fuel as fuel,
         contract_startDate as startDate,
         contract_endDate as endDate,
         ctr.contract_customerContractStartDate as customerContractStartDate,
         contract_customerContractExpiryDate as customerContractExpiryDate,
         contract_unitRate as unitRate,
         contract_standingRate as standingRate,
         contract_tariffId as tariffId,
         ctr.insertTime as latestCreatedEventTime,
         ctr.kafkaOffset as latestCreatedKafkaOffset,
         ctr.cancelled,
         row_number() over (partition by ctr.contract_contractId order by ctr.topic desc,  ctr.contract_createdAt desc) as dedupe_rownum
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract__no_dedupe` ctr
  where contract_eventId is not null
),

cte_first_contract as (
  with cte_union as (
    select contract_contractId as contractId,
           contract_createdAt as createdAt
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract__no_dedupe`
    where contract_eventId is not null
    
    union all
    
    select contractId,
           createdAt
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract_created__no_dedupe`
  )
  
  select contractId,
         min(createdAt) as createdDate
  from cte_union
  group by contractId
),

cte_cancelled as (
  select COALESCE(cancelled_contractId, contract_contractId) as contractId,
         max(insertTime) as latestCancellationEventTime,
         max(kafkaOffset) as latestCancellationKafkaOffset
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract__no_dedupe`
  where (cancelled_eventId is not null
  or cancelled = True)
  group by COALESCE(cancelled_contractId, contract_contractId)
)

select ctr.contractId,
       ctr.mpxn,
       ctr.serviceAccountId,
       ctr.fuel,
       ctr.startDate,
       ctr.endDate,
       coalesce(ctr.customerContractStartDate, ctr.startDate) as customerContractStartDate,
       ctr.customerContractExpiryDate,
       coalesce(ft.unitRate, vt.unitRate, ctr.unitRate) as currentUnitRate,
       coalesce(ft.unitRates, vt.unitRates) as currentUnitRates,
       coalesce(ft.standingRate, vt.standingRate, ctr.standingRate) as currentStandingRate,
       ctr.tariffId,
       coalesce(ft.type, vt.type, 'fixed') as tariffType,
       coalesce(ft.planName, vt.planName) as planName,
       coalesce(ft.activeFrom, vt.activeFrom) as tariffActiveFrom,
       coalesce(ft.activeTo, vt.activeTo) as tariffActiveTo,
       ctr.latestCreatedEventTime,
       c1.createdDate,
       case when can.contractId is not null then 'cancelled'
            when ctr.startDate > CURRENT_DATE() then 'pending'
            when ctr.endDate < current_date() then 'historic'
            else 'active'
       end as contractStatus,
       case when can.contractId is not null then 1 else 0 end as isCancelled
from cte_contract_dedupe ctr
LEFT JOIN cte_first_contract c1 on ctr.contractId = c1.contractId
left join cte_cancelled can on ctr.contractId = can.contractId and (can.latestCancellationEventTime > ctr.latestCreatedEventTime or (can.latestCancellationEventTime = ctr.latestCreatedEventTime and can.latestCancellationKafkaOffset >= ctr.latestCreatedKafkaOffset)) --Need the offset tiebreaker to deal with data we backfilled
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tariffs` ft on ctr.tariffId = ft.tariffId and ft.type = 'fixed'
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tariffs` vt on ctr.tariffId = vt.tariffId and vt.type = 'variable' and CURRENT_DATE() between vt.activeFrom and coalesce(vt.activeTo, '2999-01-01') 
where ctr.dedupe_rownum = 1

WITH cte_all_d300s as
(
  select 
         d300.metadata.eventId,
         lj.mpxn,
         lj.lossDate,
         parse_date('%Y%m%d', SUBSTR(d300.header.fileCreationTimestamp,1,8)) as createdDate,
         d300.header.fromMarketParticipantId,
         d300.header.toMarketParticipantId,
         d300.record.MpanDetails.mpanCoreProcess,
         d300.record.MpanDetails.additionalInformation,
         d300.record.MpanDetails.recordRejectionReasonIndicator,
         meter.meterIdSerialNumber,
         meter.initiatingFlowIndicator,
         reg.meterRegisterID,
         reg.registerReading,
         reg.readingType,
         reg.changeOfSupplierReadingRejectionCode,
         reg.proposedRegisterReading,
         reg.statusOfProposedReadingS
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys_detailed` lj
  inner join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_D0300001_split` d300 on lj.mpxn = d300.record.MpanDetails.mpanCore
                                                      and safe.parse_date('%Y%m%d', record.MpanDetails.effectiveFromSettlementDateRegiForNewSupplier) = date_add(lj.lossDate, interval 1 day)
  inner join Unnest (record.MpanDetails.meterId) as meter
  inner join Unnest (meter.meterRegisterDetails) as reg
  where lj.serviceAccountId is not null
    and lj.lossJourneyStatus in ('Loss confirmed', 'Loss completed')
    and d300.record.MpanDetails.mpanCoreProcess = 'D'

)

select Distinct d300s_out.mpxn,
       d300s_out.lossDate,
       d300s_out.createdDate as originalD300CreatedDate,
       d300s_out.toMarketParticipantID,
       d300s_out.registerReading,
       d300s_out.proposedRegisterReading,
       d300s_out.additionalInformation as OriginalInfo,
       d300s_in.createdDate as responseSarCreatedDate,
       d300s_in.changeOfSupplierReadingRejectionCode as responseRejectionAcceptanceCode,
       d300s_in.proposedRegisterReading as responseProposedRead,
       d300s_in.additionalInformation as responseComments
from cte_all_d300s d300s_out
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_bc_ovo_applications.Dispute` drs on drs.MPAN_MPRN = d300s_out.mpxn
                                               and cast(drs.DisputedReadDate as date) = date_add(d300s_out.lossDate, interval 1 day)
                                               and drs.InitiatingSupplier = 'OVOE'
left join cte_all_d300s d300s_in on d300s_out.mpxn = d300s_in.mpxn
                           and d300s_out.lossDate = d300s_in.lossDate
                           and d300s_in.toMarketParticipantId = 'OVOE'
where d300s_out.initiatingFlowIndicator = '1'
  and d300s_out.fromMarketParticipantID = 'OVOE'
  and drs.ID is null

with cte_latest_state as
(
  select *,
         row_number() over (partition by mpxn, disputedReadDate order by metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_state_v2`
  where status not like 'Invalid%'
)

select init.mpxn,
       init.disputedReadDate,
       init.accountNumber,
       date_add(init.disputedReadDate, interval -1 day) as lossDate,
       init.initiatedAt,
       init.initiatedBy,
       alt.alternatedAt,
       rej.rejectedAt,
       agr.agreedAt,
       init.gainingSupplier,
       init.losingSupplier,
       s.status,
       --s.workRequired,
       -- We'll keep it simple in this view for PC1 at this stage
       init.registers[offset(0)].registerId as registerId,
       init.registers[offset(0)].disputedRead as disputedRead,
       init.registers[offset(0)].proposedRead as proposedRead,
       init.eventComment as disputeComment,
       row_number() over (partition by init.mpxn, init.disputedReadDate
                          order by init.initiatedAt asc, alt.alternatedAt desc, rej.rejectedAt desc, agr.agreedAt desc) as disputeSequence
from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_initiated` init
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_alternated` alt on init.mpxn = alt.mpxn
                                                                                                and init.disputedReadDate = alt.disputedReadDate
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_rejected` rej on init.mpxn = rej.mpxn
                                                                                              and init.disputedReadDate = rej.disputedReadDate
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_agreed` agr on init.mpxn = agr.mpxn
                                                                                              and init.disputedReadDate = agr.disputedReadDate
left join cte_latest_state s on init.mpxn = s.mpxn
                            and init.disputedReadDate = s.disputedReadDate
                            and s.row_num = 1

SELECT
  flowNameNoVersion,
  DATE_DIFF(CURRENT_DATE(), DATE(MAX(seenOnKafka)), DAY) AS daysSinceLastSeenOnKafka,
  MAX(seenOnKafka) AS lastSeenOnKafka,
  DATE_DIFF(DATE(MAX(seenOnDataLake)), DATE(MAX(seenOnKafka)), DAY) AS dataLakeToKafkaLatency,
  MAX(seenOnDataLake) AS lastSeenOnDataLake
FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.flows_reconciliation_status`
GROUP BY flowNameNoVersion
ORDER BY flowNameNoVersion

WITH
  recon_status AS (
    SELECT
      raw.flowNameNoVersion,
      raw.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash,
      raw.rawSourceBlobPath,
      PARSE_DATE("%Y/%m/%d",REGEXP_EXTRACT(raw.rawSourceBlobPath, r"[0-9]{4}\/[0-9]{2}\/[0-9]{2}")) AS flow_receipt_date,
      LOGICAL_AND(CASE
          WHEN pf.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash IS NOT NULL THEN TRUE
          ELSE FALSE END) AS parsedFlow_seen_on_gcs,
      MAX(raw.seenAt) AS seenAt,
      MAX(fbd.backfillDate) AS backfillDate,
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flows_raw_flow_seen_on_gs_industry_data_lake` raw
    LEFT JOIN
      `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flows_parsed_flow_seen_on_gs_industry_data_lake_parsed` pf
    ON
      raw.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash = pf.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash
    LEFT JOIN
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_backfill_dates_v1` fbd
    ON
      raw.flowNameNoVersion = fbd.flowNameNoVersion
    GROUP BY
      raw.flowNameNoVersion,
      raw.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash,
      raw.rawSourceBlobPath )

SELECT
  flowNameNoVersion,
  rawSourceBlobMd5Hash,
  rawSourceBlobPath,
  seenAt,
  flow_receipt_date,
  backfillDate
FROM recon_status
WHERE parsedFlow_seen_on_gcs = FALSE
AND rawSourceBlobMd5Hash NOT IN (SELECT flow_md5_hash FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flows_denylisted_flow_md5_hash_v1`)
AND flowNameNoVersion IN (SELECT flowNameNoVersion FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flows_enabled_v1`)

    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flows_raw_flow_seen_on_gs_industry_data_lake` raw
    LEFT JOIN

WITH
  enabled_split_flows AS (
  SELECT
    flowNameNoVersion,
    topic
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flows_enabled_v1`
  WHERE
    topic LIKE 'flow%\\_%\\_split\\_consolidated\\_v%'
    OR topic = 'gcs.raw[y]kfk.parsed[n]kfk.split[n]'
    OR topic = 'gcs.raw[y]kfk.split[some]'
    OR topic = 'gcs.raw[y]kfk.split[n]'),
  split_flows AS (
  SELECT
    *
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flows_split_consolidated_flow_record_seen_on_kafka`
  WHERE
    kafka.topic IN (
    SELECT
      topic
    FROM
      enabled_split_flows)
  AND
    sourceBucket = 'SPARK'),
  uncategorised_flows AS (
  SELECT
    *
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flows_uncategorised_flow_seen_on_gs_industry_data_lake`
  WHERE
    rawSourceBlobMd5Hash NOT IN (SELECT flow_md5_hash FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flows_denylisted_flow_md5_hash_v1`)
  AND
    sourceBucket = 'SPARK'),
  raw_flows AS (
  SELECT
    *
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flows_raw_consolidated_flow_seen_on_gs_industry_data_lake`
  WHERE
    flowNameNoVersion IN (SELECT flowNameNoVersion FROM enabled_split_flows)
  AND
    rawSourceBlobMd5Hash NOT IN (SELECT flow_md5_hash FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flows_denylisted_flow_md5_hash_v1`)
  AND
    sourceBucket = 'SPARK'),
  recon_status AS (
  SELECT
    r.flowNameNoVersion,
    u.rawSourceBlobPath AS uncategorisedBlobPath,
    r.rawSourceBlobPath,
    r.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y/%m/%d",REGEXP_EXTRACT(r.rawSourceBlobPath, r"[0-9]{4}\/[0-9]{2}\/[0-9]{2}")) AS flow_receipt_date,
    MAX(s.rawSourceRecordsCount) AS splitFlowRecord_expected_count,
    SUM(CASE
        WHEN s.flowRecordId IS NOT NULL THEN 1
        ELSE 0 END) AS splitFlowRecord_seen_on_kafka_count,
    MAX(fbd.backfillDate) AS backfillDate,
    MAX(r.seenAt) AS seenAt
  FROM
    uncategorised_flows u
  JOIN
    raw_flows r
  ON
    u.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash = r.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash
  LEFT JOIN
    split_flows s
  ON
    u.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash = s.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash
  LEFT JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_backfill_dates_v1` fbd
  ON
    r.flowNameNoVersion = fbd.flowNameNoVersion
  GROUP BY
    u.rawSourceBlobPath,
    r.flowNameNoVersion,
    r.rawSourceBlobMd5Hash,
    r.rawSourceBlobPath)
SELECT
  ABS(splitFlowRecord_expected_count - splitFlowRecord_seen_on_kafka_count) AS count_diff,
  *
FROM recon_status
WHERE (splitFlowRecord_expected_count != splitFlowRecord_seen_on_kafka_count OR splitFlowRecord_expected_count IS NULL)
AND seenAt < TIMESTAMP_SUB(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), INTERVAL 24 HOUR)
AND (date_diff(flow_receipt_date, backfillDate, day) >= 0 OR backfillDate IS NULL)
