with cte_all_sars as
(
  select lj.mpxn,
         lj.lossDate,
         parse_date('%Y%m%d', sar.header.createdDate) as createdDate,
         sar.record.SarGroup.initiatingOrganisationId,
         sar.header.originatorId,
         sar.header.recipientId,
         sar.record.SarGroup.referenceNumber,
         record.SarGroup.transporterRead,
         sar.record.SarGroup.statusResponseSar,
         sar.record.SarGroup.recordRejectionAcceptanceCode,
         sar.record.SarGroup.proposedRead,
         sar.record.SarGroup.comments
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys_detailed` lj
  inner join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_SAR_split` sar on lj.mpxn = sar.record.SarGroup.meterPointReference
                                                      and safe.parse_date('%Y%m%d', record.SarGroup.dateOfTransfer) = date_add(lj.lossDate, interval 1 day)
  where lj.serviceAccountId is not null
    and lj.lossJourneyStatus in ('Loss confirmed', 'Loss completed')
),
cte_original_sars as
(
  select mpxn,
         lossDate,
         min(createdDate) as originalSarCreatedDate
  from cte_all_sars
  group by mpxn,
           lossDate
),
cte_latest_state as
(
  select *,
         row_number() over (partition by mpxn, disputedReadDate order by metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.tardis_gas_dispute_state_v2`
  where status not like 'Invalid%'
)
select init.mpxn,
       date_add(init.disputedReadDate, interval -1 day) as lossDate, -- backwards compatibility
       init.disputedReadDate,
       init.accountNumber,
       init.initiatedAt,
       init.initiatedBy,
       coalesce(sar.originalSarCreatedDate,cast(init.initiatedAt as date)) as originalSarCreatedDate, -- backwards compatibility
       init.gainingSupplier,
       init.losingSupplier,
       init.gainingSupplier as recipientId, -- backwards compatibility
       init.sarReferenceNumber,
       init.sarReferenceNumber as referenceNumber, -- backwards compatibility
       init.disputedRead,
       init.disputedRead as transporterRead, -- backwards compatibility
       init.proposedRead,
       init.eventComment as disputeComment,
       init.eventComment as originalComments, -- backwards compatibility
       s.status,
       agr.agreedRead,
       agr.agreedAt as agreedAt,
       rej.rejectionCode,
       rej.responseComment as rejectedComment,
       rej.rejectedAt as rejectedAt,
       alt.alternateProposedRead,
       alt.alternatedAt,
       alt.eventComment as alternatedComment,
       coalesce(cast(alt.alternatedAt as date), cast(agr.agreedAt as date), cast(rej.rejectedAt as date)) as responseSarCreatedDate,
       coalesce(case when alt.mpxn is not null then 'A' end, case when agr.mpxn is not null then 'Y' end, case when rej.mpxn is not null then 'P' end) as responseStatus,
       rej.rejectionCode as responseRejectionAcceptanceCode,
       coalesce(alt.alternateProposedRead, agr.agreedRead, rej.proposedRead) as responseProposedRead,
       coalesce(alt.eventComment, rej.responseComment) as responseComments,
       case when agr.agreedAt > alt.alternatedAt then cast(agr.agreedAt as date) end as alternationAcceptanceCreatedDate,
       row_number() over (partition by init.mpxn, init.disputedReadDate order by init.initiatedAt asc) as disputeSequence
from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_gas_dispute_initiated` init
left join cte_original_sars sar on init.mpxn = sar.mpxn
                               and date_add(init.disputedReadDate, interval -1 day) = sar.lossDate
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_gas_dispute_agreed` agr on init.mpxn = agr.mpxn
                                                              and init.disputedReadDate = agr.disputedReadDate
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_gas_dispute_rejected` rej on init.mpxn = rej.mpxn
                                                              and init.disputedReadDate = rej.disputedReadDate
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_gas_dispute_alternated` alt on init.mpxn = alt.mpxn
                                                              and init.disputedReadDate = alt.disputedReadDate
left join cte_latest_state s on init.mpxn = s.mpxn
                            and init.disputedReadDate = s.disputedReadDate
                            and s.row_num = 1

with cte_health_check_flags as
(
  select mpxn,
         fuel,
         andromedaMigrationDate,
         min(startDate) as chargeMandateStartDate,
         min(has_valid_unit_rate) as has_valid_unit_rates,
         min(has_valid_standing_charge_rate) as has_valid_standing_charge_rates,
         min(has_no_overlapping_charge_mandates) as has_no_overlapping_charge_mandates
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.health_check_charge_mandates_detail`
  group by mpxn,
           fuel,
           andromedaMigrationDate
)
select *,       
       CASE
        WHEN (has_valid_unit_rates = 0
           OR has_valid_standing_charge_rates = 0
           OR has_no_overlapping_charge_mandates = 0)
        THEN 'Unhealthy'
        ELSE 'Healthy'
       END as overallChargeMandateHealth
from cte_health_check_flags
query.927:
with cte_charge_mandate_checks as
(
  select ec.contractId,
         ec.mpxn,
         ec.fuel,
         ec.startDate,
         sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
         case when ec.currentUnitRate > 0 then 1 else 0 end as has_valid_unit_rate, -- Simple check on it being greater than zero for now, in due course we might want to check vs. tariff rates if we store them in Andromeda
         case when ec.currentStandingRate > 0 then 1 else 0 end as has_valid_standing_charge_rate,
         case when sum(case when overlap.contractId is not null then 1 else 0 end) = 0 then 1 else 0 end as has_no_overlapping_charge_mandates,
         sum(case when overlap.contractId is not null then 1 else 0 end) as overlappingChargeMandatesCount,
         min(overlap.contractId) as overlappingContractId
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp
  inner join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ec on sp.mpxn = ec.mpxn
  left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` overlap on ec.mpxn = overlap.mpxn
                                                                                                    and ec.contractId <> overlap.contractId
                                                                                                    and (overlap.startDate between ec.startDate and ec.endDate
                                                                                                      OR overlap.endDate between ec.startDate and ec.endDate)
  group by ec.contractId,
           ec.mpxn,
           ec.fuel,
           ec.startDate,
           sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
           ec.currentUnitRate,
           ec.currentStandingRate
)
select *
from cte_charge_mandate_checks
query.929:
with cte_health_check_flags as
(
  select sp.mpxn,
         sp.fuel,
         sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
         sp.chargeMandateStatus,
         MIN(is_linked_to_active_charge_mandate) as has_all_charges_linked_to_active_charge_mandate,
         MIN(is_within_charge_mandate_dates) as has_all_charges_within_charge_mandate_dates,
         min(has_consumption_for_consumption_charge) as has_consumption_for_all_consumption_charges
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp -- Use all supply points as base even if they have no charges
  left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.health_check_erroneous_charging_detail` ec on sp.mpxn = ec.mpxn
  where sp.chargeMandateStatus is not null -- Include everything including historic and cancelled
  group by sp.mpxn,
           sp.fuel,
           sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
           sp.chargeMandateStatus
)
select *,
       CASE
        WHEN (has_all_charges_linked_to_active_charge_mandate = 0
           OR has_all_charges_within_charge_mandate_dates = 0
           OR has_consumption_for_all_consumption_charges = 0)
        THEN 'Error'
        ELSE 'Healthy'
       END as overallErroneousChargingHealth
from cte_health_check_flags

with cte_combined_charges as
(
  select cc.mpxn,
         cc.contract_id,
         cc.charge_id,
         cc.Charge_From_Date,
         cc.Charge_To_Date,
         cc.charge_type
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_charges` cc
  union all
  select sc.mpxn,
         sc.contract_id,
         sc.charge_id,
         sc.Charge_From_Date,
         sc.Charge_To_Date,
         sc.charge_type
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.standing_charges` sc
)
select cc.*,
       sp.fuel,
       sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
       sp.chargeMandateStatus,
       ec.startDate as chargeMandateStartDate,
       ec.endDate as chargeMandateEndDate,
       case when ec.contractId is NOT NULL then 1 else 0 END as is_linked_to_active_charge_mandate,
       case
        when cast(charge_from_date as date) between ec.startDate and ec.endDate
         AND cast(charge_to_date as date) between ec.startDate and date_add(ec.endDate, interval 1 DAY) then 1 -- Add a day on to endDate as the charge_to would be midnight 
        WHEN ec.contractId is null then 1 -- Don't fail this if the active charge mandate has already failed
        ELSE 0
       END as is_within_charge_mandate_dates,
       CASE
        WHEN cc.charge_type = 'standing_charge' then 1
        when c.consumptionId is not null then 1
        else 0
       end as has_consumption_for_consumption_charge
from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp
inner join cte_combined_charges cc on sp.mpxn = cc.mpxn
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ec on cc.contract_id = ec.contractId
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_blocks` c on cc.mpxn = c.mpxn
                                                                               AND cast(cc.Charge_From_Date as date) = c.fromDate
where sp.chargeMandateStatus is not null -- Include everything including historic and cancelled
query.932:
with cte_health_check_flags as
(
  select mpxn,
         andromedaMigrationDate,
         fuel,
         min(case when consumptionPeriodContext = 'Pre-Migration' then consumptionCount END) as has_no_pre_migration_consumption_gaps,
         min(case when consumptionPeriodContext = 'Since Migration' then consumptionCount END) as has_no_consumption_gaps_since_migration_up_to_latest_consumption_date,
         case when max(consumptionCount) > 1 then 0 else 1 end as has_no_more_than_1_consumption_per_day,
         case
          when sum(case when consumptionPeriodContext = 'Pre-Migration' then consumptionCount END) <> sum(case when consumptionPeriodContext = 'Pre-Migration' then chargeCount END) then 0
          else 1
         end as has_exactly_1_charge_per_day_of_pre_migration_consumption_block,
         case
          when sum(case when consumptionPeriodContext = 'Since Migration' then consumptionCount END) <> sum(case when consumptionPeriodContext = 'Since Migration' then chargeCount END) then 0
          else 1
         end as has_exactly_1_charge_per_day_of_consumption_block_since_migration,
         MIN(has_charge_consumption_kwh_matching_rac_consumption_kwh) AS has_charge_consumption_kwh_matching_rac_consumption_kwh,
         MIN(has_charge_unit_rate_matching_contract_unit_rate) as has_all_charge_unit_rates_matching_charge_mandate_unit_rate,
         case
          when sum(case when consumptionPeriodContext = 'Missing Consumption Period' then 1 else 0 end) <= 3 then 1
          else 0
         end has_consumption_up_to_at_least_3_days_ago,
         case
          when sum(case when consumptionPeriodContext = 'Missing Consumption Period' then 1 else 0 end) = 0 then 1
          else 0
         end as has_consumption_for_yesterday
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.health_check_expected_consumption_and_charges_detail` 
  group by mpxn,
           andromedaMigrationDate,
           fuel
)
select *,
       CASE
        WHEN (has_no_pre_migration_consumption_gaps = 0
           OR has_no_consumption_gaps_since_migration_up_to_latest_consumption_date = 0
           OR has_no_more_than_1_consumption_per_day = 0
           OR has_exactly_1_charge_per_day_of_pre_migration_consumption_block = 0
           OR has_exactly_1_charge_per_day_of_consumption_block_since_migration = 0
           OR has_charge_consumption_kwh_matching_rac_consumption_kwh = 0
           OR has_all_charge_unit_rates_matching_charge_mandate_unit_rate = 0)
         THEN 'Errors Found'
         WHEN (has_consumption_up_to_at_least_3_days_ago = 0)
         THEN 'Unhealthy'
         WHEN (has_consumption_for_yesterday = 0)
         THEN 'Warning'
         ELSE 'Healthy'
        END as overallConsumptionAndChargeHealth
from cte_health_check_flags
order by andromedaMigrationDate desc
query.933:
-- Expected Consumption by Day Business Logic
with cte_contract_and_consumption_context_dates as (
  SELECT ec.contractId,
         ec.mpxn,
         ec.fuel,
         ec.currentUnitRate as unitRate, -- This will stop working once we do variable price changes.  Will need to change the grain
         ec.startDate as chargeMandateStartDate,
         ec.latestCreatedEventTime as chargeMandateCreatedTime,
         sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
         max(cast(c.toDateTime as date)) as latestConsumptionToDate,
         case when ec.endDate < CURRENT_DATE() then ec.endDate else date_add(current_Date(), interval -1 DAY) end as expectingConsumptionToDate -- Last day of consumption would be yesterday or the day before end date
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ec
  left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp on ec.mpxn = sp.mpxn
  LEFT join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_blocks` c on ec.mpxn = c.mpxn
  group by ec.contractId,
           ec.mpxn,
           ec.fuel,
           ec.currentUnitRate,
           ec.startDate,
           ec.latestCreatedEventTime,
           sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
           case when ec.endDate < CURRENT_DATE() then ec.endDate else date_add(current_Date(), interval -1 DAY) end
),

cte_expected_consumption_dates as (
  select ccc.contractId,
         ccc.mpxn,
         ccc.fuel,
         ccc.unitRate,
         ccc.andromedaMigrationDate,
         ccc.chargeMandateCreatedTime,
         d.Calendar_Date as expectedConsumptionDate,
         case when d.Calendar_Date between ccc.chargeMandateStartDate and date_add(ccc.andromedaMigrationDate, interval -1 DAY) then 'Pre-Migration'
              WHEN d.Calendar_Date between ccc.andromedaMigrationDate and date_add(latestConsumptionToDate, interval -1 DAY) then 'Since Migration'
              when d.Calendar_Date >= latestConsumptionToDate then 'Missing Consumption Period'
         END as consumptionPeriodContext
  from cte_contract_and_consumption_context_dates ccc
  inner join `data-engineering-prod.raw_mis.Reference_dim_Date` d on d.Calendar_Date between chargeMandateStartDate and expectingConsumptionToDate
                                                                 and d.Calendar_Date < current_date()
                                                                 and d.Calendar_Date >= '2018-03-01'
),

cte_expected_consumption_check_data as (
  select ecd.contractId,
         ecd.mpxn,
         ecd.fuel,
         ecd.unitRate,
         ecd.andromedaMigrationDate,
         ecd.chargeMandateCreatedTime,
         ecd.expectedConsumptionDate,
         ecd.consumptionPeriodContext,
         sum(IF(IF(LENGTH(cc.mpxn) = 13, cc.tiers, NULL) is not null, 1, 0)) as consumptionCount_E, 
         sum(IF(IF(LENGTH(cc.mpxn) = 10, cc.consumption, NULL) is not null, 1, 0)) as consumptionCount_G, 
         --min(consumptionId) as consumptionId, -- Field no longer exists
         sum(cc.consumption) as consumptionKwh
  from cte_expected_consumption_dates ecd
  left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_blocks` cc on ecd.mpxn = cc.mpxn
                                                                         AND ecd.expectedConsumptionDate between cc.fromDate and date_add(cc.toDate, interval -1 DAY)
  group by ecd.contractId,
           ecd.mpxn,
           ecd.fuel,
           ecd.unitRate,
           ecd.andromedaMigrationDate,
           ecd.chargeMandateCreatedTime,
           ecd.expectedConsumptionDate,
           ecd.consumptionPeriodContext
)

select ecc.contractId,
       ecc.mpxn,
       ecc.fuel,
       ecc.unitRate as chargeMandateUnitRate,
       ecc.andromedaMigrationDate,
       ecc.expectedConsumptionDate,
       ecc.consumptionPeriodContext,
       ecc.consumptionCount_E + ecc.consumptionCount_G as consumptionCount, 
       --ecc.consumptionId, -- Field no longer exists
       ecc.consumptionKwh,
       min(cc.charge_id) as chargeId,
       sum(case when cc.charge_id is not null then 1 else 0 end) as chargeCount,
       sum(cc.consumption) as chargeConsumptionKwh,
       CASE WHEN min(charge_id) IS NOT NULL and ecc.consumptionKwh <> sum(cc.consumption) THEN 0 ELSE 1 end as has_charge_consumption_kwh_matching_rac_consumption_kwh, -- only fail this one if there are charges
       case when min(cc.unit_rate) <> ecc.unitRate then 0 else 1 end as has_charge_unit_rate_matching_contract_unit_rate,
       case
        when ecc.expectedConsumptionDate >= ecc.AndromedaMigrationDate and min(cc.charge_first_created_time) is null
        then 9999
        when ecc.expectedConsumptionDate > cast(ecc.chargeMandateCreatedTime as date)
        THEN datetime_diff(CAST(min(cc.charge_first_created_time) as DATETIME), cast(date_add(ecc.expectedConsumptionDate, interval 1 DAY) as DATETIME), MINUTE)
       END as totalMinutesToProduceCharge
from cte_expected_consumption_check_data ecc
LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_charges` cc on ecc.mpxn = cc.mpxn
                                                                               AND ecc.expectedConsumptionDate BETWEEN cast(Charge_From_Date as date) and DATE_ADD(cast(Charge_To_Date as date), INTERVAL -1 DAY)
group by ecc.contractId,
         ecc.mpxn,
         ecc.fuel,
         ecc.unitRate,
         ecc.andromedaMigrationDate,
         ecc.chargeMandateCreatedTime,
         ecc.expectedConsumptionDate,
         ecc.consumptionPeriodContext,
         ecc.consumptionCount_E + ecc.consumptionCount_G, 
         --ecc.consumptionId, -- Field no longer exists
         ecc.consumptionKwh
query.935:
with cte_health_check_flags as
(
  select mpxn,
         andromedaMigrationDate,
         fuel,
         min(case when chargePeriodContext = 'Pre-Migration' then chargeCount END) as has_no_pre_migration_charge_gaps,
         min(case when chargePeriodContext = 'Since Migration' then chargeCount END) as has_no_charge_gaps_since_migration_up_to_latest_standing_charge_date,
         case when max(chargeCount) > 1 then 0 else 1 end as has_no_more_than_1_charge_per_day,
         MIN(has_standing_charge_amount_matching_contract_standing_charge_rates) as has_all_standing_charge_amounts_matching_contract_standing_charge_rates,
         case
          when sum(case when chargePeriodContext = 'Missing Consumption Period' then 1 else 0 end) = 0 then 1
          else 0
         end as has_standing_charge_for_yesterday
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.health_check_expected_standing_charges_detail` 
  group by mpxn,
           andromedaMigrationDate,
           fuel
)
select *,
       CASE
        WHEN (has_no_pre_migration_charge_gaps = 0
           OR has_no_charge_gaps_since_migration_up_to_latest_standing_charge_date = 0
           OR has_no_more_than_1_charge_per_day = 0
           OR has_all_standing_charge_amounts_matching_contract_standing_charge_rates = 0)
         THEN 'Errors Found'
         WHEN (has_standing_charge_for_yesterday = 0)
         THEN 'Unhealthy'
         ELSE 'Healthy'
        END as overallStandingChargeHealth
from cte_health_check_flags
query.936:
with cte_contract_and_charge_context_dates as
(
  SELECT ec.contractId,
         ec.mpxn,
         ec.fuel,
         ec.currentStandingRate as standingRate,  -- Will need a different approach once we get a VPC
         ec.startDate as chargeMandateStartDate,
         ec.latestCreatedEventTime as chargeMandateCreatedTime,
         sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
         max(cast(sc.charge_date as date)) as latestStandingChargeDate,
         case when ec.endDate < CURRENT_DATE() then ec.endDate else DATE_ADD(current_Date(), INTERVAL -1 DAY) end as expectingChargesToDate
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ec
  left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp on ec.mpxn = sp.mpxn
  LEFT join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.standing_charges` sc on ec.contractId = sc.contract_id
  group by ec.contractId,
           ec.mpxn,
           ec.fuel,
           ec.currentStandingRate,
           ec.startDate,
           ec.latestCreatedEventTime,
           sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
           case when ec.endDate < CURRENT_DATE() then ec.endDate else DATE_ADD(current_Date(), INTERVAL -1 DAY) end
),
cte_expected_charge_dates as
(
  select ccc.contractId,
         ccc.mpxn,
         ccc.fuel,
         ccc.standingRate,
         ccc.chargeMandateStartDate,
         ccc.chargeMandateCreatedTime,
         ccc.andromedaMigrationDate,
         d.Calendar_Date as expectedChargeDate,
         case
          when d.Calendar_Date between ccc.chargeMandateStartDate and date_add(ccc.andromedaMigrationDate, INTERVAL -1 DAY) then 'Pre-Migration'
          WHEN d.Calendar_Date between ccc.andromedaMigrationDate and latestStandingChargeDate then 'Since Migration'
          when d.Calendar_Date > latestStandingChargeDate then 'Missing Charge Period'
         END as chargePeriodContext
  from cte_contract_and_charge_context_dates ccc
  inner join `data-engineering-prod.raw_mis.Reference_dim_Date` d on d.Calendar_Date between chargeMandateStartDate and expectingChargesToDate
                                                                 and d.Calendar_Date <= DATE_ADD(current_Date(), INTERVAL -1 DAY)
)
select ecd.contractId,
       ecd.mpxn,
       ecd.fuel,
       ecd.standingRate,
       ecd.andromedaMigrationDate,
       ecd.expectedChargeDate,
       ecd.chargePeriodContext,
       min(sc.charge_id) as chargeId,
       sum(case when sc.charge_id is not null then 1 else 0 end) as chargeCount,
       MIN(sc.charge_amount),
       case when min(sc.charge_amount) <> ecd.standingRate then 0 else 1 end as has_standing_charge_amount_matching_contract_standing_charge_rates,
       case
        when ecd.expectedChargeDate > cast(ecd.chargeMandateCreatedTime as date)
        THEN datetime_diff(coalesce(CAST(min(sc.charge_first_created_time) as DATETIME), current_Datetime()), cast(date_add(ecd.expectedChargeDate, interval 1 DAY) as DATETIME), MINUTE)
       END as totalMinutesToProduceCharge
from cte_expected_charge_dates ecd
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.standing_charges` sc on ecd.contractId = sc.contract_id
                                                                            AND ecd.expectedChargeDate = sc.charge_date
group by ecd.contractId,
         ecd.mpxn,
         ecd.fuel,
         ecd.standingRate,
         ecd.chargeMandateCreatedTime,
         ecd.andromedaMigrationDate,
         ecd.expectedChargeDate,
         ecd.chargePeriodContext
query.938:
with cte_health_check_flags as
(
  select mpxn,
         fuel,
         andromedaMigrationDate,
         min(has_loss_notification_in_andromeda) as has_loss_notification_in_andromeda,
         min(has_happy_path_loss_status) as has_happy_path_loss_status,
         min(has_no_charge_mandate_after_confirmed_loss_date) as has_no_charge_mandate_after_confirmed_loss_date,
         min(has_had_loss_confirmed_for_completed_loss) as has_had_loss_confirmed_for_completed_loss,
         min(has_consumption_up_to_loss_date) as has_consumption_up_to_loss_date
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.health_check_loss_journeys_detail`
  group by mpxn,
           fuel,
           andromedaMigrationDate
)
select *,
       case
        WHEN (has_loss_notification_in_andromeda = 0
           OR has_no_charge_mandate_after_confirmed_loss_date = 0)
        THEN 'Errors Found'          
        when (has_happy_path_loss_status = 0
           OR has_had_loss_confirmed_for_completed_loss = 0
           OR has_consumption_up_to_loss_date = 0)
        THEN 'Unhealthy'
        ELSE 'Healthy'
       END as overallLossJourneyHealth
from cte_health_check_flags
query.939:
select l.mpxn,
       l.lossNotificationReceivedDate as lossNotificationReceivedOrDetectedDate,
       sp.fuel,
       sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
       l.lossJourneyStatus,
       l.lossDate,
       l.lossConfirmationReceivedDate,
       l.lossCompletionReceivedDate,
       1 as has_loss_notification_in_andromeda,
       case
        when lossJourneyStatus = 'Loss notification received - Past Expected Loss Date' then 0
        else 1
       end as has_happy_path_loss_status,
       case
        when cm.contractId is not null and l.lossJourneyStatus in ('Loss confirmed', 'Loss completed') then 0
        else 1
       end as has_no_charge_mandate_after_confirmed_loss_date,
       case
        when l.lossJourneyStatus = 'Loss completed' and l.lossConfirmationReceivedDate is null then 0
        else 1
       end as has_had_loss_confirmed_for_completed_loss,
       case
        when current_date() > l.lossDate and cb.mpxn is null then 0
        ELSE 1
       END as has_consumption_up_to_loss_date
from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys` l
inner join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp on l.mpxn = sp.mpxn
-- Join to any charge mandates that would be active after the loss date
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` cm on l.mpxn = cm.mpxn
                                                       and date_add(l.lossDate, interval 1 DAY) between cm.startDate and cm.endDate
-- Join to consumption finishing at midnight on day before they start with new supplier, to check we've got consumption up to the last date we'd expect it for
-- (see https://trello.com/c/E6MzXjZS/238-loss-journey-analysis for more detail on this scenario)
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_blocks` cb on l.mpxn = cb.mpxn
                                                          and l.lossDate = cb.toDate
where sp.chargeMandateStatus in ('Has Current Charge Mandate', 'Has Historic Charge Mandate')
  and l.lossNotificationReceivedDate >= sp.andromedaMigrationDate
-- Bolt on any loss notifications we can find externally but not in Andromeda
union all
select el.mpxn,
       cast(detectedDatetime as date) as lossNotificationReceivedOrDetectedDate,
       sp.fuel,
       sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
       'Missing from Andromeda' as lossJourneyStatus,
       null as lossDate,
       null as lossConfirmationReceivedDate,
       null as lossCompletionReceivedDate,
       0 as has_loss_notification_in_andromeda,
       1 as has_happy_path_loss_status,
       1 as has_no_charge_mandate_after_confirmed_loss_date,
       1 as has_had_loss_confirmed_for_completed_loss,
       1 as has_consumption_up_to_loss_date
from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.external_reconciliation_loss_notifications` el
inner join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp on el.mpxn = sp.mpxn
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys` l on el.mpxn = l.mpxn
                                                    and l.lossNotificationReceivedDate >= sp.andromedaMigrationDate
where sp.chargeMandateStatus in ('Has Current Charge Mandate', 'Has Historic Charge Mandate')
  and cast(detectedDatetime as date) >= sp.andromedaMigrationDate
  and l.mpxn is null
query.942:
with cte_supply_point_dedupe as
(
  select mpxn,
         'electricity' as fuel,
         sh.supplyStatusDate,
         sh.supplyStatus,
         sh.expectedLossDate,
         sh.confirmedLossDate,
         RANK() over (partition by mpxn order by kafkaData.topic desc, metadata.createdAt desc, kafkaData.insertTime desc) as supply_point_rank
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPoint__no_dedupe` e,
  unnest(e.supplyHistory) sh
  union all
  select mpxn,
         'gas' as fuel,
         sh.supplyStatusDate,
         sh.supplyStatus,
         sh.expectedLossDate,
         sh.confirmedLossDate,
         RANK() over (partition by mpxn order by kafkaData.topic desc, metadata.createdAt desc, kafkaData.insertTime desc) as supply_point_rank
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.spam_gasSupplyPoint__no_dedupe` g,
  unnest(g.supplyHistory) sh
),
cte_supply_history_dedupe as
(
  select sp.mpxn,
         sp.fuel,
         sp.supplyStatusDate,
         sp.supplyStatus,
         sp.expectedLossDate,
         sp.confirmedLossDate,
         row_number() over (partition by sp.mpxn, sp.supplyStatusDate, sp.supplyStatus order by sp.confirmedLossDate asc, sp.expectedLossDate asc) as supply_history_rownum      
  from cte_supply_point_dedupe sp
  where supply_point_rank = 1
),
cte_loss_notifications as
(
  select sh.mpxn,
         sh.fuel,
         sh.supplyStatusDate as lossNotificationReceivedDate,
         sh.supplyStatus,
         sh.expectedLossDate,
         coalesce(lead(sh.supplyStatusDate) over (partition by sh.mpxn, sh.supplyStatus order by sh.supplyStatusDate), DATE('2999-01-01')) as nextLossNotificationReceivedDate
  from cte_supply_history_dedupe sh
  where supplyStatus = 'Loss notification received'
    and supply_history_rownum = 1
),
cte_contracts as
(
  select ctr.*
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ctr
  left join `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_migration_secure.orion_migration_reverse_success_v1` rev on ctr.serviceAccountId = rev.accountId
  where rev.accountId is null
)
select loss_not.mpxn,
       ctr.serviceAccountId,
       ctr.contractId,
       loss_not.fuel,
       ms.Migrated_Date as orionMigrationDate,
       loss_not.lossNotificationReceivedDate,
       coalesce(case
                 when MAX(loss_conf_comp_canc.supplyStatus) in ('Loss withdrawal confirmed', 'Loss objection upheld')
                 THEN MAX(loss_conf_comp_canc.supplyStatus) -- Use this to favour the cancellation statuses
                 ELSE min(loss_conf_comp_canc.supplyStatus) -- Use this to favour completed over confirmed
                END,
                case when current_date() > loss_not.expectedLossDate then concat(loss_not.supplyStatus, ' - Past Expected Loss Date') ELSE loss_not.supplyStatus end) as lossJourneyStatus,
       coalesce(min(loss_conf_comp_canc.confirmedLossDate), loss_not.expectedLossDate) as lossDate,
       min(case when loss_conf_comp_canc.supplyStatus = 'Loss confirmed' then supplyStatusDate end) as lossConfirmationReceivedDate,
       min(case when loss_conf_comp_canc.supplyStatus = 'Loss completed' then supplyStatusDate end) as lossCompletionReceivedDate,
       min(case when loss_conf_comp_canc.supplyStatus in ('Loss withdrawal confirmed', 'Loss objection upheld') then supplyStatusDate end) as lossCancellationReceivedDate
from cte_loss_notifications loss_not
left join cte_supply_history_dedupe loss_conf_comp_canc on loss_not.mpxn = loss_conf_comp_canc.mpxn
                                                  and loss_conf_comp_canc.supplyStatus in ('Loss confirmed', 'Loss completed', 'Loss withdrawal confirmed', 'Loss objection upheld')
                                                  and loss_conf_comp_canc.supply_history_rownum = 1
                                                  and loss_conf_comp_canc.supplyStatusDate between loss_not.lossNotificationReceivedDate
                                                                                          and loss_not.nextLossNotificationReceivedDate
LEFT join cte_contracts ctr on loss_not.mpxn = ctr.mpxn
                            and case
                                 when coalesce(loss_conf_comp_canc.confirmedLossDate, loss_not.expectedLossDate) < loss_not.lossNotificationReceivedDate
                                 then coalesce(loss_conf_comp_canc.confirmedLossDate, loss_not.expectedLossDate) 
                                 else loss_not.lossNotificationReceivedDate
                                end between ctr.startDate and coalesce(ctr.endDate, '2999-01-01')
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration.orion_migration_success` ms on ctr.serviceAccountId = ms.Account_No
group by loss_not.mpxn,
         ctr.serviceAccountId,
         ctr.contractId,
         loss_not.fuel,
         ms.Migrated_Date,
         loss_not.lossNotificationReceivedDate,
         loss_not.supplyStatus,
         loss_not.expectedLossDate
query.948:
with cte_work_items as
(
  select wi.workItemId,
         wi.status,
         wi.statusChangeDateTime,
         wi.statusNote,
         wi.statusDueDate,
         wi.statusChangeAuthor,
         split(wi.entityUri, '/') as key_array,
         row_number() over (partition by wi.entityUri order by wi.metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num -- Use descending order as the correction read more likely to be through O4O
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_oot_secure.oot_work_item` wi
  where wi.entityUri like 'manual-reads%'
),
cte_reads_union as
(
  select event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.msn,
         event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime,
         event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.readingType,
         event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.tiers,
         null as gasReadingValue,
         row_number() over (partition by event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.msn, event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime order by event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_manual_read_submitted_v2`
  where event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent is not null
  union all
  select event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.msn,
         event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime,
         event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.readingType,
         event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.tiers, -- Using this to get the right shape even though we know its null
         event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.readingValue as gasReadingValue,
         row_number() over (partition by event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.msn, event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime order by event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent.metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_manual_read_submitted_v2`
  where event.GasVolumeManualReadingEvent is not null
)
select wi.key_array[offset(2)] as mpxn, replace(wi.key_array[offset(3)], '%20', ' ') as msn, cast(replace( wi.key_array[offset(4)], '%3A', ':') as timestamp) as readingDateTime,
       mr.readingType, mr.tiers, mr.gasReadingValue, wi.* except(key_array)
from cte_work_items wi
left join cte_reads_union mr on mr.msn = replace(wi.key_array[offset(3)], '%20', ' ')
                            and mr.readingDateTime = cast(replace(wi.key_array[offset(4)], '%3A', ':') as timestamp)
                            and mr.row_num = wi.row_num
query.949:
-- non-deduped S1 reads to improve performance
with cte_rac_msd_received__no_dedupe as
(
  select metadata.eventId,
         metadata.createdAt,
         metadata.traceToken,
         * except(metadata), -- Different order of fields in metadata struct so we have to specify explicitly
         kafkaData.topic as topic_cleansed -- Need to deal with nulls in v3
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_msd_received_v6` v6
  union all
  select metadata.eventId,
         metadata.createdAt,
         metadata.traceToken,
         * except(metadata) ,
         kafkaData.topic as topic_cleansed
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_msd_received_v5` v5
  union all
  select metadata.eventId,
         metadata.createdAt,
         metadata.traceToken,
         * except(metadata),
         coalesce(kafkaData.topic, 'rac_msd_received_v3') as topic_cleansed
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_msd_received_v3` v3
),

cte_union AS(
-- S1
SELECT msd.snapshotData.device.serialNumber as msn,
       lower(msd.snapshotData.device.supplyType) as fuel,
       --msd.snapshotData.device.servicePointNumber as mpxn,
       msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotTime as readingDatetime,
       DATE(msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotTime, "Europe/London") as readingDate,
       'S1 (SFE MSD)' as readingSource,
       cast(msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotCause as string) as readingType,
       snapshotData.device.cumulativeRegisters.volume as totalVolume,
       MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 0 AND lower(msd.snapshotData.device.supplyType) = 'electricity' THEN r.cumulative END) AS reg0Kwh,
       MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 1 AND lower(msd.snapshotData.device.supplyType) = 'electricity' THEN r.cumulative END) AS reg1Kwh,
       MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 2 AND lower(msd.snapshotData.device.supplyType) = 'electricity' THEN r.cumulative END) AS reg2Kwh,
       case when lower(msd.snapshotData.device.supplyType) = 'electricity' then msd.snapshotData.device.cumulativeRegisters.activeImport end as totalKwh,
       msd.createdAt
from cte_rac_msd_received__no_dedupe msd
inner join unnest (snapshotData.device.importRateRegisters.value) as r
group by msd.snapshotData.device.serialNumber,
         msd.snapshotData.device.supplyType,

with cte_core_accounts as
        (
          SELECT
              A.Account_No
            FROM
            `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Account` A
              INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Consumer` C
                ON    A.Account_No = C.Account_No
                AND C.Lifecycle_Category = 'Live (Excluding Loss)'
              LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_ops_workstreams.Polarstern_tbl_Historic_Status` PS 
                ON C.Consumer_No = PS.Consumer_No
                AND PS.Is_Latest_Polarstern_Status = TRUE
            WHERE
              A.Billing_System = 'GENTRACK'
              AND    A.Payment_Method_Category = 'PAYM'                                                                    -- PAYM
              AND A.Retailer_Code = 'OVO'                                                                                -- OVO Customer
              AND A.Is_ET_Gain = FALSE                                                                                    -- Not an ET
            GROUP BY A.Account_No
            HAVING 
              SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(c.Meter_Type_Code,1,2) = 'S2'  THEN 1 WHEN C.Meter_Type_Category = 'Smart' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = COUNT(*)        -- All live consumers are SMART     HOB 31/5/19 - now including SMETS2    AND SUM(CASE WHEN ISNULL(C.Billing_Class_Code, 'Nix zu sehen hier') = 'COM' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END) = COUNT(*)                           -- No live consumers are COMMERCIAL
            AND SUM(CASE WHEN coalesce(C.Tax_Class_Code, 'Nix zu sehen hier') IN ('COMMERCIAL', 'COMEXEMPT') THEN 0 ELSE 1 END) = COUNT(*)        -- No live consumers are COMMERCIAL
            AND SUM(CASE WHEN C.Profile_Class IN ('01', '02', 'G') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = COUNT(*)                                                -- No live consumers are COMMERCIAL
            AND SUM(CASE WHEN C.Payment_Method_Category = 'PAYM' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = COUNT(*)                                                     -- All live consumers are PAYM, too
            AND SUM(CASE WHEN PS.Has_Meter_and_Tariff_Mismatch = TRUE THEN 0 ELSE 1 END) = COUNT(*)                                                -- No live consumers are Polarstern/nretsraloP
        ),
        cte_core_accounts_agg as
        (
          select count(1) as core_accounts
          from cte_core_accounts
        ),
        cte_latest_live_accounts as
        (
          select *,
                row_number() over (order by Snapshot_Date desc) as row_num
          from `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.migrated_accounts_counts_extract`
        )
        select
        l.Still_Live_Count as Migrated,
        ca.core_accounts as ToGo,
        round(l.Still_Live_Count / (l.Still_Live_Count + ca.core_accounts) * 100, 1) as pct_accounts_migrated,
              current_date() as last_updated_date
        from cte_latest_live_accounts l
        cross join cte_core_accounts_agg ca
        where l.row_num = 1

WITH mappings AS (
  SELECT
     MPXN
    ,MSN
    ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
    ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,tier
    ,createdAt
  FROM (
    SELECT
       MPXN 
      ,inst.MSN
      ,inst.startDate AS meterMappingEffectiveFrom
      ,his.startDate AS registerConfigEffectiveFrom
      ,reg.clockingTimeId
      ,reg.timePatternRegime
      ,reg.tier
      ,metadata.createdAt
      -- use rank to find the latest configuration and meter instalation dates
      ,RANK() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN  ORDER BY inst.startDate DESC) AS latestMeterMapping
      ,RANK() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN  ORDER BY his.startDate DESC) AS latestConfigMapping
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v1`
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(installationHistory) AS inst
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(inst.meterRegisterHistory) his
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(his.meterRegisters) reg
    ) lt
  WHERE 
    latestMeterMapping = 1 
    AND latestConfigMapping = 1
    AND tier IS NOT NULL
), ranked_mappings AS (
  SELECT
     MPXN
    ,MSN
    ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
    ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,tier
    -- single entry per MPXN, tier
    ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN, tier ORDER BY createdAt DESC) rowNumMpxn
    -- single entry per MSN, tier
    ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MSN, tier ORDER BY createdAt DESC) rowNumMsn
  FROM
    mappings
), deduped_ranked AS (
  SELECT
     MPXN
    ,MSN
    ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
    ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,tier
  FROM
    ranked_mappings
  WHERE 
    rowNumMpxn = 1
    AND rowNumMsn = 1
), two_rate_list AS (
  -- get multi rate MPANs only. Choose exactly 2 tiers as we will not support more than 2 on OEP
  SELECT
    m.MPXN AS mpan
  FROM
    deduped_ranked AS m
  GROUP BY
    m.MPXN
  HAVING
    COUNT(clockingTimeId) = 2
), two_rate_only AS (
  SELECT
     MPXN
    ,MSN
    ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
    ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,tier  
  FROM
    deduped_ranked dr
  INNER JOIN
    two_rate_list AS t
      ON dr.MPXN = t.mpan
)
SELECT
   MPXN
  ,MSN
  ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
  ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
  ,clockingTimeId
  ,timePatternRegime
  ,tier  
FROM
  two_rate_only

/* =================================================================== */ 
  /* 1) Latest Register-Meter-Supply Mappings for Multi-Rate Projections */ 
  /* =================================================================== */
  -- uses SPAM supply point (NOT history). This topic has a view of the latest valid supply point to
  -- meter to register mappings. It does not have the history. It is this set of mappings which is used in
  -- consumption projections. This is true for the single rate projection process.
  -- This view also ensures that a meter can only be mapped to one supply, going
  -- further than the single rate process.
  --take the lastest view
  
  --Note: As this topic has the latest view of every supply point that has been at OVO,
  --we also find supply points that are not on supply and therefore those are removed 
  --to avoid potential duplicated msn across different mpans (msn refurbished)
  --Note 2: There are 6 ambiguos MSN that are mapped to 2 different MPANs on supply 
  
WITH
--latest view
  cte_latest_mappings AS(
  SELECT 
    MPXN,
    MSN,
    profileClassId,
    supplyStatus.status,
    meterRegisterHistory
  FROM (
    SELECT
      *,
      ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime DESC) AS mpxn_rn
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPoint_v2`)
   WHERE
     mpxn_rn=1
   AND NOT (supplyStatus.status = 'Loss completed' OR supplyStatus.status = 'Loss confirmed')
      )      
--SELECT * FROM cte_latest_mappings WHERE MSN = '15P0151250' --msn is mapped to two mpan, one is loss so the meter got refurbished   
--SELECT * FROM cte_latest_mappings WHERE MSN = '16P0142287' --msn is mapped to two mpan for the same customer, adress, dates, etc. Only 6 cases
      ,
      
  --latest register mapping
  cte_latest_mappings_reg AS(
  SELECT
    MPXN,
    MSN,
    profileClassId,
    status,
    ssc,
    effectiveFromSettlementDateScon AS registerConfigEffectiveFrom,
    meterRegisters
  FROM (
    SELECT
      MPXN,
      MSN,
      profileClassId,
      status,
      regHist.effectiveFromSettlementDateScon,
      regHist.ssc,
      regHist.meterRegisters,
      ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY regHist.effectiveFromSettlementDateScon DESC) AS rn2
    FROM
      cte_latest_mappings
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST (meterRegisterHistory) AS regHist)
  WHERE
    rn2=1 
    ),
    
  --remove cases where the entire row is duplicated
  cte_latest_mappings_reg_dedup AS(
  SELECT
    MPXN,
    MSN,
    profileClassId,
    status,
    ssc,
    registerConfigEffectiveFrom,
    reg.tier,
    reg.clockingTimeId,
    reg.switchedLoadIndicator
  FROM
    cte_latest_mappings_reg
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST (meterRegisters) AS reg
  GROUP BY
    MPXN,
    MSN,
    profileClassId,
    status,
    ssc,
    registerConfigEffectiveFrom,
    reg.tier,
    reg.clockingTimeId,
    reg.switchedLoadIndicator 
    ),
    
  --remove when switchedLoadIndicator is null
  cte_cte_latest_mappings_reg_dedup_clean AS(
  SELECT
    MPXN,
    MSN,
    profileClassId,
    status,
    ssc,
    registerConfigEffectiveFrom,
    tier,
    clockingTimeId
  FROM
    cte_latest_mappings_reg_dedup
  WHERE
    switchedLoadIndicator IS NOT NULL 
    ),

--Select multi-rate mpans. The filters used where discussed with SPAM team as the most robust way to get multi-rate supplypoints only     
  cte_mpan_two_rate_only AS(
  SELECT
    MPXN
  FROM
    cte_cte_latest_mappings_reg_dedup_clean
  GROUP BY
    MPXN,
    MSN,
    profileClassId,
    ssc
  HAVING 
  --profileClassId = '02'
  --AND
  ssc != '0393'
  AND COUNT(tier) = 2
  AND COUNT(DISTINCT tier) = 2
  AND COUNT(clockingTimeId) = 2 
  AND COUNT(DISTINCT clockingTimeId) = 2 
),

cte_multi_rate AS(
  SELECT
    a.MPXN,
    a.MSN,
    a.profileClassId,
    a.status,
    a.ssc,
    a.registerConfigEffectiveFrom,
    a.tier,
    a.clockingTimeId
  FROM cte_cte_latest_mappings_reg_dedup_clean a
  INNER JOIN cte_mpan_two_rate_only b
  ON a.MPXN = b.MPXN
 )

  
  
SELECT
  MPXN,
  MSN,
  --registerConfigEffectiveFrom,
  clockingTimeId,
  tier
FROM
  cte_multi_rate
ORDER BY MPXN

/* =================================================================== */ 
  /* 1) Latest Register-Meter-Supply Mappings for Multi-Rate Projections */ 
  /* =================================================================== */
  
--Select the list of latest MPXN-MSN mapping for electricity and multi rate only.


WITH cte_latest_mappings AS(
SELECT MPXN, installationHistory
FROM(SELECT metadata.createdAt, MPXN, installationHistory
            , ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rn 
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`)
WHERE rn=1
)
,

--latest msn mapping
cte_latest_mappings_msn AS(
    SELECT MPXN, MSN, StartDate AS meterMappingEffectiveFrom, meterRegisterHistory
    FROM (
          SELECT MPXN, inst.MSN, inst.startDate, inst.meterRegisterHistory
                , ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY inst.startDate DESC) AS rn2 
          FROM cte_latest_mappings
          INNER JOIN UNNEST (installationHistory) AS inst)
    WHERE rn2=1
),

--latest register mapping
cte_latest_mappings_msn_reg AS(
    SELECT MPXN, MSN, meterMappingEffectiveFrom, startDate AS registerConfigEffectiveFrom, meterRegisters
    FROM (
          SELECT MPXN, MSN, meterMappingEffectiveFrom, regHist.startDate, regHist.meterRegisters
                , ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN ORDER BY regHist.startDate DESC) AS rn3 
          FROM cte_latest_mappings_msn
          INNER JOIN UNNEST (meterRegisterHistory) AS regHist)
    WHERE rn3=1
),

--remove cases where the entire row is duplicated
cte_latest_mappings_msn_reg_dedup AS(
    SELECT MPXN, MSN, meterMappingEffectiveFrom, registerConfigEffectiveFrom, reg.tier, reg.clockingTimeId, reg.timePatternRegime, reg.switchedLoadIndicator, reg.timeOfUseLabel
    FROM cte_latest_mappings_msn_reg
    INNER JOIN UNNEST (meterRegisters) AS reg
    GROUP BY MPXN, MSN, meterMappingEffectiveFrom, registerConfigEffectiveFrom, reg.tier, reg.clockingTimeId, reg.timePatternRegime, reg.switchedLoadIndicator, reg.timeOfUseLabel
),

--remove when switchedLoadIndicator is null (This step might be not neccesary for multi-rate, I used in the past to clean some edge cases in single rate where both tier and clockingtimeid are null)
cte_latest_mappings_msn_reg_dedup_clean AS(
    SELECT MPXN, MSN, meterMappingEffectiveFrom, registerConfigEffectiveFrom, tier, clockingTimeId, timePatternRegime, timeOfUseLabel, switchedLoadIndicator
    FROM cte_latest_mappings_msn_reg_dedup
    --WHERE switchedLoadIndicator IS NOT NULL
)
--SELECT * FROM cte_latest_mappings_msn_reg_dedup_clean
,

--select multi rate meters 
cte_multi_rate AS(
    SELECT a.MPXN, a.MSN, a.meterMappingEffectiveFrom, a.registerConfigEffectiveFrom, a.tier, a.clockingTimeId, a.timePatternRegime, a.timeOfUseLabel, a.switchedLoadIndicator
    FROM cte_latest_mappings_msn_reg_dedup_clean a
    INNER JOIN (SELECT MPXN FROM cte_latest_mappings_msn_reg_dedup_clean GROUP BY MPXN, MSN HAVING COUNT(clockingTimeId)=2) b
    ON a.MPXN = b.MPXN
    --WHERE clockingTimeId != 1
)

-- --Select multi-rate mpans

-- FROM cte_multi_rate
-- )

SELECT   MPXN,
         MSN,
         clockingTimeId,
         timeOfUseLabel,
        CASE 
          WHEN tier IS NOT NULL THEN tier
          WHEN tier IS NULL AND timeOfUseLabel = 'anytime' THEN 0
          WHEN tier IS NULL AND timeOfUseLabel = 'offpeak' THEN 0
          WHEN tier IS NULL AND timeOfUseLabel = 'peak' THEN 1
        END AS tier
        --,switchedLoadIndicator
FROM cte_multi_rate

/* ============================================================================ */
/* 2) Longest Actual Sub-Year Read Interval for Annualised Advance Calculation  */
/* ============================================================================ */

-- Takes the last 15 months of  available smart readings. Fifteen months is used as it allows for a maximum interval
-- between two readings of a year, with the latter read dated no more than three months earlier than the current
-- date. The interval will always use the latest reading available, paired with the earliest reading no more than
-- a year earlier than this date.

WITH msd AS(
  -- 15 months of MSD history, de-duplicated.
  SELECT
     msn
    ,tier
    ,snapshotTime
    ,reading
  FROM (
    SELECT 
       value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.msn
      ,value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.snapshotTime
      ,reg.tier
      ,reg.reading
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
        PARTITION BY value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.msn, value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.snapshotTime, tier 
        ORDER BY value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.metadata.createdAt DESC) AS createdOrder
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_msd_stripped_v1`
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.registers) AS reg
    WHERE
      DATE(PARTITIONTIME) >= DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL - 15 MONTH) -- one year plus 3 months
      AND DATE(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEventByMsn.snapshotTime) >= DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL - 15 MONTH)
    )
  WHERE
    createdOrder = 1
), to_read AS (
  -- get the latest read date for each msn (all tiers). This will be the 'to' reading date used to calculate the interval consumption
  SELECT
     msn
    ,MAX(snapshotTime) AS maxDate
    ,COUNT(DISTINCT tier) AS tierCount
  FROM
    msd
  GROUP BY
    msn
), tier_counts AS (
  -- reduce the set of reads to include only those dates on which the same number of tiers exist as the to_read
  SELECT
     msd.msn
    ,snapshotTime
    ,COUNT(DISTINCT tier) AS tierCount
  FROM
    msd
  GROUP BY
     msd.msn
    ,snapshotTime
), intervals AS (
  -- calculate the difference between each read date and the latest reading
  SELECT
     to_read.msn
    ,DATE_DIFF(DATE(to_read.maxDate), DATE(msd.snapshotTime), DAY) AS daysOld
    ,to_read.maxDate AS toReadDate
    ,msd.snapshotTime
    --,msd.tier
  FROM
    msd
  INNER JOIN 
    to_read
      ON msd.msn = to_read.msn
  INNER JOIN
    tier_counts
      ON  tier_counts.msn = msd.msn
      AND tier_counts.tierCount = to_read.tierCount
      AND tier_counts.snapshotTime = msd.snapshotTime
), dates AS (
  -- select the maximum interval (up to a year)
  SELECT
     msn
    ,toReadDate
    ,MIN(snapshotTime) AS fromReadDate
    ,DATE_DIFF(DATE(toReadDate), DATE(MIN(snapshotTime)), DAY) AS intervalDays
  FROM
    intervals
  WHERE
    daysOld <= 365 -- want the maximum interval less than or equal to a year
  GROUP BY
     msn
    ,toReadDate  
), joined AS (
  -- join the selected dates back to the reading data to attach values
  SELECT
     dates.msn
    ,msd1.tier
    ,dates.fromReadDate
    ,msd1.reading AS fromReading
    ,dates.toReadDate
    ,msd2.reading AS toReading
    ,dates.intervalDays
    ,ROUND(msd2.reading - msd1.reading, 2) AS intervalConsumption
  FROM
    dates
  INNER JOIN
    msd AS msd1
      ON  msd1.msn = dates.msn
      AND msd1.snapshotTime = dates.fromReadDate
  INNER JOIN
    msd AS msd2
      ON  msd2.msn = dates.msn
      AND msd2.tier = msd1.tier
      AND msd2.snapshotTime = dates.toReadDate
)
SELECT
   msn
  ,tier
  ,fromReadDate
  ,fromReading
  ,toReadDate
  ,toReading
  ,intervalDays
  ,intervalConsumption
FROM
 joined

WITH 

/* RAW CONSUMPTION DATA */
-- fetch gas and electricity consumption data from latest versions
electricity_consumption AS (
  SELECT metadata.createdAt,
         mpan,
         msn,
         fromReading.readingDateTime AS fromDateTime,
         toReading.readingDateTime AS toDateTime,
         cons_reg.tier,
         cons_reg.clockingTimeId,
         from_reg.reading AS fromMeterReading,
         to_reg.reading AS toMeterReading,
         cons_reg.energy AS consumption,                   
         fromReading.readingType AS fromReadingType,

         --kafkaData.insertTime AS insertTime
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v5` r
  INNER JOIN UNNEST (consumption.registers) AS cons_reg
  INNER JOIN UNNEST (fromReading.registers) AS from_reg ON cons_reg.tier=from_reg.tier
  INNER JOIN UNNEST (toReading.registers) AS to_reg ON cons_reg.tier=to_reg.tier

  UNION ALL

  SELECT metadata.createdAt, 
         mpan,
         msn, 
         fromDateTime, 
         toDateTime, 
         t.tier,
         t.clockingTimeId,
         t.fromMeterReading,
         t.toMeterReading,
         t.consumption,

		FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v4`
    INNER JOIN UNNEST(tiers) t
    
	  UNION ALL

           t.tier,
           t.clockingTimeId,

		FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_historic_electricity_consumption`

/* CLEAN CONSUMPTION DATA */
-- de-duplicating on mpxn, msn, tier, fromDate, toDate. Note that this doesn't prevent

/* ====================================================================== */
/* 3) Cummulative Demand Coefficients for Annualised Advance Calculation  */
/* ====================================================================== */

-- This view simply provides the demand coefficients used in the single rate personal projections
-- calculation. These are profile class one coefficients, and should be replaced by more appropriate
-- profile class two coefficients split by switched load indicator. They do, however, provide a 
-- reasonable view of seasonality.

SELECT 
   date
  ,ROUND(SUM(usageCoefficient) OVER(ORDER BY date),5) AS cumulativeUsageCoefficient
FROM 
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.electricity_coefficients_unrestricted_domestic`
ORDER BY
  date

/* 4) Latest D0019 EAC By Register  */

-- Locates the latest D0019 EAC for each register (split by Time Pattern Regime ID) 

WITH d19 AS (
  SELECT 
     record.InstructionHeader.meteringSystemId AS mpan
    ,PARSE_DATE('%Y%m%d', eah.effectiveFromSettlementDate) AS effectiveFromDate
    ,CAST(ead.timePatternRegime AS INT64) AS timePatternRegime
    ,CAST(ead.estimatedAnnualConsumption AS FLOAT64) AS estimatedAnnualConsumption 
    -- de-duplicating events
    ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY record.InstructionHeader.meteringSystemId, ead.timePatternRegime, eah.effectiveFromSettlementDate ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS createdOrder
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.flow_D0019001_split_v2` AS zin
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST(record.InstructionHeader.estimatedAnnualConsumptionHeader) AS eah
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST(eah.estimatedAnnualConsumptionDetails) AS ead
), latest AS (
  SELECT
     mpan
    ,effectiveFromDate
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,estimatedAnnualConsumption
    -- latest EACs only for an MPAN
    ,RANK() OVER(PARTITION BY mpan ORDER BY effectiveFromDate DESC) AS effectiveOrder
  FROM
    d19
  WHERE
    createdOrder = 1
  )
SELECT 
   mpan
  ,effectiveFromDate
  ,latest.timePatternRegime
  ,estimatedAnnualConsumption
FROM
  latest
WHERE
  effectiveOrder = 1

WITH mapped AS (

        AND  map.msn = int.msn

/* ========================================================== */
/* 6) Latest EAC Data For Two-Rate Only With Cleaning Applied */
/* ========================================================== */

-- EACs are applied to the registers mapped in view 1), and cleansing assures that EACs are only used
-- in cases where we are able to find an applicable value for both registers, not just one.
-- Update: EAC greater than 25000 are excluded as presumably those are wrong estimates. In those cases the projection will be solely based on the AA

WITH mapped AS (
  -- EACs for the two rate supplies mapped in view 1)
  SELECT
     mpan
    ,effectiveFromDate
    ,map.tier
    ,map.timeOfUseLabel
    ,e.timePatternRegime
    ,estimatedAnnualConsumption
  FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.multi_rate_projections_4_eacs` AS e
  -- join on latest mappings to exclude single rate and mis-mapped TPRs
  INNER JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.multi_rate_projections_1_latest_mappings_v3` AS map
        ON  map.MPXN = e.mpan
        AND map.clockingTimeId = e.timePatternRegime
  -- filter out cases where EAC greater than 25000 as this is pressumably a wrong estimate.       
  WHERE estimatedAnnualConsumption < 25000     
        
), reg_count_check AS (
-- this asserts that the TPR join condition is met for both, not just one, register
  SELECT
     m.mpan
    ,tier
    ,timeOfUseLabel
    ,effectiveFromDate
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,estimatedAnnualConsumption
  FROM
    mapped AS m
  INNER JOIN (
              SELECT mpan 
              FROM mapped 
              GROUP BY mpan 
              HAVING COUNT(timePatternRegime) = 2
              ) ct
  ON m.mpan = ct.MPAN
)
SELECT
   mpan
  ,tier
  ,timeOfUseLabel
  ,effectiveFromDate
  ,timePatternRegime
  ,estimatedAnnualConsumption
FROM
  reg_count_check

/* ========================================================= */
/* 7) Annualised Advances For Two Rate Supplies, By Register */
/* ========================================================= */

-- Demand coefficients (3) are used to establish the proportion of a year of consumption deemed to be used within the 
-- interval period (5). This is used to give a deemed year of consumption for each register

SELECT 
   int.mpan
  ,int.tier
  ,int.clockingTimeId
  ,int.timeOfUseLabel
  ,int.fromReadDate
  ,int.fromReading
  ,c1.cumulativeUsageCoefficient AS fromCoefficient
  ,int.toReadDate
  ,int.toReading
  ,int.intervalConsumption
  ,c2.cumulativeUsageCoefficient AS toCoefficient
  ,ROUND(c2.cumulativeUsageCoefficient - c1.cumulativeUsageCoefficient, 3) AS coefficientAdvance
  ,ROUND(SAFE_DIVIDE(intervalConsumption, (c2.cumulativeUsageCoefficient - c1.cumulativeUsageCoefficient)), 1) AS annualisedAdvance
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.multi_rate_projections_5_cleaned_intervals` AS int
INNER JOIN
  -- get the cumulative coefficient value applicable to the earlier read date from the consumption interval
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.multi_rate_projections_3_coefficients` AS c1
     ON c1.date = DATE(int.fromReadDate)
INNER JOIN
  -- get the cumulative coefficient value applicable to the later read date from the consumption interval
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.multi_rate_projections_3_coefficients` AS c2
     ON c2.DATE = DATE(int.toReadDate)
WHERE 
  DATE_DIFF(DATE(int.toReadDate), DATE(int.fromReadDate), DAY) >= 14 -- two week advance minimum used... this could be varied
  -- and mpan in ('1100003670691', '2372921124213', '2372463777810')
query.964:
/* ========================================================== */
/* 8) Personal Projection Calculation For Multi-Rate Supplies */
/* ========================================================== */

-- Uses a weighted average of EAC and annualised advance based on the le
WITH eac_aa AS (
  SELECT
     COALESCE(a.mpan, e.mpan) AS mpan
    ,COALESCE(a.tier, e.tier) AS tier
    ,COALESCE(a.clockingTimeId, e.timePatternRegime) AS clockingTimeId
    ,COALESCE(a.timeOfUseLabel, e.timeOfUseLabel) AS timeOfUseLabel
    ,toReadDate AS aaEffectiveFrom
    ,fromReadDate
    ,fromReading
    ,fromCoefficient
    ,toReadDate
    ,toReading
    ,intervalConsumption
    ,toCoefficient
    ,IF(coefficientAdvance>1,1,coefficientAdvance) AS coefficientAdvance -- some years might have more than 1 Easter and the seasonality changes what leads to coefficientAdvance greater than 1 and therefore negative eacCummulativeCoefficient (line 48)
    ,annualisedAdvance
    ,effectiveFromDate AS eacEffectiveFrom
    ,estimatedAnnualConsumption
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.multi_rate_projections_7_annualised_advances` AS a
  FULL OUTER JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.multi_rate_projections_6_cleaned_eac` AS e
      ON  a.mpan = e.mpan
      AND a.tier = e.tier
), cases AS (
SELECT
   mpan
  ,tier
  ,clockingTimeId
  ,timeOfUseLabel
  ,CASE 
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NULL THEN 'eac'
    WHEN eacEffectiveFrom IS NULL THEN 'aa'
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND eacEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL THEN 'combined'
      END AS projectionSource
  ,CASE 
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND eacEffectiveFrom IS NULL THEN 1.0
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND eacEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL THEN coefficientAdvance
    ELSE 0.0
      END AS aaCummulativeCoefficient
  ,CASE 
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND eacEffectiveFrom IS NULL THEN 0.0
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND eacEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL THEN ROUND(1 - coefficientAdvance, 3)
    ELSE 1.0
      END AS eacCummulativeCoefficient
  ,CASE 
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND eacEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND DATE_DIFF(DATE(aaEffectiveFrom, "Europe/London"),eacEffectiveFrom, DAY) > 0 THEN DATE(aaEffectiveFrom, "Europe/London")
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND eacEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND DATE_DIFF(eacEffectiveFrom,DATE(aaEffectiveFrom, "Europe/London"), DAY) >= 0 THEN eacEffectiveFrom
    WHEN aaEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND eacEffectiveFrom IS NULL THEN DATE(aaEffectiveFrom, "Europe/London")
    WHEN eacEffectiveFrom IS NOT NULL AND aaEffectiveFrom IS NULL THEN eacEffectiveFrom
      END AS effectiveFrom
  ,aaEffectiveFrom
  ,fromReadDate
  ,fromReading
  ,toReadDate
  ,toReading
  ,intervalConsumption
  ,coefficientAdvance
  ,annualisedAdvance
  ,eacEffectiveFrom
  ,estimatedAnnualConsumption  
FROM
  eac_aa
ORDER BY
  mpan,tier
)
SELECT
   mpan
  ,tier
  ,clockingTimeId
  ,timeOfUseLabel
  ,projectionSource
  ,aaCummulativeCoefficient
  ,eacCummulativeCoefficient
  ,ROUND((aaCummulativeCoefficient * IFNULL(annualisedAdvance,0)) + (eacCummulativeCoefficient * IFNULL(estimatedAnnualConsumption,0)),1) AS projectedConsumption
  ,effectiveFrom
  ,aaEffectiveFrom
  ,fromReadDate
  ,fromReading
  ,toReadDate
  ,toReading
  ,intervalConsumption
  ,coefficientAdvance
  ,annualisedAdvance
  ,eacEffectiveFrom
  ,estimatedAnnualConsumption
FROM
  cases
ORDER BY mpan
-- tests: each should return no results
--select mpan, tier, count(*) from cases group by mpan, tier having count(*) <> 1
-- union all
--select mpan, null as tier, count(*) from cases group by mpan having count(*) <> 2
query.965:
/* ================================== */
/* 9) Structured Personal Projections */
/* ================================== */

-- Takes the latest personal projection and backing data and outputs with a nested structure resembling the 
-- desired topic schema for the electricity multi-rate event type


SELECT 
  STRUCT(
     mpan
    ,TIMESTAMP(effectiveFrom) AS effectiveFrom
    ,ARRAY_AGG(STRUCT(clockingTimeId, timeOfUseLabel, projectedConsumption)) AS projectedRegisterConsumption
    ,STRUCT(
       projectionSource
      ,STRUCT(
        STRUCT(
           fromReadDate AS fromReadingDate
          ,toReadDate AS toReadingDate
          ,ARRAY_AGG(STRUCT(
             clockingTimeId, timeOfUseLabel
            ,fromReading AS fromMeterRegisterReading
            ,toReading AS toMeterRegisterReading
          )) AS ElectricityRegisterReadings
          ,aaCummulativeCoefficient AS cummulativeCoefficient
          ) AS annualisedAdvancePersonalProjectionOrigin
        ,STRUCT(
          ARRAY_AGG(STRUCT(
            clockingTimeId, timeOfUseLabel, estimatedAnnualConsumption
            )) AS ElectricityRegisterEstimatedAnnualConsumption
          ,eacCummulativeCoefficient AS cummulativeCoefficient          
          ) AS estimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin
        ) AS ElectricityPersonalProjectionOrigin

query.968:
WITH fetch_reads AS (
  SELECT
    rds.*
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.non_comms_constraints_base_data_latest_reads` AS rds
  INNER JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.non_comms_constraints_base_data_earliest_read_since_gt_bill` earliest_read
      ON  rds.msn = earliest_read.msn
      AND rds.readDateTime = earliest_read.readDateTime
), mapped_elec AS (
  SELECT
     elec.msn
    ,elec.fuel
    ,elec.readDateTime
    ,elec.tier
    --,map.clockingTimeId
    ,map.meterRegisterId
    ,FLOOR(elec.reading) AS reading
  FROM
    fetch_reads AS elec
  INNER JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.u_barney_scott.2019_10_28_meter_mappings` AS map
      ON  elec.msn = map.msn
      AND elec.tier = map.tier
  WHERE
    elec.fuel = 'electricity'
), adj_elec AS (
  SELECT
       gt.msn
      ,gt.accountNumber
      --,fuel
      ,gt.migrationRead
      ,gt.migrationReadDate
      ,gt.migrationReadType
      ,gt.meterRegisterId
      ,chg.readDateTime
      ,chg.reading
      ,CASE
        WHEN gt.migrationRead < chg.reading - 30 THEN 'charge greater than £5'
        WHEN gt.migrationRead >= chg.reading - 30 AND gt.migrationRead < chg.reading THEN 'charge less than £5'       
        WHEN gt.migrationRead > chg.reading + 30 THEN 'credit greater than £5' 
        WHEN gt.migrationRead <= chg.reading + 30 AND gt.migrationRead > chg.reading + 1 THEN 'credit less than £5'       
        ELSE 'equal' END AS adjustmentType
      ,ROUND(gt.migrationRead - chg.reading, 1) AS consumptionAdjustment
      ,DATE_DIFF(DATE(chg.readDateTime), gt.migrationReadDate, DAY) AS adjustmentDays
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.non_comms_constraints_base_data_gentrack_latest_bill` AS gt
  INNER JOIN
    mapped_elec AS chg
      ON  gt.msn = chg.msn
      AND gt.meterRegisterId = chg.meterRegisterId
      AND gt.migrationReadDate <= DATE(chg.readDateTime)
), adj_gas AS (
  SELECT
       gt.msn
      ,gt.accountNumber
      --,fuel
      ,gt.migrationRead
      ,gt.migrationReadDate
      ,gt.migrationReadType
      ,chg.readDateTime
      ,FLOOR(chg.reading) AS reading
      ,CASE
        WHEN gt.migrationRead < FLOOR(chg.reading) - 30 THEN 'charge greater than £5'
        WHEN gt.migrationRead >= FLOOR(chg.reading) - 30 AND gt.migrationRead < FLOOR(chg.reading) THEN 'charge less than £5'       
        WHEN gt.migrationRead > FLOOR(chg.reading) + 30 THEN 'credit greater than £5' 
        WHEN gt.migrationRead <= FLOOR(chg.reading) + 30 AND gt.migrationRead > FLOOR(chg.reading) + 1 THEN 'credit less than £5'       
        ELSE 'equal' END AS adjustmentType
      ,ROUND(gt.migrationRead - FLOOR(chg.reading), 1) AS consumptionAdjustment
      ,DATE_DIFF(DATE(chg.readDateTime), gt.migrationReadDate, DAY) AS adjustmentDays
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.non_comms_constraints_base_data_gentrack_latest_bill` AS gt
  INNER JOIN
    fetch_reads AS chg
      ON  gt.msn = chg.msn
      AND gt.migrationReadDate <= DATE(chg.readDateTime)
  WHERE chg.fuel = 'gas'
)
SELECT DISTINCT(accountNumber) FROM adj_elec WHERE adjustmentDays = 0 AND adjustmentType <> 'equal'
UNION DISTINCT
SELECT DISTINCT(accountNumber) FROM adj_gas WHERE adjustmentDays = 0 AND adjustmentType <> 'equal'

query.975:
SELECT
      A.Account_No AS accountNumber
    FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Account` A
      INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Consumer` C
        ON    A.Account_No = C.Account_No
        AND C.Lifecycle_Category = 'Live (Excluding Loss)'              
      LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Consumer` C_not_live 
        ON A.Account_No = C_not_live.Account_No 
        AND c_not_live.Lifecycle_Category not in ( 'Live (Excluding Loss)','Transfer Cancelled') and c_not_live.lifecycle <> 'Final'
      LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_ops_workstreams.Polarstern_tbl_Historic_Status` PS 
        ON C.Consumer_No = PS.Consumer_No
        AND PS.Is_Latest_Polarstern_Status = TRUE
    WHERE
      A.Billing_System = 'GENTRACK'
      AND    A.Payment_Method_Category = 'PAYM'                                                                    -- PAYM
      AND A.Retailer_Code = 'OVO'                                                                                -- OVO Customer
      AND A.Is_ET_Gain = FALSE                                                                                    -- Not an ET
          AND C_not_live.Account_No IS NULL    
    GROUP BY A.Account_No
    HAVING 
      SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(c.Meter_Type_Code,1,2) = 'S2'  THEN 1 WHEN C.Meter_Type_Category = 'Smart' AND C.Meter_type_code NOT IN ('NS','NSS') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = COUNT(*)        -- All live consumers are SMART     HOB 31/5/19 - now including SMETS2    AND SUM(CASE WHEN ISNULL(C.Billing_Class_Code, 'Nix zu sehen hier') = 'COM' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END) = COUNT(*)                           -- No live consumers are COMMERCIAL
    AND SUM(CASE WHEN coalesce(C.Tax_Class_Code, 'Nix zu sehen hier') IN ('COMMERCIAL', 'COMEXEMPT') THEN 0 ELSE 1 END) = COUNT(*)        -- No live consumers are COMMERCIAL
    AND SUM(CASE WHEN C.Profile_Class IN ('01', '02', 'G') THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = COUNT(*)                                                -- No live consumers are COMMERCIAL
    AND SUM(CASE WHEN C.Payment_Method_Category = 'PAYM' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = COUNT(*)                                                     -- All live consumers are PAYM, too
    AND SUM(CASE WHEN PS.Has_Meter_and_Tariff_Mismatch = TRUE THEN 0 ELSE 1 END) = COUNT(*)                                                -- No live consumers are Polarstern/nretsraloP
query.976:
SELECT
  accountNumber as Account_No,
  mpxn as Meter_Point_No,
  cast(initiatedAt as date) as Dispute_Raised_Date,
  'gas' as fuel,
  -- TODO: Use the status as published by TARDIS once we have it, or a version that conforms to DRS status values
  case
   when initiatedBy in ('OVO', 'OVOE') and alternatedAt is not null then 'Ovo Read Alternated'
   when alternatedAt is not null then 'Dispute Read Alternated'
   when initiatedBy in ('OVO', 'OVOE') and rejectedAt is not null then 'Ovo Dispute Rejected'
   when rejectedAt is not null then 'Dispute Read Rejected'
   when initiatedBy not in ('OVO', 'OVOE') then 'New Dispute Received'
   else 'Ovo Read Dispute Sent'
  end as Dispute_Status,
  disputedReadDate as Disputed_Read_Date,
  case when gainingSupplier in ('OVO', 'OVOE') then 'Gain' else 'Loss' end as Gain_Or_Loss,
  'No Salesforce Case' as Has_Open_Case, 
  case when gainingSupplier in ('OVO', 'OVOE') then losingSupplier else gainingSupplier end as Other_Supplier_Code,
  'PAYM' as Payment_Method_Category,
  coalesce(alternatedAt, rejectedAt, initiatedAt) as Last_Updated_Datetime, -- TODO: this should be whichever is latest of TARDIS status update and OOT work item note/status once we have them
  'TARDIS' as Dispute_System,
  'ORION' as Billing_System
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.gas_read_disputes_raised`
where agreedAt is null -- TODO: Replace this with something like status <> 'Agreed' once TARDIS are publishing generic status events
  and disputeSequence = 1
union all

  accountNumber as Account_No,
  mpxn as Meter_Point_No,
  cast(initiatedAt as date) as Dispute_Raised_Date,

  -- TODO: Use the status as published by TARDIS once we have it, or a version that conforms to DRS status values
  case
   when initiatedBy in ('OVO', 'OVOE') and alternatedAt is not null then 'Ovo Read Alternated'
   when alternatedAt is not null then 'Dispute Read Alternated'
   when initiatedBy in ('OVO', 'OVOE') and rejectedAt is not null then 'Ovo Dispute Rejected'
   when rejectedAt is not null then 'Dispute Read Rejected'
   when initiatedBy not in ('OVO', 'OVOE') then 'New Dispute Received'
   else 'Ovo Read Dispute Sent'
  end as Dispute_Status,
  disputedReadDate as Disputed_Read_Date,
  case when gainingSupplier in ('OVO', 'OVOE') then 'Gain' else 'Loss' end as Gain_Or_Loss,
  'No Salesforce Case' as Has_Open_Case, 
  case when gainingSupplier in ('OVO', 'OVOE') then losingSupplier else gainingSupplier end as Other_Supplier_Code,
  'PAYM' as Payment_Method_Category,
  coalesce(alternatedAt, rejectedAt, initiatedAt) as Last_Updated_Datetime, -- TODO: this should be whichever is latest of TARDIS status update and OOT work item note/status once we have them
  'TARDIS' as Dispute_System,
  'ORION' as Billing_System
FROM
