# Loss confirmed supplies logic.
# 
# Author: Victor Irles


WITH 

--Get all Orion accounts.Reversed accounts get excluded as Ownership gets published as Null when a reverse migration happens and the INNER JOIN UNNEST ensures no null events get moved forward.
cte_Orion_Accounts AS(
SELECT accountId
      ,o.supplyPoint AS mpxn
      ,o.fuel
      ,DATE(o.start, "Europe/London") AS StartOwnership
      ,DATE(o.end, "Europe/London") AS EndOwnership
FROM
(SELECT *
      , ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY accountId ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime DESC) AS rn --Sort the rows by createdAt time
FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_bast.bast_account_supply_point_state_v1`)
INNER JOIN UNNEST (ownership) AS o
WHERE rn=1 --dedupe
),

migrations AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT
     accountId
    ,DATE(createdAt)  AS migrationRunDate
    ,migrationDate 
  FROM (
    SELECT
       accountId
      ,globalAccountId
      ,migrationDate
      ,sp.mpxn
      ,fuel
      ,metadata.createdAt
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY sp.mpxn ORDER BY migrationDate DESC, metadata.createdAt DESC) AS ordering
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_migration.orion_migration_success_v2`
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(supplyPointList) AS sp
  )
  WHERE
    ordering = 1
),

--Logic for loss confirmation
cte_loss_confirmation_fuels AS(
SELECT
      mpxn
      ,"elecricity" AS fuel
      , supplyStartDate
      , supplyEndDate
      , supplyEndDate AS LossConfirmationDate --SupplyEndDate is the effective Loss Confirmation Date. lossConfirmedDate is when the first D0151 flow is sent by Utiligroup
      , lossConfirmedDate AS LossConfirmationReceiveDate
FROM (
    SELECT 
       MPXN                           AS mpxn
      ,gspGroupId                     AS region
      ,sp.supplyStartDate
      ,sp.supplyEndDate
      ,sp.lossConfirmed
      ,sp.lossConfirmedDate
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn ORDER BY supplyStartDate DESC) AS LatestSP --Take the latest supply period per supplypoint

    FROM (
      SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rowNumber --Sort the rows by createdAt time
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
      ) 
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST( supplyPeriods ) AS sp
    WHERE
          rowNumber = 1 --dedupe     
)
--WHERE LatestSP=1 --only latest supplyperiod
WHERE supplyEndDate IS NOT NULL --Where an end date exists
AND lossConfirmed=true --and just those supplies that are confirmed. (to avoid cases where supplyEndDate Is not null (Loss Notification flow received) but the D0151 has not arrived yet). Those could end up being withdrawn
AND supplyEndDate <= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL 13 DAY) --For elec there is no confirmation loss date flow. Best to wait 13 days to make sure cancel has not been withdrawn. This means that lots of accounts will show up as just Gas has been lost at fist but elec will follow 13 days later.

UNION ALL

SELECT
      mpxn
      ,"gas" AS fuel
      , supplyStartDate
      , supplyEndDate
      , supplyEndDate AS LossConfirmationDate --SupplyEndDate is the effective Loss Confirmation Date. lossConfirmedDate is just the date in which we receive the flow TFRS88
      , lossConfirmedDate AS LossConfirmationReceiveDate

FROM (
    SELECT 
       MPXN AS mpxn
      ,LDZ  AS region
      ,sp.supplyStartDate
      ,sp.supplyEndDate
      ,sp.lossConfirmed
      ,sp.lossConfirmedDate
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn ORDER BY supplyStartDate DESC) AS LatestSP --Take the latest supply period per supplypoint

    FROM (
      SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rowNumber   --Sort the rows by createdAt time
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_gasSupplyPointHistory_v2`
      ) 
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST( supplyPeriods ) AS sp
    WHERE
          rowNumber = 1 --dedupe
)
--WHERE LatestSP=1 --only latest supplyperiod
WHERE lossConfirmed=true --Where an end date exists
AND supplyEndDate IS NOT NULL --and just those supplies that are confirmed. (to avoid cases where supplyEndDate Is not null (Loss Notification flow received) but the confirmation flow TRFS88 has not arrived yet). Those could end up being withdrawn

)
,

--Select distinct accounts for which at least one supplypoint is lost
cte_Lost_Accounts AS(
SELECT DISTINCT acc.accountId
FROM cte_Orion_Accounts acc
INNER JOIN cte_loss_confirmation_fuels lc
ON acc.mpxn=lc.mpxn
AND lc.LossConfirmationDate BETWEEN StartOwnership AND EndOwnership --This condition avoids selecting the wrong account in the case of a Change of Tenancy
),

--Map loss dates to supply and these to the accounts with at least one supply lost
cte_Lost_Accounts_Supply AS(
SELECT acc.accountId
      , mig.migrationDate
      , acc.StartOwnership
      , acc.EndOwnership
      , acc.fuel
      , acc.mpxn
      , lc.supplyStartDate
      , lc.LossConfirmationReceiveDate
      , lc.LossConfirmationDate
FROM cte_Orion_Accounts acc
LEFT JOIN cte_loss_confirmation_fuels lc --Map loss information to all accounts
USING (mpxn)
INNER JOIN cte_Lost_Accounts lacc --select those accounts for which at least one supply is lost only, not just the accounts for which all supplies are lost.
USING (accountId)
LEFT JOIN migrations mig
USING (accountId)
)


SELECT accountId
      , migrationDate
      , StartOwnership
      , EndOwnership
      , fuel
      , mpxn
      --, supplyStartDate
      , LossConfirmationReceiveDate
      , LossConfirmationDate
FROM cte_Lost_Accounts_Supply
WHERE (LossConfirmationDate>COALESCE(migrationDate,StartOwnership) OR LossConfirmationDate IS NULL) --Only losses in Orion OR supplies not lost but where the account has lost the other supply (e.g account 20000025)
--AND accountId IN ('') --testing
ORDER BY accountId, fuel, supplyStartDate DESC
query.979:
WITH mappings AS (
  SELECT
     MPXN
    ,MSN
    ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
    ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,tier
    ,createdAt
  FROM (
    SELECT
       MPXN 
      ,inst.MSN
      ,inst.startDate AS meterMappingEffectiveFrom
      ,his.startDate AS registerConfigEffectiveFrom
      ,reg.clockingTimeId
      ,reg.timePatternRegime
      ,reg.tier
      ,metadata.createdAt
      -- use rank to find the latest configuration and meter instalation dates
      ,RANK() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN  ORDER BY inst.startDate DESC) AS latestMeterMapping
      ,RANK() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN  ORDER BY his.startDate DESC) AS latestConfigMapping
    FROM 
      `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v1`
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(installationHistory) AS inst
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(inst.meterRegisterHistory) his
    INNER JOIN
      UNNEST(his.meterRegisters) reg
    ) lt
  WHERE 
    latestMeterMapping = 1 
    AND latestConfigMapping = 1
    AND tier IS NOT NULL
), ranked_mappings AS (
  SELECT
     MPXN
    ,MSN
    ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
    ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,tier
    -- single entry per MPXN, tier
    ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MPXN, tier ORDER BY createdAt DESC) rowNumMpxn
    -- single entry per MSN, tier
    ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY MSN, tier ORDER BY createdAt DESC) rowNumMsn
  FROM
    mappings
), deduped_ranked AS (
  SELECT
     MPXN
    ,MSN
    ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
    ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,tier
  FROM
    ranked_mappings
  WHERE 
    rowNumMpxn = 1
    AND rowNumMsn = 1
), two_rate_list AS (
  -- get multi rate MPANs only. Choose exactly 2 tiers as we will not support more than 2 on OEP
  SELECT
    m.MPXN AS mpan
  FROM
    deduped_ranked AS m
  GROUP BY
    m.MPXN
  HAVING
    COUNT(clockingTimeId) = 2
), two_rate_only AS (
  SELECT
     MPXN
    ,MSN
    ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
    ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
    ,clockingTimeId
    ,timePatternRegime
    ,tier  
  FROM
    deduped_ranked dr
  INNER JOIN
    two_rate_list AS t
      ON dr.MPXN = t.mpan
)
SELECT
   MPXN
  ,MSN
  ,meterMappingEffectiveFrom
  ,registerConfigEffectiveFrom
  ,clockingTimeId
  ,timePatternRegime
  ,tier  
FROM
  two_rate_only

--  SELECT msn, tier, count(*) from two_rate_only group by msn, tier HAVING COUNT(*) <> 1
--  SELECT mpxn, count(*) from two_rate_only group by mpxn HAVING COUNT(*) <> 2

query.986:
-- Looks back 7 days on startDate and createdDate to catch as much as possible and gives redundancy in case a day
-- gets missed.  The output SFE csv is loaded back into BQ so that we don't create the same csv again.

-- Conversions
-- 01,Warmer Home Plan,15% Reduced Rate
-- 02,Warmer Home Plan,15% P2 to P1
-- 11,Better Energy,15% Reduced Rate
-- 13,Better Energy,P2 to P1
-- 17,Simpler Energy,15% Reduced Rate
-- 18,Simpler Energy, Reduced Rage
-- 19,Simpler Energy,15% P2 to P1
-- 20,Simpler Energy,P2 to P1
-- 27,2 Year Fixed Energy,15% Rdced VAT
-- 28,2 Year Fixed Energy,P2 to P1

-- Note on VAT
-- The rates physically stored in SFE need to include VAT
-- The rates here all exc VAT, but that is fine for the rate testing etc, just that the final rates on the meter need to include VAT

with cte_gt_codes as (
-- GT codes from kate loaded manually - would need to be updated in case of price changes and new rates
-- 17-20 Append VARL
-- Otherwise append ActiveFrom YYYYMMDD
  select
    gentrack_code as GentrackCode,
    case
      when substr(gentrack_code, -2) in ('17', '18', '19', '20') then concat(gentrack_code, '_VARL') -- Adds the OVO/SFE convention _VARL for variable tariffs
      else concat(gentrack_code, '_', REPLACE(cast(active_from as string), '-', '')) -- Adds the OVO/SFE convention of versioning by adding _YYYYMMDD of activeFrom
    end as TariffDescription,
    version_id as VersionId,
    active_from as ActiveFrom,
    active_to as ActiveTo,
    tariff_id as TariffID,
    case
      when substr(gentrack_code, -2) in ('17', '18', '19', '20') then 'v'
      else 'f'
    end as TariffType,
    standing_rate as StandingRate,
    unit_rate as UnitRate
  from
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.poc_gentrack_tariff_mapping`
),

cte_gt_codes_var as (
  select
    *
  from
    cte_gt_codes
  where
    TariffType = 'v'
),

cte_gt_codes_fix as (
  select
    *
  from
    cte_gt_codes
  where
    TariffType = 'f'
),

cte_contracts as (
  select
    fuel as SupplyType,
    mpxn as ServicePointNo,
    case
      when startDate <= current_date() then timestamp(date_add(current_date(), interval 1 day))
      else cast(startDate as timestamp)
    end as ActivationTime,
    contractId,
    tariffId,
    currentUnitRate,
    currentStandingRate,
    startDate,
    createdDate
  from
    `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts`
),
cte_result as (
-- Fixed
select
  c.SupplyType,
  c.ServicePointNo,
  gtf.GentrackCode,
  gtf.TariffDescription,
  gtf.VersionId,
  cast(gtf.ActiveFrom as string) as ActiveFrom,
  cast(gtf.ActiveTo as string) as ActiveTo,
  c.ActivationTime,
  c.contractId,
  c.tariffId,
  c.currentUnitRate,
  c.currentStandingRate,
  gtf.UnitRate,
  gtf.StandingRate,
  case
    when (c.currentUnitRate = gtf.UnitRate) and (c.currentStandingRate = gtf.StandingRate) then 1
    else 0
  end as RatesCorrect
from
  cte_contracts as c
  inner join
  cte_gt_codes_fix as gtf
    on c.tariffId = gtf.TariffId
where
  c.startDate > DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL -7 DAY) or cast(c.createdDate as date) > DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL -7 DAY)
-- Variable
union all
select
  c.SupplyType,
  c.ServicePointNo,
  gtv.GentrackCode,
  gtv.TariffDescription,
  gtv.VersionId,
  cast(gtv.ActiveFrom as string) as ActiveFrom,
  cast(gtv.ActiveTo as string) as ActiveTo,
  c.ActivationTime,
  c.contractId,
  c.tariffId,
  c.currentUnitRate,
  c.currentStandingRate,
  gtv.UnitRate,
  gtv.StandingRate,
  case
    when (c.currentUnitRate = gtv.UnitRate) and (c.currentStandingRate = gtv.StandingRate) then 1
    else 0
  end as RatesCorrect
from
  cte_contracts as c
  inner join
  cte_gt_codes_var as gtv
    on c.tariffId = gtv.TariffId
where
  (c.startDate > DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL -7 DAY) or cast(c.createdDate as date) > DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL -7 DAY))
  and (current_date() >= gtv.ActiveFrom and current_date() <= ifnull(gtv.ActiveTo, date(9999,1,1))) -- Chooses the correct variable tariff (since same tariffID for different versions)
)

select
  r.*
from
  cte_result as r
  left join
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.poc_sfe_tariff_config_previous_uploads` as tc
    on r.ServicePointNo = tc.ServicePointNo
    and r.tariffId = tc.tariffId
    and r.currentUnitRate = tc.currentUnitRate
    and r.currentStandingRate = tc.currentStandingRate
where
  tc.ServicePointNo is null -- to remove the previously processed rates (takes into account both tariffId and rates for variable)
order by
  r.SupplyType,
  r.TariffDescription,
  r.ServicePointNo

--CONTRACTS
--############################################ 
WITH cte_contracts_raw AS(  
  SELECT
    a.unionRecord.Contract.mpxn,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.serviceAccountId,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.fuel,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.contractId,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.startDate,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.endDate,
    a.unionRecord.Contract.lossConfirmed,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY a.unionRecord.Contract.mpxn ORDER BY a.unionRecord.Contract.metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rn

  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract_v3` a
  LEFT JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT unionRecord.Cancelled.contractId FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract_v3`) b --Remove cancelled contracts
  ON a.unionRecord.Contract.contractId = b.contractId
  WHERE a.unionRecord.Contract IS NOT NULL 
  AND b.contractId IS NULL
  ),
  
  cte_contracts AS(
  SELECT DISTINCT fuel
                  , serviceAccountId
                  , mpxn
                  , DATE_TRUNC(CURRENT_DATE(), MONTH) AS ECbillingDate
  FROM cte_contracts_raw 
  WHERE rn=1
  AND lossConfirmed IS NULL --Just live supplies?
  ORDER BY serviceAccountId
  ),

cte_bastBillingDate AS(
  SELECT accountId
        , DATE_ADD(DATE_TRUNC(CURRENT_DATE(), MONTH), INTERVAL (status.Active.billingDayOfTheMonth-1) DAY) AS BASTbillingDate
  FROM 
    (SELECT *, row_number() OVER (PARTITION BY accountId ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS rn 
      FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_bast_secure.bast_account_billing_information_v1`)
  WHERE rn=1 
  AND status.Active IS NOT NULL
  ),
  
 cte_BillingDateJoined AS( 
  SELECT a.*, b.BASTbillingDate
  FROM cte_contracts a
  LEFT JOIN cte_bastBillingDate b
  ON a.serviceAccountId = b.accountId 
  ),
  
 cte_billingDates AS( 
  SELECT fuel
         , serviceAccountId
         , mpxn
         , IF(BASTbillingDate IS NOT NULL, BASTbillingDate, ECbillingDate) AS billingDate
  FROM cte_BillingDateJoined
  )
  --SELECT * FROM cte_billingDates where serviceAccountId = '3237185'
  ,

--ESTIMATES
--############################################
cte_estimates AS(
  SELECT 'Electricity' AS Fuel
       , ElectricityReadEstimate.mpan AS MPXN
       , ElectricityReadEstimate.msn AS MSN
       , CAST(reg.tier AS STRING) AS tier
       , CAST(reg.clockingTimeId AS STRING) AS clockingTimeId
       , ElectricityReadEstimate.dateTime
       , reg.readEstimate 
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.u_victor_irles.rac_electricity_readEstimates_DailyUpdate`
  INNER JOIN UNNEST (ElectricityReadEstimate.ElectricityRegisterEstimates) AS reg

  UNION ALL

  SELECT 'Gas' AS Fuel
       , GasReadEstimate.mprn AS MPXN
       , GasReadEstimate.msn AS MSN
       , 'G' AS tier
       , 'G' AS clockingTimeId
       , GasReadEstimate.dateTime
       , GasReadEstimate.readEstimate 
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.u_victor_irles.rac_gas_readEstimates_DailyUpdate`
)
,

--REMOVE ALREADY EXISITNG READ
--############################################
cte_consumption AS(
SELECT DISTINCT mpan AS MPXN, msn, fromDateTime, toDateTime
FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v4`
UNION ALL 
SELECT DISTINCT mprn AS MPXN, msn, fromDateTime, toDateTime
FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_gas_volume_consumption_generated_v2`
),

cte_billingDatesFiltered AS(
SELECT a.*
FROM cte_billingDates a
LEFT JOIN cte_consumption b
ON a.mpxn = b.MPXN
AND a.billingDate = DATE(b.toDateTime) --Careful here if billingdate is not UTC I'll need to add 1h in summer
WHERE b.MPXN IS NULL
)
,


--MAP ESTIMATES TO ACCOUNTS ON BILLING DATE
--############################################
cte_mapEstimates AS(
  SELECT a.*, b.MSN, b.tier, b.clockingTimeId, b.readEstimate
  FROM cte_billingDatesFiltered a --cte_estimates b
  LEFT JOIN cte_estimates b --cte_contracts_filtered a
  ON b.MPXN = a.mpxn
  AND DATE(b.dateTime) = a.billingDate
)
  
SELECT serviceAccountId AS accountId
      , fuel
      , mpxn AS MPXN
      , MSN
      , tier
      , clockingTimeId
      , billingDate
      , readEstimate
FROM cte_mapEstimates
WHERE billingDate <= CURRENT_DATE() AND billingDate >= DATE_SUB(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL 5 DAY)
--WHERE serviceAccountId = '3237185'
AND readEstimate IS NOT NULL
ORDER BY serviceAccountId

 ),

WITH
  v3 AS (
      SELECT 
         event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan                  AS mpxn
        ,event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom         AS effectiveFrom
        ,event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.projectedConsumption  AS projectedConsumption
        --,MAX(event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom) OVER(PARTITION BY event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan) AS latestProjection
        ,CASE 
          WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityAnnualAdvancementPersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL
            THEN 'Actual'
          WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL
            THEN 'Industry Estimate'
          WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityCombinedPersonalProjectionOrigin.annualisedAdvancePersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL
            THEN 'Hybrid'
         END AS projectionSource
      ,CASE WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityAnnualAdvancementPersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL 
          THEN 1.0
       WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL 
          THEN 1.0
       ELSE event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityCombinedPersonalProjectionOrigin.annualisedAdvancePersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient
          END AS actualDemandWeighting
      ,( event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityCombinedPersonalProjectionOrigin.annualisedAdvancePersonalProjectionOrigin.toMeterRegisterReading -
      event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityCombinedPersonalProjectionOrigin.annualisedAdvancePersonalProjectionOrigin.fromMeterRegisterReading) / 
      event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityCombinedPersonalProjectionOrigin.annualisedAdvancePersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient AS componentAa
      , event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityCombinedPersonalProjectionOrigin.estimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin.estimatedAnnualConsumption AS componentEac
      ,event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.metadata.createdAt
      FROM 
        `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_orion_personal_projections_published_v3` 
      WHERE
        event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan IS NOT NULL
  ),
  v2 AS (
      SELECT 
         event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan                  AS mpxn
        ,event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom         AS effectiveFrom
        ,event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.projectedConsumption  AS projectedConsumption
        --,MAX(event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom) OVER(PARTITION BY event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan) AS latestProjection
        ,CASE 
          WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityAnnualAdvancementPersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL
            THEN 'Actual'
          WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL
            THEN 'Industry Estimate'
            END AS projectionSource
       ,CASE WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityAnnualAdvancementPersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL 
          THEN 1.0
        WHEN event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin.cumulativeCoefficient IS NOT NULL 
           THEN 0.0
              END AS actualDemandWeighting
       ,NULL AS componentAA
       ,NULL AS componentEAC
       ,event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.metadata.createdAt
      FROM 
        `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_orion_personal_projections_published_v2` 
      WHERE
        event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan IS NOT NULL
  ),
  unioned AS (
    SELECT
       mpxn
      ,effectiveFrom
      ,projectedConsumption
      ,MAX(effectiveFrom) OVER(PARTITION BY mpxn) AS latestProjection
      ,projectionSource
      ,CASE
        WHEN projectionSource = 'Hybrid' THEN ROUND(componentAa)
        WHEN projectionSource = 'Actual' THEN ROUND(projectedConsumption)
        WHEN projectionSource = 'Industry Estimate' THEN NULL
        END AS componentAA
      ,CASE
        WHEN projectionSource = 'Hybrid' THEN ROUND(componentEac)
        WHEN projectionSource = 'Actual' THEN NULL
        WHEN projectionSource = 'Industry Estimate' THEN ROUND(projectedConsumption)
        END AS componentEac  
      ,actualDemandWeighting
      ,createdAt
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
        PARTITION BY 
          mpxn,
          TIMESTAMP_TRUNC(effectiveFrom , MONTH, 'UTC')
        ORDER BY 
          effectiveFrom DESC,
          createdAt DESC) AS rowNumber -- latest for a given month
    FROM (
      SELECT * FROM v3 
      UNION ALL
      SELECT * FROM v2
      )
  )
SELECT
   mpxn
  ,effectiveFrom
  ,projectedConsumption
  ,projectionSource
  ,actualDemandWeighting
  ,componentEac
  ,componentAa
  ,CASE WHEN effectiveFrom = latestProjection THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS IsLatest
  ,TIMESTAMP_TRUNC(effectiveFrom, MONTH, 'UTC') AS monthStart
FROM
  unioned
WHERE
  rowNumber = 1
ORDER BY
  mpxn, effectiveFrom DESC

with cte_sequence as
(
  select wi.workItemId,
         wi.status,
         wi.statusChangeDateTime,
         wi.statusNote,
         wi.statusDueDate,
         case
          when wi.statusChangeAuthor = 'google-oauth2|101896709569699413536' then 'Rhianna Bailey'
          when wi.statusChangeAuthor = 'google-oauth2|109028848899209592945' then 'Danielle Giltrow'
          when wi.statusChangeAuthor = 'google-oauth2|104990701221444704641' then 'Pete Grace'
          when wi.statusChangeAuthor = 'google-oauth2|104926974093175656072' then 'Mike Gibson'
          else wi.statusChangeAuthor
         end as statusChangeAuthor,
         split(e, '/') as key_array,
         row_number() over (partition by wi.workItemId order by wi.statusChangeDateTime asc, wi.metadata.createdAt asc) as statusChangeSequence
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_oot_secure.oot_work_item_v3` wi
  inner join unnest(wi.entityUris) e
  where e like 'read-disputes%'
)
select wi.* except(key_array),
       wi.key_array[offset(2)] as mpxn,
       cast(wi.key_array[offset(3)] as date) as disputedReadDate
from cte_sequence wi
query.1020:
with cte_dedupe as
(
  select wi.workItemId,
         wi.status,
         wi.statusChangeDateTime,
         wi.statusNote,
         wi.statusDueDate,
         coalesce(u.name, wi.statusChangeAuthor) as statusChangeAuthor,
         split(e, '/') as key_array,
         row_number() over (partition by wi.workItemId order by wi.statusChangeDateTime desc, wi.metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num_all,
         row_number() over (partition by wi.workItemId order by case when wi.statusChangeAuthor is not null then 1 else 2 end, -- favour when there's an author
                                                                case when wi.statusNote not like 'State Transition%' then 1 else 2 end, -- favour when it's not a state transition to get round bug we had to begin with
                                                                wi.statusChangeDateTime desc, wi.metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num_worked
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_oot_secure.oot_work_item_v3` wi
  inner join unnest(wi.entityUris) e
  left join `data-engineering-prod.landing_oot_secure.oot_users_export` u on wi.statusChangeAuthor = u.userId
  where e like 'read-disputes%'
)
select wi.* except(key_array, row_num_all, row_num_worked),
       wi.key_array[offset(2)] as mpxn,
       cast(wi.key_array[offset(3)] as date) as disputedReadDate,
       case when wrkd.statusChangeAuthor is not null then true else false end as hasBeenWorked,
       wrkd.statusChangeAuthor as lastWorkedBy,
       wrkd.status as lastWorkedStatus,
       wrkd.statusChangeDateTime as lastWorkedDatetime,
       wrkd.statusNote as lastWorkedNote,
       wrkd.statusDueDate as lastWorkedDueDate,
       case when wrkd.status in ('AwaitingSupplier', 'AwaitingCustomer') and current_date() >= wrkd.statusDueDate then true else false end as isPastDueDate
from cte_dedupe wi
left join cte_dedupe wrkd on wi.workItemId = wrkd.workItemId
                         and wrkd.row_num_worked = 1
where wi.row_num_all = 1

WITH cte_simplified as (
  SELECT COALESCE(s.value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.msn, s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.msn) as msn,
         COALESCE(s.value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime, s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime) as snapshotTime,
         COALESCE(s.value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.mpan, s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.mprn) as mpxn,
         CASE WHEN s.value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime IS NOT NULL THEN 'electricity'
              WHEN s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime IS NOT NULL THEN 'gas'
         END AS fuel,
         s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.gasVolume as importTotalVolumeRead,
         MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 0 THEN r.reading END) AS importReg0KwhRead,
         MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 1 THEN r.reading END) AS importReg1KwhRead,
         MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 2 THEN r.reading END) AS importReg2KwhRead
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_msd_simplified` s
  LEFT JOIN UNNEST(s.value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.registers) r
  GROUP BY s.value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.msn,
           s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.msn,
           s.value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime,
           s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime,
           s.value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.mpan,
           s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.mprn,
           s.value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.gasVolume
),

cte_received as (
  SELECT msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotId,
         msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotTime,
         msd.snapshotData.device.serialNumber as msn,
         lower(msd.snapshotData.device.servicePointNumber) as mpxn,
         msd.snapshotData.device.supplyType as fuel,
         msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotCause,
         msd.snapshotData.device.importChargingType,
         msd.snapshotData.device.cumulativeRegisters.volume       as importTotalVolumeRead,
         msd.snapshotData.device.cumulativeRegisters.activeImport as importTotalKwhRead,
         MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 0 THEN r.cumulative END) AS importReg0KwhRead,
         MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 1 THEN r.cumulative END) AS importReg1KwhRead,
         MIN(CASE WHEN r.tier = 2 THEN r.cumulative END) AS importReg2KwhRead,
         msd.snapshotData.device.exportChargingType,
         msd.snapshotData.device.cumulativeRegisters.activeExport AS exportTotalKwhRead
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_msd_received` msd
  INNER JOIN UNNEST (snapshotData.device.importRateRegisters.value) as r
  GROUP BY msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotId,
           msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotTime,
           msd.snapshotData.device.servicePointNumber,
           msd.snapshotData.device.serialNumber, 
           msd.snapshotData.device.supplyType,
           msd.snapshotData.device.snapshotCause,
           msd.snapshotData.device.importChargingType,
           msd.snapshotData.device.cumulativeRegisters.activeImport,
           msd.snapshotData.device.cumulativeRegisters.volume,
           msd.snapshotData.device.exportChargingType,
           msd.snapshotData.device.cumulativeRegisters.activeExport
)

SELECT distinct msd.snapshotId,
       COALESCE(msd.snapshotTime, simp.snapshotTime) as snapshotTime,
       COALESCE(msd.msn, simp.msn) as msn,
       COALESCE(CASE WHEN LENGTH(simp.mpxn) < 10 THEN SUBSTR(CONCAT('00000', simp.mpxn), -10) ELSE simp.mpxn END,
                CASE WHEN LENGTH(msd.mpxn) < 10 THEN SUBSTR(CONCAT('00000', msd.mpxn), -10) ELSE msd.mpxn END) as mpxn,
       msd.mpxn as mpxnFromMeter,
       simp.mpxn as mpxnFromMsdSimplified,
       CASE WHEN CASE WHEN LENGTH(simp.mpxn) < 10 THEN SUBSTR(CONCAT('00000', simp.mpxn), -10) ELSE simp.mpxn END
                 =
                 CASE WHEN LENGTH(msd.mpxn) < 10 THEN SUBSTR(CONCAT('00000', msd.mpxn), -10) ELSE msd.mpxn END 
            THEN 'Validated'
            WHEN msd.snapshotTime < '2018-03-01' THEN 'Pre-Validation'
            WHEN CASE WHEN LENGTH(simp.mpxn) < 10 THEN SUBSTR(CONCAT('00000', simp.mpxn), -10) ELSE simp.mpxn END
                 <>
                 CASE WHEN LENGTH(msd.mpxn) < 10 THEN SUBSTR(CONCAT('00000', msd.mpxn), -10) ELSE msd.mpxn END 
            THEN 'Suspected incorrect MPXN on Meter'
            WHEN msd.mpxn IS NULL THEN 'SMETS2'
            WHEN simp.mpxn IS NULL THEN 'Not Validated'
       END AS mpxnValidationStatus,
       COALESCE(msd.fuel, simp.fuel) as fuel,
       msd.snapshotCause,
       msd.importChargingType,
       COALESCE(msd.importTotalVolumeRead, simp.importTotalVolumeRead) as importTotalVolumeRead,
       msd.importTotalKwhRead,
       COALESCE(msd.importReg0KwhRead, simp.importReg0KwhRead) as importReg0KwhRead,
       COALESCE(msd.importReg1KwhRead, simp.importReg1KwhRead) as importReg1KwhRead,
       COALESCE(msd.importReg2KwhRead, simp.importReg2KwhRead) as importReg2KwhRead,
       msd.exportChargingType,
       msd.exportTotalKwhRead,
       CASE WHEN RANK() OVER(PARTITION BY COALESCE(CASE WHEN LENGTH(simp.mpxn) < 10 THEN SUBSTR(CONCAT('00000', simp.mpxn), -10) ELSE simp.mpxn END,
                                                   CASE WHEN LENGTH(msd.mpxn) < 10 THEN SUBSTR(CONCAT('00000', msd.mpxn), -10) ELSE msd.mpxn END) 
                             ORDER BY COALESCE(msd.snapshotTime, simp.snapshotTime) DESC) = 1
            THEN 1
            ELSE 0
       END as isLatestSnapshotForSupplyPoint
FROM cte_received msd
FULL JOIN cte_simplified simp ON msd.msn = simp.msn AND msd.snapshotTime = simp.snapshotTime
query.1025:
with cte_standing_charge_created as
(
  with cte_charge_dedupe as
  (
    select created_eventId            as event_id,
           created_chargeId           as charge_id,
           created_createdAt          as created_at,
           created_chargeDate         as charge_date,
           created_contractId         as contract_id,
           created_supplyPoint        as supply_point,
           created_amount             as charge_amount,
           insertTime                 as latestCreatedInsertTime,
           row_number() over (partition by created_chargeId order by insertTime desc, created_createdAt desc) as charge_dedupe_rownum
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_standing_charge_created`
    WHERE created_eventId is not null
  )
  select *
  from cte_charge_dedupe
  where charge_dedupe_rownum = 1
),
cte_created_times as
(
  select created_chargeId as charge_id,
         min(created_createdAt) as charge_first_created_time
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_standing_charge_created`
  group by created_chargeId
),
cte_standing_charge_cancelled as
(
  select cancelled_chargeId        as charge_id,
         max(insertTime)           as latestCancelledInsertTime
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_standing_charge_created`
  where cancelled_eventId is NOT null
  group by cancelled_chargeId
),
cte_standing_charge as
(
  select 
      sc_created.supply_point,
      sc_created.contract_id,
      sc_created.charge_id,
      ct.charge_first_created_time,
      sc_created.charge_date,
      CAST(sc_created.charge_date AS datetime) AS Charge_From_Date,
      cast(DATE_ADD(sc_created.charge_date,INTERVAL 1 DAY) as datetime) AS Charge_To_Date,
      sc_created.charge_amount,
      case when sc_cancelled.charge_id is null then 0 else 1 end is_cancelled,
      'standing_charge' as charge_type
  from
               cte_standing_charge_created sc_created
  LEFT JOIN    cte_created_times ct on sc_created.charge_id = ct.charge_id
  left join    cte_standing_charge_cancelled sc_cancelled on sc_cancelled.charge_id = sc_created.charge_id
                                                         and sc_cancelled.latestCancelledInsertTime > sc_created.latestCreatedInsertTime
)
select sc.*,
       sc.supply_point as mpxn
from cte_standing_charge sc
where is_cancelled = 0

with cte_supply_points as (
  with cte_elec_dedupe as   (
    select sp.mpxn,
           sp.gspGroupId,
           sp.msn,
           sp.profileClassId,
           NULL as meterTimeswitchCode,
           sp.lineLossFactorClassId, 
           sp.supplyStatus.status as supplyStatus,
           sp.supplyStatus.statusDate as supplyStatusDate,
           mrh as currentMeterRegisters,
           sp.meterRegisterHistory,
           sp.latestMeterDetails.meterType as meterType,
           row_number() over (partition by mpxn order by metadata.createdAt desc, kafkaData.insertTime desc, kafkaData.offset desc) as mpxn_dedupe_rownum
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPoint_legacy` sp
    left join unnest(sp.meterRegisterHistory) mrh
  ),
  
  cte_gas_dedupe as (
    select mpxn,
           ldz,
           msn,
           supplyStatus.status as supplyStatus,
           supplyStatus.statusDate as supplyStatusDate,
           latestInstallation.meterType as meterType,
           row_number() over (partition by mpxn order by metadata.createdAt desc, kafkaData.insertTime desc, kafkaData.offset) as mpxn_dedupe_rownum
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.spam_gasSupplyPoint_legacy`
  )
  
  select mpxn,
         'electricity' as fuel,
         gspGroupId as regionCode,
         gspGroupId,
         null as ldz,
         msn,
         profileClassId,
         meterTimeswitchCode,
         lineLossFactorClassId,
         supplyStatus,
         supplyStatusDate,
         currentMeterRegisters,
         meterRegisterHistory,
         meterType
  from cte_elec_dedupe
  where mpxn_dedupe_rownum = 1
    and length(mpxn) = 13 -- Validate that it's an elec MPAN to filter out duds that have been published historically
  
  union all
  
  select mpxn,
         'gas' as fuel,
         ldz as regionCode,
         null as gspGroupId,
         ldz,
         msn,
         null as profileClassId,
         null as meterTimeswitchCode,
         null as lineLossFactorClassId,
         supplyStatus,
         supplyStatusDate,
         null as currentMeterRegisters,
         null as meterRegisterHistory,
         meterType
  from cte_gas_dedupe
  where mpxn_dedupe_rownum = 1
    and length(mpxn) <= 10 -- Validate that it's a as MPRN to filter out duds that have been published historically
),

-- This deliberately pulls back supply points with cancelled charge mandates as these are of interest to us
cte_all_historical_charge_mandated_supply_points as (
  select contract_mpxn as mpxn,
         min(cast(contract_createdAt as date)) as andromedaMigrationDate
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_contract`
  where contract_contractId is not null
  group by contract_mpxn
),

cte_charge_mandate_status as (
  select sp.mpxn,
         sp.andromedaMigrationDate,
         case
          when current_date() between min(cm.startDate) and max(coalesce(cm.endDate, '2999-01-01')) then 'Has Current Charge Mandate'
          when current_date() > max(cm.endDate) then 'Has Historic Charge Mandate'
          when current_date() < MIN(cm.startDate) then 'Has Future Charge Mandate'
          when min(cm.startDate) is null then 'Has Cancelled Charge Mandate'
         END as chargeMandateStatus
  from cte_all_historical_charge_mandated_supply_points sp
  left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` cm on sp.mpxn = cm.mpxn
  group by sp.mpxn,
           sp.andromedaMigrationDate
),

-- TODO: Add in rac_personal_projections_calculated_v5.event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin.estimatedAnnualConsumptions
cte_estimated_consumption_dedupe as (
  select case when length(ieu.supplyPoint) < 10 then substr(concat('00000', ieu.supplyPoint), -10) ELSE ieu.supplyPoint END as mpxn,
         ieu.forecastedAnnualConsumption,
         ieu.effectiveFrom as forecastedAnnualConsumptionEffectiveFrom,
         row_number() over (partition by case when length(ieu.supplyPoint) < 10 then substr(concat('00000', ieu.supplyPoint), -10) ELSE ieu.supplyPoint END
                            order by ieu.effectiveFrom desc, ieu.metadata.createdAt desc) as estimated_consumption_dedupe_rownum
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_industry_estimate_updated` ieu
),

cte_register_eacs as (
  with cte_latest_eac_dedupe as (
    select event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan as mpxn,
           event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin.estimatedAnnualConsumptions,
           row_number() over (partition by event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan order by event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_personal_projections_calculated`
    where event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.ElectricityEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin is not null
  ),
  
  cte_latest_aq_dedupe as (
    select event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.mprn as mpxn,
           array(select struct(cast(null as int64) as timePatternRegime,
                               event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.GasEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin.estimatedAnnualConsumption)) as estimatedAnnualConsumptions,
           row_number() over (partition by event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.mprn order by event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.metadata.createdAt desc) as row_num
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_personal_projections_calculated`
    where event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.basedOn.GasEstimatedAnnualConsumptionPersonalProjectionOrigin is not null
  )
  
  select * except(row_num)
  from cte_latest_eac_dedupe
  where row_num = 1
  
  union all
  
  select * except(row_num)
  from cte_latest_aq_dedupe
  where row_num = 1
)

select sp.*,
       substr(sp.mpxn, 1, 2) as distributorId,
       currentMeterRegisters.ssc as ssc,
       case
         when sp.fuel = 'electricity' then 'kwh'
         when sp.fuel = 'gas' and chargeMandateStatus = 'Has Current Charge Mandate' then 'm3'
       end as meterUnitOfMeasure,
       cm.andromedaMigrationDate,
       cm.chargeMandateStatus,
       rec.estimatedAnnualConsumptions as registerEstimatedAnnualConsumptions,
       ec.forecastedAnnualConsumption,
       ec.forecastedAnnualConsumptionEffectiveFrom
from cte_supply_points sp
left join cte_charge_mandate_status cm on sp.mpxn = cm.mpxn
left join cte_estimated_consumption_dedupe ec on sp.mpxn = ec.mpxn and ec.estimated_consumption_dedupe_rownum = 1
left join cte_register_eacs rec on sp.mpxn = rec.mpxn

          ,'Elec' as Fuel

    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_state`

    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_gas_dispute_state` 
),

latest_account as (
SELECT a.Account_No
      ,e.mpxn
      ,e.Fuel
      ,e.disputedReadDate 
      ,e.status 
      ,e.workRequired 
      ,e.disputedReadValues 
      ,e.metadata
      ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY e.mpxn ORDER BY a.Start_Date DESC) Row_Num
FROM event e
LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points` a on a.Meter_Point_No = e.mpxn and e.disputedReadDate >= a.Start_Date

)

SELECT a.Account_No

      ,a.Fuel
      ,a.disputedReadDate

      ,a.workRequired 
      ,a.disputedReadValues 
      ,if(status in ("Agreed", "Agreed-Pending","Agreed-Complete", "Cancelled"), true, false) Is_Closed
      ,a.metadata
FROM latest_account a
WHERE a.Row_Num = 1

query.1036:
With
cte_data_with_calcs
As
(
SELECT *
,
(SELECT Round(SUM(proposedReadDiff))
FROM UNNEST(l.registers) x) AS totalProposedReadDiff,
(SELECT Round(SUM(totalAdjustedDifference))
FROM UNNEST(l.registers) x) AS totalTotalAdjustedDifference,
(SELECT Round(SUM(LastIndustryToPriorReadDifference ))
FROM UNNEST(l.registers) x) AS totalPriorReadDiff,
(SELECT Round(SUM(priorReadAge))
FROM UNNEST(l.registers) x) AS totalPriorReadAge
FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_loss_data_extract` l
)
Select
Distinct
mpan,
reg.latestIndustryReadMSN as msn,
PARSE_DATE('%d/%m/%Y', disputedReadDate) as readingDate,
reg.timeOfUseLabel,
Case
When reg.isTvr = 1 and totalProposedReadDiff < 350 and reg.latestIndustryReadType = 'C' Then reg.latestIndustryReadValue
When reg.isTvr = 1 and totalTotalAdjustedDifference < 350 and reg.latestIndustryReadType = 'C' Then reg.TotalAdjustedIndustry
Else
reg.latestIndustryReadValue
End as reading,
reg.latestIndustryReadType as readingType,
reg.meterType,
reg.backingReadDate,
reg.backingReadUnits,
reg.finalBilledReadType,
reg.finalBilledReadUnits
From
cte_data_with_calcs d
inner join unnest (d.registers) as reg
Left Join
(
    Select Distinct mpxn,
                    DATE(finalReadDateTime, "Europe/London") as finalReadDate,
                    min(createdAt) as createdAt
    From `product_andromeda_secure.consumption_loss_adjustments`
    Group By        mpxn,
                    DATE(finalReadDateTime, "Europe/London")
)
 ela on d.mpan = ela.mpxn and PARSE_DATE('%d/%m/%Y', disputedReadDate) = ela.finalReadDate
Where
-- those where the tardis deemed estimate or an actual from within 5 days is within tolerance
(totalProposedReadDiff <= 250
-- extends tolerance to 350 for customer reads
OR
(totalProposedReadDiff < 350 and reg.latestIndustryReadType = 'C')
-- apply tolerance to Total Adjusted industry read
OR
(reg.isTvr = 1 and totalTotalAdjustedDifference < 350 and reg.latestIndustryReadType = 'C')
-- includes those within tolerance of any other latest billed read for the same day
OR
(totalPriorReadDiff <= 250 --and totalPriorReadAge = 0
)
OR
(totalPriorReadDiff < 350 and reg.latestIndustryReadType = 'C')
OR
totalProposedReadDiff is null
)
-- not got a dispute
and TardisInitiatedAt is null
-- not already got a loss adjustment
and lossAdjustmentCreatedAt is null
-- where the industry read msn match the orion billing
and reg.latestIndustryReadMSN = reg.priorBilledReadMSN
-- up to 11 months old
and PARSE_DATE('%d/%m/%Y', disputedReadDate) > date_add(current_date, interval - 11 month)
-- where there is not already a finalRead type read for the loss date
and finalBilledReadUnits is null
--final check there are no loss adjustments
and ela.mpxn is null
query.1038:
WITH cte_elec_gains AS
(
Select reg.mpanCore as MPAN,
PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", substr(reg.effectiveFromSettlementDateRegi,1,8)) as SSD,
reg.SmetsVersion
From `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_D0217001_POST_DTC10_7_split` d217,
Unnest (record.FileSequenceNumber.registrationConfirmationDetails) reg
where reg.profileClassId = '1'
UNION ALL
Select reg.mpanCore as MPAN,
PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", substr(reg.effectiveFromSettlementDateRegi,1,8)) as SSD,
reg.SmetsVersion
From `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_D0217002_split`  d217,
Unnest (record.FileSequenceNumber.registrationConfirmationDetails) reg
where reg.profileClassId = '1'
)
,

cte_elec_reading_dedupe as
(
  select d86.record.MpanCores.mpanCore as mpxn,
         d86.record.MpanCores.bscValidationStatus as bscValidationStatus,
         mrt.meterIdSerialNumber as msn,
         mrt.readingType as readingType,
         rr.meterRegisterId as registerId,
         PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", SUBSTR(rr.readingDateTime, 1, 8)) as readingDate,
         cast(rr.registerReading as float64) as readingKwh,
         header.fileCreationTimestamp,
         universal_metadata.createdAt,
         rank() over (partition by record.MpanCores.mpanCore, rr.readingDateTime
                      order by header.fileCreationTimestamp desc, universal_metadata.createdAt desc, kafkaData.insertTime desc) as reading_dedupe_rank
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_D0086002_split__no_dedupe` d86,
  unnest(record.MpanCores.meterReadingType) mrt,
  unnest(mrt.registerReadings) rr
  where mrt.readingType <> 'F' and mrt.readingType <> 'W'
),
cte_industry_reads as
(
  select mpxn,
         msn,
         readingType,
         readingDate,
         sum(readingKwh) as readingUnits
  from cte_elec_reading_dedupe r
  where reading_dedupe_rank = 1
    and bscValidationStatus = 'V'
  group by mpxn, msn, readingType, readingDate
)
,
  cte_sfe_gain_read AS (
  SELECT
    servicePointNo as MPAN,
    requestedSwitchTime as SSD,
    CAST(processTime AS Date) AS sfeReadDate,
    deviceNo as MSN,
    initialReading 
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_SFE_COSGAINRESPONSE_validated`
  WHERE
    switchStatus = 7 )
    ,
 
 cte_disputes AS (
Select
MPAN_MPRN as MPAN,
extract (date from DisputedReadDate) as DisputedDate,
CurrentStatus
From
`source-data-mirror-prod.BC_OVO_Applications_internal.Dispute` 
Where UtilityType = 'E'
and IsMissingDispute = 'F'
)

Select distinct g.mpan,g.ssd,r.msn,r.readingUnits, r.readingType, sr.InitialReading, g.SmetsVersion,
    case when r.msn like '14P%' Then 'SECURE'
    when r.msn like '15P%' Then 'SECURE'
    when r.msn like '16P%' Then 'SECURE'
    when r.msn like '17P%' Then 'SECURE'
    when r.msn like '18P%' Then 'SECURE'
    when r.msn like '18P%' Then 'SECURE'
    Else 'NOT Secure' End as MeterType, 
    CASE
      WHEN r.mpxn IS NULL THEN 'Missing'
      WHEN r.readingType IN ('A','C', 'I', 'P') THEN 'Actual'
      WHEN r.readingType = 'D' THen 'Estimated'
      Else 'Other'
    END as ReadStatus
    ,
    case
    when d.mpan is not null then 1 else 0
    End as HasDispute
From
cte_elec_gains g
left join cte_industry_reads r
on g.MPAN = r.MPxN
and g.SSD = r.readingDate
LEFT JOIN
  cte_sfe_gain_read sr
ON
  g.mpan = sr.mpan

query.1039:

meter_details_at_gain

)
,
spam_data AS

,


OMR_data

readDate,

)

,

cte_email
as

cte_ordered_events AS

 metadata.createdAt ,

)


,
OMR_rac
AS
(
Select
kafkaData.InsertTime,
event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.msn,

DATE(event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime, "Europe/London") as ReadingDate,

tier,

row_number() over (partition by event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.msn, event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime, tier Order by event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.msn, event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.readingDateTime, tier, kafkaData.InsertTime desc) as row_num
From `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_manual_read_submitted_v2` ms
Inner Join unnest(ms.event.ElectricityManualReadingEvent.tiers) t
)

SELECT
       r.accountId,
       r.mpxn, 
       r.ssd as registrationSSD,
       s.SupplyStartDate as spamSSD,
       dc.dc,
       s.MSN as spamMSN,
       s.meterRegisterID,
       s.timeOfUseLabel,
       e.status as omrCommsStatus,
       e.channel as omrEmailType,
       e.lastAction as omrEmailTypeLastAction,
       omr.readDate as submittedOmrReadDate,
       omr.read as submittedOmrRead,
       ir.readingUnits as industryRead,
       ir.readingType as industryReadType,
       --ir.readingDate as industryReadingDate,
       rr.readingType as processedReadType,
       rr.readingValue as processedReadValue,
       con.fromDate as consumptionFromDate,
       con.fromMeterReading as consumptionFromRead,
       con.fromReadingType as consumptionFromReadType,
       con.toDate as consumptionToDate,
       con.toMeterReading as consumptionToRead,
       con.toReadingType as consumptionToReadType

--        ARRAY (SELECT AS STRUCT 
--       *
--       From
--       registrations r
--       inner join cte_meter_registers 
--       left join OMR_data omr
--       left Join cte_first_elec_reading_dedupe
--       where r.mpxn = omr.mpxn) as reads  

FROM registrations r
LEFT JOIN meter_details_at_gain s on r.mpxn = s.mpxn and r.ssd <= s.supplyStartDate
LEFT JOIN cte_DC_appointment dc on r.mpxn = dc.mpan and r.ssd = dc.ssd
LEFT JOIN OMR_data omr on r.mpxn = omr.mpxn and s.timeOfUseLabel = omr.timeOfUseLabel and omr.row_num = 1
Left JOIN cte_first_elec_reading_dedupe ir on s.mpxn = ir.mpxn and s.supplyStartDate = ir.readingDate and ir.reading_dedupe_rank = 1 and ir.registerID = s.meterRegisterID and ir.msn = s.msn
Left Join OMR_rac rr on s.msn = rr.msn and s.supplyStartDate = rr.readingDate  and (s.tier = rr.tier or s.tier is null) and rr.row_num = 1

left join cte_email e on r.accountId = e.AccountNo
Left Join cancelled_registrations c on r.mpxn = c.mpxn and c.latestUpdate = 1
order by r.ssd
query.1041:
With cte_losses_with_calcs AS
 (
 Select
 *,
(SELECT SUM(proposedReadDiff)
FROM UNNEST(l.registers) x) AS proposedReadDiffSum,
(SELECT SUM(priorReadAge)
FROM UNNEST(l.registers) x) AS priorReadAgeSum,
(SELECT SUM(lastestIndustryToPriorReadDiff)
FROM UNNEST(l.registers) x) AS priorReadDiffSum,
From `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tardis_gas_loss_data_extract` l
)
Select
Distinct
mprn,
reg.latestIndustryReadMSN as msn,
reg.latestIndustryReadValue as reading,
Case When reg.latestIndustryReadType = 'URN' Then 'A'
Else reg.latestIndustryReadType
End as readingType,
PARSE_DATE('%d/%m/%Y', disputedReadDate) as readingDate,
From cte_losses_with_calcs d
inner join unnest(d.registers) reg
Left Join
(
    Select Distinct mpxn,
                    DATE(finalReadDateTime, "Europe/London") as finalReadDate,
                    min(createdAt) as createdAt
    From `product_andromeda_secure.consumption_loss_adjustments`
    Group By        mpxn,
                    DATE(finalReadDateTime, "Europe/London")
)
 gla on d.mprn = gla.mpxn and PARSE_DATE('%d/%m/%Y', disputedReadDate) = gla.finalReadDate
where
array_length(registers) = 1
and
(
reg.priorReadMSN = reg.latestIndustryReadMSN
or
reg.priorReadMSN is null
)
and
(
proposedReadDiffSum <= 108
Or
priorReadDiffSum <= 108
or
proposedReadDiffSum is null
)
and TardisInitiatedAt is null
and drsDateRaised is null
and lossAdjustmentCreatedAt is null
and reg.finalBilledReadUnits is null
and gla.mpxn is null
query.1042:
WITH
  cte_gas_gains AS (
  SELECT
    DISTINCT
    mtd.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    ends_with(mtd.meterPointReference,'00') as InCG,
    mtd.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    mtd.meterSerialNumber,
    CASE
      WHEN sd.dccServiceFlag = 'A' THEN 'SMETS2'
      WHEN mtd.meterSerialNumber LIKE 'G4P%' THEN 'SFE SMETS1'
      WHEN mtd.meterSerialNumber LIKE 'G1$P%' THEN 'SFE SMETS1'
      ELSE 'Other'
    END AS meterTypeDerived,
    mtd.meterPointAq,
    mtd.previousSupplierShortCode,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.confirmationEffectiveDate) AS ssd,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.ldzIdentifier,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedDate,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedTime,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.lastRecordedRead,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.lastRecordedReadDate,
    sd.dccServiceFlag
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_TRF_POST_NEXUS_split` trf
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST(trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.address) addr
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST(addr.meterPointDetails) mtd
  LEFT JOIN
    UNNEST(mtd.smartData) sd
  WHERE
    record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedDate IS NOT NULL
    AND mtd.previousSupplierShortCode <> 'OVO' -- exclude loss
    -- AND PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d", trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.confirmationEffectiveDate) = '2018-12-04'
    ),
  cte_gas_reading_union AS (
  SELECT
    'MBR' AS flow,
    -- estimates
    record.Billreads.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    record.Billreads.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    record.Billreads.readType AS readingType,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      record.Billreads.actualReadDate ) AS readingDate,
    CAST(record.Billreads.meterReading AS int64) AS readingVolume,
    header.creationDate,
    header.creationTime,
    universal_metadata.createdAt
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_MBR_POST_NEXUS_split__no_dedupe` mbr
  WHERE
    record.Billreads.meterPointReference IS NOT NULL
  UNION ALL
  SELECT
    'URN' AS flow,
    -- actuals
    record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    'URN' AS readingType,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.actualReadDate) AS readingDate,
    CAST(record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.meterReading AS int64) AS readingVolume,
    header.creationDate,
    header.creationTime,
    universal_metadata.createdAt
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_URN_POST_NEXUS_split__no_dedupe` urn
  WHERE
    record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.meterPointReference IS NOT NULL ),
  cte_gas_reading_dedupe AS -- latest read
  (
  SELECT
    gru.mpxn,
    gru.msn,
    gru.readingType,
    gru.readingDate,
    gru.readingVolume,
    gru.creationDate,
    gru.creationTime,
    gru.createdAt,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY gru.mpxn, gru.readingDate ORDER BY gru.flow DESC, gru.creationDate DESC, gru.creationTime DESC, gru.createdAt DESC) AS reading_dedupe_rownum
  FROM
    cte_gas_reading_union gru ),
  cte_umr_opening_read AS (
  SELECT
    umr.record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      record.UnbundledMeterRead.actualReadDate) AS readDate,
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterReadingSource AS readSource,
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterReadingReason AS readReason,
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterReading AS reading,
    header.creationDate,
    header.creationTime,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY umr.record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterPointReference, record.UnbundledMeterRead.actualReadDate ORDER BY header.creationDate DESC, header.creationTime DESC) AS omr_reading_dedupe_rownum
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_UMR_POST_NEXUS_split` umr
  WHERE
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterReadingReason = 'O' ),
  cte_sfe_gain_read AS (
  SELECT
    servicePointNo,
    requestedSwitchTime,
    CAST(processTime AS Date) AS sfeReadDate,
    deviceNo,
    initialVolume
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_SFE_COSGAINRESPONSE_validated`
  WHERE
    switchStatus = 7 )

  SELECT
  g.metertypederived,
  g.ssd,
  g.InCG,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN g.mpxn IS NULL THEN 0
      ELSE 1
    END ) AS totalGains,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN omr.mpxn IS NULL THEN 0
      ELSE 1
    END ) AS omrSubmitted,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN r.mpxn IS NULL THEN 0
      ELSE 1
    END ) AS industryReceived,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN r.readingType IS NULL THEN 0
      WHEN r.readingType = 'URN' THEN 1
      WHEN sr.InitialVolume < (readingvolume - 108) OR sr.InitialVolume > (readingvolume + 108) THEN 0
      WHEN sr.InitialVolume > (readingvolume - 108)
    AND sr.InitialVolume < (readingvolume + 108) THEN 1
    END ) AS inToleranceOfSmartOrActual
FROM
  cte_gas_gains g
LEFT JOIN
  cte_gas_reading_dedupe r
ON
  g.mpxn = r.mpxn
  AND ((readingtype = 'URN'
      AND r.readingdate BETWEEN DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL -5 Day)
      AND DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL 5 Day)
      OR r.readingdate = ssd))
LEFT JOIN
  cte_sfe_gain_read sr
ON
  g.mpxn = sr.servicePointNo
  AND sr.sfeReadDate BETWEEN DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL -5 Day)
  AND DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL 5 Day)
LEFT JOIN
  cte_umr_opening_read omr
ON
  g.mpxn = omr.mpxn
  AND omr.readdate BETWEEN DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL -5 Day)
  AND DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL 5 Day)
WHERE
  (reading_dedupe_rownum IS NULL
    OR reading_dedupe_rownum = 1)
  AND (omr_reading_dedupe_rownum IS NULL
    OR omr_reading_dedupe_rownum = 1)
GROUP BY
  g.metertypederived,
  g.ssd,
  g.InCG
ORDER BY
  g.ssd DESC,
  g.metertypederived
query.1044:
WITH
  cte_gas_gains AS (
  SELECT
    DISTINCT mtd.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    mtd.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    mtd.numberofdialsordigits,
    mtd.correctionfactor,
    mtd.meterSerialNumber,
    CASE
      WHEN sd.dccServiceFlag = 'A' THEN 'SMETS2'
      WHEN mtd.meterSerialNumber LIKE 'G4P%' THEN 'SFE SMETS1'
      WHEN mtd.meterSerialNumber LIKE 'G1$P%' THEN 'SFE SMETS1'
      ELSE 'Other'
    END AS meterTypeDerived,
    cast(mtd.meterPointAq as float64) as AQ,
    mtd.previousSupplierShortCode,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.confirmationEffectiveDate) AS ssd,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.ldzIdentifier,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedDate,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedTime,
    safe_cast(trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.lastRecordedRead as int64) as lastRecordedRead,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",nullif(trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.lastRecordedReadDate,'')) as lastReadDate,
    sd.dccServiceFlag
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_TRF_POST_NEXUS_split` trf
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST(trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.address) addr
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST(addr.meterPointDetails) mtd
  LEFT JOIN
    UNNEST(mtd.smartData) sd
  WHERE
    record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedDate IS NOT NULL
    AND mtd.previousSupplierShortCode <> 'OVO' -- exclude loss
    ),
    cte_Prep_data AS
(
SELECT
  *, 
  (((((((AQ / 365) * (DATE_DIFF(ssd, lastReadDate, DAY)) * 3.6) / 39.5) / 1) / 1.02264))) as calc_dif,
  CASE
  --#below are the validation rules as confirmed in settlement BRDs (with some new bands added in change requests) These will be used to validate read advances to see if they fall in line 
    WHEN AQ = 1                       THEN 20000.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 2	  AND 100     THEN 200.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 101   AND 200     THEN 100.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 201   AND 500     THEN 40.00 
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 501   AND 1000    THEN 20.00 
    WHEN AQ between 1001  AND 5000    THEN 4.00 
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 5001  AND 10000   THEN 2.00 
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 10001 AND 20000   THEN 1.50 
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 20001 AND 73200   THEN 3.00 
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 73201 and 732000  THEN 2.50 
  ELSE NULL 
  END AS Tol_Flag_Upper_Limit, -- Each AQ band has a different multiplication value depending on the AQ XOSERVE hold.
  CASE
    WHEN AQ = 1                       THEN 70000.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 2     AND 100     THEN 450.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 101   AND 200     THEN 250.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 201   AND 500     THEN 550.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 501   AND 1000    THEN 250.00
    WHEN AQ between 1001  AND 5000    THEN 70.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 5001  AND 10000   THEN 20.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 10001 AND 20000   THEN 10.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 20001 AND 73200   THEN 10.00
    WHEN AQ BETWEEN 73201 and 732000  THEN 10.00
  ELSE NULL
  END AS MBT_Tol_Upper_Limit  
from cte_gas_gains
),

cte_calc_consumption as
( -- Calculates the threshold reads to either break into Lower Tolerance, or Market Breaker Tolerances
SELECT
 *,
 lastRecordedRead + (Tol_Flag_Upper_Limit * calc_dif)      AS Tol_Flag_Read,
 lastRecordedRead + (MBT_Tol_Upper_Limit  * calc_dif)      AS MBT_Flag_Read
from cte_Prep_data
-- If the read is between Tol_Flag_Read and MBT_Flag_Read, then a Tolerance Override Flag is needed for read submission
-- If above MBT_Flag_Read, then the read wil not be validated by XOSERVE without other site action (AQ correction etc)
-- If read below Tol_Flag_Read, then can be submitted without override flag for validation
),
  cte_gas_reading_union AS (
  SELECT
    'MBR' AS flow,
    -- estimates
    record.Billreads.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    record.Billreads.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    record.Billreads.readType AS readingType,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      record.Billreads.actualReadDate ) AS readingDate,
    CAST(record.Billreads.meterReading AS int64) AS readingVolume,
    header.creationDate,
    header.creationTime,
    universal_metadata.createdAt
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_MBR_POST_NEXUS_split__no_dedupe` mbr
  WHERE
    record.Billreads.meterPointReference IS NOT NULL
  UNION ALL
  SELECT
    'URN' AS flow,
    -- actuals
    record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    'URN' AS readingType,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.actualReadDate) AS readingDate,
    CAST(record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.meterReading AS int64) AS readingVolume,
    header.creationDate,
    header.creationTime,
    universal_metadata.createdAt
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_URN_POST_NEXUS_split__no_dedupe` urn
  WHERE
    record.OpeningUnbundledReadNotice.meterPointReference IS NOT NULL ),
  cte_gas_reading_dedupe AS -- latest read
  (
  SELECT
    gru.mpxn,
    gru.msn,
    gru.readingType,
    gru.readingDate,
    gru.readingVolume,
    gru.creationDate,
    gru.creationTime,
    gru.createdAt,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY gru.mpxn, gru.readingDate ORDER BY gru.flow DESC, gru.creationDate DESC, gru.creationTime DESC, gru.createdAt DESC) AS reading_dedupe_rownum
  FROM
    cte_gas_reading_union gru ),
  cte_umr_opening_read AS (
  SELECT
    umr.record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      record.UnbundledMeterRead.actualReadDate) AS readDate,
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterReadingSource AS readSource,
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterReadingReason AS readReason,
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterReading AS reading,
    header.creationDate,
    header.creationTime,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY umr.record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterPointReference, record.UnbundledMeterRead.actualReadDate ORDER BY header.creationDate DESC, header.creationTime DESC) AS omr_reading_dedupe_rownum
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_UMR_POST_NEXUS_split` umr
  WHERE
    record.UnbundledMeterRead.meterReadingReason = 'O' ),
  cte_sfe_gain_read AS (
  SELECT
    servicePointNo,
    requestedSwitchTime,
    CAST(processTime AS Date) AS sfeReadDate,
    deviceNo,
    initialVolume
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_SFE_COSGAINRESPONSE_validated`
  WHERE
    switchStatus = 7 )

SELECT distinct
    g.metertypederived,
    g.ssd,
    g.mpxn,
    g.AQ,
    cc.Tol_Flag_Read,
    cc.MBT_Flag_Read,
    sr.initialvolume as smartRead,
    g.lastRecordedRead as previousRead,
    r.readingType as industryType,
    r.readingVolume as industryVolume,
    CASE
      WHEN omr.mpxn IS NULL THEN 0
      ELSE 1
    END AS omrSubmitted,
    CASE
      WHEN r.mpxn IS NULL THEN 'Missing'
      WHEN r.readingType = 'URN' THEN 'Actual'
      WHEN sr.InitialVolume < (readingvolume - 108) OR sr.InitialVolume > (readingvolume + 108) THEN 'Outside Tolerance'
      WHEN sr.InitialVolume > (readingvolume - 108) AND sr.InitialVolume < (readingvolume + 108) THEN 'Inside Tolerance'
      WHen sr.InitialVolume is Null and r.ReadingType <> 'URN' Then 'Unknown'
      Else 'Other'
    END
    AS ReadStatus,
    Case when sr.initialvolume > tol_flag_read then 'Smart_Above_Tol' Else 'Smart_Below_Tol' End as XoSTol
    
FROM
  cte_gas_gains g
LEFT JOIN
  cte_gas_reading_dedupe r
ON
  g.mpxn = r.mpxn
  AND ((readingtype = 'URN'
      AND r.readingdate BETWEEN DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL -5 Day)
      AND DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL 5 Day)
      OR r.readingdate = ssd))
LEFT JOIN
  cte_sfe_gain_read sr
ON
  g.mpxn = sr.servicePointNo
  AND sr.sfeReadDate BETWEEN DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL -5 Day)
  AND DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL 5 Day)
LEFT JOIN
  cte_umr_opening_read omr
ON
  g.mpxn = omr.mpxn
  AND omr.readdate BETWEEN DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL -5 Day)
  AND DATE_ADD(ssd, INTERVAL 5 Day)
left join
    cte_calc_consumption cc
on g.mpxn = cc.mpxn and g.ssd = cc.ssd
WHERE
  (reading_dedupe_rownum IS NULL
    OR reading_dedupe_rownum = 1)
  AND (omr_reading_dedupe_rownum IS NULL
    OR omr_reading_dedupe_rownum = 1)

query.1049:
WITH
  cte_gas_gains AS (
  SELECT
    DISTINCT mtd.meterPointReference AS mpxn,
    mtd.meterSerialNumber AS msn,
    mtd.numberofdialsordigits,
    mtd.correctionfactor,
    mtd.meterSerialNumber,
    CASE
      WHEN sd.dccServiceFlag = 'A' THEN 'SMETS2'
      WHEN mtd.meterSerialNumber LIKE 'G4P%' THEN 'SFE SMETS1'
      WHEN mtd.meterSerialNumber LIKE 'G1$P%' THEN 'SFE SMETS1'
      ELSE 'Other'
    END AS meterTypeDerived,
    CAST(mtd.meterPointAq AS float64) AS AQ,
    mtd.previousSupplierShortCode,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.confirmationEffectiveDate) AS ssd,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.ldzIdentifier,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedDate,
    trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedTime,
    SAFE_CAST(trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.lastRecordedRead AS int64) AS lastRecordedRead,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      nullif(trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.lastRecordedReadDate,
        '')) AS lastReadDate,
    sd.dccServiceFlag
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_TRF_POST_NEXUS_split` trf
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST(trf.record.TransferOfOwnership.address) addr
  INNER JOIN
    UNNEST(addr.meterPointDetails) mtd
  LEFT JOIN
    UNNEST(mtd.smartData) sd
  WHERE
    record.TransferOfOwnership.recordedDate IS NOT NULL
    AND mtd.previousSupplierShortCode <> 'OVO' -- exclude loss
    ),
  
  
  cte_opening_failures AS (
  SELECT
    header.creationDate,
    header.creationTime,
    urs.record.UnbundledReadRejection.meterPointReference AS MPxN,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      urs.record.UnbundledReadRejection.actualReadDate) AS readDate,
    rej.rejectionReason
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_URS_split` urs
  LEFT JOIN
    UNNEST(record.UnbundledReadRejection.rejectionDetail) rej
  WHERE
    record.UnbundledReadRejection.meterReadingReason = 'O')
    
    
  , cte_opening_acceptance AS
  
  (
   SELECT
    header.creationDate,
    header.creationTime,
    record.UnbundledAcceptedReadNotification.meterPointReference AS MPxN,
    PARSE_DATE("%Y%m%d",
      record.UnbundledAcceptedReadNotification.actualReadDate) AS readDate
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_URS_split` urs
  WHERE
    record.UnbundledAcceptedReadNotification.meterReadingReason = 'O')
  
  
    
SELECT distinct
  g.metertypederived,
  g.mpxn,
  g.ssd,
  f.rejectionReason,
  f.creationDate,
  case
  When a.mpxn is Not Null Then 'Accepted'
  when r.RejectionDescription is null then f.rejectionReason
  Else r.RejectionDescription
  End as URSResult
FROM
  cte_gas_gains g
Left JOIN
  cte_opening_failures f
ON
  g.mpxn = f.mpxn
  AND f.readDate BETWEEN DATE_ADD(g.ssd, INTERVAL -5 Day) AND date_add(g.ssd, INTERVAL +5 Day)
  left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tardis_gas_rejection_reasons` r
  on f.rejectionReason = r.rejectionCode

left join
cte_opening_acceptance a
on
g.mpxn = a.mpxn
AND
a.readDate BETWEEN DATE_ADD(g.ssd, INTERVAL -5 Day) AND date_add(g.ssd, INTERVAL +5 Day)

With cte_ordered_reads
AS
(
With cte_union_topics as
(
SELECT
    metaData.createdAt
    ,mpan 
    ,msn
    ,fromDate
    ,f.reading as fromMeterReading
    ,fromReading.readingType AS fromReadingType
    ,toDate
    ,t.reading AS toMeterReading
    ,toReading.readingType AS toReadingType
    ,c.clockingTimeId
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v5` 
  INNER JOIN  UNNEST(fromReading.registers) AS f
  INNER JOIN  UNNEST(toReading.registers) AS t ON t.tier = f.tier
  INNER JOIN  UNNEST(consumption.registers) AS c ON c.tier = f.tier
Union All
SELECT
metaData.createdAt as createdAt,
mpan,
msn,
date(fromDateTime, "Europe/London") as fromDate,
t.fromMeterReading as fromMeterReading,
t.fromReadingType as fromReadingType,
date(toDateTime, "Europe/London") as toDate,
t.toMeterReading as toMeterReading,
t.toReadingType as toReadingType,
t.clockingTimeId
FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.rac_mpxn_electricity_consumption_generated_v4`
inner join unnest (tiers) t
)
Select
createdAt,
mpan,
msn,
toDate,
toMeterReading,
toReadingType,
fromDate,
fromMeterReading,
fromReadingType,
clockingTimeId,
ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY mpan,
msn,
toDate, clockingTimeId ORDER BY createdAt DESC) AS latest_consumption
From cte_union_topics
)

SELECT * FROM cte_ordered_reads
where latest_consumption = 1

/*
Name: Tariff_Payment_Mismatch
Description: Flags accounts with no DD setup on a DD tariff
Author: Alex Ashford
Created Date: 2020-07-23
Reviewed By: Pete Diwell
*/

WITH tariff_deats as (
    SELECT DISTINCT ac.tariff.tariffId 
                   ,ac.tariff.paymentMethod 
                   ,ac.tariff.planName 
                   ,ac.tariff.planDisplayName 
                   ,ac.tariff.region 
                   ,ac.tariff.retailer 
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_supply_point_tariff_costs_v6` t
    LEFT JOIN UNNEST(t.annualTariffCosts) ac
)

SELECT DISTINCT c.serviceAccountId as Account_No
               ,c.mpxn as MPXN
               ,c.fuel as Fuel
               ,c.contractId as Contract_ID
               ,c.tariffId as Tariff_ID
               ,c.tariffType as Tariff_Type
               ,COALESCE(t.planName,c.planName) as Tariff_Name
               ,t.planDisplayName as Tariff_Display_Name
               ,t.paymentMethod as Tariff_Payment_Method
               ,c.endDate as Contract_End_Date
               ,IFNULL(s.Is_Active_Subscription,0) Has_DD
               #,s.Subscription_Created_Date 
               #,s.DD_Day_Of_Month 
               #,s.DD_Amount 
FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` c
LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_payments.subscriptions` s ON s.Account_No = c.serviceAccountId and s.Is_Active_Subscription = 1
LEFT JOIN tariff_deats t on t.tariffId = c.tariffId
WHERE c.contractStatus = 'active'
AND (t.paymentMethod = 'Direct Debit' AND IFNULL(s.Is_Active_Subscription,0) = 0) #To filter DD contracts where account has not DD
AND (c.tariffType = 'variable' OR c.endDate < '2020-10-01')
ORDER BY 1

         upserted_versionId as versionId,
         upserted_versionDescription as versionDescription,
         upserted_activeFrom as activeFrom,
         upserted_activeTo as activeTo,
         -- Tariff key components
         upserted_fuel as fuel,
         upserted_planName as planName,
         upserted_profileClass as profileClass,
         upserted_region as region,
         upserted_retailer as retailer,

         -- Other attributes
         upserted_type as type,
         upserted_length as `length`,
         upserted_standingRate as standingRate,
         upserted_unitRates as unitRates,
         upserted_unitRate as unitRate,
         upserted_exitFee as exitFee,
         upserted_createdAt as latestCreatedAt,
         row_number() over (partition by upserted_tariffId, upserted_versionId order by topic desc, upserted_createdAt desc, insertTime desc) as dedupe_rownum
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_tariff__no_dedupe` ups
  where ups.upserted_eventId is not null
),
cte_cancelled as

  select cancelled_tariffId as tariffId,
         cancelled_versionId as versionId,

  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.energy_contracts_tariff__no_dedupe`
  where cancelled_eventId is not NULL
  group by cancelled_tariffId, cancelled_versionId
)

from cte_tariff_version_dedupe cr

where cr.dedupe_rownum = 1
  and canc.tariffId is null
