with cte as
(
  with cte_d300_order as
  (
    select init.mpxn, init.disputedReadDate, init.initiatedAt,
           d300.metadata.rawSourcePath, d300.header.toMarketParticipantId, d300.record.MpanDetails.meteringPointAddressLine1, d300.record.MpanDetails.meteringPointAddressLine2,
           agr.agreedAt, rej.rejectedAt, rej.rejectionCode, 
           row_number() over (partition by init.mpxn order by d300.metadata.createdAt) as d300_order
    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_initiated` init
    left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.flow_D0300001_split` d300 on init.mpxn = d300.record.MpanDetails.mpanCore
                                                             and d300.metadata.createdAt > init.metadata.createdAt
                                                             and d300.header.fromMarketParticipantId = 'OVOE'                                                           
    left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_agreed` agr on init.mpxn = agr.mpxn
    left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.tardis_elec_dispute_rejected` rej on init.mpxn = rej.mpxn
  )
  select distinct d1.*, d2.meteringPointAddressLine2 as line2_on_2nd_d300,
         case when d1.agreedAt is not null then 1 else 0 end as agreedCount,
         case when d1.rejectedAt is not null then 1 else 0 end as rejectedCount,
         case when d2.meteringPointAddressLine2 is not null then 1 else 0 end as requiredNewFlow,
         case
          when d1.meteringPointAddressLine2 <> '' then 'Hopefully right first time'
          when d1.agreedAt is not null and d2.meteringPointAddressLine2 is not null then 'Agreed after new flow sent'
          when d1.agreedAt is not null and d2.meteringPointAddressLine2 is null then 'Agreed without the need for new flow'
          when d2.meteringPointAddressLine2 is not null then 'Not yet agreed but new flow sent'
          when d2.meteringPointAddressLine2 is null then 'Not yet agreed, no new flow sent'
         end as status
  from cte_d300_order d1
  left join cte_d300_order d2 on d1.mpxn = d2.mpxn
                             and d2.meteringPointAddressLine2 <> ''
                             and d2.initiatedAt < '2019-11-25'
  where d1.d300_order = 1
  order by initiatedAt desc
),
cte_replacement_d86s as
(
  select d.mpxn, d.lossDate, d.sfeGainingSupplier, d.sfeCosLossReadingUnits, d.finalReadingUnits, d.d86ReadingUnits
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys_detailed` d
  where d.serviceAccountId is not null
  and d.fuel = 'electricity'
  and d.finalReadingUnits <> d.d86ReadingUnits
)
select c.*
from cte c
left join cte_replacement_d86s as r on c.mpxn = r.mpxn
where status = 'Not yet agreed, no new flow sent'
  and rejectedAt is null
  and initiatedAT > '2019-09-01'
  and r.mpxn is null
query.1060:
/*
Name: identity_user
Author: Alex Ashford
Created Date Date: 2020-07-08
Description: Provides a view of the latest customer data from identity
Updated: 2020-08-24
Update Desc: Move to identity users topic
Reviewed By: Amane Toda
*/

#Get latest create event
WITH created as (
    SELECT u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.id as Customer_ID
          ,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.title as Title
          ,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.givenName as First_Name
          ,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.familyName as Last_Name
          ,TRIM(CONCAT(IFNULL(u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.givenName,''),' ',IFNULL(u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.familyName,''))) as Full_Name
          ,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.birthdate as DOB
          ,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.emailAddress as Private_Email
          ,CAST(NULL AS STRING) as Work_Email
          ,CAST(NULL AS STRING) as Work_Phone
          ,CAST(FLOOR(DATE_DIFF(CURRENT_DATE(), u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.birthdate, DAY) / 365.25) AS INT64) as Age
          ,TRIM(CONCAT(IFNULL(u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.title,'') ,' ' ,IFNULL(u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.givenName,''),' ',IFNULL(u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.familyName,''))) as Mail_Merge_Name
          ,TRIM(CONCAT(IFNULL(u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.title,'') ,' ',IFNULL(u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.familyName,''))) as Mail_Merge_Salutation
          ,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.enabled as User_Enabled
          ,u.kafkaData.insertTime as Last_Updated
          ,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.phoneNumbers as Phone_Numbers
          ,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.marketingPreferences as Marketing_Preferences
          # Extra fields in the table, could include later
          #,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.formattedAddresses
          #,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.postalAddress 
          #,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.requiredActions 
          #,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.permissions
          #,u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.specialCommPreferences 
          #,u.realm --Think this will be brand
         ,ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.id ORDER BY u.kafkaData.insertTime DESC, u.kafkaData.offset DESC) Row_Num
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_identity_secure.identity_users` u
    WHERE u.event.Deleted.id IS NULL
),

#Filter to latest event
latest as (
    SELECT c.* EXCEPT(Row_Num)
    FROM created c 
    WHERE c.Row_Num = 1
),

#Get delete events
deleted as (
    SELECT u.event.Deleted.id as Customer_ID
          ,u.kafkaData.insertTime as Last_Updated
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_identity_secure.identity_users` u
    WHERE u.event.CreatedOrUpdate.user.id IS NULL
)

#Remove customers with a delete event
SELECT c.* 
FROM latest c 
LEFT JOIN deleted d on d.Customer_ID = c.Customer_ID and d.Last_Updated > c.Last_Updated
WHERE d.Customer_ID IS NULL
query.1061:
/*
Name: Account_Supply_Points
Description: View of Orion Supply Point Statuses
Author: Alex Ashford
Created At: 2020-07-28
Code outright stolen from: https://github.com/ovotech/Delta_Force_BQ_Data_Processing/blob/master/alignment_orion/consumer.sql
Reviewed By: Pete Diwell
*/

WITH orionOnboardingSequencer as (
    SELECT coalesce(event.AccountSupplyPointCreated.accountId,event.AccountSupplyPointCancelled.accountId) as Account_No,
           coalesce(cast(cast(event.AccountSupplyPointCreated.supplyPoint as int64) as string),event.AccountSupplyPointCancelled.supplyPoint) as Meter_Point_No,
           event.AccountSupplyPointCreated.supplyStartDate as Consumer_Supply_Start_Date,
           first_value(event.AccountSupplyPointCreated.supplyStartDate ) over(partition by coalesce(event.AccountSupplyPointCreated.accountId, event.AccountSupplyPointCancelled.accountId),
                                                                                          coalesce(cast(cast(event.AccountSupplyPointCreated.supplyPoint as int64) as string),event.AccountSupplyPointCancelled.supplyPoint)
                                                                              order by metadata.createdAt ASC ) as Switch_Request_Date,
           metadata.createdAt	as Created_Datetime,
           row_number() over(partition by coalesce(event.AccountSupplyPointCreated.accountId,event.AccountSupplyPointCancelled.accountId),
                                          coalesce(cast(cast(event.AccountSupplyPointCreated.supplyPoint as int64) as string),event.AccountSupplyPointCancelled.supplyPoint)
                             order by metadata.createdAt DESC) as Sequencer,
           case when event.AccountSupplyPointCancelled.supplyPoint	 is not null then 1 else 0 end as Is_Cancelled
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_onboarding_secure.orion_onboarding_supply_point_account_binding_v1`
),

cteOrionOnboarding as (
    select oos.account_no,
           CAST(cast(oos.meter_point_no as int64) AS STRING) AS meter_point_no,
           oos.meter_point_no as Installation_No,
           oos.consumer_supply_start_date,
           oos.created_datetime,
           signup.installation_signup_id as Ontrack_Installation_ID,
           signup.signup_date as Sales_Date,
           cast(NULL as date) AS Switch_Confirmed_Date,
           cast(NULL as string) as Switch_New_Retailer,
           oos.Switch_Request_Date,
           cast(NULL as string) AS Tax_Class_Code,
           signup.installation_signup_id as Consumer_Global_ID,
           signup.installation_signup_id as Sales_System_Installation_ID,
           signup.agent_code,
           signup.campaign_code,
           signup.agent as Sales_Agent,
           signup.signup_channel as Sales_Channel,
           cast(NULL as string) as Sales_Media_Code,
           signup.external_signup_reference as Sales_Ref,
           signup.external_signup_reference as External_Signup_Reference,
           case when STRPOS(signup.agent,' ') <> 0 then trim(substr(signup.agent,STRPOS(signup.agent,' '),100)) end as Sales_Agent_Username,
           signup.Broker_Partner_Code,
           signup.How_Customer_Heard_Code,
           signup.Is_Direct,
           signup.Sales_Team,
           signup.Sales_Agency,
           signup.Broker_Name,
           signup.Is_Initiated_By_Sales_Agent,
           signup.Signup_Channel_Medium as Sales_Channel_Medium
    from orionOnboardingSequencer oos
    inner join (
        select ins.*,
               acc.account_no
        from `data-engineering-prod.staging_reporting_sales.v_Installation_Signup` ins
        inner join `data-engineering-prod.staging_reporting_sales.v_Account_Signup` acc on ins.account_signup_id = acc.account_signup_id
    ) signup on oos.meter_point_no = signup.meter_point_no and oos.account_no = signup.account_no 
    where sequencer = 1
    and is_cancelled = 0 --may want to reintroduce this if needs be.
),

cteOrionLifecycleStatusUpdates as (
    select message.acquisitionId	as acquisitionId,
           message.accountId as account_no,
           CAST(cast(message.mpxn as int64) AS STRING) as meter_point_no,
           message.supplyStartDate,
           message.status,
           metadata.createdAt,
           row_number() over(partition by message.accountId,CAST(cast(message.mpxn as int64) AS STRING) order by metadata.createdAt desc) as deduper -- we want the latest so in descending fashion
    from `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_onboarding_secure.orion_onboarding_registration_update_v1`
),

supply_point_state AS (
    select SPLIT(accountId,'-')[OFFSET(0)] as Account_No,
           accountId as serviceAccountId,
           CAST(safe_cast(mpxns.supplyPoint as INT64) AS STRING) as Meter_Point_No,
           date(mpxns.start,'Europe/London') as Supply_Start_Date,
           date_add(date(mpxns.end,'Europe/London'),interval -1 day) as Supply_End_Date, --BAST go up until the end of the day, so take a day off.
           UPPER(SUBSTR(mpxns.fuel,1,1)) as Utility_Type_Code,
           mpxns.fuel as Fuel_Type,
           row_number() over(partition by accountId,CAST(safe_cast(mpxns.supplyPoint as INT64) AS STRING) order by kafkadata.inserttime desc) as Row_Num
    from `data-engineering-prod.landing_bast.bast_account_supply_point_state_v1`
    JOIN UNNEST(Ownership) mpxns
),

losses AS (
    SELECT mpxn,
           serviceAccountId,
           lossdate,
           lossNotificationReceivedDate,
           lossCancellationReceivedDate,
           lossCompletionReceivedDate,
           lossConfirmationReceivedDate,
           lossJourneyStatus,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY serviceAccountId, mpxn ORDER BY lossdate DESC) AS row_num
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys_detailed`
    WHERE serviceAccountId IS NOT NULL
    AND lossCancellationReceivedDate IS NULL
),

final_statement as (
    SELECT *,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY f.Account_No ORDER BY f.Created_Datetime DESC) Row_Num
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.final_statements` f
),

latest_migration as ( # PD 2020-07-09 - Added due to change in migration success view
    SELECT *,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY Account_No ORDER BY migrated_date DESC) Row_Num
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration.orion_migration_success`
),

account_state AS (
  select metadata.eventid,
  accountId,
  case when accountId like '%-%' then SUBSTR(accountId,1,STRPOS(accountId, '-')-1)
       else accountId
  end AS Account_No,
  status,
  accountStateTimestamp,
  hasOnlineDiscount,
  interestRewardStartDate,
  interestRewardOptOut,
  electricitySupplyStartDate,
  gasSupplyStartDate,  
  vacant,
  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY accountid ORDER BY accountStateTimestamp DESC) RN
from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_account_state`
)

SELECT DISTINCT C.serviceAccountId,
                C.Account_No,
                C.Meter_Point_No,
                C.Fuel_Type,
       IF(M.Migrated_Date > C.Supply_Start_Date, M.Last_Statement_Date_In_Apollo, C.Supply_Start_Date) AS Start_Date, -- PG 23/02/2020, changing from Migration_Date to Last_Statement_Date_In_Apollo so we capture when the migration was effective from
       C.Supply_End_Date AS End_Date,
       C.Supply_Start_Date AS True_Supply_Start_Date,
       M.Migrated_Date,
       M.Reverse_Migrated_Date, # PD 2020-07-09 - Added
       L.lossDate AS Loss_Date,
       L.lossNotificationReceivedDate as Loss_Notification_Received_Date,
       CASE WHEN M.Reverse_Migrated_Date IS NOT NULL THEN 'reverse migrated'
            WHEN f.Account_No is not null then 'lost' --final statements
       	    when l.lossJourneyStatus  in ('Loss completed','Loss confirmed') and l.lossDate <= Current_date() then 'lost'
       	    WHEN c.Supply_End_Date <= current_date() then 'lost'
       	    when l.lossJourneyStatus  in ('Loss completed','Loss confirmed','Loss notification received', 'Loss notification received - Past Expected Loss Date') then 'live (pending loss)'
       	    when oob.meter_point_no is not null then CASE cols.status            
       	    	                                             WHEN 'AregiSent' THEN 'registering'
                                                           WHEN 'RegistrationAccepted' THEN 'registering'
                                                           WHEN 'RegistrationRejected' THEN 'onboarding (in exception)'
                                                           WHEN 'RegistrationObjected' THEN 'onboarding (in exception)'
                                                           WHEN 'RegistrationCancellationRequested' THEN 'onboarding (in exception)'
                                                           WHEN 'RegistrationCancelled' THEN 'onboarding (in exception)'
                                                           WHEN 'SwitchCancelled' THEN 'transfer cancelled'
                                                           WHEN 'OnSupply' THEN 'live (excluding loss)'
       	    		                                           ELSE 'onboarding'
                                                           END 
       	    WHEN oracc.status = 'active' then 'live (excluding loss)'  
       	    else 'transfer cancelled' 
       END as Supply_Lifecycle      
FROM supply_point_state C
LEFT JOIN latest_migration M ON C.serviceAccountId = M.Account_No and M.Row_Num = 1
LEFT JOIN losses L ON C.Meter_Point_No = L.mpxn AND C.serviceAccountId=L.serviceAccountId AND L.lossNotificationReceivedDate >= M.Migrated_Date AND L.ROW_NUM = 1
LEFT JOIN final_statement f ON f.Account_No = C.serviceAccountId AND CAST(f.Created_Datetime AS DATE) > L.lossNotificationReceivedDate AND f.Row_Num = 1
left join cteOrionOnboarding oob on c.meter_point_no = oob.meter_point_no and c.account_no = oob.account_no
left join cteOrionLifecycleStatusUpdates cols on c.account_no = cols.account_no and c.meter_point_no = cols.meter_point_no and cols.deduper = 1
LEFT JOIN account_state oracc on c.Account_No = oracc.Account_No and oracc.RN = 1
WHERE C.Row_Num = 1
query.1062:
WITH account_state AS (
  select metadata.eventid,
  accountId,
  case when accountId like '%-%' then SUBSTR(accountId,1,STRPOS(accountId, '-')-1)
       else accountId
  end AS Account_No,
  status,
  accountStateTimestamp,
  hasOnlineDiscount,
  interestRewardStartDate,
  interestRewardOptOut,
  electricitySupplyStartDate,
  gasSupplyStartDate,  
  vacant,
  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY accountid ORDER BY accountStateTimestamp DESC) RN
from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_account_state`
),

orex_account_state AS (
  SELECT * 
  FROM account_state WHERE RN = 1
),

latest_migration AS (
  SELECT *,
         row_number() over (partition by account_no order by migrated_date desc) as rn
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration.orion_migration_success`
)

SELECT 
  O.accountId,
  O.Account_No,
  O.status                                          AS Status,
  CAST(O.accountStateTimestamp AS DATE)             AS Account_State_Date,
  O.hasOnlineDiscount                               AS Has_Online_Discount,
  CAST(O.interestRewardStartDate AS DATE)           AS Interest_Reward_Start_Date,
  ms.Migrated_Date,
  MIN(C.Supply_Lifecycle)                           AS Account_Supply_Lifecycle,
  CAST(O.electricitySupplyStartDate AS DATE)        AS Electricity_Supply_Start_Date,
  CAST(O.gasSupplyStartDate AS DATE)                AS Gas_Supply_Start_Date,
  ms.Reverse_Migrated_Date,
  O.vacant                                          AS Is_Unknown_Occupier
FROM orex_account_state O
LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points`      C ON O.Account_No = C.Account_No
left join latest_migration ms on ms.Account_No=o.account_no and ms.rn = 1
GROUP BY O.accountId,
  O.Account_No,                          
  CAST(O.accountStateTimestamp AS DATE),
  O.hasOnlineDiscount,                     
  CAST(O.interestRewardStartDate AS DATE),
  O.status,
  ms.Migrated_Date,
  O.electricitySupplyStartDate,
  O.gasSupplyStartDate,
  Reverse_Migrated_Date,
  O.vacant
query.1064:
with touchpoint_categories as (select  Description, 
                                    Touchpoint_Category,
                                    min(Date_Occurred) as Start_Date
                                  from `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.touchpoints`
                                  group by Description, 
                                    Touchpoint_Category),

over_65 as (SELECT cam.account_no  
            FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_identity_secure.identity_user` iu
            left join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.customer_to_account_mapping` cam on cam.customer_id = iu.customer_id
            group by cam.account_no
            having max(iu.age)>65), 
                  
debt_constraints as (SELECT distinct eh.account_no,
                        exception
                  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_ops_workstreams.Orion_tbl_Exception_History` eh
                  inner join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.accounts` a on a.account_no = eh.account_no
                                                                          and a.migrated_date=eh.snapshot_date
                  where eh.exception in ('Is Debt Risk Customer','Forecast £100 to £200 EOC Debt','Forecast £200 to £500 EOC Debt','Forecast £50 to £100 EOC Debt')
                  and eh.snapshot_date>='2018-11-01')

SELECT  d.Calendar_Date,
  d.Reporting_Week_Ending_Date,
  tl.Description,
  tl.Touchpoint_Category,
  case when date_diff(d.calendar_date,a.Migrated_Date,Day)<28 then 'Recently Migrated'
    else 'Not Recently Migrated' end as Is_Recently_Migrated,
  case when o65.account_no is not null then 'Over 65' else 'Under 65' end as Is_Over_65,
  case when v.serviceAccountId is not null then 'Variable' else 'Fixed' end as Is_Variable_At_Migration,
  case when rw.account_no is not null then 'In Renewal Window' else 'Not in Renewal Window' end as Is_In_Renewal_Window,
  case when dc.account_no is not null then 'Debt Risk' else 'Not a Debt Risk' end as Is_Debt_Risk_Customer_At_Migration, --can break down by specifics if needed later
  count(distinct a.account_no) as Account_Count,
  count(distinct alt.Account_no) as Touchpoint_Count
from `data-engineering-prod.reference.tbl_Date` d
inner join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.accounts` a on d.calendar_date between Migrated_Date and ifnull(Reverse_Migrated_Date,current_Date()) --need to include losses and COTs at some point
inner join touchpoint_categories tl on 1=1
--left join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.loss_journeys` lj on lj.account_no = a.account_no
--left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.move_out_requests` mor on mor.account_no = a.account_no
left join over_65 o65 on o65.account_no = a.account_no
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` v on v.serviceAccountId = a.account_no
                                                                        and v.tariffType='variable'
                                                                        and a.migrated_date between v.startdate and ifnull(v.enddate,'2999-01-01')
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.upcoming_events` rw on rw.account_no = a.account_no
                                                                    and rw.event_name = 'Renewal Window Opens'
                                                                    and d.calendar_date between rw.event_date and date_add(rw.event_date, interval +49 day)
left join debt_constraints dc on dc.account_no = a.account_no
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.touchpoints` alt on alt.account_no = a.account_no
                                                                                  and alt.description=tl.description
                                                                                  and alt.touchpoint_category= tl.touchpoint_category
                                                                                  and alt.date_occurred = d.calendar_date                                                 
where 
  a.status='active'
and d.calendar_date between '2018-07-01' and date_add(current_date, interval -1 day)
group by calendar_date,
  Reporting_Week_Ending_Date,
  description,
  touchpoint_category,
  Is_Recently_Migrated,
  Is_Over_65,
  Is_Variable_At_Migration,
  Is_In_Renewal_Window,
  Is_Debt_Risk_Customer_At_Migration
query.1065:
select
	MS.Account_No,
  MS.Migrated_Date,
  CASE 
		WHEN IFNULL(EG.Number_Of_Distinct_Months,0) >=2 THEN 'Engaged'
		WHEN IFNULL(EG.Number_Of_Logins_In_Month_Prior_To_Migration,0) >= 2 THEN 'Engaged'
		ELSE 'Disengaged'
	END                                                                    AS Engagement_Pre_Migration
#  CASE
#    WHEN LG.Days_Since_Migration BETWEEN 0 AND 90 AND IFNULL(LG.Volume_Of_Successful_Logins,0)>=2   THEN 'Engaged'
#    WHEN LG.Days_Since_Migration <= 30                                                              THEN 'Too Soon To Determine'
#    ELSE 'Disengaged'
#  END                                                                    AS Engagement_Post_Migration
from 
	           `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration.orion_migration_success`        as MS
	LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_migration.pre_migration_engagement`   AS EG   ON MS.Account_No = EG.Account_No
#  LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.logins`                               AS LG   ON EC.Account_No = LG.Account_No
ORDER BY
  MS.Account_No
query.1066:
WITH crm_v_consumer AS
(
SELECT 
  C.Meter_Point_No,
  C.Installation_No,
  C.Consumer_No,
  C.Account_No,
  C.Consumer_Supply_Start_Date,
  CASE
    WHEN C.Account_No = A.serviceAccountId THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END Account_In_Orion
FROM 
              `data-engineering-prod.reporting_crm.v_Consumer`              C
  INNER JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts`   A ON C.Meter_Point_No = A.mpxn
WHERE
  C.Lifecycle_Category <> 'Transfer Cancelled'
)
,
consumer AS
(
SELECT
  CON.*,
  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY CON.Meter_Point_No, CON.Account_In_Orion ORDER BY CON.Consumer_Supply_Start_Date ASC)    AS Apollo_Orion_Row_Number
FROM
              crm_v_consumer CON
   INNER JOIN crm_v_consumer ORE ON CON.Meter_Point_No = ORE.Meter_Point_No AND ORE.Account_In_Orion = 1 AND CON.Consumer_Supply_Start_Date >= ORE.Consumer_Supply_Start_Date
)
,
cot AS
(
SELECT
  A.*,
  O.Orion_Account_No
FROM
(
select 
  Meter_Point_No,
  Installation_No,
  Consumer_No                AS Apollo_Consumer_No,
  Account_No                 AS Apollo_Account_No,
  Consumer_Supply_Start_Date AS Apollo_Move_In_Date
from 
  consumer 
WHERE 
  Apollo_Orion_Row_Number = 1 
  and Account_In_Orion = 0
) A
LEFT JOIN
(
select 
  Meter_Point_No,
  Account_No AS Orion_Account_No
from 
  consumer 
WHERE 
  Apollo_Orion_Row_Number = 1 
  and Account_In_Orion = 1
) O ON A.Meter_Point_No = O.Meter_Point_No
)
,
register_history AS
(
SELECT
  Installation_No,
  Register_ID,
  Install_Date,
  Install_Read,
  MIN(Snapshot_Date) AS Min_Snapshot_Date
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.staging_reporting_meters.v_Register_History`
WHERE
  Install_Read is not NULL
GROUP BY
  Installation_No,
  Register_ID,
  Install_Date,
  Install_Read
)
,
consumption_charges AS
(
SELECT
  c.supply_point,
  MAX(CASE WHEN CAST(c.charge_to_Date AS DATE) < m.enddate THEN CAST(c.charge_to_Date AS DATE)  ELSE DATE_ADD(m.enddate, INTERVAL 1 DAY) END) AS Most_Recent_Consumption_Charge_To_Date,
  m.enddate                           AS Charge_Mandate_End_Date, 
  m.startdate                         AS Charge_Mandate_Start_Date
from
              `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_charges`    C
  INNER JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.charge_mandates`        M ON C.mpxn = M.mpxn
GROUP BY
  c.supply_point,
  m.enddate,
  m.startdate 
)
,
consumption_blocks AS
(  
SELECT
  C.supply_point                                                      As Meter_Point_No,
  C.Most_Recent_Consumption_Charge_To_Date AS Latest_Consumption_Charged_Date_In_Orion,
  C.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
  C.Charge_Mandate_Start_Date,
  B.tometerreading
FROM
                consumption_charges                                                 C
  INNER JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_blocks`   B ON C.supply_point = B.mpxn and C.Most_Recent_Consumption_Charge_To_Date = B.toDate
)
select
  C.Meter_Point_No,
  C.Apollo_Consumer_No,
  C.Orion_Account_No,
  C.Apollo_Account_No,
  DM.Min_Snapshot_Date                                            AS Apollo_Consumer_Recognised_Date,
  DATE_ADD(RH.Min_Snapshot_Date, INTERVAL 1 DAY)                  AS Apollo_Opening_Read_Recognised_Date,
  B.Charge_Mandate_Start_Date,
  B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
  C.Apollo_Move_In_Date                                           AS Apollo_Supply_Start_Date,
  CASE
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1 = 0  THEN 'No Overlap Or Gap'
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1 > 0  THEn 'Overlap'
    ELSE 'Gap'
  END                                                                                                 AS Days_Direction,
  CASE
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1 < 0 THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                                                                                 AS Has_Gap_In_Days,
  CASE
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1 < 0 THEN ABS(DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1)
    ELSE 0
  END                                                                                                 AS Number_Of_Uncharged_Days,
  CASE
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1 > 0 THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                                                                                 AS Has_Overlap_In_Days,
  CASE
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1 > 0 THEN ABS(DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1)
    ELSE 0
  END                                                                                                 AS Number_Of_Double_Charged_Days,
  FLOOR(ROUND(B.tometerreading,4))                                                                    AS Read_Used_To_Generate_Latest_Consumption_Charge_In_Orion,
  ROUND(RH.Install_Read,4)                                                                            AS Apollo_Opening_Read,
  CASE
    WHEN RH.Install_Read IS NULL THEN NULL
    WHEN FLOOR(ROUND(B.tometerreading,4)) - ROUND(CAST(RH.Install_Read AS INT64),4) = 0  THEN 'No Overlap Or Gap'
    WHEN FLOOR(ROUND(B.tometerreading,4)) - ROUND(CAST(RH.Install_Read AS INT64),4) > 0  THEn 'Overlap'
    ELSE 'Gap'
  END                                                                                                 AS Consumption_Direction,
  CASE
    WHEN RH.Install_Read IS NULL THEN NULL
    WHEN FLOOR(ROUND(B.tometerreading,4)) < RH.Install_Read THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                                                                                 AS Has_Gap_In_Consumption,
  CASE
    WHEN RH.Install_Read IS NULL THEN NULL
    WHEN FLOOR(ROUND(B.tometerreading,4)) > RH.Install_Read THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                                                                                 AS Has_Overlap_In_Consumption,
  ABS(FLOOR(ROUND(B.tometerreading,4)) - ROUND(CAST(RH.Install_Read AS INT64),4))                     AS Consumption_Difference,
  CASE
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1 = 0 THEN 'No Overlap Or Gap Expected'
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(B.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,C.Apollo_Move_In_Date,DAY)+1 > 0  THEN 'Overlap In Days Expected'
    ELSE 'Gap In Days Expected'
  END                                                                                                 AS Prediction_Based_On_Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
  CASE
    WHEN C.Apollo_Move_In_Date <= B.Charge_Mandate_Start_Date THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                                                                                 AS Apollo_Move_In_Date_Before_Or_Equal_To_Charge_Mandate_Start_Date
from
              cot                                                               C
  LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.reporting_meters.v_Register`                R ON c.Installation_No = R.Installation_No AND R.install_date = C.Apollo_Move_In_Date
  LEFT JOIN   consumption_blocks                                                B ON c.Meter_Point_No = B.Meter_Point_No
  LEFT JOIN   (
              SELECT 
                Service_No,
                MIN(Snapshot_Date) AS Min_Snapshot_Date
              FROM
               `data-engineering-prod.reporting_mart.v_Service_Snapshots_Data_Mart`       
              WHERE
               Lifecycle_Category <> 'Transfer Cancelled'
              GROUP BY
               Service_No
            )                       DM on C.Apollo_Consumer_No = dm.Service_No
 LEFT JOIN  register_history        RH ON R.Register_ID = RH.Register_ID and RH.Install_Date = C.Apollo_Move_In_Date
ORDER BY
  C.Orion_Account_No
query.1068:
WITH charges_final AS
(
SELECT
  Account_No,
  Meter_Point_No,
  Fuel_Type,
  Charge_Type,
  MIN(Balance_Update_Triggered)               AS Balance_Update_Triggered,
  MIN(Charge_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match) AS Charge_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match,
  MIN(CASE
        WHEN Balance_Update_Triggered = 1 AND Charge_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match = 1 THEN 1
        ELSE 0
      END)                                     AS Healthy_On_Charges,
  Migrated_Date,
  Supply_Lifecycle
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.health_check_charges_detail_refreshed_hourly` 
GROUP BY
  Account_No,
  Meter_Point_No,
  Fuel_Type,
  Charge_Type,
  Migrated_Date,
  Supply_Lifecycle
)

SELECT
  Account_No,
  Meter_Point_No,
  Fuel_Type,
  Charge_Type,
  Balance_Update_Triggered,
  Charge_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match,
  CASE
    WHEN Healthy_On_Charges = 1 THEN 'Healthy Supply Points'
    ELSE 'Unhealthy Supply Points'
  END Charges_Health_Category,
  Migrated_Date,
  Supply_Lifecycle
FROM
  charges_final
query.1069:
WITH balance_updates as
 (
 select
 transactionId,
 accountId,
 type AS transaction_type,
 amount AS transaction_amount,
 balance AS new_balance_amount,
 balanceUpdateTime
 from
 `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_balance_updated` 
 ),
 
 standing AS
 (
 sELECT
 a.Account_No,
 a.Meter_Point_No,
 b.fuel AS Fuel_Type,
 c.charge_id AS Charge_ID,
 'standing' AS Charge_Type,
 CAST(c.Charge_From_Date AS DATE) AS Charge_From_Date,
 CAST(c.Charge_To_Date AS DATE) AS Charge_To_Date,
 CAST(c.Charge_Amount AS FLOAT64) AS Charge_Amount,
 CAST(d.transaction_amount AS FLOAT64) AS Transaction_Amount,
 CASE
 WHEN d.transactionId IS NOT NULL THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END Balance_Update_Triggered,
 CASE
 WHEN d.transactionId IS NULL THEN 1
 WHEN CAST(c.Charge_Amount AS FLOAT64) = CAST(d.transaction_amount AS FLOAT64) THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END Charge_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match,
 a.Migrated_Date,
 a.Supply_Lifecycle
 FROM 
 `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points` a
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` cc ON a.Meter_Point_No = cc.mpxn AND a.Account_No = SUBSTR(cc.serviceaccountid,1,7)
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.charge_mandates` b ON cc.energyContractId = b.contractId
 INNER join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.standing_charges` c on b.contractId = c.contract_Id 
 left join balance_updates d ON c.charge_id = d.transactionId and d.transaction_type = 'standing_charge'
 ),
 
 consumption AS
 (
 sELECT
 a.Account_No,
 a.Meter_Point_No,
 b.fuel AS Fuel_Type,
 c.charge_id AS Charge_ID,
 'consumption' AS Charge_Type,
 CAST(c.Charge_From_Date AS DATE) AS Charge_From_Date,
 CAST(c.Charge_To_Date AS DATE) AS Charge_To_Date,
 CAST(c.Charge_Amount AS FLOAT64) AS Charge_Amount,
 CAST(d.transaction_amount AS FLOAT64) AS Transaction_Amount,
 CASE
 WHEN d.transactionId IS NOT NULL THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END Balance_Update_Triggered,
 CASE
 WHEN d.transactionId IS NULL THEN 1
 WHEN CAST(c.Charge_Amount AS FLOAT64) = CAST(d.transaction_amount AS FLOAT64) THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END Charge_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match,
 a.Migrated_Date,
 a.Supply_Lifecycle
 FROM 
 `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points` a
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` cc ON a.Meter_Point_No = cc.mpxn AND a.Account_No = SUBSTR(cc.serviceaccountid,1,7)
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.charge_mandates` b ON cc.energyContractId = b.contractId
 INNER join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.consumption_charges` c on b.contractId = c.contract_Id 
 left join balance_updates d ON c.charge_id = d.transactionId and d.transaction_type = 'consumption_charge'
 )
 
 SELECT
 *
 FROM
 standing
 UNION ALL
 SELECT
 *
 FROM
 consumption
query.1072:
SELECT
  Account_No,
  Meter_Point_No,
  Fuel_Type,
  MIN(IFNULL(Exactly_1_Charge_Mandate_Present_On_Customer_Contract_Day,0))                    AS Exactly_1_Charge_Mandate_Present_On_Customer_Contract_Day,
  MIN(IFNULL(Customer_Contract_End_Date_Matches_Charge_Mandate_End_Date,0))                   AS Customer_Contract_End_Date_Matches_Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
  MIN(IFNULL(Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Unit_Rate,0))                 AS Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Unit_Rate,
  MIN(IFNULL(Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Standing_Rate,0))         AS Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Standing_Rate,
  MIN(IFNULL(Customer_Contracts_Do_Not_Overlap,0))                                            AS Customer_Contracts_Are_Non_Overlapping,
  MIN(IFNULL(Charge_Mandate_Has_Customer_Contract,0))                                         AS Charge_Mandate_Has_Customer_Contract,
  MIN(IFNULL(Active_Supply_Point_Has_Exactly_1_Customer_Contract,0))                          AS Active_Supply_Point_Has_Exactly_1_Customer_Contract,
  MIN(IFNULL(Contracts_Are_Correct_Length,0))                                                 AS Contracts_Are_Correct_Length,
  CASE 
      WHEN (CASE
                WHEN MIN(IFNULL(Exactly_1_Charge_Mandate_Present_On_Customer_Contract_Day,0)) = 1 AND  
                       MIN(IFNULL(Customer_Contract_End_Date_Matches_Charge_Mandate_End_Date,0)) = 1 AND
                         MIN(IFNULL(Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Unit_Rate,0))= 1 AND        
                           MIN(IFNULL(Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Standing_Rate,0)) = 1 AND 
                             MIN(IFNULL(Customer_Contracts_Do_Not_Overlap,0)) = 1 AND                          
                               MIN(IFNULL(Charge_Mandate_Has_Customer_Contract,0)) = 1 AND 
                                  MIN(IFNULL(Active_Supply_Point_Has_Exactly_1_Customer_Contract,0)) = 1 AND 
                                     MIN(IFNULL(Contracts_Are_Correct_Length,0)) = 1 THEN 1
                ELSE 0
             END) = 1 THEN 'Healthy Supply Points'
    ELSE 'Unhealthy Supply Points'
  END Contracts_Health_Category,
  Migrated_Date,
  Supply_Lifecycle
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.health_check_contracts_detail_refreshed_hourly`
GROUP BY
  Account_No,
  Meter_Point_No,
  Fuel_Type,
  Migrated_Date,
  Supply_Lifecycle
query.1073:
WITH orion_all_contracts AS
 (
 SELECT DISTINCT
 A.Account_No,
 A.Meter_Point_No,
 A.Fuel_Type,
 C.StartDate            AS Customer_Contract_Start_Date,
 C.ExpiryDate           AS Customer_Contract_End_Date,
 ROUND(C.unitRate,4)    AS Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate,
 C.standingRate         AS Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate,
 C.energyContractId     AS Contract_Id,
 A.Migrated_Date,
 A.Supply_Lifecycle
 FROM
 `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points` A
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` C ON A.Account_No = SUBSTR(C.serviceAccountId,1,7) AND A.Meter_Point_No = C.mpxn
 ),
 
 pre_final AS
 (
 SELECT
 OA.Account_No,
 OA.Meter_Point_No,
 OA.Fuel_Type, 
 OA.Contract_Id,
 OA.Migrated_Date,
 OA.Customer_Contract_Start_Date,
 OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date,
 OA.Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate,
 OA.Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate,
 EC.unitRate      AS Charge_Mandate_Unit_Rate,
 EC.standingRate  AS Charge_Mandate_Standing_Rate,
 EC.startDate     AS Charge_Mandate_Start_Date,
 EC.endDate       AS Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
 CASE
 WHEN (CASE
 WHEN OA.Customer_Contract_Start_Date > OA.Migrated_Date THEN OA.Customer_Contract_Start_Date
 ELSE OA.Migrated_Date
 END) >= EC.startdate AND (CASE
 WHEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date < OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date THEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date
 ELSE OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date
 END) <= EC.enddate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END AS Charge_Mandate_Present_On_Customer_Contract_Day,
 COUNT(DISTINCT EC.contractId) AS Number_Of_Active_Charge_Mandates,
 CASE
 WHEN EC.contractId IS NULL THEN 1
 WHEN (CASE
 WHEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date < OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date THEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date
 ELSE OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date
 END) = EC.endDate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END AS Customer_Contract_End_Date_Matches_Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
 CASE
 WHEN EC.contractId IS NULL THEN 1
 WHEN OA.Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate = EC.UnitRate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END AS Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Unit_Rate,
 CASE
 WHEN EC.contractId IS NULL THEN 1
 WHEN OA.Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate = EC.StandingRate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END AS Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Standing_Rate
 FROM
 orion_all_contracts OA
 LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.charge_mandates` EC ON EC.contractId = OA.Contract_ID
 LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.loss_journeys` LJ ON OA.Meter_Point_No = LJ.Meter_Point_No
 GROUP BY
 OA.Account_No,
 OA.Meter_Point_No,
 OA.Fuel_Type,
 OA.Contract_ID,
 OA.Customer_Contract_Start_Date,
 OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date,
 OA.Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate,
 OA.Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate,
 OA.Migrated_Date, 
 EC.unitRate,
 EC.standingRate,
 EC.startDate,
 EC.endDate,
 CASE
 WHEN (CASE
 WHEN OA.Customer_Contract_Start_Date > OA.Migrated_Date THEN OA.Customer_Contract_Start_Date
 ELSE OA.Migrated_Date
 END) >= EC.startdate AND (CASE
 WHEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date < OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date THEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date
 ELSE OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date
 END) <= EC.enddate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END,
 CASE
 WHEN EC.contractId IS NULL THEN 1
 WHEN (CASE
 WHEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date < OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date THEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date
 ELSE OA.Customer_Contract_End_Date
 END) = EC.endDate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END,
 CASE
 WHEN EC.contractId IS NULL THEN 1
 WHEN OA.Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate = EC.UnitRate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END,
CASE
 WHEN EC.contractId IS NULL THEN 1
 WHEN OA.Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate = EC.StandingRate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END
 )
  
 #check that only 1 OREX customer contract is active at any one time per customer per meter point
 ,
 non_overlapping AS
 (
 SELECT 
 SUBSTR(OR1.serviceAccountId,1,7) AS Account_No,
 OR1.mpxn AS Meter_Point_No,
 OR1.fuel AS Fuel_Type,
 CASE
 WHEN SUBSTR(OR2.serviceAccountId,1,7) IS NULL THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END AS Customer_Contracts_Do_Not_Overlap,
 OR1.energyContractId AS Contract_Id,
 MIN(OR2.energyContractId) AS Overlapping_Contract_Id
 FROM
 `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` OR1
 LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` OR2 ON SUBSTR(OR1.serviceAccountId,1,7) = SUBSTR(OR2.serviceAccountId,1,7) 
 AND OR1.mpxn = OR2.mpxn 
 AND (OR2.StartDate BETWEEn OR1.StartDate AND OR1.expiryDate 
 OR OR2.expiryDate BETWEEN OR1.StartDate AND OR1.expiryDate)
 AND OR2.energyContractId <> OR1.energyContractId 
 GROUP BY
 SUBSTR(OR1.serviceAccountId,1,7),
 OR1.mpxn,
 OR1.fuel,
 CASE
 WHEN SUBSTR(OR2.serviceAccountId,1,7) IS NULL THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END,
 OR1.energyContractId
 ),
 
 #check that there aren't any energy contracts without a corresponding orex customer contract
 
 orphan_energy_contract AS
 (
 SELECT
 dt.Calendar_Date,
 SUBSTR(o.serviceAccountId,1,7) AS Account_No,
 ec.mpxn AS Meter_Point_No,
 ec.fuel AS Fuel_Type,
 ec.startDate As Charge_Mandate_Start_Date,
 ec.endDate AS Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
 ec.contractID AS Contract_Id,
 CASE
 WHEN o.serviceAccountId IS NOT NULL THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END Charge_Mandate_Is_Not_Orphaned
 FROM
 `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.charge_mandates` ec
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.reference.tbl_Date` dt ON dt.Calendar_Date BETWEEN ec.startDate AND ec.endDate
 LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` o on ec.mpxn = o.mpxn 
 AND ec.startDate BETWEEN o.startDate AND o.expiryDate
 ),
 
 orex_cust_contract AS
 (
 SELECT
 pf.Account_No,
 pf.Meter_Point_No,
 pf.Fuel_Type,
 pf.Contract_Id,
 n.Overlapping_Contract_Id,
 pf.Migrated_Date,
 pf.Customer_Contract_Start_Date,
 pf.Customer_Contract_End_Date,
 pf.Charge_Mandate_Start_Date,
 pf.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
 pf.Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate,
 pf.Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate,
 pf.Charge_Mandate_Unit_Rate,
 pf.Charge_Mandate_Standing_Rate,
 CASE
 WHEN pf.Charge_Mandate_Present_On_Customer_Contract_Day = 1 AND pf.Number_Of_Active_Charge_Mandates = 1 THEN 1
 WHEN n.Customer_Contracts_Do_Not_Overlap = 0 THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END AS Exactly_1_Charge_Mandate_Present_On_Customer_Contract_Day,
 pf.Customer_Contract_End_Date_Matches_Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
 pf.Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Unit_Rate,
 pf.Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Standing_Rate,
 n.Customer_Contracts_Do_Not_Overlap
 FROM
 pre_final pf
 LEFT JOIN non_overlapping n on pf.Contract_ID = n.Contract_ID
 ),
 
 active_acc_contract AS
 (
 SELECT 
 O.Account_No,
 O.Migrated_Date,
 O.Meter_Point_No,
 O.Supply_Lifecycle,
 CASE
 WHEN COUNT(DISTINCT C.energycontractid) = 1 THEN 1 
 ELSE 0 
 END Active_Supply_Point_Has_Exactly_1_Customer_Contract
 FROM 
 `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points` O
 LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` C ON O.Account_No = SUBSTR(C.serviceaccountid,1,7) AND O.Meter_Point_No = C.mpxn AND CURRENT_DATE() BETWEEN C.startDate AND C.expiryDate
 GROUP BY
 O.Account_No,
 O.Migrated_Date,
 O.Meter_Point_No,
 O.Supply_Lifecycle
 ),
 
 contract_length AS
 (
 SELECT 
 SUBSTR(serviceaccountid,1,7) AS Account_No,
 mpxn,
 C.energycontractid AS Contract_ID,
 MIN(CASE
 WHEN LJ.Expected_Loss_Date IS NOT NULL THEN 1
 WHEN DATE_ADD(DATE_ADD(startdate,interval 2 year),interval -1 day) = expiryDate THEN 1
 WHEN DATE_ADD(DATE_ADD(startdate,interval 1 year),interval -1 day) = expiryDate THEN 1
 ELSE 0
 END) Contracts_Are_Correct_Length
 FROM
 `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` C
 LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.loss_journeys` LJ ON C.mpxn = LJ.meter_point_no
 GROUP BY
 serviceaccountid,
 mpxn,
 C.energycontractid
 )
 
 SELECT DISTINCT
   oa.Account_No,
   oa.Meter_Point_No, 
   oa.Fuel_Type,
   oa.Migrated_Date,
   oa.Supply_Lifecycle,
   oa.Contract_Id,
   o.Overlapping_Contract_Id,
   oa.Customer_Contract_Start_Date,
   oa.Customer_Contract_End_Date,
   o.Charge_Mandate_Start_Date,
   o.Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
   o.Exactly_1_Charge_Mandate_Present_On_Customer_Contract_Day,
   o.Customer_Contract_End_Date_Matches_Charge_Mandate_End_Date,
   o.Customer_Contract_Unit_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Unit_Rate,
   o.Customer_Contract_Standing_Rate_Matches_Charge_Mandate_Standing_Rate,
   o.Customer_Contracts_Do_Not_Overlap,
   IFNULL(c.Charge_Mandate_Is_Not_Orphaned,1) AS Charge_Mandate_Has_Customer_Contract,
   a.Active_Supply_Point_Has_Exactly_1_Customer_Contract,
   l.Contracts_Are_Correct_Length
 FROM
            orion_all_contracts     oa 
 LEFT JOIN  orex_cust_contract      o ON oa.Contract_Id = o.Contract_Id
 LEFT JOIN  orphan_energy_contract  c ON oa.Contract_Id = c.Contract_Id 
 LEFT JOIN  active_acc_contract     a ON oa.Account_No = a.Account_No 
 LEFT JOIN  contract_length         l ON oa.Contract_Id = l.Contract_Id 
 ORDER BY
 oa.Account_No
query.1076:
WITH onlinedisc_final AS
(
SELECT
  Account_No,
  Meter_Point_No,
  Fuel_Type,
  Migrated_Date,
  Supply_Lifecycle,
  MIN(Online_Discount_Transaction_For_Each_Standing_Charge) AS Online_Discount_Transaction_For_Each_Standing_Charge,
  MIN(Balance_Update_Triggered) AS Balance_Update_Triggered,
  MIN(Online_Discount_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match) AS Online_Discount_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match,
  MIN(CASE
        WHEN Online_Discount_Transaction_For_Each_Standing_Charge = 1 AND Balance_Update_Triggered = 1 AND Online_Discount_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match = 1 THEN 1
        ELSE 0
      END) Healthy_On_Online_Discount
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.health_check_online_discount_detail_refreshed_hourly` 
GROUP BY
  Account_No,
  Meter_Point_No,
  Fuel_Type,
  Migrated_Date,
  Supply_Lifecycle
)

SELECT
  Account_No,
  Meter_Point_No,
  Fuel_Type,
  Online_Discount_Transaction_For_Each_Standing_Charge,
  Balance_Update_Triggered,
  Online_Discount_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match,
  CASE
    WHEN Healthy_On_Online_Discount = 1 THEN 'Healthy Supply Points'
    ELSE 'Unhealthy Supply Points'
  END Online_Discount_Health_Category,
  Migrated_Date,
  Supply_Lifecycle
FROM
  onlinedisc_final
query.1077:
WITH balance_updates as
 (
 select
 transactionId,
 accountId,
 type AS transaction_type,
 amount AS transaction_amount,
 balance AS new_balance_amount,
 balanceUpdateTime
 from
 `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_balance_updated` 
 )
 
 SELECT
 A.Account_No,
 A.Meter_Point_No,
 A.Fuel_Type,
 CM.Charge_Id,
 OD.Date_Online_Discount_Applies_To,
 CAST(OD.Online_Discount_Amount AS FLOAT64)    AS Online_Discount_Amount,
 cast(BU.transaction_amount AS FLOAT64)        AS Transaction_Amount,
 CASE
    WHEN OD.Account_No IS NOT NULL THEN 1
    ELSE 0
 END AS Online_Discount_Transaction_For_Each_Standing_Charge,
 case 
    when OD.Account_No IS NULL THEN 1
    WHEN BU.transactionId is NOT NULL THEN 1 
    else 0
 end AS Balance_Update_Triggered,
 case 
    when OD.Account_No IS NULL THEN 1
    when BU.transactionId is NULL THEN 1
    ELSE (CASE 
              WHEN cast(BU.transaction_amount AS FLOAT64) = CAST(OD.Online_Discount_Amount AS FLOAT64) then 1 
              else 0
            end)
 END AS Online_Discount_Amount_And_Balance_Update_Match,
 A.Migrated_Date,
 A.Supply_Lifecycle
 FROM 
            `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points`       a
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_account_state`        O  ON A.Account_No = SUBSTR(O.accountid,1,7) AND O.hasOnlineDiscount = true
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract`    cc ON a.Meter_Point_No = cc.mpxn AND a.Account_No = SUBSTR(cc.serviceaccountid,1,7)
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.standing_charges` CM ON CC.energyContractId = CM.contract_Id
 LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.online_discount`             OD ON OD.Charge_Id = CM.Charge_Id
 LEFT JOIN  balance_updates                                                   BU ON OD.Charge_Id = BU.transactionId AND BU.transaction_type = 'online_discount'

SELECT
  Account_No,
  MIN(Direct_Debit_Set_Up)                                AS Direct_Debit_Set_Up,
  MIN(Latest_DD_Payment_Did_Not_Fail)                     AS Latest_DD_Payment_Did_Not_Fail,
  MIN(Confirmed_DD_Payments_Match_Balance_Updates)        AS All_Confirmed_DD_Payments_Match_Balance_Updates,
  MIN(Refund_Triggered_Balance_Update)                    AS All_Refunds_Have_Corresponding_Balance_Update,
  MIN(Refund_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount)        AS All_Refund_Amounts_Match_Balance_Update_Amounts,
  MIN(Card_Payment_Triggered_Balance_Update)              AS All_Card_Payments_Have_Corresponding_Balance_Update,
  MIN(Card_Payment_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount)  AS All_Card_Payment_Amounts_Match_Balance_Update_Amounts,
  CASE
    WHEN MIN(Direct_Debit_Set_Up) = 1 
      AND MIN(Latest_DD_Payment_Did_Not_Fail) = 1 
        AND MIN(Confirmed_DD_Payments_Match_Balance_Updates) = 1 
          AND MIN(Refund_Triggered_Balance_Update) = 1
            AND MIN(Refund_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount) = 1
              AND MIN(Card_Payment_Triggered_Balance_Update) = 1
                AND MIN(Card_Payment_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount) = 1 THEN 'Healthy Accounts'
    ELSE 'Unhealthy Accounts'
  END Payment_Health_Category,
  Migrated_Date,
  Account_Supply_Lifecycle
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.health_check_payments_detail_refreshed_hourly`
GROUP BY
  Account_No,
  Migrated_Date,
  Account_Supply_Lifecycle
query.1081:
WITH latest_transaction AS
 (
 WITH latest_submitted AS
 (
 SELECT
 transactionid,
 SUBSTR(serviceaccountid,1,7) AS Account_No,
 chargedate,
 row_number() over (partition by serviceaccountid order by chargedate desc) RN
 FROM 
 `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_paymentEvent`
 where 
 status = 'submitted'
 and chargeDate >= '2018-03-26'
 )
 SELECT 
 transactionid,
 Account_No,
 chargedate
 FROM 
 latest_submitted 
 WHERE
 RN = 1
 ),
 
#did the refund result in a balance update?
refunds AS 
(
SELECT
  SUBSTR(R.serviceaccountid,1,7)      as Account_No,
  R.transactionId                     AS Refund_Transaction_Id,  
  CAST(R.refundexpecteddate AS DATE)  AS Refund_Expected_Date,
  R.amount/100                        AS Refund_Amount,
  CASE
    WHEN B.transactionid IS NOT NULL THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                 AS Refund_Triggered_Balance_Update,
  CASE
    WHEN B.transactionid IS NULL THEN 1
    WHEN R.amount/100 = B.amount THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                 AS Refund_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount
FROM
            `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_refund_statusUpdated` R
  LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_balance_updated`              B ON R.transactionId = B.transactionId
where
  R.status = 'submitted'
)
,
#did the card payment result in a balance update?
card_payments AS
(  
SELECT
  SUBSTR(C.serviceaccountid,1,7)        as Account_No,
  C.transactionId                       AS Card_Payment_Transaction_Id,                    
  C.amount/100                          AS Card_Payment_Amount,
  C.paymenttakendate                    AS Payment_Taken_Datetime,
  CASE
    WHEN B.transactionid IS NOT NULL THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                   AS Card_Payment_Triggered_Balance_Update,
  CASE
    WHEN B.transactionid IS NULL THEN 1
    WHEN C.amount/100 = B.amount THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                                   AS Card_Payment_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount
FROM
            `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_card_paymentExecuted` C
  LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_balance_updated`              B ON C.transactionId = B.transactionId
)
  
 
 SELECT DISTINCT
  o.Account_No,
  s.Subscription_ID,
  c.transactionid               AS Confirmed_DD_Payment_Transaction_Id,
  f.transactionid               AS Latest_Submitted_DD_Payment_Transaction_Id,
  ref.Refund_Transaction_Id,
  cp.Card_Payment_Transaction_Id,
  CAST(c.amount/100 AS FLOAT64) AS Confirmed_DD_Payment_Amount,
  ref.Refund_Amount,
  cp.Card_Payment_Amount,
  CASE
    WHEn s.Account_No IS NOT NULL THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END                           AS Direct_Debit_Set_Up,
  CASE
    WHEn s.Account_No IS NULL THEN 1
    WHEN f.transactionid IS NOT NULL THEN 0
  ELSE 1
  END                           AS Latest_DD_Payment_Did_Not_Fail,
  CASE
    WHEn s.Account_No IS NULL THEN 1
    WHEN c.transactionid is null THEN 1
    WHEN CAST(c.amount/100 AS FLOAT64) = CAST(b.amount AS FLOAT64) THEN 1 
  ELSE 0
  END                           AS Confirmed_DD_Payments_Match_Balance_Updates,
  CASE
    WHEN ref.account_no is null THEN 1
    ELSE ref.Refund_Triggered_Balance_Update
  END                           AS Refund_Triggered_Balance_Update,
  CASE
    WHEN ref.account_no is null THEN 1
    ELSE ref.Refund_Triggered_Balance_Update
  END                           AS Refund_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount,
  CASE
    WHEN cp.account_no is null THEN 1
    ELSE cp.Card_Payment_Triggered_Balance_Update
  END                           AS Card_Payment_Triggered_Balance_Update,
  CASE
    WHEN cp.account_no is null THEN 1
    ELSE cp.Card_Payment_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount
  END                           AS Card_Payment_Amount_Matches_Balance_Update_Amount,
  o.Migrated_Date,
  o.Account_Supply_Lifecycle
 FROM
            `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.accounts`                      o
 INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract`      ct  ON O.Account_No = SUBSTR(ct.serviceaccountid,1,7)
 LEFT join  `data-engineering-prod.product_payments.subscriptions`              s   on s.Account_No = o.Account_No AND s.Is_Active_Subscription = 1
 LEFT JOIN  latest_transaction                                                  l   ON o.Account_No = l.Account_No 
 LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_paymentEvent`   f   ON l.transactionid = f.transactionid and f.status = 'failed' and f.chargeDate >= '2018-03-26'
 LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_paymentEvent`   c   ON o.Account_No = SUBSTR(c.serviceaccountid,1,7) and c.status = 'confirmed' and c.chargeDate >= '2018-03-26'
 LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_balance_updated`        b   ON c.transactionid = b.transactionid 
 LEFT JOIN  refunds                                                             ref ON o.Account_No = ref.Account_No
 LEFT JOIN  card_payments                                                       cp  ON o.Account_No = cp.Account_No
 WHERE
  o.Migrated_Date IS NOT NULL
 ORDER BY
  o.Account_No,
  s.Subscription_ID,
  c.transactionid
query.1085:
SELECT
  SP.Account_No,
  L.mpxn                          AS Meter_Point_No,
  SP.Fuel_Type,
  SP.Migrated_Date,
  L.lossNotificationReceivedDate  AS Loss_Notification_Received_Date,
  L.lossDate                      AS Expected_Loss_Date,
  L.lossConfirmationReceivedDate  AS Loss_Confirmation_Received_Date,

query.1087:
with migrations as(select ms.Account_No,
                        ms.Migrated_Date,
                        cast(rs.ReverseMigrationActionedAt as Date) as Reverse_Migrated_Date,
                        l.Account_Supply_End_Date
                    from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration.orion_migration_success` ms
                    left join `data-engineering-prod.landing_orion_migration_secure.orion_migration_reverse_success_v1` rs on rs.accountId = ms.Account_No
                    inner join `data-engineering-prod.reporting_mart.v_Account_Snapshots_Data_Mart_Latest` l on l.account_no = ms.account_no),

date_totals as (SELECT d.calendar_date,
  count(distinct a.account_no) as Migrated_Accounts,
  count(Distinct case when ifnull(account_supply_end_date,'2999-01-01')>d.calendar_date then a.account_no else null end) as Live_Migrated_Accounts
--  ,
--  count(distinct case when Account_Supply_Lifecycle = 'live (excluding loss)' then a.account_no else null end) as Live_Accounts
FROM `data-engineering-prod.reference.tbl_Date` d
inner join migrations a on d.calendar_date between a.migrated_date and ifnull(date_add(a.reverse_migrated_date, interval -1 day) ,'2999-01-01')
where d.calendar_date<=current_date()
group by d.calendar_date)

select ifnull(dt.calendar_date, mt.date) as calendar_date,
  Migrated_Accounts,
  Live_Migrated_Accounts,
  --Live_Accounts,
  Target
from date_totals dt
full outer join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.migration_targets` mt on mt.date=dt.calendar_date

WITH od_created AS
  (
  WITH dedupe AS
  (
  SELECT
    CreatedOnlineDiscountAccountId                        AS Account_Id,
    netDiscount/100                                       AS Discount_Amount, 
    discountDay                                           AS Date_Online_Discount_Applies_To,
    CreatedOnlineDiscountStandingChargeId                 AS Charge_Id,
    createdat                                             AS Latest_Created_Event_Datetime,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY CreatedOnlineDiscountStandingChargeId  ORDER BY createdAt DESC) AS RN
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_online_discount`
  WHERE
    CreatedOnlineDiscountStandingChargeId IS NOT NULL
  )
  SELECT * EXCEPT (RN) FROM dedupe WHERE RN = 1
  )
,
  
  od_cancelled AS
  (
  SELECT
    CancelledOnlineDiscountStandingChargeId               AS Charge_Id,
    MAX(createdAt)                                        AS Latest_Cancelled_Event_Datetime
  FROM 
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_online_discount`
  WHERE
    CancelledOnlineDiscountStandingChargeId IS NOT NULL
  GROUP BY
    CancelledOnlineDiscountStandingChargeId
  )
  
select 
    od_created.Account_Id AS Account_No,
    od_created.Charge_Id,
    od_created.Discount_Amount AS Online_Discount_Amount,
    od_created.Date_Online_Discount_Applies_To
from    
            od_created
left join   od_cancelled on od_cancelled.Charge_Id = od_created.Charge_Id
                         and Latest_Cancelled_Event_Datetime > Latest_Created_Event_Datetime
where 
    od_created.Charge_Id is not null
    AND od_cancelled.Charge_Id is null
query.1091:
WITH annual_statement AS
(
SELECT
  Account_No,
  Migrated_Date,
  CAST(Interest_Reward_Start_Date AS DATE) As Supply_Start_Date,
  CASE
			WHEN CAST(CURRENT_DATE() AS DATE) > DATE_ADD(CAST(Interest_Reward_Start_Date AS DATE), INTERVAL DATE_DIFF(CAST(CURRENT_DATE() AS DATE),CAST(Interest_Reward_Start_Date AS DATE),YEAR) YEAR) THEN DATE_ADD(CAST(Interest_Reward_Start_Date AS DATE), INTERVAL DATE_DIFF(CAST(CURRENT_DATE() AS DATE),CAST(Interest_Reward_Start_Date AS DATE),YEAR)+1 YEAR)
			ELSE DATE_ADD(CAST(Interest_Reward_Start_Date AS DATE),INTERVAL DATE_DIFF(CAST(CURRENT_DATE() AS DATE),CAST(Interest_Reward_Start_Date AS DATE),YEAR) YEAR)
	END Next_Anniversary_Date
from 
   `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.accounts` 
WHERE
  status = 'active'
),

renewal AS
(
SELECT DISTINCT
    SUBSTR(serviceAccountID,1,7)            AS Account_No,
    expiryDate                              AS Renewal_Due_Date
FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` 
WHERE
    CURRENT_DATE() BETWEEN startDate AND expiryDate
)

SELECT
  Account_No,
  'Annual Statement Due' AS Event_Name,
  Next_Anniversary_Date AS Event_Date,
  DATE_DIFF(Next_Anniversary_Date,CURRENT_DATE(),DAY) AS Days_To_Event
FROM
  annual_statement
UNION ALL
SELECT
  Account_No,
  'Renewal Due' AS Event_Name,
  Renewal_Due_Date AS Event_Date,
  DATE_DIFF(Renewal_Due_Date,CURRENT_DATE(),DAY) AS Days_To_Event
FROM
  renewal
UNION ALL
SELECT
  Account_No,
  'Renewal Window Opens' AS Event_Name,
  DATE_ADD(Renewal_Due_Date, INTERVAL -49 DAY) AS Event_Date,
  DATE_DIFF(DATE_ADD(Renewal_Due_Date, INTERVAL -49 DAY),CURRENT_DATE(),DAY) AS Days_To_Event
FROM
  renewal
ORDER BY
  Account_No

query.1101:
WITH
  cte_orion_customer_contracts AS (
  WITH
    cte_contract_dedupe AS (
    SELECT
      *,
      startDate AS contractStartDate,
      expiryDate AS contractExpiryDate,
      ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY energyContractId ORDER BY createdAt DESC) AS contract_dedupe_rownum
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` )
  SELECT
    *
  FROM
    cte_contract_dedupe
  WHERE
    contract_dedupe_rownum = 1 ),
  cte_losses AS (
  WITH
    cte_loss_dedupe AS (
    SELECT
      mpxn,
      lossDate,
      lossNotificationReceivedDate,
      ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY mpxn ORDER BY lossNotificationReceivedDate DESC) AS loss_dedupe_rownum
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys`
    WHERE
      lossJourneyStatus <> 'Loss notification received - Past Expected Loss Date' )
  SELECT
    *
  FROM
    cte_loss_dedupe
  WHERE
    loss_dedupe_rownum = 1 )
SELECT
  ctr.serviceAccountId,
  cm.mpxn,
  cm.fuel,
  ctr.contractStartDate,
  -- Andromeda only knows when we've been mandated to start charging from, not the true contract start date, so we need to get this from Orion
  ctr.contractExpiryDate,
  -- For consistency in case Orion is doing anything weird with the charge mandates we'll get the contract end date from Orion
  -- Andromeda currently has no knowledge of future contracts / charge mandates, other than to know Orion doesn't do renewals yet so we can supply nulls to begin with!
  l.lossDate
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.charge_mandates` cm
INNER JOIN
  cte_orion_customer_contracts ctr
ON
  cm.contractId = ctr.energyContractId
LEFT JOIN
  cte_orion_customer_contracts next_ctr
ON
  next_ctr.mpxn = ctr.mpxn
  AND next_ctr.contractStartDate = DATE_ADD(ctr.contractExpiryDate, INTERVAL 1 day)
LEFT JOIN
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points` sp
ON
  cm.mpxn = sp.mpxn
LEFT JOIN
  `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.registers` r
ON
  sp.mpxn = r.mpxn
LEFT JOIN
  cte_losses l
ON
  cm.mpxn = l.mpxn
  AND l.lossDate >= ctr.contractStartDate
WHERE
  CURRENT_DATE() BETWEEN ctr.contractStartDate
  AND ctr.contractExpiryDate
ORDER BY
  lossDate DESC
query.1102:
WITH
  data AS (
  SELECT
    t1.serviceAccountId,
    t1.mpxn AS MPXN1,
    t1.endDate AS END1,
    t2.mpxn AS MPXN2,
    t2.endDate AS END2,
    CASE
      WHEN t2.MPXN IS NULL THEN "Single fuel"
      WHEN t1.endDate = t2.endDate THEN "Same"
      ELSE "Different"
    END AS Date_Check,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY t1.serviceAccountId) AS RN
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.draft_accounts_for_renewal` t1
  LEFT JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.draft_accounts_for_renewal` t2
  ON
    t1.serviceAccountId = t2.serviceAccountId
    AND t1.mpxn != t2.mpxn
  ORDER BY
    Date_Check ASC,
    t1.endDate ASC )
SELECT
  serviceAccountId AS Account_No,
  MPXN1 AS First_Fuel,
  END1 AS First_Fuel_End_Date,
  MPXN2 AS Second_Fuel,
  END2 AS Second_Fuel_End_Date,
  Date_Check,
  b.Current_Balance
FROM
  data d
LEFT JOIN
  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.current_balances` b
ON
  d.serviceAccountId = b.Account_No
WHERE
  RN = 1
ORDER BY
  First_Fuel_End_Date ASC

query.1129:
with cte_eoc1 as
(
  select cam.Account_No,
         cast(min(cf.metadata.createdAt) as datetime) as EOC1_Triggered_Datetime,
         cast(min(case when cf.status = 'Delivered' then cf.metadata.createdAt end) as datetime) as EOC1_Delivered_Datetime,
         sum(case when description = 'The comms has been successfully delivered.' then 1 end) as delivered_count,
         sum(case when description = 'The email was opened by the customer.' then 1 end) as opened_count,
         sum(case when description = 'The link https://my.ovoenergy.com/ was clicked by the customer.' then 1 end) as went_to_myovo_count,
         -- Not passing through these more niche interactions but they're available if needed!
         sum(case when description = 'The link http://www.ovoenergy.com/terms was clicked by the customer.' then 1 end) as went_to_terms_and_conds_count,
         sum(case when description = 'The link https://www.ovoenergy.com/ovo-answers was clicked by the customer.' then 1 end) as went_to_ovo_answers_count,
         sum(case when description = 'The link http://www.ovoenergy.com was clicked by the customer.' then 1 end) as went_to_ovo_homepage_count,
         sum(case when description = 'The link www.citizensadvice.org.uk/energy was clicked by the customer.' then 1 end) as went_to_citizens_advice_count
  from `data-engineering-prod.landing_comms_secure.comms_feedback_v5` cf
  inner join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.customer_to_account_mapping` cam on replace(cf.customer.customerId, 'ovo-energy:', '') = cam.Customer_Id
  where commDescription = 'Contract about to expire'
  group by cam.Account_No
)

select distinct 
       ctr.contractId as Expiring_Contract_ID,
       ctr.serviceAccountId as Account_No,
       ctr.mpxn as Meter_Point_No,
       ctr.fuel as Fuel,
       ctr.planName as Expiring_Contract_Plan_Name,
       ctr.customerContractStartDate as Expiring_Contract_Start_Date,
       ctr.customerContractExpiryDate as Contract_Expiry_Date, -- TODO: Flag that we're relying on this to be able to do renewal window reporting
       date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval -49 day) as Renewal_Window_Opened_Date,
       eoc1.EOC1_Triggered_Datetime,
       eoc1.EOC1_Delivered_Datetime,
       case when eoc1.opened_count > 1 or went_to_myovo_count > 1 then 1 else 0 end as Opened_EOC1, -- sometimes we get the interaction event without the opened event
       case when went_to_myovo_count > 1 then 1 else 0 end AS Clicked_Through_To_MyOVO_From_EOC1,
       case when ctr_28.startDate <= date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval 28 day) then case when ctr_28.startDate < cast(ctr_28.createdDate as date) then ctr_28.startDate else cast(ctr_28.createdDate as date) end END as Renewal_Date, -- Use the start date if it's before the creation date as it's probably due to lag in manual process for refixing
       case when ctr_28.startDate <= date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval 28 day) then case when ctr_28.startDate < cast(ctr_28.createdDate as date) then cast(ctr_28.startDate as timestamp) else ctr_28.createdDate end END as Renewal_Datetime,
       ctr_28.startDate as Renewal_Contract_Start_Date,
       ctr_28.planName as Renewal_Plan_Name,
       ctr_28.contractId as Renewal_Contract_ID,
       lj.lossNotificationReceivedDate as Loss_Notification_Date,
       lj.lossDate as Loss_Date,
       case
        when lj.lossDate <= ctr.customerContractExpiryDate then 'Lost'
        when moj.Account_No is not null then 'Change of Tenancy'
        when lj.lossNotificationReceivedDate <= ctr.customerContractExpiryDate then 'Loss Notified'
        when cast(new_ctr.createdDate as date) <= ctr.customerContractExpiryDate or new_ctr.tariffType = 'fixed' then 'Renewed Before Expiry' -- If the new contract after renewal window then will be backdated renewal done manually so need to include this
        when new_ctr.tariffType = 'variable' then 'Variable'
        else 'In Process'
       END as Action_Before_Contract_Expiry,
       case
        when lj.lossDate <= date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval 28 day) then 'Lost'
        when moj.Account_No is not null then 'Change of Tenancy'
        when lj.lossNotificationReceivedDate <= date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval 28 day) then 'Loss Notified'
        when cast(new_ctr.createdDate as date) <= ctr.customerContractExpiryDate or new_ctr.tariffType = 'fixed' then 'Renewed Before Expiry'
        when ctr_28.tariffType = 'fixed' then 'Refixed Within 28 Days'
        when ctr_28.tariffType = 'variable' then 'Variable'
        else 'In Process'
       END as Action_At_28_Days_After_Contract_Expiry
from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ctr
left join cte_eoc1 eoc1 on ctr.serviceAccountId = eoc1.Account_No
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` new_ctr on ctr.mpxn = new_ctr.mpxn
                                                      and new_ctr.startDate = date_add(ctr.endDate, interval 1 day)
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys_detailed` lj on ctr.mpxn = lj.mpxn
                                                     and lj.lossNotificationReceivedDate >= date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval -49 day)
                                                     and lj.lossCancellationReceivedDate is null
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.move_out_journeys` moj on ctr.serviceAccountId = moj.Account_No
                                                      and cast(moj.Request_Timestamp as date) >= date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval -49 day)
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ctr_28 on ctr.mpxn = ctr_28.mpxn
                                                                           and date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval 28 day) between ctr_28.startDate and coalesce(ctr_28.endDate, '2999-01-01')
where date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval -49 day) < current_date()
  and ctr.endDate >= date_add(ctr.customerContractExpiryDate, interval -49 day) -- Exclude anyone already lost or moved out by time window would have opened
query.1130:
# Reporting for tariffs over the cap post-April VPC

# Get caps for most recent cap date for DD only
WITH priceCapRates AS (
  SELECT region_name,
         GSP,
         GSP_Id as mpanPrefix,
         case when GSP_Id='10' then 'EA'
              when GSP_Id='11' then 'EM'
              when GSP_Id='12' then 'NT'
              when GSP_Id='13' then 'NW'
              when GSP_Id='14' then 'WM'
              when GSP_Id='15' then 'NO'
              when GSP_Id='16' then 'NW'
              when GSP_Id='17' then 'SC'
              when GSP_Id='18' then 'SC'
              when GSP_Id='19' then 'SE'
              when GSP_Id='20' then 'SO'
              when GSP_Id='21' then 'WA'
              when GSP_Id='22' then 'SW'
              when GSP_Id='23' then 'NE'
         end as LDZ, # Align gas region notation
         case when fuel='E' then 'electricity'
              when fuel='G' then 'gas'
         end as fuel, # Align fuel notation
         case when profile_class='Gas' then '00'
              when profile_class='PC1' then '01'
              when profile_class='PC2' then '02'
         end as profileclass, # Align profile class notation
         standing_charge/100 as VPCstandingRateCap, # Convert pence to pounds
         rate/100 as VPCunitRateCap, # Convert pence to pounds
         effective_from_date as VPCcapStart,
         effective_to_date as VPCcapEnd
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.custom_regulatory.tbl_Price_Cap_Rates_v2`
  WHERE tariff_cap='SVT' # Standard Variable Tariffs - only applies to variable contracts
    AND payment_type='D' # DD payments
    AND effective_from_date='2020-04-01' # April caps only
),
# Get all contracts that are currently live
allContracts AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT c.serviceAccountId,
                  c.mpxn,
                  c.fuel,
                  c.contractId,
                  c.startDate,
                  c.endDate,
                  c.tariffId,
                  c.tariffType,
                  c.planName,
                  t.profileClass,
                  IF(t.profileClass='02' and t.planName not like '%Economy 7', '01', t.profileClass) as tariffProfileClass,
                  c.contractStatus,
                  t.region as currentRegion
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` c
  INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tariffs` t # Only need current tariff region and profile class here
    ON c.tariffId=t.tariffId
  WHERE c.endDate>=current_date()
     OR c.endDate IS NULL
),
correctRegion AS (
  SELECT ac.*,
         if(ac.fuel='electricity',pcr.GSP,pcr.LDZ) as correctRegion, # Gas and elec regions have different notation
         pcr.mpanprefix as correctRegionMpanPrefix,
         pcr.VPCunitRateCap,
         pcr.VPCstandingRateCap,
         pcr.VPCcapStart
  FROM allContracts ac
  LEFT JOIN (select distinct account_no, utility_type_code, mpan_prefix from `data-science-retail.pricing_programme_solution.purified_alignment_gas_and_elec`) pp # Correct region data for account
    ON pp.account_no=ac.serviceAccountID
    AND pp.Utility_Type_Code=upper(substr(ac.fuel,1,1))
  LEFT JOIN priceCapRates pcr # Bring in price cap rates
    ON pp.mpan_prefix=pcr.mpanprefix
    AND ac.tariffProfileClass=pcr.profileClass
),
# Join everything above on to PP region data for all accounts
final_data as (
SELECT cr.*,
       asp.loss_date as lossDate,
       asp.supply_lifecycle as supplyLifecycle,
       asp.migrated_date as migratedDate,
       case when (cr.currentRegion<>cr.correctRegion) then 'Incorrect region'
            else 'Correct region'
       end as regionComparison
FROM correctRegion cr
LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points` asp # Bring in account data
  ON cr.serviceAccountId=asp.account_no
  AND cr.mpxn=asp.meter_point_no
)
# Filter out accounts where the region is correct or rate is under the cap
SELECT *
FROM final_data
WHERE regionComparison='Incorrect region' # Keep accounts with region mismatch
ORDER BY serviceAccountId,
         fuel

query.1135:
WITH
  cte_recommended_dds AS (
  SELECT
    rdd.accountId,
    rdd.amount,
    rdd.predictedFinalBalance,
    rdd.isVariable,
    rdd.remainingDirectDebits,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY rdd.accountId ORDER BY rdd.metadata.createdAt DESC) AS row_num
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.public.orex_recommended_direct_debit_generated_v1` rdd ),
  cte_combined AS (
  SELECT
    cb.*,
    s.DD_Day_Of_Month,
    s.DD_Amount,
    rdd.isVariable,
    rdd.remainingDirectDebits,
    FLOOR((rdd.amount / 100)) - s.DD_Amount AS Payment_Shortfall,
    FLOOR((rdd.amount / 100)) AS Recommended_Amount,
    FLOOR((rdd.predictedFinalBalance / 100)) AS Predicted_EOC_Balance
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.accounts_extract` a
  LEFT JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.move_out_journeys` moj
  ON
    a.Account_No = moj.Account_No
  LEFT JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.current_balances` cb
  ON
    a.Account_No = cb.Account_No
  LEFT JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_payments.subscriptions` s
  ON
    cb.Account_No = s.Account_No
    AND s.Is_Active_Subscription = 1
  LEFT JOIN
    cte_recommended_dds rdd
  ON
    cb.Account_No = rdd.accountId
    AND rdd.row_num = 1
  WHERE
    a.Status = 'active'
    AND a.Account_Supply_Lifecycle = 'live (excluding loss)'
    AND moj.Account_No IS NULL )
SELECT
  *,
  CASE
    WHEN DD_Amount >= Recommended_Amount THEN 'Paying recommended amount'
    WHEN DD_Day_Of_Month IS NULL THEN 'No DD set up'
    WHEN DD_Amount < Recommended_Amount AND Predicted_EOC_Balance >= 0 THEN 'Direct Debit reduced since recommendation'
    WHEN Recommended_Amount IS NULL THEN 'Yet to generate recommendation'
    WHEN Predicted_EOC_Balance < -50 THEN 'Predicted EOC debt > £50'
    WHEN Predicted_EOC_Balance < 0 THEN 'Predicted EOC Debt <= £50'
    ELSE 'Uncategorised'
  END AS Paying_Right_Amount_Status,
  CASE
    WHEN isVariable = true THEN 'Variable'
    WHEN isVariable = false THEN 'Fixed'
  END AS Contract_Type,
  CASE
    WHEN remainingDirectDebits = 0 THEN 'No Direct Debit payments remaining'
    WHEN remainingDirectDebits <= 3 THEN '3 or fewer payments remaining'
    WHEN remainingDirectDebits > 6 THEN '7 or more payments remaining'
    ELSE '4 to 6 payments remaining'
  END AS Payments_Remaining,
  CASE
    WHEN Payment_Shortfall <= 0 THEN 'Paying recommended amount or greater'
    WHEN Payment_Shortfall <= 5 THEN 'Paying within £5'
    WHEN Payment_Shortfall <= 10 THEN 'Paying within £10'
    WHEN Payment_Shortfall <= 20 THEN 'Paying within £20'
    ELSE 'Payment greater than £20 than recommended amount'
  END AS Payment_Shortfall_Status
FROM
  cte_combined
query.1136:
WITH
  data AS (
  WITH
    rdd AS (
    SELECT
      metadata.createdAt AS Created_Datetime,
      rdd.accountId AS Account_No,
      rdd.amount/100 AS Recommended_Amount,
      rdd.isVariable,
      ROUND(rdd.predictedFinalBalance/100,2) AS Predicted_EOC_Balance
    FROM
      `data-engineering-prod.public.orex_recommended_direct_debit_generated_v1` rdd )
  SELECT
    rdd.Account_No,
    rdd.Predicted_EOC_Balance,
    rdd.Recommended_Amount,
    rdd.isVariable,
    s.DD_Amount,
    rdd.Created_Datetime,
    s.Subscription_Created_Datetime,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY rdd.Account_No, CAST(rdd.Recommended_Amount AS STRING) ORDER BY rdd.Created_Datetime ASC, s.Subscription_Created_Datetime DESC) AS row_num
  FROM
    rdd
  LEFT JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_payments.subscriptions` s
  ON
    rdd.Account_No = s.Account_No
  WHERE
    s.Subscription_Created_Datetime < rdd.Created_Datetime
  ORDER BY
    Account_No ASC,
    rdd.Created_Datetime DESC,
    s.Subscription_Created_Datetime DESC )
SELECT
  *,
  CASE
    WHEN DD_Amount >= Recommended_Amount THEN 'Paying recommended amount'
    WHEN DD_Amount < Recommended_Amount AND Predicted_EOC_Balance >= 0 THEN 'Direct Debit reduced since recommendation'
    WHEN Recommended_Amount IS NULL THEN 'Yet to generate recommendation'
    WHEN Predicted_EOC_Balance < -50 THEN 'Predicted EOC debt > £50'
    WHEN Predicted_EOC_Balance < 0 THEN 'Predicted EOC Debt <= £50'
    ELSE 'Uncategorised'
  END AS Paying_Right_Amount_Status
FROM
  data
WHERE
  row_num = 1
