query.1151:
-- TODO the window for loss final statements is larger for read disputes. Do we need to account for this here?
with account_supplies as (
  -- subquery to find latest account supply point state event for an account
  select *, row_number() over (partition by accountId order by kafkaData.insertTime desc) as row_number from `data-engineering-prod.auto_capture_v2.bast_account_supply_point_state_v1` order by accountId
)
-- Move out final statements
-- Find any move outs that have an associated final statement. The deadline is determined by adding 4 weeks to the latest between the day the account moved out and the day we were told about the move out. We then report on how many days outside of that window the final statement was created.
select
      move_outs.account_id as AccountId,
      move_outs.move_out_date as AccountCloseDate,
      f.statementId as StatementId,
      extract(date from f.createdAt) as StatementCreatedDate, --TODO should we fix this to be the statementDate (currently not visible in bigquery) rather than the kafka create time
      date_diff(extract(date from f.createdAt), greatest(move_outs.move_out_date, move_outs.created_date), day) as DaysBeforeStatement,
      date_diff(extract(date from f.createdAt), greatest(move_outs.move_out_date, move_outs.created_date), day) <= 28 as WithinWindow,
      "Move out" as AccountCloseReason
      from `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.bast_move_outs` move_outs
      join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.active_final_statements` f on move_outs.account_id = f.accountId
union all
-- Loss final statements
-- Find any account losses that have an associated final statement AND have no active supplies after the loss. The deadline is determined by adding 6 weeks to the loss date. We then report on how many days outside of that window the final statement was created.
select
      losses.account_id as AccountId,
      losses.loss_date as AccountCloseDate,
      f.statementId as StatementId,
      extract(date from f.createdAt) as StatementCreatedDate, --TODO should we fix this to be the statementDate (currently not visible in bigquery) rather than the kafka create time
      date_diff(extract(date from f.createdAt), losses.loss_date, day) as DaysBeforeStatement,
      date_diff(extract(date from f.createdAt), losses.loss_date, day) <= 42 as WithinWindow,
      "Loss" as AccountCloseReason
      from `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.bast_losses` losses
      join account_supplies supplies on supplies.accountId = losses.account_id and supplies.row_number = 1 -- The account supply point is ordered by insert time so the row with number 1 is the latest row
      join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.active_final_statements` f on losses.account_id = f.accountId
      where not exists (select * from unnest(supplies.ownership) o where o.end is null or o.end > timestamp(losses.loss_timestamp)) -- A supply is active after the loss if it has a later end time or no end time
query.1152:
-- TODO the window for loss final statements is larger for read disputes. Do we need to account for this here?
with account_supplies as (
  -- subquery to find latest account supply point state event for an account
  select *, row_number() over (partition by accountId order by kafkaData.insertTime desc) as row_number from `data-engineering-prod.auto_capture_v2.bast_account_supply_point_state_v1` order by accountId
)
-- Move out final statements
-- Find any move outs that have no associated final statement. The deadline is determined by adding 4 weeks to the latest between the day the account moved out and the day we were told about the move out
select
      move_outs.account_id as AccountId,
      move_outs.move_out_date as AccountCloseDate,
      date_add(greatest(move_outs.move_out_date, move_outs.created_date), interval 28 day) as FinalStatementDeadline,
      date_diff(date_add(greatest(move_outs.move_out_date, move_outs.created_date), interval 28 day), CURRENT_DATE(), day) as DaysRemaining,
      "Move out" as AccountCloseReason
      from `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.bast_move_outs` move_outs
      left join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.active_final_statements` f on move_outs.account_id = f.accountId
      where f.accountId is null
union all
-- Loss final statements
-- Find any account losses that have no associated final statement AND have no active supplies after the loss. The deadline is determined by adding 6 weeks to the loss date
select
      losses.account_id as AccountId,
      losses.loss_date as AccountCloseDate,
      date_add(losses.loss_date, interval 42 day) as FinalStatementDeadline,
      date_diff(date_add(losses.loss_date, interval 42 day), CURRENT_DATE(), day) as DaysRemaining,
      "Loss" as AccountCloseReason
      from `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.bast_losses` losses
      join account_supplies supplies on supplies.accountId = losses.account_id and supplies.row_number = 1 -- The account supply point is ordered by insert time so the row with number 1 is the latest row
      left join `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.active_final_statements` f on losses.account_id = f.accountId
      where f.accountId is null
      and not exists (select * from unnest(supplies.ownership) o where o.end is null or o.end > timestamp(losses.loss_timestamp)) -- A supply is active after the loss if it has a later end time or no end time
query.1153:
WITH
  cte_most_recent_subscription AS (
  SELECT
    *,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY Account_No ORDER BY Subscription_Created_Date DESC) AS ROW
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.product_payments.subscriptions` ),
  cte_final_statements AS (
  SELECT
    unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId,
    unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.metadata.createdAt,
    unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.closingBalance,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId ORDER BY unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.metadata.createdAt DESC) AS ROW
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_bast_secure.bast_statement_uploaded`
  WHERE
    unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId IS NOT NULL 
    
  UNION ALL
    
  SELECT
    unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId,
    unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.metadata.createdAt,
    unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.closingBalance,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId ORDER BY unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.metadata.createdAt DESC) AS ROW
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_statement_uploaded`
  WHERE
    unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId IS NOT NULL ),
  cte_data AS (
  SELECT
    b.Account_No AS accountId,
    b.Current_Balance AS currentBalance,
    fs.createdAt AS finalStatementUploadTime,
    ROUND(fs.closingBalance/100,2) AS finalClosingBalance,
    sub.Is_Active_Subscription,
    sub.DD_Amount,
    sub.DD_Day_Of_Month
  FROM
    cte_final_statements AS fs
  LEFT JOIN
    `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.current_balances` AS b
  ON
    fs.accountId = b.Account_No
  LEFT JOIN
    cte_most_recent_subscription sub
  ON
    b.Account_No = sub.Account_No
  WHERE
    sub.ROW = 1
    AND fs.ROW = 1),
  final_refund_data AS (
  SELECT
    *,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY serviceAccountId, amount ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS refund_account_amount_row
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_refund_statusUpdated`
  WHERE status != 'requested'
  ORDER BY
    metadata.createdAt DESC)
SELECT
  cte_data.*,
  acc.status,
  CASE
    WHEN DATE_DIFF(CURRENT_DATE(), DATE(finalStatementUploadTime), DAY) < 13 THEN "In previous 12 days"
    ELSE "Older than 12 days"
  END AS isLast12Days,
  CASE
    WHEN finalClosingBalance = 0 THEN "Zero balance"
    WHEN finalClosingBalance > 0 THEN "Positive closing balance"
    WHEN finalClosingBalance < 0 THEN "Negative closing balance"
  END AS finalBalanceStatus,
  CASE
    WHEN currentBalance = 0 THEN "Zero balance"
    WHEN currentBalance > 0 THEN "Positive balance"
    WHEN currentBalance < 0 THEN "Negative balance"
  END AS currentBalanceStatus,
  frd.status AS finalRefundStatus,
  ROUND(frd.amount/100,2) AS finalRefundAmount,
  frd.refundExpectedDate,
  frd.metadata.createdAt AS refundEventCreation,
  ARRAY_TO_STRING(frd.reason, '--') AS refundFailureReason,
  CASE
    WHEN finalClosingBalance <= 0 THEN "Final balance zero or negative"
    WHEN finalClosingBalance = ROUND(frd.amount/100,2) THEN "Refund matches final balance"
    WHEN finalClosingBalance != ROUND(frd.amount/100,2) THEN "Refund doesn't matches final balance"
  END AS finalRefundCheck
FROM
  cte_data
LEFT JOIN
  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.accounts_extract` acc
ON
  cte_data.accountId = acc.Account_No
LEFT JOIN
  final_refund_data frd
ON
  cte_data.accountId = frd.serviceAccountId AND cte_data.finalClosingBalance = ROUND(frd.amount/100,2)
WHERE
  acc.status = 'active'
  AND (frd.refund_account_amount_row = 1 OR frd.refund_account_amount_row IS NULL)
ORDER BY
  finalStatementUploadTime DESC

WITH base as (SELECT acc.account_no,
                    s.DD_Amount,
                    s.DD_Day_Of_Month,
                    c.startDate as Customer_Contract_Start_Date,
                    c.endDate as Customer_Contract_End_Date,
                    CAST(CB.current_balance AS FLOAT64) AS Current_Balance,
                    case when s.account_no is not null then 1 else 0 end as Has_Active_DD,
                    count(distinct d.calendar_date) as Number_Of_Payments_Remaining,
                    ifnull(s.DD_Amount,0)*count(d.calendar_date) as Forecast_Payments
              FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.accounts` acc
              left join `data-engineering-prod.product_payments.subscriptions` s on s.account_no=acc.account_no
                                                                                        and s.is_active_subscription=1         
              left JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.current_balances`  AS CB ON acc.Account_No = CB.Account_No                 
             INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` c on c.serviceAccountID = acc.account_no
                                                                                       and current_Date between c.startDate and c.EndDate
              LEFT JOIN  `data-engineering-prod.raw_mis.Reference_dim_Date`                   D ON D.Calendar_Date BETWEEN CURRENT_DATE() AND c.enddate
                                                                                             and EXTRACT(DAY FROM D.calendar_date) = s.DD_Day_Of_Month
             group by account_no,
               s.DD_Amount,
               DD_Day_Of_Month,
               Customer_Contract_Start_Date,
               Customer_Contract_End_Date,
               Has_Active_DD,
               Current_Balance),

latest_forecast_consumption_cte AS (
                              SELECT
                                mpxn,
                                forecastedAnnualConsumption
                              FROM 
                                    (SELECT
                                        mpxn,
                                        forecastedAnnualConsumption,
                                        row_number() over (partition by mpxn order by forecastedAnnualConsumptionEffectiveFrom desc) as seq 
                                      FROM 
                                          `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.supply_points`)
                              where seq=1),
                                                   
projected_consumption_cte as ( select fc.mpxn, 
                                      fc.forecastedAnnualConsumption,
                                      pp.projectedConsumption
                            from latest_forecast_consumption_cte fc
                            left join (
                                  SELECT event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan as MPXN,  
                                        event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom,
                                        event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.projectedConsumption,
                                        row_number() over (partition by event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.mpan order by event.ElectricityAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom desc) as seq
                                  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_personal_projections_calculated_v3`

                                  union all 

                                  SELECT event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.mprn as MPXN,  
                                        event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom,
                                        event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.projectedConsumption,
                                        row_number() over (partition by event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.mprn order by event.GasAnnualProjectionEvent.effectiveFrom desc) as seq
                                  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda.rac_personal_projections_calculated_v3`
                                  ) pp on pp.mpxn=fc.mpxn 
                                        and pp.seq=1),
      
forecast_charges_cte AS (SELECT con.serviceAccountId as Account_No,
                             sum(currentstandingRate + daily_coefficient*forecastedAnnualConsumption*currentunitRate) as Forecast_Charges,
                             sum(currentstandingRate + daily_coefficient*projectedConsumption*currentunitRate) as Forecast_Charges_Personal_Projection
                            FROM        projected_consumption_cte                                   AS pc
                            INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` AS con   on pc.mpxn=con.mpxn 
                                                                                            and current_Date between con.startDate and con.EndDate
                            inner join  `data-engineering-prod.landing_payments_secure.static_billing_coefficients_for_payments_use_only` AS bc ON LOWER(bc.fuel) = LOWER(con.fuel) 
                            WHERE
                            bc.SettlementDate >= Current_date
                            AND bc.SettlementDate <= con.EndDate
                            group by con.serviceAccountId
                            )
 
SELECT DISTINCT
  base.Account_No,
  base.Customer_Contract_Start_Date,
  base.Customer_Contract_End_Date,
  base.Number_Of_Payments_Remaining,
  base.DD_Amount AS Current_DD_Amount,
  base.Current_Balance,
  B.Forecast_Charges,
  base.Forecast_Payments,
  base.Current_Balance
    -B.Forecast_Charges
      +base.Forecast_Payments AS Forecast_Balance,
  base.Current_Balance
    -B.Forecast_Charges_Personal_Projection
      +base.Forecast_Payments AS Forecast_Balance_Personal_Projection,
      B.Forecast_Charges_Personal_Projection,
      base.Has_Active_DD
FROM
            base
left JOIN  forecast_charges_cte  AS B ON base.Account_No = B.Account_No
query.1161:
with cte_first_snapshots as
(
  select Task_ID,
         Snapshot_Date as First_Snapshot_Date,
         Time_Taken,
         Proportion_Required_For,
         row_number() over (partition by Task_ID order by Snapshot_Date asc) as first_snapshot_rownum
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.manual_process_snapshots`
)
-- Data for everything once it's being snapshotted
select snap.Snapshot_Date,
       stat.* except(Weekly_Volume),
       cast(stat.Weekly_Volume as float64) as Weekly_Volume,
       cast(snap.Time_Taken as float64) as Time_Taken,
       cast(snap.Proportion_Required_For as float64) as Proportion_Required_For,
       cast((stat.Weekly_Volume * snap.Proportion_Required_For * snap.Time_Taken) / 60 as float64) as Total_Hours_Per_Week
from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.manual_process_snapshots` snap
INNER join `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.manual_processes_static_data` stat on snap.Task_ID = stat.Task_ID
union all
-- Processes we've added retrospectively need to have their first snapshot timings applied for all dates back to when the process was applied
select d.Calendar_Date as Snapshot_Date,
       stat.* except(Weekly_Volume),
       cast(stat.Weekly_Volume as float64) as Weekly_Volume,
       cast(fs.Time_Taken as float64) as Time_Taken,
       cast(fs.Proportion_Required_For as float64) as Proportion_Required_For,
       cast((stat.Weekly_Volume * fs.Proportion_Required_For * fs.Time_Taken) / 60 as float64) as Total_Hours_Per_Week
from cte_first_snapshots fs
inner join `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.manual_processes_static_data` stat on fs.Task_ID = stat.Task_ID
inner join `data-engineering-prod.reference.tbl_Date` d on d.Calendar_Date between stat.First_Applied_Date and date_add(fs.First_Snapshot_Date, interval -1 DAY)
where fs.first_snapshot_rownum = 1
order by Snapshot_Date, Total_Hours_Per_Week desc

query.1167:
with cte as
(
with cte_latest_contract as
(
  select ctr.*,
  row_number() over (partition by serviceAccountId order by startDate desc) as row_num
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ctr
),
cte_requests_union as
(
  select coalesce(max(sheet.Request_Timestamp), cast(bmo.created_date as datetime)) as Request_Timestamp,
         bmo.account_id as Account_No,
         max(sheet.Past_or_Future) as Past_or_Future,
         bmo.move_out_date as Move_Out_Date,
         bmo.move_out_date as Tenancy_End_Date,
         bmo.cancelled as Move_Out_Cancelled
  from  `data-engineering-prod.product_orion_secure.bast_move_out_copy` bmo
  left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.move_out_requests` sheet on bmo.account_id = sheet.Account_No
                                                                                      and bmo.Move_Out_Date = sheet.Tenancy_End_Date
  group by bmo.account_id, bmo.move_out_date, bmo.created_date, bmo.cancelled 
)
select mo.*,
       cm.mpxn as Meter_Point_No,
       cm.endDate as Contract_End_Date,
       case
        when cm.endDate = mo.tenancy_end_date then 'Updated correctly'
        when cm.endDate = date_add(mo.tenancy_end_date, interval -1 day) then 'Updated correctly'
        WHEN cm.endDate > mo.tenancy_end_date THEN 'Needs updating'
        WHEN cm.endDate < mo.tenancy_end_date THEN 'Ends before move out'
       END as Contract_Status,
       lj.lossDate
from cte_requests_union mo
left join cte_latest_contract cm on mo.Account_No = cm.serviceAccountId
                                and cm.row_num = 1
left join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.loss_journeys_detailed` lj on mo.Account_No = lj.serviceAccountId # PJD - changed from loss_journeys to cut down query size
left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.probate_responses` p on mo.Account_No = p.Account_No
where (lj.lossDate is null or lj.lossDate > mo.Tenancy_End_Date)
  and p.Account_No is null
)
select *
from cte
where Contract_Status is not null

  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_statement_uploaded`

cte_balances as

         bu.balance,

  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_balance_updated` bu
)
select mo.*,
       case

        ELSE 'No DD Set Up'
       END as DD_Status,

query.1170:
with cte as

with cte_latest_contract as

  select ctr.*,
  row_number() over (partition by serviceAccountId order by startDate desc) as row_num
  from `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` ctr
),

  select Request_Timestamp,
         Account_No,

         Tenancy_End_Date
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.move_out_requests`

         cast(bast.Account_No as string) as Account_No,

  from `data-engineering-prod.u_peter_grace.move_outs_from_bast_20191011` bast
  left join `data-engineering-prod.raw_orion_migration_secure.move_out_requests` sheet on cast(bast.Account_No as string) = sheet.Account_No
  where sheet.Account_No is null
)

       cm.mpxn as Meter_Point_No,

       case
        when cm.endDate = mo.tenancy_end_date then 'Updated correctly'

  CASE
    WHEN c.startDate <= CURRENT_DATE() AND c.endDate >= CURRENT_DATE() THEN "Active today (fixed)"
    WHEN c.startDate <= CURRENT_DATE() AND c.endDate IS NULL THEN "Active today (variable)"
    WHEN c.startDate > CURRENT_DATE() THEN "Future contract"

query.1173:
WITH
  customerData AS (
  SELECT
    accountId,
    customerId,
    accountCommsPreference,
    isPrimaryCustomer,
    isFinanciallyLiable,
    metadata.createdAt AS lastUpdated,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY customerId, accountId ORDER BY metadata.createdAt DESC) AS ROW
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_account_customer_binding_updated`
  WHERE status = 'active'
  ORDER BY
    ROW DESC ),
  loginData AS (
    SELECT userId as customerId, COUNT(*) as loginCount
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_identity.identity_loginlogout_v1`
    WHERE eventType = "LoggedIn" GROUP BY customerId ),
  data AS (
  SELECT
    c.accountId,
    c.customerId,
    commsPreference,
    c.isPrimaryCustomer,
    c.isFinanciallyLiable,
    c.lastUpdated AS lastUpdated,
    l.loginCount,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY c.customerId ORDER BY commsPreference DESC) AS prefRow
  FROM
    customerData c, UNNEST(accountCommsPreference) AS commsPreference
  LEFT JOIN loginData l ON c.customerId = l.customerId
  WHERE
    c.row = 1
  )

  SELECT 
    isPrimaryCustomer,
    isFinanciallyLiable,
    commsPreference,
    SUM(loginCount) AS loginSum,
    count(*) as count,
    CAST(ROUND(AVG(loginCount),0) AS INT64) AS averageLogins
FROM data 
  WHERE prefRow = 1
  GROUP BY isPrimaryCustomer, isFinanciallyLiable, commsPreference
  ORDER BY isPrimaryCustomer DESC, isFinanciallyLiable DESC, commsPreference ASC, count DESC
query.1175:
WITH
  cte_orion_comms AS (
  SELECT
    metadata.createdAt AS Datetime,
    commId AS Comm_ID,
    customer.customerId AS Customer_ID,
    status,
    description,
    channel AS Channel,
    templateManifest.id AS Template_ID,
    templateManifest.version AS Template_Version,
    commDescription
  FROM
    `data-engineering-prod.landing_comms_secure.comms_feedback`
  WHERE
    customer.customerId LIKE 'ovo-energy:%'),
  cte_triggered_comms AS (
  SELECT
    *
  FROM
    cte_orion_comms
  WHERE
    status = 'Pending'
    AND description = 'Trigger for communication accepted' ),
  cte_delivered_comms AS (
  SELECT
    Datetime,
    Comm_ID
  FROM
    cte_orion_comms
  WHERE
    status = 'Delivered'
    AND description = 'The comms has been successfully delivered.' ),
  cte_opened_comms AS (
  SELECT
    Datetime,
    Comm_ID
  FROM
    cte_orion_comms
  WHERE
    status = 'Delivered'
    AND description = 'The email was opened by the customer.' )
SELECT
  t.Comm_ID,
  t.Datetime AS Triggered_Datetime,
  d.Datetime AS Delivered_Datetime,
  o.Datetime AS Opened_Datetime,
  Template_ID,
  Template_Version,
  Channel,
  Customer_ID
FROM
  cte_triggered_comms t
LEFT JOIN
  cte_delivered_comms d
ON
  t.Comm_ID = d.Comm_ID
LEFT JOIN
  cte_opened_comms o
ON
  t.Comm_ID = o.Comm_ID

query.1181:
SELECT
  CONCAT(t.id,'-',t.type,'-',CAST(t.year AS STRING),'-',FORMAT("%02d",t.month)) AS Transaction_ID,
  NULL AS Account_Balance,
  t.id AS Account_No,
  NULL AS Amount_Paid,
  NULL AS Client_Process,
  NULL AS Consumer_No,
  CONCAT(CAST(t.year AS STRING), FORMAT("%02d",t.month+1)) AS Created_YYYYMM,
  NULL AS End_Use_ID,
  NULL AS Extra_Description,
  NULL AS File_ID_Reference,
  NULL AS Invoice_Number,
  NULL AS Ledger_Type_Code,
  NULL AS Statement_Number,
  CASE
    WHEN t.type = "vat" THEN t.amount
    ELSE 0
  END AS Tax_Amount,
  CASE
    WHEN t.type <> "vat" THEN t.amount
    ELSE 0
  END AS Transaction_Amount,
  DATE_ADD(DATE_ADD(CAST(CONCAT(CAST(t.year AS STRING),'-',FORMAT("%02d",t.month+1),'-','01') AS date),INTERVAL 1 MONTH),INTERVAL -1 DAY) AS Transaction_Date,
  DATETIME(t.year ,CAST(FORMAT("%02d",t.month+1) AS INT64),1, 23, 59, 59) AS Transaction_Datetime,
  NULL AS Transaction_Description,
  CASE
    WHEN t.type IN ('standing', 'consumption') THEN CAST(CONCAT(CAST(t.year AS STRING),'-',FORMAT("%02d",t.month+1),'-','01') AS date)
  END AS Transaction_Period_Start,
  CASE
    WHEN t.type IN ('standing', 'consumption') THEN DATE_ADD(DATE_ADD(CAST(CONCAT(CAST(t.year AS STRING),'-',FORMAT("%02d",t.month+1),'-','01') AS date),INTERVAL 1 MONTH),INTERVAL -1 DAY)
  END AS Transaction_Period_End,
  NULL AS Transaction_Status_ID,
  t.type AS Transaction_Type_Code,
  UPPER(IFNULL(SUBSTR(t.fuel,1,1),
      'Z')) AS Utility_Type,
  "ORION" AS Billing_System,
  NULL AS Meter_Point_No,
  t.type AS Transaction_Type_Description,
  t.type AS Transaction_Type_Category
FROM
  `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.report_transactions` t
WHERE
  t.amount != 0

WITH statementData AS (
  --OREX Data
  SELECT universal_metadata.createdAt,
         unionRecord.StatementUploaded.accountId AS accountID,
         NULL AS supplyPoint,
         "Regular statement" AS statementType
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_statement_uploaded`
  WHERE unionRecord.StatementUploaded.accountId IS NOT NULL
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT universal_metadata.createdAt,
         unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId AS accountID,
         NULL AS supplyPoint,
         "Final statement" AS statementType
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_statement_uploaded`
  WHERE unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId IS NOT NULL
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT universal_metadata.createdAt,
         unionRecord.FinalSupplyPointStatementUploaded.accountId AS accountID,
         unionRecord.FinalSupplyPointStatementUploaded.supplyPoint AS supplyPoint,
         "Final supply statement" AS statementType
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_statement_uploaded`
  WHERE unionRecord.FinalSupplyPointStatementUploaded.accountId IS NOT NULL
  
  UNION ALL
  
  --BAST DATA
  SELECT kafkaData.insertTime,
         unionRecord.StatementUploaded.accountId AS accountID,
         NULL AS supplyPoint,
         "Regular statement" AS statementType
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_bast_secure.bast_statement_uploaded`
  WHERE unionRecord.StatementUploaded.accountId IS NOT NULL
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT kafkaData.insertTime,
         unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId AS accountID,
         NULL AS supplyPoint,
         "Final statement" AS statementType
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_bast_secure.bast_statement_uploaded`
  WHERE unionRecord.FinalAccountStatementUploaded.accountId IS NOT NULL
),

latestDate AS (
  SELECT u.createdAt,
         u.accountId,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY u.accountId ORDER BY u.createdAt desc) AS Row_No
  FROM statementData u 
)

SELECT u.createdAt AS Statement_Uploaded_DateTime,
       u.accountId AS Account_No,
       u.statementType AS Statement_Type,
       u.supplyPoint AS Meter_Point_No,
       CAST(d.createdAt AS DATE) AS Statements_Up_To

LEFT JOIN latestDate d on u.accountId = d.accountId WHERE d.Row_No = 1

query.1187:
# Reporting for tariffs over the cap post-April VPC

# Get caps for most recent cap date for DD only
WITH priceCapRates AS (
  SELECT region_name,
         GSP,
         GSP_Id as mpanPrefix,
         case when GSP_Id='10' then 'EA'
              when GSP_Id='11' then 'EM'
              when GSP_Id='12' then 'NT'
              when GSP_Id='13' then 'NW'
              when GSP_Id='14' then 'WM'
              when GSP_Id='15' then 'NO'
              when GSP_Id='16' then 'NW'
              when GSP_Id='17' then 'SC'
              when GSP_Id='18' then 'SC'
              when GSP_Id='19' then 'SE'
              when GSP_Id='20' then 'SO'
              when GSP_Id='21' then 'WA'
              when GSP_Id='22' then 'SW'
              when GSP_Id='23' then 'NE'
         end as LDZ, # Align gas region notation
         case when fuel='E' then 'electricity'
              when fuel='G' then 'gas'
         end as fuel, # Align fuel notation
         case when profile_class='Gas' then '00'
              when profile_class='PC1' then '01'
              when profile_class='PC2' then '02'
         end as profileclass, # Align profile class notation
         standing_charge/100 as standingRateCap, # Convert pence to pounds
         rate/100 as unitRateCap, # Convert pence to pounds
         effective_from_date as capStart,
         effective_to_date as capEnd
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.custom_regulatory.tbl_Price_Cap_Rates_v2`
  WHERE tariff_cap='SVT' # Standard Variable Tariffs - only applies to variable contracts
    AND payment_type='D' # DD payments
    AND effective_from_date='2020-04-01' # April caps only
),
# Get all contracts that are currently live
allContracts AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT c.serviceAccountId,
                  c.mpxn,
                  c.fuel,
                  c.contractId,
                  c.startDate,
                  c.endDate,
                  c.tariffId,
                  c.tariffType,
                  c.planName,
                  t.region,
                  t.profileClass
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts` c
  INNER JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tariffs` t # Only need current tariff region and profile class here
    ON c.tariffId=t.tariffId
  WHERE c.endDate >= current_date()
     OR c.endDate IS NULL
),
# Get all tariffs for Apr20 VPC
allTariffs AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT tariffId,
                  type,
                  fuel,
                  planName,
                  profileClass,
                  region,
                  exitFee,
                  versionDescription,
                  activeFrom,
                  activeTo,
                  # Split out day and night rates - if anytime, put for both
                  IF(array_length(unitRates)=2,IF(unitRates[offset(0)].clockingTimeLabel='day',unitRates[offset(0)].unitRate,unitRates[offset(1)].unitRate),unitRates[offset(0)].unitRate) AS unitRateDay,
                  IF(array_length(unitRates)=2,IF(unitRates[offset(0)].clockingTimeLabel='night',unitRates[offset(0)].unitRate,unitRates[offset(1)].unitRate),unitRates[offset(0)].unitRate) AS unitRateNight,
                  standingRate
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tariffs` t
  WHERE type='variable'
    AND (versionDescription='01 Apr 2020' OR # Standard variable tariffs for Apr20 VPC
         versionDescription='Switching overcharge VPC 1 Apr 2020' # Switching Overcharge rates for Apr20
         )
),
# Get post VPC tariffs for the contract
allContractsAndTariffs AS (
  SELECT c.serviceAccountId,
         c.mpxn,
         c.fuel,
         c.contractId,
         c.startDate,
         c.endDate,
         c.tariffId as oldTariffId,
         c.tariffType as oldTariffType,
         c.planName as oldPlanName,
         t.tariffId as newTariffId,
         t.type as newTariffType,
         t.planName as newPlanName,
         t.versionDescription,
         t.activeFrom,
         t.activeTo,
         t.profileClass as meterProfileClass,
         IF(t.profileClass='02' and t.planName not like '%Economy 7', '01', t.profileClass) as tariffProfileClass, # PC2 accounts not on a PC2 tariff should compare to PC1 rates
         t.region,
         round(t.unitRateDay*0.58 + t.unitRateNight*0.42,5) as unitRate, # Multipliers for day/night rates - will match up for anytime too
         t.standingRate
  FROM allContracts c
  LEFT JOIN allTariffs t
    ON (c.tariffId = t.tariffId) # Variable tariff IDs will remain the same post-VPC
    OR (c.fuel=t.fuel AND # Need to find a variable tariff for fixed tariffs to roll on to
        c.region=t.region AND
        c.profileClass=t.profileClass AND
        substr(c.planName,-1,1)=substr(t.planName,-1,1) # Economy7 -> Economy7
        )
  WHERE t.versionDescription='01 Apr 2020' AND # Only want standard tariffs
        t.planName like '%Simpler%' # Cannot predict if customer would have warm home discount        
),
# Join everything above on to PP region data for all accounts
final_data as (
SELECT ac.*,
       if(ac.fuel='electricity',pcr.GSP,pcr.LDZ) as correctRegion, # Gas and elec regions have different notation
       pcr.mpanprefix as correctRegionMpanPrefix,
       asp.loss_date as lossDate,
       asp.supply_lifecycle as supplyLifecycle,
       asp.migrated_date as migratedDate,
       pcr.unitRateCap,
       pcr.standingRateCap,
       pcr.capStart,
       case when ac.unitRate>pcr.unitRateCap or ac.standingRate>pcr.standingRateCap then 'Over the cap'
            else 'Under the cap'
       end as capComparison,
       case when (ac.fuel='electricity' AND ac.region<>pcr.GSP) OR (ac.fuel='gas' AND ac.region<>pcr.LDZ) then 'Incorrect region'
            else 'Correct region'
       end as regionComparison
FROM allContractsAndTariffs ac
LEFT JOIN (select distinct account_no, utility_type_code, mpan_prefix from `data-science-retail.pricing_programme_solution.purified_alignment_gas_and_elec`) pp # Correct region data for account
  ON pp.account_no=ac.serviceAccountID
  AND pp.Utility_Type_Code=upper(substr(ac.fuel,1,1))
LEFT JOIN priceCapRates pcr # Bring in price cap rates
  ON pp.mpan_prefix=pcr.mpanprefix
  AND ac.tariffProfileClass=pcr.profileClass
LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points` asp # Bring in account data
  ON ac.serviceAccountId=asp.account_no
  AND ac.mpxn=asp.meter_point_no
)
# Filter out accounts where the region is correct or rate is under the cap
SELECT *
FROM final_data
WHERE region<>correctRegion # Keep accounts with region mismatch
   OR unitRate>unitRateCap # Keep accounts over cap
   OR standingRate>standingRateCap
ORDER BY serviceAccountId,
         fuel
query.1189:
# PROJECT PURIFY ALIGNMENT

# Get caps for most recent cap date for DD only
WITH priceCapRates AS (
  SELECT *
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.price_cap_rates` r
  WHERE Payment <> "Standard"
--     AND capStart='2019-10-01'
),
# Get all contracts
allContracts AS (
  SELECT *
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.contracts`
),
# Get all tariffs and add a row number by activeFrom date for each tariff ID
allTariffs AS (
  SELECT *,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY tariffId ORDER BY activeFrom DESC) as row
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.tariffs`
),
# Get all tariffs for the contract (variable will change over time)
allContractsAndTariffs AS (
  SELECT c.serviceAccountId,
         c.mpxn,
         c.fuel,
         c.contractId,
         c.tariffId,
         c.startDate,
         c.endDate,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY contractId ORDER BY startDate DESC, COALESCE(activeFrom, '1970-01-01') DESC) as descRow,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY contractId ORDER BY startDate ASC, COALESCE(activeFrom, '1970-01-01') ASC) as ascRow,
         t.type,
         t.planName,
         t.versionDescription,
         t.activeFrom,
         t.activeTo,
         t.profileClass,
         t.region,
         t.standingRate,
         t.unitRates
  FROM allContracts c
  LEFT JOIN allTariffs t ON c.tariffId = t.tariffId 
  WHERE (t.type = 'variable' AND ((t.activeFrom <= c.startDate AND COALESCE(t.activeTo, '2999-01-01') >= c.startDate)
                              OR (t.activeFrom >= c.startDate AND t.activeFrom <= COALESCE(c.endDate, '2999-01-01'))))
     OR t.type = 'fixed'
),
# ascRow and descRow will get the start and end of the contracts, even over tariff changes
contractsPricePaid AS (
  SELECT serviceAccountId,
         mpxn,
         fuel,
         contractId,
         tariffId,
         CASE WHEN ascRow = 1 THEN startDate
              ELSE activeFrom
         END AS priceStartDate,
         CASE WHEN descRow = 1 THEN COALESCE(endDate, CURRENT_DATE())
              ELSE activeTo
         END AS priceEndDate,
         type,
         planName,
         versionDescription,
         profileClass,
         region,
         standingRate,
         unitRates[offset(0)].unitRate AS unitRate
  FROM allContractsandTariffs
),
# Join everything above on to PP region data for all accounts and filter out where the region doesn't match
accounts AS (
SELECT ac.*,
       pp.correctRegion,
       pcr.mpanprefix as correct_region_mpanprefix,
       date_diff(if(current_date()>ac.priceEndDate,ac.priceEndDate,current_date()),ac.priceStartDate,DAY) as daysWrongRegion,
       asp.loss_date,
       asp.supply_lifecycle,
       asp.migrated_date,
       case when ac.type='variable' then pcr.unitratecap end as unitratecap,
       pcr.capstart,
       if(current_date() BETWEEN ac.priceStartDate and ac.priceEndDate,'Live','Historic') as tariffcurrentlylive
FROM contractsPricePaid ac
LEFT JOIN `data-science-retail.pricing_programme_solution.project_purify_gas_alignment` pp
  ON pp.account_no=ac.serviceAccountID
LEFT JOIN priceCapRates pcr
  ON pp.account_gas_mpan_prefix=cast(pcr.mpanprefix as string)
--   AND ac.type='variable'
LEFT JOIN `data-engineering-prod.product_orion.account_supply_points` asp
  ON ac.serviceAccountId=asp.account_no
  AND ac.mpxn=asp.meter_point_no
WHERE ((ac.priceStartDate BETWEEN pcr.capStart AND pcr.capEnd) 
       OR (pcr.capStart BETWEEN ac.priceStartDate AND COALESCE(ac.priceEndDate, CURRENT_DATE()))
      )
  AND correctregion<>ac.region
  AND ac.fuel='gas'
  AND capStart<=coalesce(asp.loss_date,'2999-01-01')
)
# Add on correct tariff and fix
SELECT acc.*,
       case when t.unitRate<acc.unitRate then 'Overcharged'
            when t.unitRate=acc.unitRate then 'Charged correctly'
            when t.unitRate>acc.unitRate then 'Undercharged'
            else 'No current lookup tariff'
       end as overCharged,
       case when acc.type='fixed' then 'Fixed, no cap'
            when unitratecap<acc.unitRate then 'Over cap'
            when unitratecap>=acc.unitRate then 'Under cap'
       end as overCap,
       t.tariffId as correctTariff,
       t.unitRates[offset(0)].unitRate AS correctUnitRate,
       t.standingRate AS correctStandingRate,
       case when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate>UnitRateCap and acc.priceStartDate>current_date() then 'Future variable tariff, will start over cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate>UnitRateCap and loss_date<=current_date() then 'Historic variable tariff, lost, was over cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate>UnitRateCap and acc.priceEndDate<current_date() then 'Historic variable tariff, was over cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate>UnitRateCap and loss_date>current_date() then 'Current variable tariff, pending loss, over cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate>UnitRateCap and acc.priceEndDate=current_date() then 'Current variable tariff, over cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate>UnitRateCap and acc.priceEndDate>current_date() then 'Current variable tariff, over cap, refixing'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate<=UnitRateCap and acc.priceStartDate>current_date() then 'Future variable tariff, will start under cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate<=UnitRateCap and loss_date<=current_date() then 'Historic variable tariff, lost, was under cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate<=UnitRateCap and acc.priceEndDate<current_date() then 'Historic variable tariff, was under cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate<=UnitRateCap and loss_date>current_date() then 'Current variable tariff, pending loss, under cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate<=UnitRateCap and acc.priceEndDate=current_date() then 'Current variable tariff, under cap'
            when acc.type='variable' and acc.unitRate<=UnitRateCap and acc.priceEndDate>current_date() then 'Current variable tariff, under cap, refixing'
            when acc.type='fixed' and loss_date>current_date() and acc.priceEndDate<loss_date then 'Fixed tariff, pending loss, rolls variable before loss date'
            when acc.type='fixed' and loss_date>current_date() and acc.priceEndDate>=loss_date then 'Fixed tariff, pending loss'
            when acc.type='fixed' and acc.priceEndDate<'2020-04-01' then 'Fixed tariff, may roll variable before April'
            when acc.type='fixed' and acc.priceEndDate>='2020-04-01' then 'Fixed tariff, may roll variable after April'
       end as fixCategory
FROM accounts acc
LEFT JOIN alltariffs t ON acc.correctRegion=t.region
                       AND acc.fuel=t.fuel
                       AND acc.planName=t.planName
                       AND acc.type=t.type
                       AND acc.profileClass=t.profileClass
                       AND acc.versionDescription=t.versionDescription
                       AND substr(t.tariffId,-2,2)='=='

WITH Resolved_Payments as (
    SELECT transactionId
          ,status
          ,statusDatetime
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_paymentEvent` 
    WHERE status in ('chargeback_cancelled','late_failure_settled')
),

Failed_Payments as (
    SELECT f.transactionId
          ,f.status
          ,f.statusDatetime
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_paymentEvent` f
    LEFT JOIN Resolved_Payments r on r.transactionId = f.transactionId and r.statusDateTime > f.statusDateTime
    WHERE f.status in ('failed','cancelled','chargeback_settled')
    and r.transactionId IS NULL
),

Requested_Date as (
    SELECT f.transactionId
          ,f.status
          ,f.statusDatetime
    FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_paymentEvent` f
    WHERE f.status in ('created')
)

SELECT p.serviceAccountID  as Account_No
      ,p.transactionId as Transaction_ID
      ,p.chargeDate as Transaction_Date
      ,CAST(d.statusDateTime AS DATE) as Requested_Date
      ,p.amount as Transaction_Amount_In_Pence
      ,p.subscriptionID as Subscription_ID
      ,p.mandateID as Mandate_ID
FROM `data-engineering-prod.raw_payments_secure.payments_paymentEvent` p 
LEFT JOIN Failed_Payments f on p.transactionId = f.transactionId and p.statusDateTime < f.statusDatetime
JOIN Requested_Date d on d.transactionId = p.transactionId 
WHERE p.status = 'confirmed'
and f.transactionId IS NULL

       unionRecord.TariffUpserted.metadata.createdAt as upserted_createdAt,
       unionRecord.TariffUpserted.metadata.traceToken as upserted_traceToken,
       unionRecord.TariffUpserted.tariffId as upserted_tariffId,
       unionRecord.TariffUpserted.activeFrom as upserted_activeFrom,
       unionRecord.TariffUpserted.activeTo as upserted_activeTo,

query.1592:
with 
latest_data_per_sp as (
  select * except(n) from (SELECT *, row_number() over(partition by MPXN order by kafkadata.inserttime desc, kafkadata.offset desc) n 
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_andromeda_secure.spam_electricitySupplyPointHistory_v2`
  where PARTITIONTIME >= "2020-04-01 00:00:00") where n = 1),

with_latest_meter_and_supply as (
  select *, 
         (select as struct * from unnest(installationHistory) ih order by ih.startDate desc limit 1) latestInstallation,
         (select as struct * from unnest(supplyPeriods) sps order by sps.supplyStartDate desc limit 1) latestSupplyPeriod
  from latest_data_per_sp
),

with_convenience_fields as (
  select *,
         case 
           when latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed	is true and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate < current_date()
             -- is loss confirmed and has an end date set and end date is before today
           then "offSupply"
           when (latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is null and (latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is false or latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is null))
             or (latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate >= current_date())
             -- isn't missing supply period data, and either doesn't have a loss journey (is not loss confirmed and has no end date set)
             -- or is in the loss journey but hasn't reached loss yet (has end date set and end date is before or equal to today)
           then "onSupply"
           when latestSupplyPeriod.supplyStartDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate < current_date() and (latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is false or latestSupplyPeriod.lossConfirmed is null)
           -- when it looks like it should have been lost, but we haven't received lossConfirmed, it's likely in dispute and so still on supply
           then "unconfirmedLoss"
           else "insufficientData" end supplyOnOff,
         latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate is not null and current_date() <= date_add(latestSupplyPeriod.supplyEndDate, interval 20 day) inLoss, 
         (select as struct * from unnest(latestInstallation.meterRegisterHistory) mrh order by mrh.startDate desc limit 1) latestRegisterConfiguration,
         regexp_contains(latestInstallation.meterType, '^(S[1-2].*)$') isSmart
  from with_latest_meter_and_supply)

select 
-- meter-point related fields
  MPXN, supplyPointType, profileClassId, gspGroupId, lineLossFactorClassId, supplyOnOff, inLoss, isSmart, addressLines, postCode,
-- latest known details
  latestSupplyPeriod, latestInstallation, latestRegisterConfiguration,
-- histories
  supplyPeriods, installationHistory,
-- metadata
  metadata, kafkaData, PARTITIONTIME
from with_convenience_fields

WITH dedupe AS (

    *,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY metadata.eventId ORDER BY kafkaData.insertTime desc) AS RN
  FROM `data-engineering-prod.landing_orex_secure.orex_account_state_v3`

SELECT d.metadata
      ,COALESCE(d.body.AccountState.accountId, d.body.Deleted.accountId) as accountId
      ,COALESCE(d.body.AccountState.accountStateTimestamp, d.metadata.createdAt) as accountStateTimestamp
      ,d.body.AccountState.hasOnlineDiscount as hasOnlineDiscount
      ,d.body.AccountState.interestRewardStartDate as interestRewardStartDate
      ,d.body.AccountState.migratedInterestCalculationDate as migratedInterestCalculationDate
      ,IF(d.body.Deleted.accountId IS NULL,'active','deleted') status
      ,d.body.AccountState.electricitySupplyStartDate as electricitySupplyStartDate
      ,d.body.AccountState.gasSupplyStartDate as gasSupplyStartDate
      ,d.body.AccountState.interestRewardOptOut as interestRewardOptOut
      ,d.body.AccountState.vacant as vacant
      ,d.body.AccountState.createdAt as accountCreatedAt
      ,d.kafkaData
      ,d.PARTITIONTIME
FROM dedupe d
WHERE RN = 1

query.1619:
with cte_simplified_readings as
(
  select cast(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime as date) as snapshotDate,
         value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.mpan as mpxn,
         r.reading
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_msd_simplified` s,
  unnest(value.ElectricityMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.electricityImport.registers) r
  union all
  select cast(value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.snapshotTime as date) as snapshotDate,
         value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.mprn as mpxn,
         value.GasMidnightSnapshotReadingEvent.gasVolume as reading
  from `data-engineering-prod.raw_andromeda_secure.rac_msd_simplified` s
)
select cc.serviceAccountId, cc.mpxn, cm.startDate, cm.endDate, r.snapshotDate, r.reading
from `data-engineering-prod.raw_orex_secure.orex_customer_contract` cc
inner join `data-engineering-prod.product_andromeda_secure.charge_mandates` cm on cc.energyContractId = cm.contractId
inner join cte_simplified_readings r on cm.mpxn = r.mpxn
where cc.serviceAccountId = '6159461-v1-70D11B80'
  and ((r.snapshotDate between cm.startDate and cm.endDate AND EXTRACT(DAY FROM r.snapshotDate) = 1)
     OR r.snapshotDate = cm.startDate
     or r.snapshotDate = date_add(cm.endDate, interval 1 DAY))
order by snapshotDate
